INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1001, 'In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1002, 'The earth was without form, and void; and darkness was on the face of the deep. And the Spirit of God was hovering over the face of the waters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1003, 'Then God said, &ldquo;Let there be light&rdquo;; and there was light.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1004, 'And God saw the light, that it was good; and God divided the light from the darkness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1005, 'God called the light Day, and the darkness He called Night. So the evening and the morning were the first day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1006, 'Then God said, &ldquo;Let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1007, 'Thus God made the firmament, and divided the waters which were under the firmament from the waters which were above the firmament; and it was so.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1008, 'And God called the firmament Heaven. So the evening and the morning were the second day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1009, 'Then God said, &ldquo;Let the waters under the heavens be gathered together into one place, and let the dry land appear&rdquo;; and it was so.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1010, 'And God called the dry land Earth, and the gathering together of the waters He called Seas. And God saw that it was good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1011, 'Then God said, &ldquo;Let the earth bring forth grass, the herb that yields seed, and the fruit tree that yields fruit according to its kind, whose seed is in itself, on the earth&rdquo;; and it was so.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1012, 'And the earth brought forth grass, the herb that yields seed according to its kind, and the tree that yields fruit, whose seed is in itself according to its kind. And God saw that it was good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1013, 'So the evening and the morning were the third day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1014, 'Then* God said, &ldquo;Let there be lights in the firmament of the heavens to divide the day from the night; and let them be for signs and seasons, and for days and years;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1015, '&ldquo;and let them be for lights in the firmament of the heavens to give light on the earth&rdquo;; and it was so.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1016, 'Then God made two great lights: the greater light to rule the day, and the lesser light to rule the night. He made the stars also.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1017, 'God set them in the firmament of the heavens to give light on the earth,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1018, 'and to rule over the day and over the night, and to divide the light from the darkness. And God saw that it was good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1019, 'So the evening and the morning were the fourth day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1020, 'Then God said, &ldquo;Let the waters abound with an abundance of living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth across the face of the firmament of the heavens.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1021, 'So God created great sea creatures and every living thing that moves, with which the waters abounded, according to their kind, and every winged bird according to its kind. And God saw that it was good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1022, 'And God blessed them, saying, &ldquo;Be fruitful and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1023, 'So the evening and the morning were the fifth day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1024, 'Then* God said, &ldquo;Let the earth bring forth the living creature according to its kind: cattle and creeping thing and beast of the earth, each according to its kind&rdquo;; and it was so.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1025, 'And God made the beast of the earth according to its kind, cattle according to its kind, and everything that creeps on the earth according to its kind. And God saw that it was good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1026, 'Then God said, &ldquo;Let Us make man in Our image, according to Our likeness; let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, over the birds of the air, and over the cattle, over all the earth and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1027, 'So God created man in His own image; in the image of God He created him; male and female He created them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1028, 'Then God blessed them, and God said to them, &ldquo;Be fruitful and multiply; fill the earth and subdue it; have dominion over the fish of the sea, over the birds of the air, and over every living thing that moves on the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1029, 'And God said, &ldquo;See, I have given you every herb that yields seed which is on the face of all the earth, and every tree whose fruit yields seed; to you it shall be for food.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1030, '&ldquo;Also, to every beast of the earth, to every bird of the air, and to everything that creeps on the earth, in which there is life, I have given every green herb for food&rdquo;; and it was so.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 1031, 'Then God saw everything that He had made, and indeed it was very good. So the evening and the morning were the sixth day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2001, 'Thus the heavens and the earth, and all the host of them, were finished.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2002, 'And on the seventh day God ended His work which He had done, and He rested on the seventh day from all His work which He had done.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2003, 'Then God blessed the seventh day and sanctified it, because in it He rested from all His work which God had created and made.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2004, 'This is the history of the heavens and the earth when they were created, in the day that the Lord God made the earth and the heavens,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2005, 'before any plant of the field was in the earth and before any herb of the field had grown. For the Lord God had not caused it to rain on the earth, and there was no man to till the ground;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2006, 'but a mist went up from the earth and watered the whole face of the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2007, 'And the Lord God formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living being.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2008, 'The Lord God planted a garden eastward in Eden, and there He put the man whom He had formed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2009, 'And out of the ground the Lord God made every tree grow that is pleasant to the sight and good for food. The tree of life was also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2010, 'Now a river went out of Eden to water the garden, and from there it parted and became four riverheads.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2011, 'The name of the first is Pishon; it is the one which skirts the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2012, 'And the gold of that land is good. Bdellium and the onyx stone are there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2013, 'The name of the second river is Gihon; it is the one which goes around the whole land of Cush.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2014, 'The name of the third river is Hiddekel; it is the one which goes toward the east of Assyria. The fourth river is the Euphrates.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2015, 'Then the Lord God took the man and put him in the garden of Eden to tend and keep it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2016, 'And the Lord God commanded the man, saying, &ldquo;Of every tree of the garden you may freely eat;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2017, '&ldquo;but of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil you shall not eat, for in the day that you eat of it you shall surely die.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2018, 'And the Lord God said, &ldquo;It is not good that man should be alone; I will make him a helper comparable to him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2019, 'Out of the ground the Lord God formed every beast of the field and every bird of the air, and brought them to Adam to see what he would call them. And whatever Adam called each living creature, that was its name.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2020, 'So *Adam gave names to all cattle, to the birds of the air, and to every beast of the field. But for Adam there was not found a helper comparable to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2021, 'And the Lord God caused a deep sleep to fall on Adam, and he slept; and He took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh in its place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2022, 'Then the rib which the Lord God had taken from man He made into a woman, and He brought her to the man.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2023, 'And Adam said: &ldquo;This is now bone of my bones And flesh of my flesh; She shall be called Woman, Because she was taken out of Man.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2024, 'Therefore a man shall leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife, and they shall become one flesh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 2025, 'And they were both naked, the man and his wife, and were not ashamed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3001, 'Now the serpent was more cunning than any beast of the field which the Lord God had made. And he said to the woman, &ldquo;Has God indeed said, &lsquo;You shall not eat of every tree of the garden&rsquo;?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3002, 'And the woman said to the serpent, &ldquo;We may eat the fruit of the trees of the garden;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3003, '&ldquo;but of the fruit of the tree which is in the midst of the garden, God has said, &lsquo;You shall not eat it, nor shall you touch it, lest you die.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3004, 'Then the serpent said to the woman, &ldquo;You will not surely die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3005, '&ldquo;For God knows that in the day you eat of it your eyes will be opened, and you will be like God, knowing good and evil.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3006, 'So when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, that it was pleasant to the eyes, and a tree desirable to make one wise, she took of its fruit and ate. She also gave to her husband with her, and he ate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3007, 'Then the eyes of both of them were opened, and they knew that they were naked; and they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves coverings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3008, 'And they heard the sound of the Lord God walking in the garden in the cool of the day, and Adam and his wife hid themselves from the presence of the Lord God among the trees of the garden.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3009, 'Then the Lord God called to Adam and said to him, &ldquo;Where are you?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3010, 'So he said, &ldquo;I heard Your voice in the garden, and I was afraid because I was naked; and I hid myself.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3011, 'And He said, &ldquo;Who told you that you were naked? Have you eaten from the tree of which I commanded you that you should not eat?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3012, 'Then the man said, &ldquo;The woman whom You gave to be with me, she gave me of the tree, and I ate.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3013, 'And the Lord God said to the woman, &ldquo;What is this you have done?&rdquo; The woman said, &ldquo;The serpent deceived me, and I ate.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3014, 'So the Lord God said to the serpent: &ldquo;Because you have done this, You are cursed more than all cattle, And more than every beast of the field; On your belly you shall go, And you shall eat dust All the days of your life. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3015, 'And I will put enmity Between you and the woman, And between your seed and her Seed; He shall bruise your head, And you shall bruise His heel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3016, 'To the woman He said: &ldquo;I will greatly multiply your sorrow and your conception; In pain you shall bring forth children; Your desire shall be for your husband, And he shall rule over you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3017, 'Then to Adam He said, &ldquo;Because you have heeded the voice of your wife, and have eaten from the tree of which I commanded you, saying, &lsquo;You shall not eat of it&rsquo;: &ldquo;Cursed is the ground for your sake; In toil you shall eat of it All the days of your life.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3018, 'Both thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for you, And you shall eat the herb of the field.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3019, 'In the sweat of your face you shall eat bread Till you return to the ground, For out of it you were taken; For dust you are, And to dust you shall return.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3020, 'And Adam called his wife&rsquo;s name Eve, because she was the mother of all living.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3021, 'Also for Adam and his wife the Lord God made* tunics of skin, and clothed them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3022, 'Then the Lord God said, &ldquo;Behold, the man has become like one of Us, to know good and evil. And now, lest he put out his hand and take also of the tree of life, and eat, and live forever&rdquo; &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3023, 'therefore the Lord God sent him out of the garden of Eden to till the ground from which he was taken.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 3024, 'So He drove out the man; and He placed cherubim at the east of the garden of Eden, and a flaming sword which turned every way, to guard the way to the tree of life.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4001, 'Now Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bore Cain, and said, &ldquo;I have acquired a man from the Lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4002, 'Then she bore again, this time his brother Abel. Now Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4003, 'And in the process of time it came to pass that Cain brought an offering of the fruit of the ground to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4004, 'Abel also brought of the firstborn of his flock and of their fat. And the Lord respected Abel and his offering,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4005, 'but He did not respect Cain and his offering. And Cain was very angry, and his countenance fell.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4006, 'So the Lord said to Cain, &ldquo;Why are you angry? And why has your countenance fallen?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4007, '&ldquo;If you do well, will you not be accepted? And if you do not do well, sin lies at the door. And its desire is for you, but you should rule over it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4008, 'Now *Cain talked with Abel his brother;a and it came to pass, when they were in the field, that Cain rose up against Abel his brother and killed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4009, 'Then the Lord said to Cain, &ldquo;Where is Abel your brother?&rdquo; He said, &ldquo;I do not know. Am I my brother&rsquo;s keeper?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4010, 'And He said, &ldquo;What have you done? The voice of your brother&rsquo;s blood cries out to Me from the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4011, '&ldquo;So now you are cursed from the earth, which has opened its mouth to receive your brother&rsquo;s blood from your hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4012, '&ldquo;When you till the ground, it shall no longer yield its strength to you. A fugitive and a vagabond you shall be on the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4013, 'And Cain said to the Lord, &ldquo;My punishment is greater than I can bear!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4014, '&ldquo;Surely You have driven me out this day from the face of the ground; I shall be hidden from Your face; I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond on the earth, and it will happen that anyone who finds me will kill me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4015, 'And the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Therefore,a whoever kills Cain, vengeance shall be taken on him sevenfold.&rdquo; And the Lord set a mark on Cain, lest anyone finding him should kill him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4016, 'Then *Cain went out from the presence of the Lord and dwelt in the land of Nod on the east of Eden.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4017, 'And Cain knew his wife, and she conceived and bore Enoch. And he built a city, and called the name of the city after the name of his son &ndash; Enoch.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4018, 'To Enoch was born Irad; and Irad begot Mehujael, and Mehujael begot Methushael, and Methushael begot Lamech.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4019, 'Then Lamech took for himself two wives: the name of one was Adah, and the name of the second was Zillah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4020, 'And Adah bore Jabal. He was the father of those who dwell in tents and have livestock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4021, 'His brother&rsquo;s name was Jubal. He was the father of all those who play the harp and flute.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4022, 'And as for Zillah, she also bore Tubal-Cain, an instructor of every craftsman in bronze and iron. And the sister of Tubal-Cain was Naamah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4023, 'Then Lamech said to his wives: &ldquo;Adah and Zillah, hear my voice; Wives of Lamech, listen to my speech! For I have killed a man for wounding me, Even a young man for hurting me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4024, 'If Cain shall be avenged sevenfold, Then Lamech seventy-sevenfold.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4025, 'And Adam knew his wife again, and she bore a son and named him Seth, &ldquo;For God has appointed another seed for me instead of Abel, whom Cain killed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 4026, 'And as for Seth, to him also a son was born; and he named him Enosh. Then men began to call on the name of the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5001, 'This is the book of the genealogy of Adam. In the day that God created man, He made him in the likeness of God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5002, 'He created them male and female, and blessed them and called them Mankind in the day they were created.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5003, 'And Adam lived one hundred and thirty years, and begot a son in his own likeness, after his image, and named him Seth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5004, 'After he begot Seth, the days of Adam were eight hundred years; and he had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5005, 'So all the days that Adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5006, 'Seth lived one hundred and five years, and begot Enosh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5007, 'After he begot Enosh, Seth lived eight hundred and seven years, and had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5008, 'So all the days of Seth were nine hundred and twelve years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5009, 'Enosh lived ninety years, and begot Cainan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5010, 'After he begot Cainan, Enosh lived eight hundred and fifteen years, and had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5011, 'So all the days of Enosh were nine hundred and five years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5012, 'Cainan lived seventy years, and begot Mahalalel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5013, 'After he begot Mahalalel, Cainan lived eight hundred and forty years, and had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5014, 'So all the days of Cainan were nine hundred and ten years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5015, 'Mahalalel lived sixty-five years, and begot Jared.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5016, 'After he begot Jared, Mahalalel lived eight hundred and thirty years, and had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5017, 'So all the days of Mahalalel were eight hundred and ninety-five years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5018, 'Jared lived one hundred and sixty-two years, and begot Enoch.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5019, 'After he begot Enoch, Jared lived eight hundred years, and had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5020, 'So all the days of Jared were nine hundred and sixty-two years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5021, 'Enoch lived sixty-five years, and begot Methuselah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5022, 'After he begot Methuselah, Enoch walked with God three hundred years, and had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5023, 'So all the days of Enoch were three hundred and sixty-five years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5024, 'And Enoch walked with God; and he was not, for God took him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5025, 'Methuselah lived one hundred and eighty-seven years, and begot Lamech.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5026, 'After he begot Lamech, Methuselah lived seven hundred and eighty-two years, and had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5027, 'So all the days of Methuselah were nine hundred and sixty-nine years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5028, 'Lamech lived one hundred and eighty-two years, and had a son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5029, 'And he called his name Noah, saying, &ldquo;This one will comfort us concerning our work and the toil of our hands, because of the ground which the Lord has cursed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5030, 'After he begot Noah, Lamech lived five hundred and ninety-five years, and had sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5031, 'So all the days of Lamech were seven hundred and seventy-seven years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 5032, 'And *Noah was five hundred years old, and Noah begot Shem, Ham, and Japheth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6001, 'Now it came to pass, when men began to multiply on the face of the earth, and daughters were born to them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6002, 'that the sons of God saw the daughters of men, that they were beautiful; and they took wives for themselves of all whom they chose.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6003, 'And the Lord said, &ldquo;My Spirit shall not strive with man forever, for he is indeed flesh; yet his days shall be one hundred and twenty years.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6004, 'There were giants on the earth in those days, and also afterward, when the sons of God came in to the daughters of men and they bore children to them. Those were the mighty men who were of old, men of renown.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6005, 'Then the Lord saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth, and that every intent of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6006, 'And the Lord was sorry that He had made man on the earth, and He was grieved in His heart.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6007, 'So the Lord said, &ldquo;I will destroy man whom I have created from the face of the earth, both man and beast, creeping thing and birds of the air, for I am sorry that I have made them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6008, 'But Noah found grace in the eyes of the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6009, 'This is the genealogy of Noah. *Noah was a just man, perfect in his generations. Noah walked with God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6010, 'And Noah begot three sons: Shem, Ham, and Japheth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6011, 'The earth also was corrupt before God, and the earth was filled with violence.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6012, 'So God looked upon the earth, and indeed it was corrupt; for all flesh had corrupted their way on the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6013, 'And God said to Noah, &ldquo;The end of all flesh has come before Me, for the earth is filled with violence through them; and behold, I will destroy them with the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6014, '&ldquo;Make yourself an ark of gopherwood; make rooms in the ark, and cover it inside and outside with pitch.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6015, '&ldquo;And this is how you shall make it: The length of the ark shall be three hundred cubits, its width fifty cubits, and its height thirty cubits.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6016, '&ldquo;You shall make a window for the ark, and you shall finish it to a cubit from above; and set the door of the ark in its side. You shall make it with lower, second, and third decks.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6017, '&ldquo;And behold, I Myself am bringing floodwaters on the earth, to destroy from under heaven all flesh in which is the breath of life; everything that is on the earth shall die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6018, '&ldquo;But I will establish My covenant with you; and you shall go into the ark &ndash; you, your sons, your wife, and your sons&rsquo; wives with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6019, '&ldquo;And of every living thing of all flesh you shall bring two of every sort into the ark, to keep them alive with you; they shall be male and female.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6020, '&ldquo;Of the birds after their kind, of animals after their kind, and of every creeping thing of the earth after its kind, two of every kind will come to you to keep them alive.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6021, '&ldquo;And you shall take for yourself of all food that is eaten, and you shall gather it to yourself; and it shall be food for you and for them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 6022, 'Thus Noah did; according to all that God commanded him, so he did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7001, 'Then the* Lord said to Noah, &ldquo;Come into the ark, you and all your household, because I have seen that you are righteous before Me in this generation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7002, '&ldquo;You shall take with you seven each of every clean animal, a male and his female; two each of animals that are unclean, a male and his female;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7003, '&ldquo;also seven each of birds of the air, male and female, to keep the species alive on the face of all the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7004, '&ldquo;For after seven more days I will cause it to rain on the earth forty days and forty nights, and I will destroy from the face of the earth all living things that I have made.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7005, 'And Noah did according to all that the Lord commanded him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7006, 'Noah was six hundred years old when the floodwaters were on the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7007, 'So Noah, with his sons, his wife, and his sons&rsquo; wives, went into the ark because of the waters of the flood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7008, 'Of clean animals, of animals that are unclean, of birds, and of everything that creeps on the earth,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7009, 'two by two they went into the ark to Noah, male and female, as God had commanded Noah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7010, 'And it came to pass after seven days that the waters of the flood were on the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7011, 'In* the six hundredth year of Noah&rsquo;s life, in the second month, the seventeenth day of the month, on that day all the fountains of the great deep were broken up, and the windows of heaven were opened.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7012, 'And the rain was on the earth forty days and forty nights.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7013, 'On the very same day Noah and Noah&rsquo;s sons, Shem, Ham, and Japheth, and Noah&rsquo;s wife and the three wives of his sons with them, entered the ark &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7014, 'they and every beast after its kind, all cattle after their kind, every creeping thing that creeps on the earth after its kind, and every bird after its kind, every bird of every sort.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7015, 'And they went into the ark to Noah, two by two, of all flesh in which is the breath of life.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7016, 'So those that entered, male and female of all flesh, went in as God had commanded him; and the Lord shut him in.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7017, 'Now the flood was on the earth forty days. The waters increased and lifted up the ark, and it rose high above the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7018, 'The waters prevailed and greatly increased on the earth, and the ark moved about on the surface of the waters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7019, 'And the waters prevailed exceedingly on the earth, and all the high hills under the whole heaven were covered.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7020, 'The waters prevailed fifteen cubits upward, and the mountains were covered.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7021, 'And all flesh died that moved on the earth: birds and cattle and beasts and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth, and every man.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7022, 'All in whose nostrils was the breath of the spirit of life, all that was on the dry land, died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7023, 'So He destroyed all living things which were on the face of the ground: both man and cattle, creeping thing and bird of the air. They were destroyed from the earth. Only Noah and those who were with him in the ark remained alive.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 7024, 'And the waters prevailed on the earth one hundred and fifty days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8001, 'Then God remembered Noah, and every living thing, and all the animals that were with him in the ark. And God made a wind to pass over the earth, and the waters subsided.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8002, 'The fountains of the deep and the windows of heaven were also stopped, and the rain from heaven was restrained.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8003, 'And the waters receded continually from the earth. At the end of the hundred and fifty days the waters decreased.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8004, 'Then the* ark rested in the seventh month, the seventeenth day of the month, on the mountains of Ararat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8005, 'And the waters decreased continually until the tenth month. In the tenth month, on the first day of the month, the tops of the mountains were seen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8006, 'So it came to pass, at the end of forty days, that Noah opened the window of the ark which he had made.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8007, 'Then he sent out a raven, which kept going to and fro until the waters had dried up from the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8008, 'He also sent out from himself a dove, to see if the waters had receded from the face of the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8009, 'But the dove found no resting place for the sole of her foot, and she returned into the ark to him, for the waters were on the face of the whole earth. So he put out his hand and took her, and drew her into the ark to himself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8010, 'And he waited yet another seven days, and again he sent the dove out from the ark.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8011, 'Then the dove came to him in the evening, and behold, a freshly plucked olive leaf was in her mouth; and Noah knew that the waters had receded from the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8012, 'So he waited yet another seven days and sent out the dove, which did not return again to him anymore.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8013, 'And it came to pass in the six hundred and first year, in the first month, the first day of the month, that the waters were dried up from the earth; and Noah removed the covering of the ark and looked, and indeed the surface of the ground was dry.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8014, 'And in the second month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, the earth was dried.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8015, 'Then God spoke to Noah, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8016, '&ldquo;Go out of the ark, you and your wife, and your sons and your sons&rsquo; wives with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8017, '&ldquo;Bring out with you every living thing of all flesh that is with you: birds and cattle and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth, so that they may abound on the earth, and be fruitful and multiply on the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8018, 'So Noah went out, and his sons and his wife and his sons&rsquo; wives with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8019, 'Every animal, every creeping thing, every bird, and whatever creeps on the earth, according to their families, went out of the ark.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8020, 'Then Noah built an altar to the Lord, and took of every clean animal and of every clean bird, and offered burnt offerings on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8021, 'And the Lord smelled a soothing aroma.| Then the Lord said in His heart,* &ldquo;I will never again curse the ground for man&rsquo;s sake, although the imagination of man&rsquo;s heart is evil from his youth; nor will I again destroy every living thing as I have done.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 8022, '&ldquo;While the earth remains, Seedtime and harvest, Cold and heat, Winter and summer, And day and night Shall not cease.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9001, 'So God blessed Noah and his sons, and said to them: &ldquo;Be fruitful and multiply, and fill the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9002, '&ldquo;And the fear of you and the dread of you shall be on every beast of the earth, on every bird of the air, on all that move on the earth, and on all the fish of the sea. They are given into your hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9003, '&ldquo;Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you. I have given you all things, even as the green herbs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9004, '&ldquo;But you shall not eat flesh with its life, that is, its blood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9005, '&ldquo;Surely for your lifeblood I will demand a reckoning; from the hand of every beast I will require it, and from the hand of man. From the hand of every man&rsquo;s brother I will require the life of man.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9006, '&ldquo;Whoever sheds man&rsquo;s blood, By man his blood shall be shed; For in the image of God He made man.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9007, 'And as for you, be fruitful and multiply; Bring forth abundantly in the earth and have dominion over it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9008, 'Then *God spoke to Noah and to his sons with him, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9009, '&ldquo;And as for Me, behold, I establish My covenant with you and with your descendantsa after you,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9010, '&ldquo;and with every living creature that is with you: the birds, the cattle, and every beast of the earth with you, of all that go out of the ark, every beast of the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9011, '&ldquo;Thus I establish My covenant with you: Never again shall all flesh be cut off by the waters of the flood; never again shall there be a flood to destroy the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9012, 'And God said: &ldquo;This is the sign of the covenant which I make between Me and you, and every living creature that is with you, for perpetual generations:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9013, '&ldquo;I set My rainbow in the cloud, and it shall be for the sign of the covenant between Me and the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9014, '&ldquo;It shall be, when I bring a cloud over the earth, that the rainbow shall be seen in the cloud;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9015, '&ldquo;and I will remember My covenant which is between Me and you and every living creature of all flesh; the waters shall never again become a flood to destroy all flesh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9016, '&ldquo;The rainbow shall be in the cloud, and I will look on it to remember the everlasting covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh that is on the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9017, 'And God said to Noah, &ldquo;This is the sign of the covenant which I have established between Me and all flesh that is on the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9018, 'Now the* sons of Noah who went out of the ark were Shem, Ham, and Japheth. And Ham was the father of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9019, 'These three were the sons of Noah, and from these the whole earth was populated.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9020, 'And Noah began to be a farmer, and he planted a vineyard.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9021, 'Then he drank of the wine and was drunk, and became uncovered in his tent.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9022, 'And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and told his two brothers outside.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9023, 'But Shem and Japheth took a garment, laid it on both their shoulders, and went backward and covered the nakedness of their father. Their faces were turned away, and they did not see their father&rsquo;s nakedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9024, 'So Noah awoke from his wine, and knew what his younger son had done to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9025, 'Then he said: &ldquo;Cursed be Canaan; A servant of servants He shall be to his brethren.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9026, 'And he said: &ldquo;Blessed be the Lord, The God of Shem, And may Canaan be his servant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9027, 'May God enlarge Japheth, And may he dwell in the tents of Shem; And may Canaan be his servant.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9028, 'And Noah lived after the flood three hundred and fifty years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 9029, 'So all the days of Noah were nine hundred and fifty years; and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10001, 'Now this is the genealogy of the sons of Noah: Shem, Ham, and Japheth. And sons were born to them after the flood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10002, 'The sons of Japheth were Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10003, 'The sons of Gomer were Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10004, 'The sons of Javan were Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10005, 'From these the coastland peoples of the Gentiles were separated into their lands, everyone according to his language, according to their families, into their nations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10006, 'The sons of Ham were Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10007, 'The sons of Cush were Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabtechah; and the sons of Raamah were Sheba and Dedan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10008, 'Cush begot Nimrod; he began to be a mighty one on the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10009, 'He was a mighty hunter before the Lord; therefore it is said, &ldquo;Like Nimrod the mighty hunter before the Lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10010, 'And the beginning of his kingdom was Babel, Erech, Accad, and Calneh, in the land of Shinar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10011, 'From that land he went to Assyria and built Nineveh, Rehoboth Ir, Calah,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10012, 'and Resen between Nineveh and Calah (that is the principal city).');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10013, 'Mizraim begot Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10014, 'Pathrusim, and Casluhim (from whom came the Philistines and Caphtorim).');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10015, 'Canaan begot Sidon his firstborn, and Heth;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10016, 'the Jebusite, the Amorite, and the Girgashite;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10017, 'the Hivite, the Arkite, and the Sinite;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10018, 'the Arvadite, the Zemarite, and the Hamathite. Afterward the families of the Canaanites were dispersed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10019, 'And the border of the Canaanites was from Sidon as you go toward Gerar, as far as Gaza; then as you go toward Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah, and Zeboiim, as far as Lasha.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10020, 'These were the sons of Ham, according to their families, according to their languages, in their lands and in their nations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10021, 'And children were born also to Shem, the father of all the children of Eber, the brother of Japheth the elder.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10022, 'The sons of Shem were Elam, Asshur, Arphaxad, Lud, and Aram.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10023, 'The sons of Aram were Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10024, 'Arphaxad begot Salah, and Salah begot Eber.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10025, 'To Eber were born two sons: the name of one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided; and his brother&rsquo;s name was Joktan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10026, 'Joktan begot Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10027, 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10028, 'Obal, Abimael, Sheba,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10029, 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10030, 'And their dwelling place was from Mesha as you go toward Sephar, the mountain of the east.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10031, 'These were the sons of Shem, according to their families, according to their languages, in their lands, according to their nations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 10032, 'These were the families of the sons of Noah, according to their generations, in their nations; and from these the nations were divided on the earth after the flood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11001, 'Now the whole earth had one language and one speech.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11002, 'And it came to pass, as they journeyed from the east, that they found a plain in the land of Shinar, and they dwelt there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11003, 'Then they said to one another, &ldquo;Come, let us make bricks and bake them thoroughly.&rdquo; They had brick for stone, and they had asphalt for mortar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11004, 'And they said, &ldquo;Come, let us build ourselves a city, and a tower whose top is in the heavens; let us make a name for ourselves, lest we be scattered abroad over the face of the whole earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11005, 'But the Lord came down to see the city and the tower which the sons of men had built.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11006, 'And the Lord said, &ldquo;Indeed the people are one and they all have one language, and this is what they begin to do; now nothing that they propose to do will be withheld from them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11007, '&ldquo;Come, let Us go down and there confuse their language, that they may not understand one another&rsquo;s speech.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11008, 'So the Lord scattered them abroad from there over the face of all the earth, and they ceased building the city.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11009, 'Therefore its name is called Babel, because there the Lord confused the language of all the earth; and from there the Lord scattered them abroad over the face of all the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11010, 'This is the genealogy of Shem: Shem was one hundred years old, and begot Arphaxad two years after the flood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11011, 'After he begot Arphaxad, Shem lived five hundred years, and begot sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11012, 'Arphaxad lived thirty-five years, and begot Salah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11013, 'After he begot Salah, Arphaxad lived four hundred and three years, and begot sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11014, 'Salah lived thirty years, and begot Eber.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11015, 'After he begot Eber, Salah lived four hundred and three years, and begot sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11016, 'Eber lived thirty-four years, and begot Peleg.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11017, 'After he begot Peleg, Eber lived four hundred and thirty years, and begot sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11018, 'Peleg lived thirty years, and begot Reu.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11019, 'After he begot Reu, Peleg lived two hundred and nine years, and begot sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11020, 'Reu lived thirty-two years, and begot Serug.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11021, 'After he begot Serug, Reu lived two hundred and seven years, and begot sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11022, 'Serug lived thirty years, and begot Nahor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11023, 'After he begot Nahor, Serug lived two hundred years, and begot sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11024, 'Nahor lived twenty-nine years, and begot Terah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11025, 'After he begot Terah, Nahor lived one hundred and nineteen years, and begot sons and daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11026, 'Now Terah lived seventy years, and begot Abram, Nahor, and Haran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11027, 'This is the genealogy of Terah: Terah begot Abram, Nahor, and Haran. Haran begot Lot.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11028, 'And Haran died before his father Terah in his native land, in Ur of the Chaldeans.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11029, 'Then Abram and Nahor took wives: the name of Abram&rsquo;s wife was Sarai, and the name of Nahor&rsquo;s wife, Milcah, the daughter of Haran the father of Milcah and the father of Iscah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11030, 'But Sarai was barren; she had no child.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11031, 'And Terah took his son Abram and his grandson Lot, the son of Haran, and his daughter-in-law Sarai, his son Abram&rsquo;s wife, and they went out with them from Ur of the Chaldeans to go to the land of Canaan; and they came to Haran and dwelt there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 11032, 'So the days of Terah were two hundred and five years, and Terah died in Haran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12001, 'Now the* Lord had said to Abram: &ldquo;Get out of your country, From your family And from your father&rsquo;s house, To a land that I will show you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12002, '  I will make you a great nation; I will bless you And make your name great; And you shall be a blessing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12003, 'I will bless those who bless you, And I will curse him who curses you; And in you all the families of the earth shall be blessed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12004, 'So Abram departed as the Lord had spoken to him, and Lot went with him. And Abram was seventy-five years old when he departed from Haran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12005, 'Then Abram took Sarai his wife and Lot his brother&rsquo;s son, and all their possessions that they had gathered, and the people whom they had acquired in Haran, and they departed to go to the land of Canaan. So they came to the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12006, 'Abram passed through the land to the place of Shechem, as far as the terebinth tree of Moreh. And the Canaanites were then in the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12007, 'Then the Lord appeared to Abram and said, &ldquo;To your descendants I will give this land.&rdquo; And there he built an altar to the Lord, who had appeared to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12008, 'And he moved from there to the mountain east of Bethel, and he pitched his tent with Bethel on the west and Ai on the east; there he built an altar to the Lord and called on the name of the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12009, 'So Abram journeyed, going on still toward the South.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12010, 'Now there was a famine in the land, and Abram went down to Egypt to dwell there, for the famine was severe in the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12011, 'And it came to pass, when he was close to entering Egypt, that he said to Sarai his wife, &ldquo;Indeed I know that you are a woman of beautiful countenance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12012, '&ldquo;Therefore it will happen, when the Egyptians see you, that they will say, &lsquo;This is his wife&rsquo;; and they will kill me, but they will let you live.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12013, '&ldquo;Please say you are my sister, that it may be well with me for your sake, and that I may live because of you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12014, 'So it was, when Abram came into Egypt, that the Egyptians saw the woman, that she was very beautiful.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12015, 'The princes of Pharaoh also saw her and commended her to Pharaoh. And the woman was taken to Pharaoh&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12016, 'He treated Abram well for her sake. He had sheep, oxen, male donkeys, male and female servants, female donkeys, and camels.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12017, 'But the Lord plagued Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because of Sarai, Abram&rsquo;s wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12018, 'And Pharaoh called Abram and said, &ldquo;What is this you have done to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12019, '&ldquo;Why did you say, &lsquo;She is my sister&rsquo;? I might have taken her as my wife. Now therefore, here is your wife; take her and go your way.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 12020, 'So Pharaoh commanded his men concerning him; and they sent him away, with his wife and all that he had.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13001, 'Then Abram went up from Egypt, he and his wife and all that he had, and Lot with him, to the South.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13002, 'Abram was very rich in livestock, in silver, and in gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13003, 'And he went on his journey from the South as far as Bethel, to the place where his tent had been at the beginning, between Bethel and Ai,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13004, 'to the place of the altar which he had made there at first. And there Abram called on the name of the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13005, 'Lot also, who went with Abram, had flocks and herds and tents.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13006, 'Now the land was not able to support them, that they might dwell together, for their possessions were so great that they could not dwell together.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13007, 'And there was strife between the herdsmen of Abram&rsquo;s livestock and the herdsmen of Lot&rsquo;s livestock. The Canaanites and the Perizzites then dwelt in the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13008, 'So Abram said to Lot, &ldquo;Please let there be no strife between you and me, and between my herdsmen and your herdsmen; for we are brethren.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13009, '&ldquo;Is not the whole land before you? Please separate from me. If you take the left, then I will go to the right; or, if you go to the right, then I will go to the left.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13010, 'And Lot lifted his eyes and saw all the plain of Jordan, that it was well watered everywhere (before the Lord destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah) like the garden of the Lord, like the land of Egypt as you go toward Zoar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13011, 'Then Lot chose for himself all the plain of Jordan, and Lot journeyed east. And they separated from each other.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13012, 'Abram dwelt in the land of Canaan, and Lot dwelt in the cities of the plain and pitched his tent even as far as Sodom.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13013, 'But the men of Sodom were exceedingly wicked and sinful against the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13014, 'And the Lord said to Abram, after Lot had separated from him: &ldquo;Lift your eyes now and look from the place where you are northward, southward, eastward, and westward;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13015, '&ldquo;for all the land which you see I give to you and your descendants forever.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13016, '&ldquo;And I will make your descendants as the dust of the earth; so that if a man could number the dust of the earth, then your descendants also could be numbered.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13017, '&ldquo;Arise, walk in the land through its length and its width, for I give it to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 13018, 'Then Abram moved his tent, and went and dwelt by the terebinth trees of Mamre, which are in Hebron, and built an altar there to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14001, 'And it came to pass in the days of Amraphel king of Shinar, Arioch king of Ellasar, Chedorlaomer king of Elam, and Tidal king of nations,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14002, 'that they made war with Bera king of Sodom, Birsha king of Gomorrah, Shinab king of Admah, Shemeber king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar).');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14003, 'All these joined together in the Valley of Siddim (that is, the Salt Sea).');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14004, 'Twelve years they served Chedorlaomer, and in the thirteenth year they rebelled.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14005, 'In the fourteenth year Chedorlaomer and the kings that were with him came and attacked the Rephaim in Ashteroth Karnaim, the Zuzim in Ham, the Emim in Shaveh Kiriathaim,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14006, 'and the Horites in their mountain of Seir, as far as El Paran, which is by the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14007, 'Then they turned back and came to En Mishpat (that is, Kadesh), and attacked all the country of the Amalekites, and also the Amorites who dwelt in Hazezon Tamar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14008, 'And the king of Sodom, the king of Gomorrah, the king of Admah, the king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar) went out and joined together in battle in the Valley of Siddim');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14009, 'against Chedorlaomer king of Elam, Tidal king of nations, Amraphel king of Shinar, and Arioch king of Ellasar &ndash; four kings against five.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14010, 'Now the Valley of Siddim was full of asphalt pits; and the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled; some fell there, and the remainder fled to the mountains.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14011, 'Then they took all the goods of Sodom and Gomorrah, and all their provisions, and went their way.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14012, 'They also took Lot, Abram&rsquo;s brother&rsquo;s son who dwelt in Sodom, and his goods, and departed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14013, 'Then one who had escaped came and told Abram the Hebrew, for he dwelt by the terebinth trees of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshcol and brother of Aner; and they were allies with Abram.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14014, 'Now when* Abram heard that his brother was taken captive, he armed his three hundred and eighteen trained servants who were born in his own house, and went in pursuit as far as Dan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14015, 'He divided his forces against them by night, and he and his servants attacked them and pursued them as far as Hobah, which is north of Damascus.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14016, 'So he brought back all the goods, and also brought back his brother Lot and his goods, as well as the women and the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14017, 'And the king of Sodom went out to meet him at the Valley of Shaveh (that is, the King&rsquo;s Valley), after his return from the defeat of Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14018, 'Then Melchizedek king of Salem brought out bread and wine; he was the priest of God Most High.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14019, 'And he blessed him and said: &ldquo;Blessed be Abram of God Most High, Possessor of heaven and earth;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14020, 'And blessed be God Most High, Who has delivered your enemies into your hand.&rdquo;| And he gave him a tithe of all.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14021, 'Now the king of Sodom said to Abram, &ldquo;Give me the persons, and take the goods for yourself.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14022, 'But Abram said to the king of Sodom, &ldquo;I have raised my hand to the Lord, God Most High, the Possessor of heaven and earth,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14023, '&ldquo;that I will take nothing, from a thread to a sandal strap, and that I will not take anything that is yours, lest you should say, &lsquo;I have made Abram rich&rsquo; &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 14024, '&ldquo;except only what the young men have eaten, and the portion of the men who went with me: Aner, Eshcol, and Mamre; let them take their portion.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15001, 'After these things the* word of the Lord came to Abram in a vision, saying, &ldquo;Do not be afraid, Abram. I am your shield, your exceedingly great reward.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15002, 'But Abram said, &ldquo;Lord God, what will You give me, seeing I go childless, and the heir of my house is Eliezer of Damascus?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15003, 'Then Abram said, &ldquo;Look, You have given me no offspring; indeed one born in my house is my heir!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15004, 'And behold, the word of the Lord came to him, saying, &ldquo;This one shall not be your heir, but one who will come from your own body shall be your heir.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15005, 'Then He brought him outside and said, &ldquo;Look now toward heaven, and count the stars if you are able to number them.&rdquo; And He said to him, &ldquo;So shall your descendants be.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15006, 'And he believed in the Lord, and He accounted it to him for righteousness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15007, 'Then He said to him, &ldquo;I am the Lord, who brought you out of Ur of the Chaldeans, to give you this land to inherit it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15008, 'And he said, &ldquo;Lord God, how shall I know that I will inherit it?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15009, 'So He said to him, &ldquo;Bring Me a three-year-old heifer, a three-year-old female goat, a three-year-old ram, a turtledove, and a young pigeon.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15010, 'Then he brought all these to Him and cut them in two, down the middle, and placed each piece opposite the other; but he did not cut the birds in two.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15011, 'And when the vultures came down on the carcasses, Abram drove them away.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15012, 'Now when the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell upon Abram; and behold, horror and great darkness fell upon him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15013, 'Then He said to Abram: &ldquo;Know certainly that your descendants will be strangers in a land that is not theirs, and will serve them, and they will afflict them four hundred years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15014, '&ldquo;And also the nation whom they serve I will judge; afterward they shall come out with great possessions.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15015, '&ldquo;Now as for you, you shall go to your fathers in peace; you shall be buried at a good old age.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15016, '&ldquo;But in the fourth generation they shall return here, for the iniquity of the Amorites is not yet complete.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15017, 'And it came to pass, when the sun went down and it was dark, that behold, there appeared a smoking oven and a burning torch that passed between those pieces.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15018, 'On the same day the Lord made a covenant with Abram, saying: &ldquo;To your descendants I have given this land, from the river of Egypt to the great river, the River Euphrates &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15019, '&ldquo;the Kenites, the Kenezzites, the Kadmonites,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15020, '&ldquo;the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 15021, '&ldquo;the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16001, 'Now Sarai, Abram&rsquo;s wife, had borne him no children. And she had an Egyptian maidservant whose name was Hagar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16002, 'So Sarai said to Abram, &ldquo;See now, the Lord has restrained me from bearing children. Please, go in to my maid; perhaps I shall obtain children by her.&rdquo; And Abram heeded the voice of Sarai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16003, 'Then Sarai, Abram&rsquo;s wife, took Hagar her maid, the Egyptian, and gave her to her husband Abram to be his wife, after Abram had dwelt ten years in the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16004, 'So he went in to Hagar, and she conceived. And when she saw that she had conceived, her mistress became despised in her eyes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16005, 'Then Sarai said to Abram, &ldquo;My wrong be upon you! I gave my maid into your embrace; and when she saw that she had conceived, I became despised in her eyes. The Lord judge between you and me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16006, 'So Abram said to Sarai, &ldquo;Indeed your maid is in your hand; do to her as you please.&rdquo; And when Sarai dealt harshly with her, she fled from her presence.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16007, 'Now the Angel of the Lord found her by a spring of water in the wilderness, by the spring on the way to Shur.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16008, 'And He said, &ldquo;Hagar, Sarai&rsquo;s maid, where have you come from, and where are you going?&rdquo; She said, &ldquo;I am fleeing from the presence of my mistress Sarai.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16009, 'The Angel of the Lord said to her, &ldquo;Return to your mistress, and submit yourself under her hand.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16010, 'Then the Angel of the Lord said to her, &ldquo;I will multiply your descendants exceedingly, so that they shall not be counted for multitude.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16011, 'And the Angel of the Lord said to her: &ldquo;Behold, you are with child, And you shall bear a son. You shall call his name Ishmael, Because the Lord has heard your affliction.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16012, 'He shall be a wild man; His hand shall be against every man, And every man&rsquo;s hand against him. And he shall dwell in the presence of all his brethren.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16013, 'Then she called the name of the Lord who spoke to her, You-Are-the-God-Who-Sees; for she said, &ldquo;Have I also here seen Him who sees me?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16014, 'Therefore the well was called Beer Lahai Roi; observe, it is between Kadesh and Bered.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16015, 'So Hagar bore Abram a son; and Abram named his son, whom Hagar bore, Ishmael.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 16016, 'Abram was eighty-six years old when Hagar bore Ishmael to Abram.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17001, 'When Abram was ninety-nine years old, the Lord appeared to Abram and said to him, &ldquo;I am Almighty God; walk before Me and be blameless.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17002, '&ldquo;And I will make My covenant between Me and you, and will multiply you exceedingly.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17003, 'Then Abram fell on his face, and God talked with him, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17004, '&ldquo;As for Me, behold, My covenant is with you, and you shall be a father of many nations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17005, '&ldquo;No longer shall your name be called Abram, but your name shall be Abraham; for I have made you a father of many nations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17006, '&ldquo;I will make you exceedingly fruitful; and I will make nations of you, and kings shall come from you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17007, '&ldquo;And I will establish My covenant between Me and you and your descendants after you in their generations, for an everlasting covenant, to be God to you and your descendants after you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17008, '&ldquo;Also I give to you and your descendants after you the land in which you are a stranger, all the land of Canaan, as an everlasting possession; and I will be their God.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17009, 'And God said to Abraham: &ldquo;As for you, you shall keep My covenant, you and your descendants after you throughout their generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17010, '&ldquo;This is My covenant which you shall keep, between Me and you and your descendants after you: Every male child among you shall be circumcised;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17011, '&ldquo;and you shall be circumcised in the flesh of your foreskins, and it shall be a sign of the covenant between Me and you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17012, '&ldquo;He who is eight days old among you shall be circumcised, every male child in your generations, he who is born in your house or bought with money from any foreigner who is not your descendant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17013, '&ldquo;He who is born in your house and he who is bought with your money must be circumcised, and My covenant shall be in your flesh for an everlasting covenant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17014, '&ldquo;And the uncircumcised male child, who is not circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin, that person shall be cut off from his people; he has broken My covenant.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17015, 'Then God said to Abraham, &ldquo;As for Sarai your wife, you shall not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall be her name.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17016, '&ldquo;And I will bless her and also give you a son by her; then I will bless her, and she shall be a mother of nations; kings of peoples shall be from her.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17017, 'Then Abraham fell on his face and laughed, and said in his heart, &ldquo;Shall a child be born to a man who is one hundred years old? And shall Sarah, who is ninety years old, bear a child?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17018, 'And Abraham said to God, &ldquo;Oh, that Ishmael might live before You!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17019, 'Then God said: &ldquo;No, Sarah your wife shall bear you a son, and you shall call his name Isaac; I will establish My covenant with him for an everlasting covenant, and with his descendants after him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17020, '&ldquo;And as for Ishmael, I have heard you. Behold, I have blessed him, and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him exceedingly. He shall beget twelve princes, and I will make him a great nation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17021, '&ldquo;But My covenant I will establish with Isaac, whom Sarah shall bear to you at this set time next year.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17022, 'Then He finished talking with him, and God went up from Abraham.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17023, 'So Abraham took Ishmael his son, all who were born in his house and all who were bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham&rsquo;s house, and circumcised the flesh of their foreskins that very same day, as God had said to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17024, 'Abraham was ninety-nine years old when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17025, 'And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17026, 'That very same day Abraham was circumcised, and his son Ishmael;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 17027, 'and all the men of his house, born in the house or bought with money from a foreigner, were circumcised with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18001, 'Then the Lord appeared to him by the terebinth trees of Mamre,a as he was sitting in the tent door in the heat of the day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18002, 'So he lifted his eyes and looked, and behold, three men were standing by him; and when he saw them, he ran from the tent door to meet them, and bowed himself to the ground,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18003, 'and said, &ldquo;My Lord, if I have now found favor in Your sight, do not pass on by Your servant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18004, '&ldquo;Please let a little water be brought, and wash your feet, and rest yourselves under the tree.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18005, '&ldquo;And I will bring a morsel of bread, that you may refresh your hearts. After that you may pass by, inasmuch as you have come to your servant.&rdquo; They said, &ldquo;Do as you have said.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18006, 'So Abraham hurried into the tent to Sarah and said, &ldquo;Quickly, make ready three measures of fine meal; knead it and make cakes.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18007, 'And Abraham ran to the herd, took a tender and good calf, gave it to a young man, and he hastened to prepare it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18008, 'So he took butter and milk and the calf which he had prepared, and set it before them; and he stood by them under the tree as they ate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18009, 'Then they said to him, &ldquo;Where is Sarah your wife?&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;Here, in the tent.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18010, 'And He said, &ldquo;I will certainly return to you according to the time of life, and behold, Sarah your wife shall have a son.&rdquo; (Sarah was listening in the tent door which was behind him.)');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18011, 'Now Abraham and Sarah were old, well advanced in age; and Sarah had passed the age of childbearing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18012, 'Therefore Sarah laughed within herself, saying, &ldquo;After I have grown old, shall I have pleasure, my lord being old also?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18013, 'And the Lord said to Abraham, &ldquo;Why did Sarah laugh, saying, &lsquo;Shall I surely bear a child, since I am old?&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18014, '&ldquo;Is anything too hard for the Lord? At the appointed time I will return to you, according to the time of life, and Sarah shall have a son.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18015, 'But Sarah denied it, saying, &ldquo;I did not laugh,&rdquo; for she was afraid. And He said, &ldquo;No, but you did laugh!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18016, 'Then the men rose from there and looked toward Sodom, and Abraham went with them to send them on the way.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18017, 'And the Lord said, &ldquo;Shall I hide from Abraham what I am doing,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18018, '&ldquo;since Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation, and all the nations of the earth shall be blessed in him?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18019, '&ldquo;For I have known him, in order that he may command his children and his household after him, that they keep the way of the Lord, to do righteousness and justice, that the Lord may bring to Abraham what He has spoken to him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18020, 'And the* Lord said, &ldquo;Because the outcry against Sodom and Gomorrah is great, and because their sin is very grave,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18021, '&ldquo;I will go down now and see whether they have done altogether according to the outcry against it that has come to Me; and if not, I will know.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18022, 'Then the men turned away from there and went toward Sodom, but Abraham still stood before the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18023, 'And Abraham came near and said, &ldquo;Would You also destroy the righteous with the wicked?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18024, '&ldquo;Suppose there were fifty righteous within the city; would You also destroy the place and not spare it for the fifty righteous that were in it?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18025, '&ldquo;Far be it from You to do such a thing as this, to slay the righteous with the wicked, so that the righteous should be as the wicked; far be it from You! Shall not the Judge of all the earth do right?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18026, 'So the Lord said, &ldquo;If I find in Sodom fifty righteous within the city, then I will spare all the place for their sakes.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18027, 'Then Abraham answered and said, &ldquo;Indeed now, I who am but dust and ashes have taken it upon myself to speak to the Lord:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18028, '&ldquo;Suppose there were five less than the fifty righteous; would You destroy all of the city for lack of five?&rdquo; So He said, &ldquo;If I find there forty-five, I will not destroy it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18029, 'And he spoke to Him yet again and said, &ldquo;Suppose there should be forty found there?&rdquo; So He said, &ldquo;I will not do it for the sake of forty.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18030, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak: Suppose thirty should be found there?&rdquo; So He said, &ldquo;I will not do it if I find thirty there.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18031, 'And he said, &ldquo;Indeed now, I have taken it upon myself to speak to the Lord: Suppose twenty should be found there?&rdquo; So He said, &ldquo;I will not destroy it for the sake of twenty.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18032, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak but once more: Suppose ten should be found there?&rdquo; And He said, &ldquo;I will not destroy it for the sake of ten.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 18033, 'So the Lord went His way as soon as He had finished speaking with Abraham; and Abraham returned to his place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19001, 'Now the two angels came to Sodom in the evening, and Lot was sitting in the gate of Sodom. When Lot saw them, he rose to meet them, and he bowed himself with his face toward the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19002, 'And he said, &ldquo;Here now, my lords, please turn in to your servant&rsquo;s house and spend the night, and wash your feet; then you may rise early and go on your way.&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;No, but we will spend the night in the open square.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19003, 'But he insisted strongly; so they turned in to him and entered his house. Then he made them a feast, and baked unleavened bread, and they ate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19004, 'Now before they lay down, the men of the city, the men of Sodom, both old and young, all the people from every quarter, surrounded the house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19005, 'And they called to Lot and said to him, &ldquo;Where are the men who came to you tonight? Bring them out to us that we may know them carnally.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19006, 'So Lot went out to them through the doorway, shut the door behind him,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19007, 'and said, &ldquo;Please, my brethren, do not do so wickedly!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19008, '&ldquo;See now, I have two daughters who have not known a man; please, let me bring them out to you, and you may do to them as you wish; only do nothing to these men, since this is the reason they have come under the shadow of my roof.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19009, 'And they said, &ldquo;Stand back!&rdquo; Then they said, &ldquo;This one came in to stay here, and he keeps acting as a judge; now we will deal worse with you than with them.&rdquo; So they pressed hard against the man Lot, and came near to break down the door.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19010, 'But the men reached out their hands and pulled Lot into the house with them, and shut the door.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19011, 'And they struck the men who were at the doorway of the house with blindness, both small and great, so that they became weary trying to find the door.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19012, 'Then the men said to Lot, &ldquo;Have you anyone else here? Son-in-law, your sons, your daughters, and whomever you have in the city &ndash; take them out of this place!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19013, '&ldquo;For we will destroy this place, because the outcry against them has grown great before the face of the Lord, and the Lord has sent us to destroy it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19014, 'So Lot went out and spoke to his sons-in-law, who had married his daughters, and said, &ldquo;Get up, get out of this place; for the Lord will destroy this city!&rdquo; But to his sons-in-law he seemed to be joking.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19015, 'When the morning dawned, the angels urged Lot to hurry, saying, &ldquo;Arise, take your wife and your two daughters who are here, lest you be consumed in the punishment of the city.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19016, 'And while he lingered, the men took hold of his hand, his wife&rsquo;s hand, and the hands of his two daughters, the Lord being merciful to him, and they brought him out and set him outside the city.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19017, 'So it came to pass, when they had brought them outside, that hea said, &ldquo;Escape for your life! Do not look behind you nor stay anywhere in the plain. Escape to the mountains, lest you be destroyed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19018, 'Then Lot said to them, &ldquo;Please, no, my lords!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19019, '&ldquo;Indeed now, your servant has found favor in your sight, and you have increased your mercy which you have shown me by saving my life; but I cannot escape to the mountains, lest some evil overtake me and I die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19020, '&ldquo;See now, this city is near enough to flee to, and it is a little one; please let me escape there (is it not a little one?) and my soul shall live.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19021, 'And he said to him, &ldquo;See, I have favored you concerning this thing also, in that I will not overthrow this city for which you have spoken.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19022, '&ldquo;Hurry, escape there. For I cannot do anything until you arrive there.&rdquo; Therefore the name of the city was called Zoar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19023, 'The sun had risen upon the earth when Lot entered Zoar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19024, 'Then the Lord rained brimstone and fire on Sodom and Gomorrah, from the Lord out of the heavens.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19025, 'So He overthrew those cities, all the plain, all the inhabitants of the cities, and what grew on the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19026, 'But his wife looked back behind him, and she became a pillar of salt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19027, 'And Abraham went early in the morning to the place where he had stood before the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19028, 'Then he looked toward Sodom and Gomorrah, and toward all the land of the plain; and he saw, and behold, the smoke of the land which went up like the smoke of a furnace.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19029, 'And it came to pass, when God destroyed the cities of the plain, that God remembered Abraham, and sent Lot out of the midst of the overthrow, when He overthrew the cities in which Lot had dwelt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19030, 'Then Lot went up out of Zoar and dwelt in the mountains, and his two daughters were with him; for he was afraid to dwell in Zoar. And he and his two daughters dwelt in a cave.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19031, 'Now the firstborn said to the younger, &ldquo;Our father is old, and there is no man on the earth to come in to us as is the custom of all the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19032, '&ldquo;Come, let us make our father drink wine, and we will lie with him, that we may preserve the lineage of our father.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19033, 'So they made their father drink wine that night. And the firstborn went in and lay with her father, and he did not know when she lay down or when she arose.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19034, 'It happened on the next day that the firstborn said to the younger, &ldquo;Indeed I lay with my father last night; let us make him drink wine tonight also, and you go in and lie with him, that we may preserve the lineage of our father.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19035, 'Then they made their father drink wine that night also. And the younger arose and lay with him, and he did not know when she lay down or when she arose.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19036, 'Thus both the daughters of Lot were with child by their father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19037, 'The firstborn bore a son and called his name Moab; he is the father of the Moabites to this day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 19038, 'And the younger, she also bore a son and called his name Ben-Ammi; he is the father of the people of Ammon to this day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20001, 'And Abraham journeyed from there to the South, and dwelt between Kadesh and Shur, and stayed in Gerar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20002, 'Now Abraham said of Sarah his wife, &ldquo;She is my sister.&rdquo; And Abimelech king of Gerar sent and took Sarah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20003, 'But God came to Abimelech in a dream by night, and said to him, &ldquo;Indeed you are a dead man because of the woman whom you have taken, for she is a man&rsquo;s wife.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20004, 'But Abimelech had not come near her; and he said, &ldquo;Lord, will You slay a righteous nation also?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20005, '&ldquo;Did he not say to me, &lsquo;She is my sister&rsquo;? And she, even she herself said, &lsquo;He is my brother.&rsquo; In the integrity of my heart and innocence of my hands I have done this.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20006, 'And God said to him in a dream, &ldquo;Yes, I know that you did this in the integrity of your heart. For I also withheld you from sinning against Me; therefore I did not let you touch her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20007, '&ldquo;Now therefore, restore the man&rsquo;s wife; for he is a prophet, and he will pray for you and you shall live. But if you do not restore her, know that you shall surely die, you and all who are yours.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20008, 'So Abimelech rose early in the morning, called all his servants, and told all these things in their hearing; and the men were very much afraid.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20009, 'And Abimelech called Abraham and said to him, &ldquo;What have you done to us? How have I offended you, that you have brought on me and on my kingdom a great sin? You have done deeds to me that ought not to be done.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20010, 'Then Abimelech said to Abraham, &ldquo;What did you have in view, that you have done this thing?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20011, 'And Abraham said, &ldquo;Because I thought, surely the fear of God is not in this place; and they will kill me on account of my wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20012, '&ldquo;But indeed she is truly my sister. She is the daughter of my father, but not the daughter of my mother; and she became my wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20013, '&ldquo;And it came to pass, when God caused me to wander from my father&rsquo;s house, that I said to her, &lsquo;This is your kindness that you should do for me: in every place, wherever we go, say of me, &ldquo;He is my brother.&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20014, 'Then Abimelech took sheep, oxen, and male and female servants, and gave them to Abraham; and he restored Sarah his wife to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20015, 'And Abimelech said, &ldquo;See, my land is before you; dwell where it pleases you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20016, 'Then to Sarah he said, &ldquo;Behold, I have given your brother a thousand pieces of silver; indeed this vindicates youa before all who are with you and before everybody.&rdquo; Thus she was rebuked.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20017, 'So Abraham prayed to God; and God healed Abimelech, his wife, and his female servants. Then they bore children;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 20018, 'for the Lord had closed up all the wombs of the house of Abimelech because of Sarah, Abraham&rsquo;s wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21001, 'And the Lord visited Sarah as He had said, and the Lord did for Sarah as He had spoken.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21002, 'For Sarah conceived and bore Abraham a son in his old age, at the set time of which God had spoken to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21003, 'And Abraham called the name of his son who was born to him &ndash; whom Sarah bore to him &ndash; Isaac.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21004, 'Then Abraham circumcised his son Isaac when he was eight days old, as God had commanded him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21005, 'Now Abraham was one hundred years old when his son Isaac was born to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21006, 'And Sarah said, &ldquo;God has made me laugh, and all who hear will laugh with me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21007, 'She also said, &ldquo;Who would have said to Abraham that Sarah would nurse children? For I have borne him a son in his old age.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21008, 'So the child grew and was weaned. And Abraham made a great feast on the same day that Isaac was weaned.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21009, 'And Sarah saw the son of Hagar the Egyptian, whom she had borne to Abraham, scoffing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21010, 'Therefore she said to Abraham, &ldquo;Cast out this bondwoman and her son; for the son of this bondwoman shall not be heir with my son, namely with Isaac.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21011, 'And the matter was very displeasing in Abraham&rsquo;s sight because of his son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21012, 'But God said to Abraham, &ldquo;Do not let it be displeasing in your sight because of the lad or because of your bondwoman. Whatever Sarah has said to you, listen to her voice; for in Isaac your seed shall be called.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21013, '&ldquo;Yet I will also make a nation of the son of the bondwoman, because he is your seed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21014, 'So Abraham rose early in the morning, and took bread and a skin of water; and putting it on her shoulder, he gave it and the boy to Hagar, and sent her away. Then she departed and wandered in the Wilderness of Beersheba.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21015, 'And the water in the skin was used up, and she placed the boy under one of the shrubs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21016, 'Then she went and sat down across from him at a distance of about a bowshot; for she said to herself, &ldquo;Let me not see the death of the boy.&rdquo; So she sat opposite him, and lifted her voice and wept.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21017, 'And God heard the voice of the lad. Then the angel of God called to Hagar out of heaven, and said to her, &ldquo;What ails you, Hagar? Fear not, for God has heard the voice of the lad where he is.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21018, '&ldquo;Arise, lift up the lad and hold him with your hand, for I will make him a great nation.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21019, 'Then God opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water. And she went and filled the skin with water, and gave the lad a drink.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21020, 'So God was with the lad; and he grew and dwelt in the wilderness, and became an archer.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21021, 'He dwelt in the Wilderness of Paran; and his mother took a wife for him from the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21022, 'And it came to pass at that time that Abimelech and Phichol, the commander of his army, spoke to Abraham, saying, &ldquo;God is with you in all that you do.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21023, '&ldquo;Now therefore, swear to me by God that you will not deal falsely with me, with my offspring, or with my posterity; but that according to the kindness that I have done to you, you will do to me and to the land in which you have dwelt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21024, 'And Abraham said, &ldquo;I will swear.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21025, 'Then Abraham rebuked Abimelech because of a well of water which Abimelech&rsquo;s servants had seized.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21026, 'And Abimelech said, &ldquo;I do not know who has done this thing; you did not tell me, nor had I heard of it until today.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21027, 'So Abraham took sheep and oxen and gave them to Abimelech, and the two of them made a covenant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21028, 'And Abraham set seven ewe lambs of the flock by themselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21029, 'Then Abimelech asked Abraham, &ldquo;What is the meaning of these seven ewe lambs which you have set by themselves?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21030, 'And he said, &ldquo;You will take these seven ewe lambs from my hand, that they may be my witness that I have dug this well.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21031, 'Therefore he called that place Beersheba, because the two of them swore an oath there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21032, 'Thus they made a covenant at Beersheba. So Abimelech rose with Phichol, the commander of his army, and they returned to the land of the Philistines.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21033, 'Then Abraham planted a tamarisk tree in Beersheba, and there called on the name of the Lord, the Everlasting God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 21034, 'And Abraham stayed in the land of the Philistines many days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22001, 'Now it* came to pass after these things that God tested Abraham, and said to him, &ldquo;Abraham!&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Here I am.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22002, 'Then He said, &ldquo;Take now your son, your only son Isaac, whom you love, and go to the land of Moriah, and offer him there as a burnt offering on one of the mountains of which I shall tell you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22003, 'So Abraham rose early in the morning and saddled his donkey, and took two of his young men with him, and Isaac his son; and he split the wood for the burnt offering, and arose and went to the place of which God had told him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22004, 'Then on the third day Abraham lifted his eyes and saw the place afar off.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22005, 'And Abraham said to his young men, &ldquo;Stay here with the donkey; the lad and I will go yonder and worship, and we will come back to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22006, 'So Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering and laid it on Isaac his son; and he took the fire in his hand, and a knife, and the two of them went together.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22007, 'But Isaac spoke to Abraham his father and said, &ldquo;My father!&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Here I am, my son.&rdquo; Then he said, &ldquo;Look, the fire and the wood, but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22008, 'And Abraham said, &ldquo;My son, God will provide for Himself the lamb for a burnt offering.&rdquo; So the two of them went together.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22009, 'Then they came to the place of which God had told him. And Abraham built an altar there and placed the wood in order; and he bound Isaac his son and laid him on the altar, upon the wood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22010, 'And Abraham stretched out his hand and took the knife to slay his son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22011, 'But the Angel of the Lord called to him from heaven and said, &ldquo;Abraham, Abraham!&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;Here I am.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22012, 'And He said, &ldquo;Do not lay your hand on the lad, or do anything to him; for now I know that you fear God, since you have not withheld your son, your only son, from Me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22013, 'Then Abraham lifted his eyes and looked, and there behind him was a ram caught in a thicket by its horns. So Abraham went and took the ram, and offered it up for a burnt offering instead of his son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22014, 'And Abraham called the name of the place, The-Lord-Will-Provide; as it is said to this day, &ldquo;In the Mount of the Lord it shall be provided.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22015, 'Then the Angel of the Lord called to Abraham a second time out of heaven,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22016, 'and said: &ldquo;By Myself I have sworn, says the Lord, because you have done this thing, and have not withheld your son, your only son &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22017, '&ldquo;blessing I will bless you, and multiplying I will multiply your descendants as the stars of the heaven and as the sand which is on the seashore; and your descendants shall possess the gate of their enemies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22018, '&ldquo;In your seed all the nations of the earth shall be blessed, because you have obeyed My voice.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22019, 'So Abraham returned to his young men, and they rose and went together to Beersheba; and Abraham dwelt at Beersheba.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22020, 'Now it came to pass after these things that it was told Abraham, saying, &ldquo;Indeed Milcah also has borne children to your brother Nahor:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22021, '&ldquo;Huz his firstborn, Buz his brother, Kemuel the father of Aram,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22022, '&ldquo;Chesed, Hazo, Pildash, Jidlaph, and Bethuel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22023, 'And Bethuel begot Rebekah. These eight Milcah bore to Nahor, Abraham&rsquo;s brother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 22024, 'His concubine, whose name was Reumah, also bore Tebah, Gaham, Thahash, and Maachah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23001, 'Sarah lived one hundred and twenty-seven years; these were the years of the life of Sarah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23002, 'So Sarah died in Kirjath Arba (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan, and Abraham came to mourn for Sarah and to weep for her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23003, 'Then Abraham stood up from before his dead, and spoke to the sons of Heth, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23004, '&ldquo;I am a foreigner and a visitor among you. Give me property for a burial place among you, that I may bury my dead out of my sight.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23005, 'And the sons of Heth answered Abraham, saying to him,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23006, '&ldquo;Hear us, my lord: You are a mighty prince among us; bury your dead in the choicest of our burial places. None of us will withhold from you his burial place, that you may bury your dead.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23007, 'Then Abraham stood up and bowed himself to the people of the land, the sons of Heth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23008, 'And he spoke with them, saying, &ldquo;If it is your wish that I bury my dead out of my sight, hear me, and meet with Ephron the son of Zohar for me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23009, '&ldquo;that he may give me the cave of Machpelah which he has, which is at the end of his field. Let him give it to me at the full price, as property for a burial place among you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23010, 'Now Ephron dwelt among the sons of Heth; and Ephron the Hittite answered Abraham in the presence of the sons of Heth, all who entered at the gate of his city, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23011, '&ldquo;No, my lord, hear me: I give you the field and the cave that is in it; I give it to you in the presence of the sons of my people. I give it to you. Bury your dead!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23012, 'Then Abraham bowed himself down before the people of the land;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23013, 'and he spoke to Ephron in the hearing of the people of the land, saying, &ldquo;If you will give it, please hear me. I will give you money for the field; take it from me and I will bury my dead there.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23014, 'And Ephron answered Abraham, saying to him,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23015, '&ldquo;My lord, listen to me; the land is worth four hundred shekels of silver. What is that between you and me? So bury your dead.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23016, 'And Abraham listened to Ephron; and Abraham weighed out the silver for Ephron which he had named in the hearing of the sons of Heth, four hundred shekels of silver, currency of the merchants.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23017, 'So the field of Ephron which was in Machpelah, which was before Mamre, the field and the cave which was in it, and all the trees that were in the field, which were within all the surrounding borders, were deeded');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23018, 'to Abraham as a possession in the presence of the sons of Heth, before all who went in at the gate of his city.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23019, 'And after this, Abraham buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the field of Machpelah, before Mamre (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 23020, 'So the field and the cave that is in it were deeded to Abraham by the sons of Heth as property for a burial place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24001, 'Now Abraham was old, well advanced in age; and the Lord had blessed Abraham in all things.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24002, 'So Abraham said to the oldest servant of his house, who ruled over all that he had, &ldquo;Please, put your hand under my thigh,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24003, '&ldquo;and I will make you swear by the Lord, the God of heaven and the God of the earth, that you will not take a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, among whom I dwell;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24004, '&ldquo;but you shall go to my country and to my family, and take a wife for my son Isaac.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24005, 'And the servant said to him, &ldquo;Perhaps the woman will not be willing to follow me to this land. Must I take your son back to the land from which you came?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24006, 'But Abraham said to him, &ldquo;Beware that you do not take my son back there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24007, '&ldquo;The Lord God of heaven, who took me from my father&rsquo;s house and from the land of my family, and who spoke to me and swore to me, saying, &lsquo;To your descendantsa I give this land,&rsquo; He will send His angel before you, and you shall take a wife for my son from ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24008, '&ldquo;And if the woman is not willing to follow you, then you will be released from this oath; only do not take my son back there.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24009, 'So the servant put his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master, and swore to him concerning this matter.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24010, 'Then the servant took ten of his master&rsquo;s camels and departed, for all his master&rsquo;s goods were in his hand. And he arose and went to Mesopotamia, to the city of Nahor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24011, 'And he made his camels kneel down outside the city by a well of water at evening time, the time when women go out to draw water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24012, 'Then he said, &ldquo;O Lord God of my master Abraham, please give me success this day, and show kindness to my master Abraham.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24013, '&ldquo;Behold, here I stand by the well of water, and the daughters of the men of the city are coming out to draw water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24014, '&ldquo;Now let it be that the young woman to whom I say, &lsquo;Please let down your pitcher that I may drink,&rsquo; and she says, &lsquo;Drink, and I will also give your camels a drink&rsquo; &ndash; let her be the one You have appointed for Your servant Isaac. And by this I will know that ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24015, 'And it happened, before he had finished speaking, that behold, Rebekah, who was born to Bethuel, son of Milcah, the wife of Nahor, Abraham&rsquo;s brother, came out with her pitcher on her shoulder.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24016, 'Now the young woman was very beautiful to behold, a virgin; no man had known her. And she went down to the well, filled her pitcher, and came up.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24017, 'And the servant ran to meet her and said, &ldquo;Please let me drink a little water from your pitcher.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24018, 'So she said, &ldquo;Drink, my lord.&rdquo; Then she quickly let her pitcher down to her hand, and gave him a drink.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24019, 'And when she had finished giving him a drink, she said, &ldquo;I will draw water for your camels also, until they have finished drinking.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24020, 'Then she quickly emptied her pitcher into the trough, ran back to the well to draw water, and drew for all his camels.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24021, 'And the man, wondering at her, remained silent so as to know whether the Lord had made his journey prosperous or not.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24022, 'So it was, when the camels had finished drinking, that the man took a golden nose ring weighing half a shekel, and two bracelets for her wrists weighing ten shekels of gold,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24023, 'and said, &ldquo;Whose daughter are you? Tell me, please, is there room in your father&rsquo;s house for us to lodge?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24024, 'So she said to him, &ldquo;I am the daughter of Bethuel, Milcah&rsquo;s son, whom she bore to Nahor.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24025, 'Moreover she said to him, &ldquo;We have both straw and feed enough, and room to lodge.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24026, 'Then the man bowed down his head and worshiped the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24027, 'And he said, &ldquo;Blessed be the Lord God of my master Abraham, who has not forsaken His mercy and His truth toward my master. As for me, being on the way, the Lord led me to the house of my master&rsquo;s brethren.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24028, 'So the young woman ran and told her mother&rsquo;s household these things.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24029, 'Now Rebekah had a brother whose name was Laban, and Laban ran out to the man by the well.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24030, 'So it came to pass, when he saw the nose ring, and the bracelets on his sister&rsquo;s wrists, and when he heard the words of his sister Rebekah, saying, &ldquo;Thus the man spoke to me,&rdquo; that he went to the man. And there he stood by the camels at the well.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24031, 'And he said, &ldquo;Come in, O blessed of the Lord! Why do you stand outside? For I have prepared the house, and a place for the camels.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24032, 'Then the man came to the house. And he unloaded the camels, and provided straw and feed for the camels, and water to wash his feet and the feet of the men who were with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24033, 'Food was set before him to eat, but he said, &ldquo;I will not eat until I have told about my errand.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Speak on.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24034, 'So he said, &ldquo;I am Abraham&rsquo;s servant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24035, '&ldquo;The Lord has blessed my master greatly, and he has become great; and He has given him flocks and herds, silver and gold, male and female servants, and camels and donkeys.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24036, '&ldquo;And Sarah my master&rsquo;s wife bore a son to my master when she was old; and to him he has given all that he has.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24037, '&ldquo;Now my master made me swear, saying, &lsquo;You shall not take a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose land I dwell; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24038, '&lsquo;but you shall go to my father&rsquo;s house and to my family, and take a wife for my son.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24039, '&ldquo;And I said to my master, &lsquo;Perhaps the woman will not follow me.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24040, '&ldquo;But he said to me, &lsquo;The Lord, before whom I walk, will send His angel with you and prosper your way; and you shall take a wife for my son from my family and from my father&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24041, '&lsquo;You will be clear from this oath when you arrive among my family; for if they will not give her to you, then you will be released from my oath.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24042, '&ldquo;And this day I came to the well and said, &lsquo;O Lord God of my master Abraham, if You will now prosper the way in which I go,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24043, '&lsquo;behold, I stand by the well of water; and it shall come to pass that when the virgin comes out to draw water, and I say to her, &ldquo;Please give me a little water from your pitcher to drink,&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24044, '&lsquo;and she says to me, &ldquo;Drink, and I will draw for your camels also,&rdquo; &ndash; let her be the woman whom the Lord has appointed for my master&rsquo;s son.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24045, '&ldquo;But before I had finished speaking in my heart, there was Rebekah, coming out with her pitcher on her shoulder; and she went down to the well and drew water. And I said to her, &lsquo;Please let me drink.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24046, '&ldquo;And she made haste and let her pitcher down from her shoulder, and said, &lsquo;Drink, and I will give your camels a drink also.&rsquo; So I drank, and she gave the camels a drink also.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24047, '&ldquo;Then I asked her, and said, &lsquo;Whose daughter are you?&rsquo; And she said, &lsquo;The daughter of Bethuel, Nahor&rsquo;s son, whom Milcah bore to him.&rsquo; So I put the nose ring on her nose and the bracelets on her wrists.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24048, '&ldquo;And I bowed my head and worshiped the Lord, and blessed the Lord God of my master Abraham, who had led me in the way of truth to take the daughter of my master&rsquo;s brother for his son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24049, '&ldquo;Now if you will deal kindly and truly with my master, tell me. And if not, tell me, that I may turn to the right hand or to the left.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24050, 'Then Laban and Bethuel answered and said, &ldquo;The thing comes from the Lord; we cannot speak to you either bad or good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24051, '&ldquo;Here is Rebekah before you; take her and go, and let her be your master&rsquo;s son&rsquo;s wife, as the Lord has spoken.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24052, 'And it came to pass, when Abraham&rsquo;s servant heard their words, that he worshiped the Lord, bowing himself to the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24053, 'Then the servant brought out jewelry of silver, jewelry of gold, and clothing, and gave them to Rebekah. He also gave precious things to her brother and to her mother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24054, 'And he and the men who were with him ate and drank and stayed all night. Then they arose in the morning, and he said, &ldquo;Send me away to my master.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24055, 'But her brother and her mother said, &ldquo;Let the young woman stay with us a few days, at least ten; after that she may go.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24056, 'And he said to them, &ldquo;Do not hinder me, since the Lord has prospered my way; send me away so that I may go to my master.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24057, 'So they said, &ldquo;We will call the young woman and ask her personally.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24058, 'Then they called Rebekah and said to her, &ldquo;Will you go with this man?&rdquo; And she said, &ldquo;I will go.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24059, 'So they sent away Rebekah their sister and her nurse, and Abraham&rsquo;s servant and his men.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24060, 'And they blessed Rebekah and said to her: &ldquo;Our sister, may you become The mother of thousands of ten thousands; And may your descendants possess The gates of those who hate them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24061, 'Then Rebekah and her maids arose, and they rode on the camels and followed the man. So the servant took Rebekah and departed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24062, 'Now Isaac came from the way of Beer Lahai Roi, for he dwelt in the South.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24063, 'And Isaac went out to meditate in the field in the evening; and he lifted his eyes and looked, and there, the camels were coming.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24064, 'Then Rebekah lifted her eyes, and when she saw Isaac she dismounted from her camel;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24065, 'for she had said to the servant, &ldquo;Who is this man walking in the field to meet us?&rdquo; The servant said, &ldquo;It is my master.&rdquo; So she took a veil and covered herself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24066, 'And the servant told Isaac all the things that he had done.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 24067, 'Then Isaac brought her into his mother Sarah&rsquo;s tent; and he took Rebekah and she became his wife, and he loved her. So Isaac was comforted after his mother&rsquo;s death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25001, 'Abraham again took a wife, and her name was Keturah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25002, 'And she bore him Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25003, 'Jokshan begot Sheba and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were Asshurim, Letushim, and Leummim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25004, 'And the sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abidah, and Eldaah. All these were the children of Keturah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25005, 'And Abraham gave all that he had to Isaac.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25006, 'But Abraham gave gifts to the sons of the concubines which Abraham had; and while he was still living he sent them eastward, away from Isaac his son, to the country of the east.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25007, 'This is the sum of the years of Abraham&rsquo;s life which he lived: one hundred and seventy-five years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25008, 'Then Abraham breathed his last and died in a good old age, an old man and full of years, and was gathered to his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25009, 'And his sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him in the cave of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25010, 'the field which Abraham purchased from the sons of Heth. There Abraham was buried, and Sarah his wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25011, 'And it came to pass, after the death of Abraham, that God blessed his son Isaac. And Isaac dwelt at Beer Lahai Roi.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25012, 'Now this is the genealogy of Ishmael, Abraham&rsquo;s son, whom Hagar the Egyptian, Sarah&rsquo;s maidservant, bore to Abraham.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25013, 'And these were the names of the sons of Ishmael, by their names, according to their generations: The firstborn of Ishmael, Nebajoth; then Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25014, 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25015, 'Hadar, Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25016, 'These were the sons of Ishmael and these were their names, by their towns and their settlements, twelve princes according to their nations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25017, 'These were the years of the life of Ishmael: one hundred and thirty-seven years; and he breathed his last and died, and was gathered to his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25018, '(They dwelt from Havilah as far as Shur, which is east of Egypt as you go toward Assyria.) He died in the presence of all his brethren.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25019, 'This is the genealogy of Isaac, Abraham&rsquo;s son. Abraham begot Isaac.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25020, 'Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah as wife, the daughter of Bethuel the Syrian of Padan Aram, the sister of Laban the Syrian.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25021, 'Now Isaac pleaded with the Lord for his wife, because she was barren; and the Lord granted his plea, and Rebekah his wife conceived.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25022, 'But the children struggled together within her; and she said, &ldquo;If all is well, why am I like this?&rdquo; So she went to inquire of the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25023, 'And the Lord said to her: &ldquo;Two nations are in your womb, Two peoples shall be separated from your body; One people shall be stronger than the other, And the older shall serve the younger.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25024, 'So when her days were fulfilled for her to give birth, indeed there were twins in her womb.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25025, 'And the first came out red. He was like a hairy garment all over; so they called his name Esau.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25026, 'Afterward his brother came out, and his hand took hold of Esau&rsquo;s heel; so his name was called Jacob. Isaac was sixty years old when she bore them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25027, 'So the boys grew. And Esau was a skillful hunter, a man of the field; but Jacob was a mild man, dwelling in tents.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25028, 'And Isaac loved Esau because he ate of his game, but Rebekah loved Jacob.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25029, 'Now Jacob cooked a stew; and Esau came in from the field, and he was weary.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25030, 'And Esau said to Jacob, &ldquo;Please feed me with that same red stew, for I am weary.&rdquo; Therefore his name was called Edom.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25031, 'But Jacob said, &ldquo;Sell me your birthright as of this day.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25032, 'And Esau said, &ldquo;Look, I am about to die; so what is this birthright to me?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25033, 'Then Jacob said, &ldquo;Swear to me as of this day.&rdquo; So he swore to him, and sold his birthright to Jacob.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 25034, 'And Jacob gave Esau bread and stew of lentils; then he ate and drank, arose, and went his way. Thus Esau despised his birthright.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26001, 'There was a famine in the land, besides the first famine that was in the days of Abraham. And Isaac went to Abimelech king of the Philistines, in Gerar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26002, 'Then the Lord appeared to him and said: &ldquo;Do not go down to Egypt; live in the land of which I shall tell you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26003, '&ldquo;Dwell in this land, and I will be with you and bless you; for to you and your descendants I give all these lands, and I will perform the oath which I swore to Abraham your father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26004, '&ldquo;And I will make your descendants multiply as the stars of heaven; I will give to your descendants all these lands; and in your seed all the nations of the earth shall be blessed;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26005, '&ldquo;because Abraham obeyed My voice and kept My charge, My commandments, My statutes, and My laws.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26006, 'So Isaac dwelt in Gerar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26007, 'And the men of the place asked about his wife. And he said, &ldquo;She is my sister&rdquo;; for he was afraid to say, &ldquo;She is my wife,&rdquo; because he thought, &ldquo;lest the men of the place kill me for Rebekah, because she is beautiful to behold.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26008, 'Now it came to pass, when he had been there a long time, that Abimelech king of the Philistines looked through a window, and saw, and there was Isaac, showing endearment to Rebekah his wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26009, 'Then Abimelech called Isaac and said, &ldquo;Quite obviously she is your wife; so how could you say, &lsquo;She is my sister&rsquo;?&rdquo; Isaac said to him, &ldquo;Because I said, &lsquo;Lest I die on account of her.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26010, 'And Abimelech said, &ldquo;What is this you have done to us? One of the people might soon have lain with your wife, and you would have brought guilt on us.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26011, 'So Abimelech charged all his people, saying, &ldquo;He who touches this man or his wife shall surely be put to death.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26012, 'Then Isaac sowed in that land, and reaped in the same year a hundredfold; and the Lord blessed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26013, 'The man began to prosper, and continued prospering until he became very prosperous;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26014, 'for he had possessions of flocks and possessions of herds and a great number of servants. So the Philistines envied him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26015, 'Now the Philistines had stopped up all the wells which his father&rsquo;s servants had dug in the days of Abraham his father, and they had filled them with earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26016, 'And Abimelech said to Isaac, &ldquo;Go away from us, for you are much mightier than we.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26017, 'Then Isaac departed from there and pitched his tent in the Valley of Gerar, and dwelt there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26018, 'And Isaac dug again the wells of water which they had dug in the days of Abraham his father, for the Philistines had stopped them up after the death of Abraham. He called them by the names which his father had called them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26019, 'Also Isaac&rsquo;s servants dug in the valley, and found a well of running water there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26020, 'But the herdsmen of Gerar quarreled with Isaac&rsquo;s herdsmen, saying, &ldquo;The water is ours.&rdquo; So he called the name of the well Esek, because they quarreled with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26021, 'Then they dug another well, and they quarreled over that one also. So he called its name Sitnah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26022, 'And he moved from there and dug another well, and they did not quarrel over it. So he called its name Rehoboth, because he said, &ldquo;For now the Lord has made room for us, and we shall be fruitful in the land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26023, 'Then he went up from there to Beersheba.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26024, 'And the Lord appeared to him the same night and said, &ldquo;I am the God of your father Abraham; do not fear, for I am with you. I will bless you and multiply your descendants for My servant Abraham&rsquo;s sake.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26025, 'So he built an altar there and called on the name of the Lord, and he pitched his tent there; and there Isaac&rsquo;s servants dug a well.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26026, 'Then Abimelech came to him from Gerar with Ahuzzath, one of his friends, and Phichol the commander of his army.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26027, 'And Isaac said to them, &ldquo;Why have you come to me, since you hate me and have sent me away from you?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26028, 'But they said, &ldquo;We have certainly seen that the Lord is with you. So we said, &lsquo;Let there now be an oath between us, between you and us; and let us make a covenant with you,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26029, '&lsquo;that you will do us no harm, since we have not touched you, and since we have done nothing to you but good and have sent you away in peace. You are now the blessed of the Lord.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26030, 'So he made them a feast, and they ate and drank.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26031, 'Then they arose early in the morning and swore an oath with one another; and Isaac sent them away, and they departed from him in peace.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26032, 'It came to pass the same day that Isaac&rsquo;s servants came and told him about the well which they had dug, and said to him, &ldquo;We have found water.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26033, 'So he called it Shebah.a Therefore the name of the city is Beershebab to this day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26034, 'When Esau was forty years old, he took as wives Judith the daughter of Beeri the Hittite, and Basemath the daughter of Elon the Hittite.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 26035, 'And they were a grief of mind to Isaac and Rebekah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27001, 'Now it came to pass, when Isaac was old and his eyes were so dim that he could not see, that he called Esau his older son and said to him, &ldquo;My son.&rdquo; And he answered him, &ldquo;Here I am.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27002, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Behold now, I am old. I do not know the day of my death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27003, '&ldquo;Now therefore, please take your weapons, your quiver and your bow, and go out to the field and hunt game for me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27004, '&ldquo;And make me savory food, such as I love, and bring it to me that I may eat, that my soul may bless you before I die.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27005, 'Now Rebekah was listening when Isaac spoke to Esau his son. And Esau went to the field to hunt game and to bring it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27006, 'So Rebekah spoke to Jacob her son, saying, &ldquo;Indeed I heard your father speak to Esau your brother, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27007, '&lsquo;Bring me game and make savory food for me, that I may eat it and bless you in the presence of the Lord before my death.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27008, '&ldquo;Now therefore, my son, obey my voice according to what I command you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27009, '&ldquo;Go now to the flock and bring me from there two choice kids of the goats, and I will make savory food from them for your father, such as he loves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27010, '&ldquo;Then you shall take it to your father, that he may eat it, and that he may bless you before his death.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27011, 'And Jacob said to Rebekah his mother, &ldquo;Look, Esau my brother is a hairy man, and I am a smooth-skinned man.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27012, '&ldquo;Perhaps my father will feel me, and I shall seem to be a deceiver to him; and I shall bring a curse on myself and not a blessing.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27013, 'But his mother said to him, &ldquo;Let your curse be on me, my son; only obey my voice, and go, get them for me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27014, 'And he went and got them and brought them to his mother, and his mother made savory food, such as his father loved.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27015, 'Then Rebekah took the choice clothes of her elder son Esau, which were with her in the house, and put them on Jacob her younger son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27016, 'And she put the skins of the kids of the goats on his hands and on the smooth part of his neck.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27017, 'Then she gave the savory food and the bread, which she had prepared, into the hand of her son Jacob.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27018, 'So he went to his father and said, &ldquo;My father.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Here I am. Who are you, my son?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27019, 'Jacob said to his father, &ldquo;I am Esau your firstborn; I have done just as you told me; please arise, sit and eat of my game, that your soul may bless me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27020, 'But Isaac said to his son, &ldquo;How is it that you have found it so quickly, my son?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Because the Lord your God brought it to me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27021, 'Then Isaac said to Jacob, &ldquo;Please come near, that I may feel you, my son, whether you are really my son Esau or not.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27022, 'So Jacob went near to Isaac his father, and he felt him and said, &ldquo;The voice is Jacob&rsquo;s voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27023, 'And he did not recognize him, because his hands were hairy like his brother Esau&rsquo;s hands; so he blessed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27024, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Are you really my son Esau?&rdquo; He said, &ldquo;I am.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27025, 'He said, &ldquo;Bring it near to me, and I will eat of my son&rsquo;s game, so that my soul may bless you.&rdquo; So he brought it near to him, and he ate; and he brought him wine, and he drank.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27026, 'Then his father Isaac said to him, &ldquo;Come near now and kiss me, my son.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27027, 'And he came near and kissed him; and he smelled the smell of his clothing, and blessed him and said: &ldquo;Surely, the smell of my son Is like the smell of a field Which the Lord has blessed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27028, 'Therefore may God give you Of the dew of heaven, Of the fatness of the earth, And plenty of grain and wine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27029, 'Let peoples serve you, And nations bow down to you. Be master over your brethren, And let your mother&rsquo;s sons bow down to you. Cursed be everyone who curses you, And blessed be those who bless you!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27030, 'Now it happened, as soon as Isaac had finished blessing Jacob, and Jacob had scarcely gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, that Esau his brother came in from his hunting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27031, 'He also had made savory food, and brought it to his father, and said to his father, &ldquo;Let my father arise and eat of his son&rsquo;s game, that your soul may bless me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27032, 'And his father Isaac said to him, &ldquo;Who are you?&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;I am your son, your firstborn, Esau.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27033, 'Then Isaac trembled exceedingly, and said, &ldquo;Who? Where is the one who hunted game and brought it to me? I ate all of it before you came, and I have blessed him &ndash; and indeed he shall be blessed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27034, 'When Esau heard the words of his father, he cried with an exceedingly great and bitter cry, and said to his father, &ldquo;Bless me &ndash; me also, O my father!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27035, 'But he said, &ldquo;Your brother came with deceit and has taken away your blessing.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27036, 'And Esau said, &ldquo;Is he not rightly named Jacob? For he has supplanted me these two times. He took away my birthright, and now look, he has taken away my blessing!&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Have you not reserved a blessing for me?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27037, 'Then Isaac answered and said to Esau, &ldquo;Indeed I have made him your master, and all his brethren I have given to him as servants; with grain and wine I have sustained him. What shall I do now for you, my son?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27038, 'And Esau said to his father, &ldquo;Have you only one blessing, my father? Bless me &ndash; me also, O my father!&rdquo; And Esau lifted up his voice and wept.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27039, 'Then Isaac his father answered and said to him: &ldquo;Behold, your dwelling shall be of the fatness of the earth, And of the dew of heaven from above.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27040, 'By your sword you shall live, And you shall serve your brother; And it shall come to pass, when you become restless, That you shall break his yoke from your neck.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27041, 'So Esau hated Jacob because of the blessing with which his father blessed him|, and Esau said in his heart, &ldquo;The days of mourning for my father are at hand; then I will kill my brother Jacob.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27042, 'And the words of Esau her older son were told to Rebekah. So she sent and called Jacob her younger son, and said to him, &ldquo;Surely your brother Esau comforts himself concerning you by intending to kill you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27043, '&ldquo;Now therefore, my son, obey my voice: arise, flee to my brother Laban in Haran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27044, '&ldquo;And stay with him a few days, until your brother&rsquo;s fury turns away,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27045, '&ldquo;until your brother&rsquo;s anger turns away from you, and he forgets what you have done to him; then I will send and bring you from there. Why should I be bereaved also of you both in one day?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 27046, 'And Rebekah said to Isaac, &ldquo;I am weary of my life because of the daughters of Heth; if Jacob takes a wife of the daughters of Heth, like these who are the daughters of the land, what good will my life be to me?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28001, 'Then Isaac called Jacob and blessed him, and charged him, and said to him: &ldquo;You shall not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28002, '&ldquo;Arise, go to Padan Aram, to the house of Bethuel your mother&rsquo;s father; and take yourself a wife from there of the daughters of Laban your mother&rsquo;s brother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28003, '&ldquo;May God Almighty bless you, And make you fruitful and multiply you, That you may be an assembly of peoples;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28004, 'And give you the blessing of Abraham, To you and your descendants with you, That you may inherit the land In which you are a stranger, Which God gave to Abraham.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28005, 'So Isaac sent Jacob away, and he went to Padan Aram, to Laban the son of Bethuel the Syrian, the brother of Rebekah, the mother of Jacob and Esau.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28006, 'Esau saw that Isaac had blessed Jacob and sent him away to Padan Aram to take himself a wife from there, and that as he blessed him he gave him a charge, saying, &ldquo;You shall not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan,&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28007, 'and that Jacob had obeyed his father and his mother and had gone to Padan Aram.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28008, 'Also Esau saw that the daughters of Canaan did not please his father Isaac.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28009, 'So Esau went to Ishmael and took Mahalath the daughter of Ishmael, Abraham&rsquo;s son, the sister of Nebajoth, to be his wife in addition to the wives he had.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28010, 'Now Jacob went out from Beersheba and went toward Haran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28011, 'So he came to a certain place and stayed there all night, because the sun had set. And he took one of the stones of that place and put it at his head, and he lay down in that place to sleep.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28012, 'Then he dreamed, and behold, a ladder was set up on the earth, and its top reached to heaven; and there the angels of God were ascending and descending on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28013, 'And behold, the Lord stood above it and said: &ldquo;I am the Lord God of Abraham your father and the God of Isaac; the land on which you lie I will give to you and your descendants.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28014, '&ldquo;Also your descendants shall be as the dust of the earth; you shall spread abroad to the west and the east, to the north and the south; and in you and in your seed all the families of the earth shall be blessed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28015, '&ldquo;Behold, I am with you and will keep you wherever you go, and will bring you back to this land; for I will not leave you until I have done what I have spoken to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28016, 'Then Jacob awoke from his sleep and said, &ldquo;Surely the Lord is in this place, and I did not know it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28017, 'And he was afraid and said, &ldquo;How awesome is this place! This is none other than the house of God, and this is the gate of heaven!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28018, 'Then Jacob rose early in the morning, and took the stone that he had put at his head, set it up as a pillar, and poured oil on top of it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28019, 'And he called the name of that place Bethel; but the name of that city had been Luz previously.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28020, 'Then Jacob made a vow, saying, &ldquo;If God will be with me, and keep me in this way that I am going, and give me bread to eat and clothing to put on,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28021, '&ldquo;so that I come back to my father&rsquo;s house in peace, then the Lord shall be my God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 28022, '&ldquo;And this stone which I have set as a pillar shall be God&rsquo;s house, and of all that You give me I will surely give a tenth to You.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29001, 'So Jacob went on his journey and came to the land of the people of the East.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29002, 'And he looked, and saw a well in the field; and behold, there were three flocks of sheep lying by it; for out of that well they watered the flocks. A large stone was on the well&rsquo;s mouth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29003, 'Now all the flocks would be gathered there; and they would roll the stone from the well&rsquo;s mouth, water the sheep, and put the stone back in its place on the well&rsquo;s mouth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29004, 'And Jacob said to them, &ldquo;My brethren, where are you from?&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;We are from Haran.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29005, 'Then he said to them, &ldquo;Do you know Laban the son of Nahor?&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;We know him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29006, 'So he said to them, &ldquo;Is he well?&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;He is well. And look, his daughter Rachel is coming with the sheep.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29007, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Look, it is still high day; it is not time for the cattle to be gathered together. Water the sheep, and go and feed them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29008, 'But they said, &ldquo;We cannot until all the flocks are gathered together, and they have rolled the stone from the well&rsquo;s mouth; then we water the sheep.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29009, 'Now while he was still speaking with them, Rachel came with her father&rsquo;s sheep, for she was a shepherdess.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29010, 'And it came to pass, when Jacob saw Rachel the daughter of Laban his mother&rsquo;s brother, and the sheep of Laban his mother&rsquo;s brother, that Jacob went near and rolled the stone from the well&rsquo;s mouth, and watered the flock of Laban his mother&rsquo;s brother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29011, 'Then Jacob kissed Rachel, and lifted up his voice and wept.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29012, 'And Jacob told Rachel that he was her father&rsquo;s relative and that he was Rebekah&rsquo;s son. So she ran and told her father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29013, 'Then it came to pass, when Laban heard the report about Jacob his sister&rsquo;s son, that he ran to meet him, and embraced him and kissed him, and brought him to his house. So he told Laban all these things.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29014, 'And Laban said to him, &ldquo;Surely you are my bone and my flesh.&rdquo; And he stayed with him for a month.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29015, 'Then Laban said to Jacob, &ldquo;Because you are my relative, should you therefore serve me for nothing? Tell me, what should your wages be?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29016, 'Now Laban had two daughters: the name of the elder was Leah, and the name of the younger was Rachel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29017, 'Leah&rsquo;s eyes were delicate, but Rachel was beautiful of form and appearance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29018, 'Now Jacob loved Rachel; so he said, &ldquo;I will serve you seven years for Rachel your younger daughter.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29019, 'And Laban said, &ldquo;It is better that I give her to you than that I should give her to another man. Stay with me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29020, 'So Jacob served seven years for Rachel, and they seemed only a few days to him because of the love he had for her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29021, 'Then Jacob said to Laban, &ldquo;Give me my wife, for my days are fulfilled, that I may go in to her.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29022, 'And Laban gathered together all the men of the place and made a feast.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29023, 'Now it came to pass in the evening, that he took Leah his daughter and brought her to Jacob; and he went in to her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29024, 'And Laban gave his maid Zilpah to his daughter Leah as a maid.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29025, 'So it came to pass in the morning, that behold, it was Leah. And he said to Laban, &ldquo;What is this you have done to me? Was it not for Rachel that I served you? Why then have you deceived me?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29026, 'And Laban said, &ldquo;It must not be done so in our country, to give the younger before the firstborn.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29027, '&ldquo;Fulfill her week, and we will give you this one also for the service which you will serve with me still another seven years.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29028, 'Then Jacob did so and fulfilled her week. So he gave him his daughter Rachel as wife also.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29029, 'And Laban gave his maid Bilhah to his daughter Rachel as a maid.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29030, 'Then Jacob also went in to Rachel, and he also loved Rachel more than Leah. And he served with Laban still another seven years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29031, 'When the Lord saw that Leah was unloved, He opened her womb; but Rachel was barren.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29032, 'So Leah conceived and bore a son, and she called his name Reuben; for she said, &ldquo;The Lord has surely looked on my affliction. Now therefore, my husband will love me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29033, 'Then she conceived again and bore a son, and said, &ldquo;Because the Lord has heard that I am unloved, He has therefore given me this son also.&rdquo; And she called his name Simeon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29034, 'She conceived again and bore a son, and said, &ldquo;Now this time my husband will become attached to me, because I have borne him three sons.&rdquo; Therefore his name was called Levi.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 29035, 'And she conceived again and bore a son, and said, &ldquo;Now I will praise the Lord.&rdquo; Therefore she called his name Judah. Then she stopped bearing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30001, 'Now when Rachel saw that she bore Jacob no children, Rachel envied her sister, and said to Jacob, &ldquo;Give me children, or else I die!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30002, 'And Jacob&rsquo;s anger was aroused against Rachel, and he said, &ldquo;Am I in the place of God, who has withheld from you the fruit of the womb?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30003, 'So she said, &ldquo;Here is my maid Bilhah; go in to her, and she will bear a child on my knees, that I also may have children by her.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30004, 'Then she gave him Bilhah her maid as wife, and Jacob went in to her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30005, 'And Bilhah conceived and bore Jacob a son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30006, 'Then Rachel said, &ldquo;God has judged my case; and He has also heard my voice and given me a son.&rdquo; Therefore she called his name Dan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30007, 'And Rachel&rsquo;s maid Bilhah conceived again and bore Jacob a second son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30008, 'Then Rachel said, &ldquo;With great wrestlings I have wrestled with my sister, and indeed I have prevailed.&rdquo; So she called his name Naphtali.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30009, 'When Leah saw that she had stopped bearing, she took Zilpah her maid and gave her to Jacob as wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30010, 'And Leah&rsquo;s maid Zilpah bore Jacob a son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30011, 'Then Leah said, &ldquo;A troop comes!&rdquo;a So she called his name Gad.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30012, 'And Leah&rsquo;s maid Zilpah bore Jacob a second son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30013, 'Then Leah said, &ldquo;I am happy, for the daughters will call me blessed.&rdquo; So she called his name Asher.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30014, 'Now Reuben went in the days of wheat harvest and found mandrakes in the field, and brought them to his mother Leah. Then Rachel said to Leah, &ldquo;Please give me some of your son&rsquo;s mandrakes.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30015, 'But she said to her, &ldquo;Is it a small matter that you have taken away my husband? Would you take away my son&rsquo;s mandrakes also?&rdquo; And Rachel said, &ldquo;Therefore he will lie with you tonight for your son&rsquo;s mandrakes.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30016, 'When Jacob came out of the field in the evening, Leah went out to meet him and said, &ldquo;You must come in to me, for I have surely hired you with my son&rsquo;s mandrakes.&rdquo; And he lay with her that night.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30017, 'And God listened to Leah, and she conceived and bore Jacob a fifth son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30018, 'Leah said, &ldquo;God has given me my wages, because I have given my maid to my husband.&rdquo; So she called his name Issachar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30019, 'Then Leah conceived again and bore Jacob a sixth son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30020, 'And Leah said, &ldquo;God has endowed me with a good endowment; now my husband will dwell with me, because I have borne him six sons.&rdquo; So she called his name Zebulun.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30021, 'Afterward she bore a daughter, and called her name Dinah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30022, 'Then God remembered Rachel, and God listened to her and opened her womb.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30023, 'And she conceived and bore a son, and said, &ldquo;God has taken away my reproach.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30024, 'So she called his name Joseph, and said, &ldquo;The Lord shall add to me another son.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30025, 'And it came to pass, when Rachel had borne Joseph, that Jacob said to Laban, &ldquo;Send me away, that I may go to my own place and to my country.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30026, '&ldquo;Give me my wives and my children for whom I have served you, and let me go; for you know my service which I have done for you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30027, 'And Laban said to him, &ldquo;Please stay, if I have found favor in your eyes, for I have learned by experience that the Lord has blessed me for your sake.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30028, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Name me your wages, and I will give it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30029, 'So Jacob said to him, &ldquo;You know how I have served you and how your livestock has been with me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30030, '&ldquo;For what you had before I came was little, and it has increased to a great amount; the Lord has blessed you since my coming. And now, when shall I also provide for my own house?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30031, 'So he said, &ldquo;What shall I give you?&rdquo; And Jacob said, &ldquo;You shall not give me anything. If you will do this thing for me, I will again feed and keep your flocks:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30032, '&ldquo;Let me pass through all your flock today, removing from there all the speckled and spotted sheep, and all the brown ones among the lambs, and the spotted and speckled among the goats; and these shall be my wages.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30033, '&ldquo;So my righteousness will answer for me in time to come, when the subject of my wages comes before you: every one that is not speckled and spotted among the goats, and brown among the lambs, will be considered stolen, if it is with me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30034, 'And Laban said, &ldquo;Oh, that it were according to your word!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30035, 'So he removed that day the male goats that were speckled and spotted, all the female goats that were speckled and spotted, every one that had some white in it, and all the brown ones among the lambs, and gave them into the hand of his sons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30036, 'Then he put three days&rsquo; journey between himself and Jacob, and Jacob fed the rest of Laban&rsquo;s flocks.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30037, 'Now Jacob took for himself rods of green poplar and of the almond and chestnut trees, peeled white strips in them, and exposed the white which was in the rods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30038, 'And the rods which he had peeled, he set before the flocks in the gutters, in the watering troughs where the flocks came to drink, so that they should conceive when they came to drink.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30039, 'So the flocks conceived before the rods, and the flocks brought forth streaked, speckled, and spotted.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30040, 'Then Jacob separated the lambs, and made the flocks face toward the streaked and all the brown in the flock of Laban; but he put his own flocks by themselves and did not put them with Laban&rsquo;s flock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30041, 'And it came to pass, whenever the stronger livestock conceived, that Jacob placed the rods before the eyes of the livestock in the gutters, that they might conceive among the rods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30042, 'But when the flocks were feeble, he did not put them in; so the feebler were Laban&rsquo;s and the stronger Jacob&rsquo;s.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 30043, 'Thus the man became exceedingly prosperous, and had large flocks, female and male servants, and camels and donkeys.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31001, 'Now Jacob heard the words of Laban&rsquo;s sons, saying, &ldquo;Jacob has taken away all that was our father&rsquo;s, and from what was our father&rsquo;s he has acquired all this wealth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31002, 'And Jacob saw the countenance of Laban, and indeed it was not favorable toward him as before.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31003, 'Then the* Lord said to Jacob, &ldquo;Return to the land of your fathers and to your family, and I will be with you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31004, 'So Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah to the field, to his flock,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31005, 'and said to them, &ldquo;I see your father&rsquo;s countenance, that it is not favorable toward me as before; but the God of my father has been with me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31006, '&ldquo;And you know that with all my might I have served your father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31007, '&ldquo;Yet your father has deceived me and changed my wages ten times, but God did not allow him to hurt me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31008, '&ldquo;If he said thus: &lsquo;The speckled shall be your wages,&rsquo; then all the flocks bore speckled. And if he said thus: &lsquo;The streaked shall be your wages,&rsquo; then all the flocks bore streaked.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31009, '&ldquo;So God has taken away the livestock of your father and given them to me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31010, '&ldquo;And it happened, at the time when the flocks conceived, that I lifted my eyes and saw in a dream, and behold, the rams which leaped upon the flocks were streaked, speckled, and gray-spotted.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31011, '&ldquo;Then the Angel of God spoke to me in a dream, saying, &lsquo;Jacob.&rsquo; And I said, &lsquo;Here I am.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31012, '&ldquo;And He said, &lsquo;Lift your eyes now and see, all the rams which leap on the flocks are streaked, speckled, and gray-spotted; for I have seen all that Laban is doing to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31013, '&lsquo;I am the God of Bethel, where you anointed the pillar and where you made a vow to Me. Now arise, get out of this land, and return to the land of your family.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31014, 'Then Rachel and Leah answered and said to him, &ldquo;Is there still any portion or inheritance for us in our father&rsquo;s house?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31015, '&ldquo;Are we not considered strangers by him? For he has sold us, and also completely consumed our money.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31016, '&ldquo;For all these riches which God has taken from our father are really ours and our children&rsquo;s; now then, whatever God has said to you, do it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31017, 'Then Jacob rose and set his sons and his wives on camels.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31018, 'And he carried away all his livestock and all his possessions which he had gained, his acquired livestock which he had gained in Padan Aram, to go to his father Isaac in the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31019, 'Now Laban had gone to shear his sheep, and Rachel had stolen the household idols that were her father&rsquo;s.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31020, 'And Jacob stole away, unknown to Laban the Syrian, in that he did not tell him that he intended to flee.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31021, 'So he fled with all that he had. He arose and crossed the river, and headed toward the mountains of Gilead.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31022, 'And Laban was told on the third day that Jacob had fled.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31023, 'Then he took his brethren with him and pursued him for seven days&rsquo; journey, and he overtook him in the mountains of Gilead.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31024, 'But God had come to Laban the Syrian in a dream by night, and said to him, &ldquo;Be careful that you speak to Jacob neither good nor bad.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31025, 'So Laban overtook Jacob. Now Jacob had pitched his tent in the mountains, and Laban with his brethren pitched in the mountains of Gilead.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31026, 'And Laban said to Jacob: &ldquo;What have you done, that you have stolen away unknown to me, and carried away my daughters like captives taken with the sword?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31027, '&ldquo;Why did you flee away secretly, and steal away from me, and not tell me; for I might have sent you away with joy and songs, with timbrel and harp?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31028, '&ldquo;And you did not allow me to kiss my sons and my daughters. Now you have done foolishly in so doing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31029, '&ldquo;It is in my power to do you harm, but the God of your father spoke to me last night, saying, &lsquo;Be careful that you speak to Jacob neither good nor bad.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31030, '&ldquo;And now you have surely gone because you greatly long for your father&rsquo;s house, but why did you steal my gods?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31031, 'Then Jacob answered and said to Laban, &ldquo;Because I was afraid, for I said, &lsquo;Perhaps you would take your daughters from me by force.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31032, '&ldquo;With whomever you find your gods, do not let him live. In the presence of our brethren, identify what I have of yours and take it with you.&rdquo; For Jacob did not know that Rachel had stolen them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31033, 'And Laban went into Jacob&rsquo;s tent, into Leah&rsquo;s tent, and into the two maids&rsquo; tents, but he did not find them. Then he went out of Leah&rsquo;s tent and entered Rachel&rsquo;s tent.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31034, 'Now Rachel had taken the household idols, put them in the camel&rsquo;s saddle, and sat on them. And Laban searched all about the tent but did not find them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31035, 'And she said to her father, &ldquo;Let it not displease my lord that I cannot rise before you, for the manner of women is with me.&rdquo; And he searched but did not find the household idols.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31036, 'Then Jacob was angry and rebuked Laban, and Jacob answered and said to Laban: &ldquo;What is my trespass? What is my sin, that you have so hotly pursued me?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31037, '&ldquo;Although you have searched all my things, what part of your household things have you found? Set it here before my brethren and your brethren, that they may judge between us both!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31038, '&ldquo;These twenty years I have been with you; your ewes and your female goats have not miscarried their young, and I have not eaten the rams of your flock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31039, '&ldquo;That which was torn by beasts I did not bring to you; I bore the loss of it. You required it from my hand, whether stolen by day or stolen by night.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31040, '&ldquo;There I was! In the day the drought consumed me, and the frost by night, and my sleep departed from my eyes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31041, '&ldquo;Thus I have been in your house twenty years; I served you fourteen years for your two daughters, and six years for your flock, and you have changed my wages ten times.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31042, '&ldquo;Unless the God of my father, the God of Abraham and the Fear of Isaac, had been with me, surely now you would have sent me away empty-handed. God has seen my affliction and the labor of my hands, and rebuked you last night.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31043, 'And Laban answered and said to Jacob, &ldquo;These daughters are my daughters, and these children are my children, and this flock is my flock; all that you see is mine. But what can I do this day to these my daughters or to their children whom they have borne?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31044, '&ldquo;Now therefore, come, let us make a covenant, you and I, and let it be a witness between you and me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31045, 'So Jacob took a stone and set it up as a pillar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31046, 'Then Jacob said to his brethren, &ldquo;Gather stones.&rdquo; And they took stones and made a heap, and they ate there on the heap.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31047, 'Laban called it Jegar Sahadutha, but Jacob called it Galeed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31048, 'And Laban said, &ldquo;This heap is a witness between you and me this day.&rdquo; Therefore its name was called Galeed,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31049, 'also Mizpah, because he said, &ldquo;May the Lord watch between you and me when we are absent one from another.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31050, '&ldquo;If you afflict my daughters, or if you take other wives besides my daughters, although no man is with us &ndash; see, God is witness between you and me!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31051, 'Then Laban said to Jacob, &ldquo;Here is this heap and here is this pillar, which I have placed between you and me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31052, '&ldquo;This heap is a witness, and this pillar is a witness, that I will not pass beyond this heap to you, and you will not pass beyond this heap and this pillar to me, for harm.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31053, '&ldquo;The God of Abraham, the God of Nahor, and the God of their father judge between us.&rdquo; And Jacob swore by the Fear of his father Isaac.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31054, 'Then Jacob offered a sacrifice on the mountain, and called his brethren to eat bread. And they ate bread and stayed all night on the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 31055, 'And early in the morning Laban arose, and kissed his sons and daughters and blessed them. Then Laban departed and returned to his place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32001, 'So Jacob went on his way,* and the angels of God met him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32002, 'When Jacob saw them, he said, &ldquo;This is God&rsquo;s camp.&rdquo; And he called the name of that place Mahanaim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32003, 'Then Jacob sent messengers before him to Esau his brother in the land of Seir, the country of Edom.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32004, 'And he commanded them, saying, &ldquo;Speak thus to my lord Esau, &lsquo;Thus your servant Jacob says: &ldquo;I have dwelt with Laban and stayed there until now.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32005, '&ldquo;I have oxen, donkeys, flocks, and male and female servants; and I have sent to tell my lord, that I may find favor in your sight.&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32006, 'Then the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, &ldquo;We came to your brother Esau, and he also is coming to meet you, and four hundred men are with him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32007, 'So Jacob was greatly afraid and distressed; and he divided the people that were with him, and the flocks and herds and camels, into two companies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32008, 'And he said, &ldquo;If Esau comes to the one company and attacks it, then the other company which is left will escape.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32009, 'Then Jacob said, &ldquo;O God of my father Abraham and God of my father Isaac, the Lord who said to me, &lsquo;Return to your country and to your family, and I will deal well with you&rsquo;:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32010, '&ldquo;I am not worthy of the least of all the mercies and of all the truth which You have shown Your servant; for I crossed over this Jordan with my staff|, and now I have become two companies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32011, '&ldquo;Deliver me, I pray, from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau; for I fear him, lest he come and attack me and the mother with the children.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32012, '&ldquo;For You said, &lsquo;I will surely treat you well, and make your descendants as the sand of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32013, 'So he lodged there that same night, and took what came to his hand as a present for Esau his brother:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32014, 'two hundred female goats and twenty male goats, two hundred ewes and twenty rams,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32015, 'thirty milk camels with their colts, forty cows and ten bulls, twenty female donkeys and ten foals.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32016, 'Then he delivered them to the hand of his servants, every drove by itself, and said to his servants, &ldquo;Pass over before me, and put some distance between successive droves.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32017, 'And he commanded the first one, saying, &ldquo;When Esau my brother meets you and asks you, saying, &lsquo;To whom do you belong, and where are you going? Whose are these in front of you?&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32018, '&ldquo;then you shall say, &lsquo;They are your servant Jacob&rsquo;s. It is a present sent to my lord Esau; and behold, he also is behind us.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32019, 'So he commanded the second, the third, and all who followed the droves, saying, &ldquo;In this manner you shall speak to Esau when you find him;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32020, '&ldquo;and also say, &lsquo;Behold, your servant Jacob is behind us.&rsquo;&rdquo; For he said, &ldquo;I will appease him with the present that goes before me, and afterward I will see his face; perhaps he will accept me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32021, 'So the present went on over before him, but he himself lodged that night in the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32022, 'And he arose that night and took his two wives, his two female servants, and his eleven sons, and crossed over the ford of Jabbok.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32023, 'He took them, sent them over the brook, and sent over what he had.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32024, 'Then Jacob was left alone; and a Man wrestled with him until the breaking of day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32025, 'Now when He saw that He did not prevail against him, He touched the socket of his hip; and the socket of Jacob&rsquo;s hip was out of joint as He wrestled with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32026, 'And He said, &ldquo;Let Me go, for the day breaks.&rdquo; But he said, &ldquo;I will not let You go unless You bless me!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32027, 'So He said to him, &ldquo;What is your name?&rdquo; He said, &ldquo;Jacob.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32028, 'And He said, &ldquo;Your name shall no longer be called Jacob, but Israel; for you have struggled with God and with men, and have prevailed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32029, 'Then Jacob asked, saying, &ldquo;Tell me Your name, I pray.&rdquo; And He said, &ldquo;Why is it that you ask about My name?&rdquo; And He blessed him there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32030, 'So Jacob called the name of the place Peniel: &ldquo;For I have seen God face to face, and my life is preserved.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32031, 'Just as he crossed over Penuel the sun rose on him, and he limped on his hip.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 32032, 'Therefore to this day the children of Israel do not eat the muscle that shrank, which is on the hip socket, because He touched the socket of Jacob&rsquo;s hip in the muscle that shrank.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33001, 'Now Jacob lifted his eyes and looked, and there, Esau was coming, and with him were four hundred men. So he divided the children among Leah, Rachel, and the two maidservants.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33002, 'And he put the maidservants and their children in front, Leah and her children behind, and Rachel and Joseph last.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33003, 'Then he crossed over before them and bowed himself to the ground seven times, until he came near to his brother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33004, 'But Esau ran to meet him, and embraced him, and fell on his neck and kissed him, and they wept.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33005, 'And he lifted his eyes and saw the women and children, and said, &ldquo;Who are these with you?&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;The children whom God has graciously given your servant.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33006, 'Then the maidservants came near, they and their children, and bowed down.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33007, 'And Leah also came near with her children, and they bowed down. Afterward Joseph and Rachel came near, and they bowed down.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33008, 'Then Esau said, &ldquo;What do you mean by all this company which I met?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;These are to find favor in the sight of my lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33009, 'But Esau said, &ldquo;I have enough, my brother; keep what you have for yourself.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33010, 'And Jacob said, &ldquo;No, please, if I have now found favor in your sight, then receive my present from my hand, inasmuch as I have seen your face as though I had seen the face of God, and you were pleased with me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33011, '&ldquo;Please, take my blessing that is brought to you, because God has dealt graciously with me, and because I have enough.&rdquo; So he urged him, and he took it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33012, 'Then Esau said, &ldquo;Let us take our journey; let us go, and I will go before you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33013, 'But Jacob said to him, &ldquo;My lord knows that the children are weak, and the flocks and herds which are nursing are with me. And if the men should drive them hard one day, all the flock will die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33014, '&ldquo;Please let my lord go on ahead before his servant. I will lead on slowly at a pace which the livestock that go before me, and the children, are able to endure, until I come to my lord in Seir.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33015, 'And Esau said, &ldquo;Now let me leave with you some of the people who are with me.&rdquo; But he said, &ldquo;What need is there? Let me find favor in the sight of my lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33016, 'So Esau returned that day on his way to Seir.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33017, 'And Jacob journeyed to Succoth, built himself a house, and made booths for his livestock. Therefore the name of the place is called Succoth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33018, 'Then Jacob came safely to the city of Shechem, which is in the land of Canaan, when he came from Padan Aram; and he pitched his tent before the city.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33019, 'And he bought the parcel of land, where he had pitched his tent, from the children of Hamor, Shechem&rsquo;s father, for one hundred pieces of money.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 33020, 'Then he erected an altar there and called it El Elohe Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34001, 'Now Dinah the daughter of Leah, whom she had borne to Jacob, went out to see the daughters of the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34002, 'And when Shechem the son of Hamor the Hivite, prince of the country, saw her, he took her and lay with her, and violated her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34003, 'His soul was strongly attracted to Dinah the daughter of Jacob, and he loved the young woman and spoke kindly to the young woman.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34004, 'So Shechem spoke to his father Hamor, saying, &ldquo;Get me this young woman as a wife.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34005, 'And Jacob heard that he had defiled Dinah his daughter. Now his sons were with his livestock in the field; so Jacob held his peace until they came.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34006, 'Then Hamor the father of Shechem went out to Jacob to speak with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34007, 'And the sons of Jacob came in from the field when they heard it; and the men were grieved and very angry, because he had done a disgraceful thing in Israel by lying with Jacob&rsquo;s daughter, a thing which ought not to be done.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34008, 'But Hamor spoke with them, saying, &ldquo;The soul of my son Shechem longs for your daughter. Please give her to him as a wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34009, '&ldquo;And make marriages with us; give your daughters to us, and take our daughters to yourselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34010, '&ldquo;So you shall dwell with us, and the land shall be before you. Dwell and trade in it, and acquire possessions for yourselves in it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34011, 'Then Shechem said to her father and her brothers, &ldquo;Let me find favor in your eyes, and whatever you say to me I will give.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34012, '&ldquo;Ask me ever so much dowry and gift, and I will give according to what you say to me; but give me the young woman as a wife.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34013, 'But the sons of Jacob answered Shechem and Hamor his father, and spoke deceitfully, because he had defiled Dinah their sister.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34014, 'And they said to them, &ldquo;We cannot do this thing, to give our sister to one who is uncircumcised, for that would be a reproach to us.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34015, '&ldquo;But on this condition we will consent to you: If you will become as we are, if every male of you is circumcised,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34016, '&ldquo;then we will give our daughters to you, and we will take your daughters to us; and we will dwell with you, and we will become one people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34017, '&ldquo;But if you will not heed us and be circumcised, then we will take our daughter and be gone.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34018, 'And their words pleased Hamor and Shechem, Hamor&rsquo;s son.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34019, 'So the young man did not delay to do the thing, because he delighted in Jacob&rsquo;s daughter. He was more honorable than all the household of his father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34020, 'And Hamor and Shechem his son came to the gate of their city, and spoke with the men of their city, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34021, '&ldquo;These men are at peace with us. Therefore let them dwell in the land and trade in it. For indeed the land is large enough for them. Let us take their daughters to us as wives, and let us give them our daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34022, '&ldquo;Only on this condition will the men consent to dwell with us, to be one people: if every male among us is circumcised as they are circumcised.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34023, '&ldquo;Will not their livestock, their property, and every animal of theirs be ours? Only let us consent to them, and they will dwell with us.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34024, 'And all who went out of the gate of his city heeded Hamor and Shechem his son; every male was circumcised, all who went out of the gate of his city.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34025, 'Now it came to pass on the third day, when they were in pain, that two of the sons of Jacob, Simeon and Levi, Dinah&rsquo;s brothers, each took his sword and came boldly upon the city and killed all the males.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34026, 'And they killed Hamor and Shechem his son with the edge of the sword, and took Dinah from Shechem&rsquo;s house, and went out.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34027, 'The sons of Jacob came upon the slain, and plundered the city, because their sister had been defiled.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34028, 'They took their sheep, their oxen, and their donkeys, what was in the city and what was in the field,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34029, 'and all their wealth. All their little ones and their wives they took captive; and they plundered even all that was in the houses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34030, 'Then Jacob said to Simeon and Levi, &ldquo;You have troubled me by making me obnoxious among the inhabitants of the land, among the Canaanites and the Perizzites; and since I am few in number, they will gather themselves together against me and kill me. I shall');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 34031, 'But they said, &ldquo;Should he treat our sister like a harlot?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35001, 'Then God said to Jacob, &ldquo;Arise, go up to Bethel and dwell there; and make an altar there to God, who appeared to you when you fled from the face of Esau your brother.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35002, 'And Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him, &ldquo;Put away the foreign gods that are among you, purify yourselves, and change your garments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35003, '&ldquo;Then let us arise and go up to Bethel; and I will make an altar there to God, who answered me in the day of my distress and has been with me in the way which I have gone.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35004, 'So they gave Jacob all the foreign gods which were in their hands, and the earrings which were in their ears; and Jacob hid them under the terebinth tree which was by Shechem.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35005, 'And they journeyed, and the terror of God was upon the cities that were all around them, and they did not pursue the sons of Jacob.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35006, 'So Jacob came to Luz (that is, Bethel), which is in the land of Canaan, he and all the people who were with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35007, 'And he built an altar there and called the place El Bethel, because there God appeared to him when he fled from the face of his brother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35008, 'Now Deborah, Rebekah&rsquo;s nurse, died, and she was buried below Bethel under the terebinth tree. So the name of it was called Allon Bachuth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35009, 'Then God appeared to Jacob again, when he came from Padan Aram, and blessed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35010, 'And God said to him, &ldquo;Your name is Jacob; your name shall not be called Jacob anymore, but Israel shall be your name.&rdquo; So He called his name Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35011, 'Also God said to him: &ldquo;I am God Almighty. Be fruitful and multiply; a nation and a company of nations shall proceed from you, and kings shall come from your body.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35012, '&ldquo;The land which I gave Abraham and Isaac I give to you; and to your descendants after you I give this land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35013, 'Then God went up from him in the place where He talked with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35014, 'So Jacob set up a pillar in the place where He talked with him, a pillar of stone; and he poured a drink offering on it, and he poured oil on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35015, 'And Jacob called the name of the place where God spoke with him, Bethel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35016, 'Then they journeyed from Bethel. And when there was but a little distance to go to Ephrath, Rachel labored in childbirth, and she had hard labor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35017, 'Now it came to pass, when she was in hard labor, that the midwife said to her, &ldquo;Do not fear; you will have this son also.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35018, 'And so it was, as her soul was departing (for she died), that she called his name Ben-Oni; but his father called him Benjamin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35019, 'So Rachel died and was buried on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem).');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35020, 'And Jacob set a pillar on her grave, which is the pillar of Rachel&rsquo;s grave to this day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35021, 'Then Israel journeyed and pitched his tent beyond the tower of Eder.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35022, 'And it happened, when Israel dwelt in that land, that Reuben went and lay with Bilhah his father&rsquo;s concubine; and Israel heard about it. Now the sons of Jacob were twelve:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35023, 'the sons of Leah were Reuben, Jacob&rsquo;s firstborn, and Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35024, 'the sons of Rachel were Joseph and Benjamin;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35025, 'the sons of Bilhah, Rachel&rsquo;s maidservant, were Dan and Naphtali;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35026, 'and the sons of Zilpah, Leah&rsquo;s maidservant, were Gad and Asher. These were the sons of Jacob who were born to him in Padan Aram.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35027, 'Then Jacob came to his father Isaac at Mamre, or Kirjath Arba (that is, Hebron), where Abraham and Isaac had dwelt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35028, 'Now the days of Isaac were one hundred and eighty years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 35029, 'So Isaac breathed his last and died, and was gathered to his people, being old and full of days. And his sons Esau and Jacob buried him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36001, 'Now this is the genealogy of Esau, who is Edom.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36002, 'Esau took his wives from the daughters of Canaan: Adah the daughter of Elon the Hittite; Aholibamah the daughter of Anah, the daughter of Zibeon the Hivite;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36003, 'and Basemath, Ishmael&rsquo;s daughter, sister of Nebajoth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36004, 'Now Adah bore Eliphaz to Esau, and Basemath bore Reuel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36005, 'And Aholibamah bore Jeush, Jaalam, and Korah. These were the sons of Esau who were born to him in the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36006, 'Then Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, and all the persons of his household, his cattle and all his animals, and all his goods which he had gained in the land of Canaan, and went to a country away from the presence of his brother Jacob.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36007, 'For their possessions were too great for them to dwell together, and the land where they were strangers could not support them because of their livestock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36008, 'So Esau dwelt in Mount Seir. Esau is Edom.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36009, 'And this is the genealogy of Esau the father of the Edomites in Mount Seir.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36010, 'These were the names of Esau&rsquo;s sons: Eliphaz the son of Adah the wife of Esau, and Reuel the son of Basemath the wife of Esau.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36011, 'And the sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36012, 'Now Timna was the concubine of Eliphaz, Esau&rsquo;s son, and she bore Amalek to Eliphaz. These were the sons of Adah, Esau&rsquo;s wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36013, 'These were the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These were the sons of Basemath, Esau&rsquo;s wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36014, 'These were the sons of Aholibamah, Esau&rsquo;s wife, the daughter of Anah, the daughter of Zibeon. And she bore to Esau: Jeush, Jaalam, and Korah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36015, 'These were the chiefs of the sons of Esau. The sons of Eliphaz, the firstborn son of Esau, were Chief Teman, Chief Omar, Chief Zepho, Chief Kenaz,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36016, 'Chief Korah, Chief Gatam, and Chief Amalek. These were the chiefs of Eliphaz in the land of Edom. They were the sons of Adah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36017, 'These were the sons of Reuel, Esau&rsquo;s son: Chief Nahath, Chief Zerah, Chief Shammah, and Chief Mizzah. These were the chiefs of Reuel in the land of Edom. These were the sons of Basemath, Esau&rsquo;s wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36018, 'And these were the sons of Aholibamah, Esau&rsquo;s wife: Chief Jeush, Chief Jaalam, and Chief Korah. These were the chiefs who descended from Aholibamah, Esau&rsquo;s wife, the daughter of Anah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36019, 'These were the sons of Esau, who is Edom, and these were their chiefs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36020, 'These were the sons of Seir the Horite who inhabited the land: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36021, 'Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. These were the chiefs of the Horites, the sons of Seir, in the land of Edom.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36022, 'And the sons of Lotan were Hori and Hemam. Lotan&rsquo;s sister was Timna.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36023, 'These were the sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36024, 'These were the sons of Zibeon: both Ajah and Anah. This was the Anah who found the water in the wilderness as he pastured the donkeys of his father Zibeon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36025, 'These were the children of Anah: Dishon and Aholibamah the daughter of Anah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36026, 'These were the sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36027, 'These were the sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36028, 'These were the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36029, 'These were the chiefs of the Horites: Chief Lotan, Chief Shobal, Chief Zibeon, Chief Anah,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36030, 'Chief Dishon, Chief Ezer, and Chief Dishan. These were the chiefs of the Horites, according to their chiefs in the land of Seir.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36031, 'Now these were the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the children of Israel:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36032, 'Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom, and the name of his city was Dinhabah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36033, 'And when Bela died, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36034, 'When Jobab died, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36035, 'And when Husham died, Hadad the son of Bedad, who attacked Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his place. And the name of his city was Avith.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36036, 'When Hadad died, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36037, 'And when Samlah died, Saul of Rehoboth-by-the-River reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36038, 'When Saul died, Baal-Hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36039, 'And when Baal-Hanan the son of Achbor died, Hadar reigned in his place; and the name of his city was Pau. His wife&rsquo;s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36040, 'And these were the names of the chiefs of Esau, according to their families and their places, by their names: Chief Timnah, Chief Alvah, Chief Jetheth,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36041, 'Chief Aholibamah, Chief Elah, Chief Pinon,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36042, 'Chief Kenaz, Chief Teman, Chief Mibzar,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 36043, 'Chief Magdiel, and Chief Iram. These were the chiefs of Edom, according to their dwelling places in the land of their possession. Esau was the father of the Edomites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37001, 'Now Jacob dwelt in the land where his father was a stranger, in the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37002, 'This is the history of Jacob. Joseph, being seventeen years old, was feeding the flock with his brothers. And the lad was with the sons of Bilhah and the sons of Zilpah, his father&rsquo;s wives; and Joseph brought a bad report of them to his father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37003, 'Now Israel loved Joseph more than all his children, because he was the son of his old age. Also he made him a tunic of many colors.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37004, 'But when his brothers saw that their father loved him more than all his brothers, they hated him and could not speak peaceably to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37005, 'Now Joseph had a dream, and he told it to his brothers; and they hated him even more.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37006, 'So he said to them, &ldquo;Please hear this dream which I have dreamed:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37007, '&ldquo;There we were, binding sheaves in the field. Then behold, my sheaf arose and also stood upright; and indeed your sheaves stood all around and bowed down to my sheaf.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37008, 'And his brothers said to him, &ldquo;Shall you indeed reign over us? Or shall you indeed have dominion over us?&rdquo; So they hated him even more for his dreams and for his words.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37009, 'Then he dreamed still another dream and told it to his brothers, and said, &ldquo;Look, I have dreamed another dream. And this time, the sun, the moon, and the eleven stars bowed down to me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37010, 'So he told it to his father and his brothers; and his father rebuked him and said to him, &ldquo;What is this dream that you have dreamed? Shall your mother and I and your brothers indeed come to bow down to the earth before you?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37011, 'And his brothers envied him, but his father kept the matter in mind.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37012, 'Then his brothers went to feed their father&rsquo;s flock in Shechem.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37013, 'And Israel said to Joseph, &ldquo;Are not your brothers feeding the flock in Shechem? Come, I will send you to them.&rdquo; So he said to him, &ldquo;Here I am.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37014, 'Then he said to him, &ldquo;Please go and see if it is well with your brothers and well with the flocks, and bring back word to me.&rdquo; So he sent him out of the Valley of Hebron, and he went to Shechem.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37015, 'Now a certain man found him, and there he was, wandering in the field. And the man asked him, saying, &ldquo;What are you seeking?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37016, 'So he said, &ldquo;I am seeking my brothers. Please tell me where they are feeding their flocks.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37017, 'And the man said, &ldquo;They have departed from here, for I heard them say, &lsquo;Let us go to Dothan.&rsquo;&rdquo; So Joseph went after his brothers and found them in Dothan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37018, 'Now when they saw him afar off, even before he came near them, they conspired against him to kill him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37019, 'Then they said to one another, &ldquo;Look, this dreamer is coming!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37020, '&ldquo;Come therefore, let us now kill him and cast him into some pit; and we shall say, &lsquo;Some wild beast has devoured him.&rsquo; We shall see what will become of his dreams!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37021, 'But Reuben heard it, and he delivered him out of their hands, and said, &ldquo;Let us not kill him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37022, 'And Reuben said to them, &ldquo;Shed no blood, but cast him into this pit which is in the wilderness, and do not lay a hand on him&rdquo; &ndash; that he might deliver him out of their hands, and bring him back to his father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37023, 'So it came to pass, when Joseph had come to his brothers, that they stripped Joseph of his tunic, the tunic of many colors that was on him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37024, 'Then they took him and cast him into a pit. And the pit was empty; there was no water in it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37025, 'And they sat down to eat a meal. Then they lifted their eyes and looked, and there was a company of Ishmaelites, coming from Gilead with their camels, bearing spices, balm, and myrrh, on their way to carry them down to Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37026, 'So Judah said to his brothers, &ldquo;What profit is there if we kill our brother and conceal his blood?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37027, '&ldquo;Come and let us sell him to the Ishmaelites, and let not our hand be upon him, for he is our brother and our flesh.&rdquo; And his brothers listened.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37028, 'Then Midianite traders passed by; so the brothers pulled Joseph up and lifted him out of the pit, and sold him to the Ishmaelites for twenty shekels of silver. And they took Joseph to Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37029, 'Then Reuben returned to the pit, and indeed Joseph was not in the pit; and he tore his clothes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37030, 'And he returned to his brothers and said, &ldquo;The lad is no more; and I, where shall I go?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37031, 'So they took Joseph&rsquo;s tunic, killed a kid of the goats, and dipped the tunic in the blood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37032, 'Then they sent the tunic of many colors, and they brought it to their father and said, &ldquo;We have found this. Do you know whether it is your son&rsquo;s tunic or not?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37033, 'And he recognized it and said, &ldquo;It is my son&rsquo;s tunic. A wild beast has devoured him. Without doubt Joseph is torn to pieces.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37034, 'Then Jacob tore his clothes, put sackcloth on his waist, and mourned for his son many days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37035, 'And all his sons and all his daughters arose to comfort him; but he refused to be comforted, and he said, &ldquo;For I shall go down into the grave to my son in mourning.&rdquo; Thus his father wept for him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 37036, 'Now the Midianites had sold him in Egypt to Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh and captain of the guard.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38001, 'It came to pass at that time that Judah departed from his brothers, and visited a certain Adullamite whose name was Hirah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38002, 'And Judah saw there a daughter of a certain Canaanite whose name was Shua, and he married her and went in to her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38003, 'So she conceived and bore a son, and he called his name Er.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38004, 'She conceived again and bore a son, and she called his name Onan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38005, 'And she conceived yet again and bore a son, and called his name Shelah. He was at Chezib when she bore him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38006, 'Then Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, and her name was Tamar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38007, 'But Er, Judah&rsquo;s firstborn, was wicked in the sight of the Lord, and the Lord killed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38008, 'And Judah said to Onan, &ldquo;Go in to your brother&rsquo;s wife and marry her, and raise up an heir to your brother.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38009, 'But Onan knew that the heir would not be his; and it came to pass, when he went in to his brother&rsquo;s wife, that he emitted on the ground, lest he should give an heir to his brother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38010, 'And the thing which he did displeased the Lord; therefore He killed him also.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38011, 'Then Judah said to Tamar his daughter-in-law, &ldquo;Remain a widow in your father&rsquo;s house till my son Shelah is grown.&rdquo; For he said, &ldquo;Lest he also die like his brothers.&rdquo; And Tamar went and dwelt in her father&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38012, 'Now in the process of time the daughter of Shua, Judah&rsquo;s wife, died; and Judah was comforted, and went up to his sheepshearers at Timnah, he and his friend Hirah the Adullamite.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38013, 'And it was told Tamar, saying, &ldquo;Look, your father-in-law is going up to Timnah to shear his sheep.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38014, 'So she took off her widow&rsquo;s garments, covered herself with a veil and wrapped herself, and sat in an open place which was on the way to Timnah; for she saw that Shelah was grown, and she was not given to him as a wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38015, 'When Judah saw her, he thought she was a harlot, because she had covered her face.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38016, 'Then he turned to her by the way, and said, &ldquo;Please let me come in to you&rdquo;; for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law. So she said, &ldquo;What will you give me, that you may come in to me?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38017, 'And he said, &ldquo;I will send a young goat from the flock.&rdquo; So she said, &ldquo;Will you give me a pledge till you send it?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38018, 'Then he said, &ldquo;What pledge shall I give you?&rdquo; So she said, &ldquo;Your signet and cord, and your staff that is in your hand.&rdquo; Then he gave them to her, and went in to her, and she conceived by him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38019, 'So she arose and went away, and laid aside her veil and put on the garments of her widowhood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38020, 'And Judah sent the young goat by the hand of his friend the Adullamite, to receive his pledge from the woman&rsquo;s hand, but he did not find her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38021, 'Then he asked the men of that place, saying, &ldquo;Where is the harlot who was openly by the roadside?&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;There was no harlot in this place.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38022, 'So he returned to Judah and said, &ldquo;I cannot find her. Also, the men of the place said there was no harlot in this place.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38023, 'Then Judah said, &ldquo;Let her take them for herself, lest we be shamed; for I sent this young goat and you have not found her.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38024, 'And it came to pass, about three months after, that Judah was told, saying, &ldquo;Tamar your daughter-in-law has played the harlot; furthermore she is with child by harlotry.&rdquo; So Judah said, &ldquo;Bring her out and let her be burned!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38025, 'When she was brought out, she sent to her father-in-law, saying, &ldquo;By the man to whom these belong, I am with child.&rdquo; And she said, &ldquo;Please determine whose these are &ndash; the signet and cord, and staff.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38026, 'So Judah acknowledged them and said, &ldquo;She has been more righteous than I, because I did not give her to Shelah my son.&rdquo; And he never knew her again.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38027, 'Now it came to pass, at the time for giving birth, that behold, twins were in her womb.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38028, 'And so it was, when she was giving birth, that the one put out his hand; and the midwife took a scarlet thread and bound it on his hand, saying, &ldquo;This one came out first.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38029, 'Then it happened, as he drew back his hand, that his brother came out unexpectedly; and she said, &ldquo;How did you break through? This breach be upon you!&rdquo; Therefore his name was called Perez.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 38030, 'Afterward his brother came out who had the scarlet thread on his hand. And his name was called Zerah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39001, 'Now Joseph had been taken down to Egypt. And Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh, captain of the guard, an Egyptian, bought him from the Ishmaelites who had taken him down there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39002, 'The Lord was with Joseph, and he was a successful man; and he was in the house of his master the Egyptian.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39003, 'And his master saw that the Lord was with him and that the Lord made all he did to prosper in his hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39004, 'So Joseph found favor in his sight, and served him. Then he made him overseer of his house, and all that he had he put under his authority.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39005, 'So it was, from the time that he had made him overseer of his house and all that he had, that the Lord blessed the Egyptian&rsquo;s house for Joseph&rsquo;s sake; and the blessing of the Lord was on all that he had in the house and in the field.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39006, 'Thus he left all that he had in Joseph&rsquo;s hand, and he did not know what he had except for the bread which he ate. Now Joseph was handsome in form and appearance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39007, 'And it came to pass after these things that his master&rsquo;s wife cast longing eyes on Joseph, and she said, &ldquo;Lie with me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39008, 'But he refused and said to his master&rsquo;s wife, &ldquo;Look, my master does not know what is with me in the house, and he has committed all that he has to my hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39009, '&ldquo;There is no one greater in this house than I, nor has he kept back anything from me but you, because you are his wife. How then can I do this great wickedness, and sin against God?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39010, 'So it was, as she spoke to Joseph day by day, that he did not heed her, to lie with her or to be with her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39011, 'But it happened about this time, when Joseph went into the house to do his work, and none of the men of the house was inside,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39012, 'that she caught him by his garment, saying, &ldquo;Lie with me.&rdquo; But he left his garment in her hand, and fled and ran outside.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39013, 'And so it was, when she saw that he had left his garment in her hand and fled outside,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39014, 'that she called to the men of her house and spoke to them, saying, &ldquo;See, he has brought in to us a Hebrew to mock us. He came in to me to lie with me, and I cried out with a loud voice.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39015, '&ldquo;And it happened, when he heard that I lifted my voice and cried out, that he left his garment with me, and fled and went outside.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39016, 'So she kept his garment with her until his master came home.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39017, 'Then she spoke to him with words like these, saying, &ldquo;The Hebrew servant whom you brought to us came in to me to mock me;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39018, '&ldquo;so it happened, as I lifted my voice and cried out, that he left his garment with me and fled outside.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39019, 'So it was, when his master heard the words which his wife spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;Your servant did to me after this manner,&rdquo; that his anger was aroused.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39020, 'Then Joseph&rsquo;s master took him and put him into the prison, a place where the king&rsquo;s prisoners were confined. And he was there in the prison.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39021, 'But the Lord was with Joseph and showed him mercy, and He gave him favor in the sight of the keeper of the prison.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39022, 'And the keeper of the prison committed to Joseph&rsquo;s hand all the prisoners who were in the prison; whatever they did there, it was his doing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 39023, 'The keeper of the prison did not look into anything that was under Joseph&rsquo;s authority, because the Lord was with him; and whatever he did, the Lord made it prosper.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40001, 'It came to pass after these things that the butler and the baker of the king of Egypt offended their lord, the king of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40002, 'And Pharaoh was angry with his two officers, the chief butler and the chief baker.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40003, 'So he put them in custody in the house of the captain of the guard, in the prison, the place where Joseph was confined.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40004, 'And the captain of the guard charged Joseph with them, and he served them; so they were in custody for a while.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40005, 'Then the butler and the baker of the king of Egypt, who were confined in the prison, had a dream, both of them, each man&rsquo;s dream in one night and each man&rsquo;s dream with its own interpretation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40006, 'And Joseph came in to them in the morning and looked at them, and saw that they were sad.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40007, 'So he asked Pharaoh&rsquo;s officers who were with him in the custody of his lord&rsquo;s house, saying, &ldquo;Why do you look so sad today?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40008, 'And they said to him, &ldquo;We each have had a dream, and there is no interpreter of it.&rdquo; So Joseph said to them, &ldquo;Do not interpretations belong to God? Tell them to me, please.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40009, 'Then the chief butler told his dream to Joseph, and said to him, &ldquo;Behold, in my dream a vine was before me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40010, '&ldquo;and in the vine were three branches; it was as though it budded, its blossoms shot forth, and its clusters brought forth ripe grapes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40011, '&ldquo;Then Pharaoh&rsquo;s cup was in my hand; and I took the grapes and pressed them into Pharaoh&rsquo;s cup, and placed the cup in Pharaoh&rsquo;s hand.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40012, 'And Joseph said to him, &ldquo;This is the interpretation of it: The three branches are three days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40013, '&ldquo;Now within three days Pharaoh will lift up your head and restore you to your place, and you will put Pharaoh&rsquo;s cup in his hand according to the former manner, when you were his butler.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40014, '&ldquo;But remember me when it is well with you, and please show kindness to me; make mention of me to Pharaoh, and get me out of this house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40015, '&ldquo;For indeed I was stolen away from the land of the Hebrews; and also I have done nothing here that they should put me into the dungeon.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40016, 'When the chief baker saw that the interpretation was good, he said to Joseph, &ldquo;I also was in my dream, and there were three white baskets on my head.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40017, '&ldquo;In the uppermost basket were all kinds of baked goods for Pharaoh, and the birds ate them out of the basket on my head.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40018, 'So Joseph answered and said, &ldquo;This is the interpretation of it: The three baskets are three days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40019, '&ldquo;Within three days Pharaoh will lift off your head from you and hang you on a tree; and the birds will eat your flesh from you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40020, 'Now it came to pass on the third day, which was Pharaoh&rsquo;s birthday, that he made a feast for all his servants; and he lifted up the head of the chief butler and of the chief baker among his servants.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40021, 'Then he restored the chief butler to his butlership again, and he placed the cup in Pharaoh&rsquo;s hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40022, 'But he hanged the chief baker, as Joseph had interpreted to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 40023, 'Yet the chief butler did not remember Joseph, but forgot him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41001, 'Then it came to pass, at the end of two full years, that Pharaoh had a dream; and behold, he stood by the river.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41002, 'Suddenly there came up out of the river seven cows, fine looking and fat; and they fed in the meadow.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41003, 'Then behold, seven other cows came up after them out of the river, ugly and gaunt, and stood by the other cows on the bank of the river.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41004, 'And the ugly and gaunt cows ate up the seven fine looking and fat cows. So Pharaoh awoke.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41005, 'He slept and dreamed a second time; and suddenly seven heads of grain came up on one stalk, plump and good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41006, 'Then behold, seven thin heads, blighted by the east wind, sprang up after them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41007, 'And the seven thin heads devoured the seven plump and full heads. So Pharaoh awoke, and indeed, it was a dream.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41008, 'Now it came to pass in the morning that his spirit was troubled, and he sent and called for all the magicians of Egypt and all its wise men. And Pharaoh told them his dreams, but there was no one who could interpret them for Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41009, 'Then the chief butler spoke to Pharaoh, saying: &ldquo;I remember my faults this day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41010, '&ldquo;When Pharaoh was angry with his servants, and put me in custody in the house of the captain of the guard, both me and the chief baker,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41011, '&ldquo;we each had a dream in one night, he and I. Each of us dreamed according to the interpretation of his own dream.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41012, '&ldquo;Now there was a young Hebrew man with us there, a servant of the captain of the guard. And we told him, and he interpreted our dreams for us; to each man he interpreted according to his own dream.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41013, '&ldquo;And it came to pass, just as he interpreted for us, so it happened. He restored me to my office, and he hanged him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41014, 'Then Pharaoh sent and called Joseph, and they brought him quickly out of the dungeon; and he shaved, changed his clothing, and came to Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41015, 'And Pharaoh said to Joseph, &ldquo;I have had a dream, and there is no one who can interpret it. But I have heard it said of you that you can understand a dream, to interpret it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41016, 'So Joseph answered Pharaoh, saying, &ldquo;It is not in me; God will give Pharaoh an answer of peace.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41017, 'Then Pharaoh said to Joseph: &ldquo;Behold, in my dream I stood on the bank of the river.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41018, '&ldquo;Suddenly seven cows came up out of the river, fine looking and fat; and they fed in the meadow.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41019, '&ldquo;Then behold, seven other cows came up after them, poor and very ugly and gaunt, such ugliness as I have never seen in all the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41020, '&ldquo;And the gaunt and ugly cows ate up the first seven, the fat cows.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41021, '&ldquo;When they had eaten them up, no one would have known that they had eaten them, for they were just as ugly as at the beginning. So I awoke.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41022, '&ldquo;Also I saw in my dream, and suddenly seven heads came up on one stalk, full and good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41023, '&ldquo;Then behold, seven heads, withered, thin, and blighted by the east wind, sprang up after them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41024, '&ldquo;And the thin heads devoured the seven good heads. So I told this to the magicians, but there was no one who could explain it to me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41025, 'Then Joseph said to Pharaoh, &ldquo;The dreams of Pharaoh are one; God has shown Pharaoh what He is about to do:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41026, '&ldquo;The seven good cows are seven years, and the seven good heads are seven years; the dreams are one.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41027, '&ldquo;And the seven thin and ugly cows which came up after them are seven years, and the seven empty heads blighted by the east wind are seven years of famine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41028, '&ldquo;This is the thing which I have spoken to Pharaoh. God has shown Pharaoh what He is about to do.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41029, '&ldquo;Indeed seven years of great plenty will come throughout all the land of Egypt;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41030, '&ldquo;but after them seven years of famine will arise, and all the plenty will be forgotten in the land of Egypt; and the famine will deplete the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41031, '&ldquo;So the plenty will not be known in the land because of the famine following, for it will be very severe.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41032, '&ldquo;And the dream was repeated to Pharaoh twice because the thing is established by God, and God will shortly bring it to pass.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41033, '&ldquo;Now therefore, let Pharaoh select a discerning and wise man, and set him over the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41034, '&ldquo;Let Pharaoh do this, and let him appoint officers over the land, to collect one-fifth of the produce of the land of Egypt in the seven plentiful years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41035, '&ldquo;And let them gather all the food of those good years that are coming, and store up grain under the authority of Pharaoh, and let them keep food in the cities.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41036, '&ldquo;Then that food shall be as a reserve for the land for the seven years of famine which shall be in the land of Egypt, that the land may not perish during the famine.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41037, 'So the advice was good in the eyes of Pharaoh and in the eyes of all his servants.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41038, 'And Pharaoh said to his servants, &ldquo;Can we find such a one as this, a man in whom is the Spirit of God?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41039, 'Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, &ldquo;Inasmuch as God has shown you all this, there is no one as discerning and wise as you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41040, '&ldquo;You shall be over my house, and all my people shall be ruled according to your word; only in regard to the throne will I be greater than you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41041, 'And Pharaoh said to Joseph, &ldquo;See, I have set you over all the land of Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41042, 'Then Pharaoh took his signet ring off his hand and put it on Joseph&rsquo;s hand; and he clothed him in garments of fine linen and put a gold chain around his neck.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41043, 'And he had him ride in the second chariot which he had; and they cried out before him, &ldquo;Bow the knee!&rdquo; So he set him over all the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41044, 'Pharaoh also said to Joseph, &ldquo;I am Pharaoh, and without your consent no man may lift his hand or foot in all the land of Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41045, 'And Pharaoh called Joseph&rsquo;s name Zaphnath-Paaneah. And he gave him as a wife Asenath, the daughter of Poti-Pherah priest of On. So Joseph went out over all the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41046, 'Joseph was thirty years old when he stood before Pharaoh king of Egypt. And Joseph went out from the presence of Pharaoh, and went throughout all the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41047, 'Now in the seven plentiful years the ground brought forth abundantly.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41048, 'So he gathered up all the food of the seven years which were in the land of Egypt, and laid up the food in the cities; he laid up in every city the food of the fields which surrounded them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41049, 'Joseph gathered very much grain, as the sand of the sea, until he stopped counting, for it was immeasurable.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41050, 'And to Joseph were born two sons before the years of famine came, whom Asenath, the daughter of Poti-Pherah priest of On, bore to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41051, 'Joseph called the name of the firstborn Manasseh: &ldquo;For God has made me forget all my toil and all my father&rsquo;s house.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41052, 'And the name of the second he called Ephraim: &ldquo;For God has caused me to be fruitful in the land of my affliction.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41053, 'Then the seven years of plenty which were in the land of Egypt ended,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41054, 'and the seven years of famine began to come, as Joseph had said. The famine was in all lands, but in all the land of Egypt there was bread.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41055, 'So when all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried to Pharaoh for bread. Then Pharaoh said to all the Egyptians, &ldquo;Go to Joseph; whatever he says to you, do.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41056, 'The famine was over all the face of the earth, and Joseph opened all the storehouses and sold to the Egyptians. And the famine became severe in the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 41057, 'So all countries came to Joseph in Egypt to buy grain, because the famine was severe in all lands.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42001, 'When Jacob saw that there was grain in Egypt, Jacob said to his sons, &ldquo;Why do you look at one another?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42002, 'And he said, &ldquo;Indeed I have heard that there is grain in Egypt; go down to that place and buy for us there, that we may live and not die.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42003, 'So Joseph&rsquo;s ten brothers went down to buy grain in Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42004, 'But Jacob did not send Joseph&rsquo;s brother Benjamin with his brothers, for he said, &ldquo;Lest some calamity befall him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42005, 'And the sons of Israel went to buy grain among those who journeyed, for the famine was in the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42006, 'Now Joseph was governor over the land; and it was he who sold to all the people of the land. And Joseph&rsquo;s brothers came and bowed down before him with their faces to the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42007, 'Joseph saw his brothers and recognized them, but he acted as a stranger to them and spoke roughly to them. Then he said to them, &ldquo;Where do you come from?&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;From the land of Canaan to buy food.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42008, 'So Joseph recognized his brothers, but they did not recognize him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42009, 'Then Joseph remembered the dreams which he had dreamed about them, and said to them, &ldquo;You are spies! You have come to see the nakedness of the land!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42010, 'And they said to him, &ldquo;No, my lord, but your servants have come to buy food.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42011, '&ldquo;We are all one man&rsquo;s sons; we are honest men; your servants are not spies.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42012, 'But he said to them, &ldquo;No, but you have come to see the nakedness of the land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42013, 'And they said, &ldquo;Your servants are twelve brothers, the sons of one man in the land of Canaan; and in fact, the youngest is with our father today, and one is no more.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42014, 'But Joseph said to them, &ldquo;It is as I spoke to you, saying, &lsquo;You are spies!&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42015, '&ldquo;In this manner you shall be tested: By the life of Pharaoh, you shall not leave this place unless your youngest brother comes here.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42016, '&ldquo;Send one of you, and let him bring your brother; and you shall be kept in prison, that your words may be tested to see whether there is any truth in you; or else, by the life of Pharaoh, surely you are spies!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42017, 'So he put them all together in prison three days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42018, 'Then Joseph said to them the third day, &ldquo;Do this and live, for I fear God:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42019, '&ldquo;If you are honest men, let one of your brothers be confined to your prison house; but you, go and carry grain for the famine of your houses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42020, '&ldquo;And bring your youngest brother to me; so your words will be verified, and you shall not die.&rdquo; And they did so.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42021, 'Then they said to one another, &ldquo;We are truly guilty concerning our brother, for we saw the anguish of his soul when he pleaded with us, and we would not hear; therefore this distress has come upon us.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42022, 'And Reuben answered them, saying, &ldquo;Did I not speak to you, saying, &lsquo;Do not sin against the boy&rsquo;; and you would not listen? Therefore behold, his blood is now required of us.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42023, 'But they did not know that Joseph understood them, for he spoke to them through an interpreter.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42024, 'And he turned himself away from them and wept. Then he returned to them again, and talked with them. And he took Simeon from them and bound him before their eyes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42025, 'Then Joseph gave a command to fill their sacks with grain, to restore every man&rsquo;s money to his sack, and to give them provisions for the journey. Thus he did for them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42026, 'So they loaded their donkeys with the grain and departed from there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42027, 'But as one of them opened his sack to give his donkey feed at the encampment, he saw his money; and there it was, in the mouth of his sack.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42028, 'So he said to his brothers, &ldquo;My money has been restored, and there it is, in my sack!&rdquo; Then their hearts failed them and they were afraid, saying to one another, &ldquo;What is this that God has done to us?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42029, 'Then they went to Jacob their father in the land of Canaan and told him all that had happened to them, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42030, '&ldquo;The man who is lord of the land spoke roughly to us, and took us for spies of the country.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42031, '&ldquo;But we said to him, &lsquo;We are honest men; we are not spies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42032, '&lsquo;We are twelve brothers, sons of our father; one is no more, and the youngest is with our father this day in the land of Canaan.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42033, '&ldquo;Then the man, the lord of the country, said to us, &lsquo;By this I will know that you are honest men: Leave one of your brothers here with me, take food for the famine of your households, and be gone.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42034, '&lsquo;And bring your youngest brother to me; so I shall know that you are not spies, but that you are honest men. I will grant your brother to you, and you may trade in the land.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42035, 'Then it happened as they emptied their sacks, that surprisingly each man&rsquo;s bundle of money was in his sack; and when they and their father saw the bundles of money, they were afraid.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42036, 'And Jacob their father said to them, &ldquo;You have bereaved me: Joseph is no more, Simeon is no more, and you want to take Benjamin. All these things are against me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42037, 'Then Reuben spoke to his father, saying, &ldquo;Kill my two sons if I do not bring him back to you; put him in my hands, and I will bring him back to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 42038, 'But he said, &ldquo;My son shall not go down with you, for his brother is dead, and he is left alone. If any calamity should befall him along the way in which you go, then you would bring down my gray hair with sorrow to the grave.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43001, 'Now the famine was severe in the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43002, 'And it came to pass, when they had eaten up the grain which they had brought from Egypt, that their father said to them, &ldquo;Go back, buy us a little food.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43003, 'But Judah spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;The man solemnly warned us, saying, &lsquo;You shall not see my face unless your brother is with you.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43004, '&ldquo;If you send our brother with us, we will go down and buy you food.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43005, '&ldquo;But if you will not send him, we will not go down; for the man said to us, &lsquo;You shall not see my face unless your brother is with you.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43006, 'And Israel said, &ldquo;Why did you deal so wrongfully with me as to tell the man whether you had still another brother?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43007, 'But they said, &ldquo;The man asked us pointedly about ourselves and our family, saying, &lsquo;Is your father still alive? Have you another brother?&rsquo; And we told him according to these words. Could we possibly have known that he would say, &lsquo;Bring your brother down&rsquo;?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43008, 'Then Judah said to Israel his father, &ldquo;Send the lad with me, and we will arise and go, that we may live and not die, both we and you and also our little ones.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43009, '&ldquo;I myself will be surety for him; from my hand you shall require him. If I do not bring him back to you and set him before you, then let me bear the blame forever.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43010, '&ldquo;For if we had not lingered, surely by now we would have returned this second time.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43011, 'And their father Israel said to them, &ldquo;If it must be so, then do this: Take some of the best fruits of the land in your vessels and carry down a present for the man &ndash; a little balm and a little honey, spices and myrrh, pistachio nuts and almonds.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43012, '&ldquo;Take double money in your hand, and take back in your hand the money that was returned in the mouth of your sacks; perhaps it was an oversight.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43013, '&ldquo;Take your brother also, and arise, go back to the man.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43014, '&ldquo;And may God Almighty give you mercy before the man, that he may release your other brother and Benjamin. If I am bereaved, I am bereaved!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43015, 'So the men took that present and Benjamin, and they took double money in their hand, and arose and went down to Egypt; and they stood before Joseph.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43016, 'When Joseph saw Benjamin with them, he said to the steward of his house, &ldquo;Take these men to my home, and slaughter an animal and make ready; for these men will dine with me at noon.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43017, 'Then the man did as Joseph ordered, and the man brought the men into Joseph&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43018, 'Now the men were afraid because they were brought into Joseph&rsquo;s house; and they said, &ldquo;It is because of the money, which was returned in our sacks the first time, that we are brought in, so that he may make a case against us and seize us, to take us as sl');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43019, 'When they drew near to the steward of Joseph&rsquo;s house, they talked with him at the door of the house,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43020, 'and said, &ldquo;O sir, we indeed came down the first time to buy food;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43021, '&ldquo;but it happened, when we came to the encampment, that we opened our sacks, and there, each man&rsquo;s money was in the mouth of his sack, our money in full weight; so we have brought it back in our hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43022, '&ldquo;And we have brought down other money in our hands to buy food. We do not know who put our money in our sacks.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43023, 'But he said, &ldquo;Peace be with you, do not be afraid. Your God and the God of your father has given you treasure in your sacks; I had your money.&rdquo; Then he brought Simeon out to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43024, 'So the man brought the men into Joseph&rsquo;s house and gave them water, and they washed their feet; and he gave their donkeys feed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43025, 'Then they made the present ready for Joseph&rsquo;s coming at noon, for they heard that they would eat bread there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43026, 'And when Joseph came home, they* brought him the present which was in their hand into the house, and bowed down before him to the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43027, 'Then he asked them about their well-being, and said, &ldquo;Is your father well, the old man of whom you spoke? Is he still alive?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43028, 'And they answered, &ldquo;Your servant our father is in good health; he is still alive.&rdquo; And they bowed their heads down and prostrated themselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43029, 'Then he lifted his eyes and saw his brother Benjamin, his mother&rsquo;s son, and said, &ldquo;Is this your younger brother of whom you spoke to me?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;God be gracious to you, my son.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43030, 'Now his heart yearned for his brother; so Joseph made haste and sought somewhere to weep. And he went into his chamber and wept there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43031, 'Then he washed his face and came out; and he restrained himself|, and said, &ldquo;Serve the bread.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43032, 'So they set him a place by himself, and them by themselves, and the Egyptians who ate with him by themselves; because the Egyptians could not eat food with the Hebrews, for that is an abomination to the Egyptians.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43033, 'And they sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright and the youngest according to his youth; and the men looked in astonishment at one another.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 43034, 'Then he took servings to them from before him, but Benjamin&rsquo;s serving was five times as much as any of theirs. So they drank and were merry with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44001, 'And he commanded the steward of his house, saying, &ldquo;Fill the men&rsquo;s sacks with food, as much as they can carry, and put each man&rsquo;s money in the mouth of his sack.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44002, '&ldquo;Also put my cup, the silver cup, in the mouth of the sack of the youngest, and his grain money.&rdquo; So he did according to the word that Joseph had spoken.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44003, 'As soon as the morning dawned, the men were sent away, they and their donkeys.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44004, 'When they had gone out of the city, and were not yet far off, Joseph said to his steward, &ldquo;Get up, follow the men; and when you overtake them, say to them, &lsquo;Why have you repaid evil for good?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44005, '&lsquo;Is not this the one from which my lord drinks, and with which he indeed practices divination? You have done evil in so doing.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44006, 'So he overtook them, and he spoke to them these same words.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44007, 'And they said to him, &ldquo;Why does my lord say these words? Far be it from us that your servants should do such a thing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44008, '&ldquo;Look, we brought back to you from the land of Canaan the money which we found in the mouth of our sacks. How then could we steal silver or gold from your lord&rsquo;s house?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44009, '&ldquo;With whomever of your servants it is found, let him die, and we also will be my lord&rsquo;s slaves.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44010, 'And he said, &ldquo;Now also let it be according to your words; he with whom it is found shall be my slave, and you shall be blameless.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44011, 'Then each man speedily let down his sack to the ground, and each opened his sack.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44012, 'So he searched. He began with the oldest and left off with the youngest; and the cup was found in Benjamin&rsquo;s sack.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44013, 'Then they tore their clothes, and each man loaded his donkey and returned to the city.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44014, 'So Judah and his brothers came to Joseph&rsquo;s house, and he was still there; and they fell before him on the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44015, 'And Joseph said to them, &ldquo;What deed is this you have done? Did you not know that such a man as I can certainly practice divination?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44016, 'Then Judah said, &ldquo;What shall we say to my lord? What shall we speak? Or how shall we clear ourselves? God has found out the iniquity of your servants; here we are, my lord&rsquo;s slaves, both we and he also with whom the cup was found.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44017, 'But he said, &ldquo;Far be it from me that I should do so; the man in whose hand the cup was found, he shall be my slave. And as for you, go up in peace to your father.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44018, 'Then Judah came near to him and said: &ldquo;O my lord, please let your servant speak a word in my lord&rsquo;s hearing, and do not let your anger burn against your servant; for you are even like Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44019, '&ldquo;My lord asked his servants, saying, &lsquo;Have you a father or a brother?&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44020, '&ldquo;And we said to my lord, &lsquo;We have a father, an old man, and a child of his old age, who is young; his brother is dead, and he alone is left of his mother&rsquo;s children, and his father loves him.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44021, '&ldquo;Then you said to your servants, &lsquo;Bring him down to me, that I may set my eyes on him.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44022, '&ldquo;And we said to my lord, &lsquo;The lad cannot leave his father, for if he should leave his father, his father would die.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44023, '&ldquo;But you said to your servants, &lsquo;Unless your youngest brother comes down with you, you shall see my face no more.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44024, '&ldquo;So it was, when we went up to your servant my father, that we told him the words of my lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44025, '&ldquo;And our father said, &lsquo;Go back and buy us a little food.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44026, '&ldquo;But we said, &lsquo;We cannot go down; if our youngest brother is with us, then we will go down; for we may not see the man&rsquo;s face unless our youngest brother is with us.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44027, '&ldquo;Then your servant my father said to us, &lsquo;You know that my wife bore me two sons;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44028, '&lsquo;and the one went out from me, and I said, &ldquo;Surely he is torn to pieces&rdquo;; and I have not seen him since.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44029, '&lsquo;But if you take this one also from me, and calamity befalls him, you shall bring down my gray hair with sorrow to the grave.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44030, '&ldquo;Now therefore, when I come to your servant my father, and the lad is not with us, since his life is bound up in the lad&rsquo;s life,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44031, '&ldquo;it will happen, when he sees that the lad is not with us, that he will die. So your servants will bring down the gray hair of your servant our father with sorrow to the grave.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44032, '&ldquo;For your servant became surety for the lad to my father, saying, &lsquo;If I do not bring him back to you, then I shall bear the blame before my father forever.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44033, '&ldquo;Now therefore, please let your servant remain instead of the lad as a slave to my lord, and let the lad go up with his brothers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 44034, '&ldquo;For how shall I go up to my father if the lad is not with me, lest perhaps I see the evil that would come upon my father?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45001, 'Then* Joseph could not restrain himself before all those who stood by him, and he cried out, &ldquo;Make everyone go out from me!&rdquo; So no one stood with him while Joseph made himself known to his brothers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45002, 'And he wept aloud, and the Egyptians and the house of Pharaoh heard it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45003, 'Then Joseph said to his brothers, &ldquo;I am Joseph; does my father still live?&rdquo; But his brothers could not answer him, for they were dismayed in his presence.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45004, 'And Joseph said to his brothers, &ldquo;Please come near to me.&rdquo; So they came near. Then he said: &ldquo;I am Joseph your brother, whom you sold into Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45005, '&ldquo;But now, do not therefore be grieved or angry with yourselves because you sold me here; for God sent me before you to preserve life.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45006, '&ldquo;For these two years the famine has been in the land, and there are still five years in which there will be neither plowing nor harvesting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45007, '&ldquo;And God sent me before you to preserve a posterity for you in the earth, and to save your lives by a great deliverance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45008, '&ldquo;So now it was not you who sent me here, but God; and He has made me a father to Pharaoh, and lord of all his house, and a ruler throughout all the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45009, '&ldquo;Hurry and go up to my father, and say to him, &lsquo;Thus says your son Joseph: &ldquo;God has made me lord of all Egypt; come down to me, do not tarry.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45010, '&ldquo;You shall dwell in the land of Goshen, and you shall be near to me, you and your children, your children&rsquo;s children, your flocks and your herds, and all that you have.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45011, '&ldquo;There I will provide for you, lest you and your household, and all that you have, come to poverty; for there are still five years of famine.&rdquo;&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45012, '&ldquo;And behold, your eyes and the eyes of my brother Benjamin see that it is my mouth that speaks to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45013, '&ldquo;So you shall tell my father of all my glory in Egypt, and of all that you have seen; and you shall hurry and bring my father down here.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45014, 'Then he fell on his brother Benjamin&rsquo;s neck and wept, and Benjamin wept on his neck.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45015, 'Moreover he kissed all his brothers and wept over them, and after that his brothers talked with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45016, 'Now the report of it was heard in Pharaoh&rsquo;s house, saying, &ldquo;Joseph&rsquo;s brothers have come.&rdquo; So it pleased Pharaoh and his servants well.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45017, 'And Pharaoh said to Joseph, &ldquo;Say to your brothers, &lsquo;Do this: Load your animals and depart; go to the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45018, '&lsquo;Bring your father and your households and come to me; I will give you the best of the land of Egypt, and you will eat the fat of the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45019, '&lsquo;Now you are commanded &ndash; do this: Take carts out of the land of Egypt for your little ones and your wives; bring your father and come.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45020, '&lsquo;Also do not be concerned about your goods, for the best of all the land of Egypt is yours.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45021, 'Then the sons of Israel did so; and Joseph gave them carts, according to the command of Pharaoh, and he gave them provisions for the journey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45022, 'He gave to all of them, to each man, changes of garments; but to Benjamin he gave three hundred pieces of silver and five changes of garments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45023, 'And he sent to his father these things: ten donkeys loaded with the good things of Egypt, and ten female donkeys loaded with grain, bread, and food for his father for the journey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45024, 'So he sent his brothers away, and they departed; and he said to them, &ldquo;See that you do not become troubled along the way.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45025, 'Then they went up out of Egypt, and came to the land of Canaan to Jacob their father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45026, 'And they told him, saying, &ldquo;Joseph is still alive, and he is governor over all the land of Egypt.&rdquo; And Jacob&rsquo;s heart stood still, because he did not believe them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45027, 'But when they told him all the words which Joseph had said to them, and when he saw the carts which Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of Jacob their father revived.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 45028, 'Then Israel said, &ldquo;It is enough. Joseph my son is still alive. I will go and see him before I die.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46001, 'So *Israel took his journey with all that he had, and came to Beersheba, and offered sacrifices to the God of his father Isaac.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46002, 'Then God spoke to Israel in the visions of the night, and said, &ldquo;Jacob, Jacob!&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Here I am.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46003, 'So He said, &ldquo;I am God, the God of your father; do not fear to go down to Egypt, for I will make of you a great nation there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46004, '&ldquo;I will go down with you to Egypt, and I will also surely bring you up again; and Joseph will put his hand on your eyes.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46005, 'Then Jacob arose from Beersheba; and the sons of Israel carried their father Jacob, their little ones, and their wives, in the carts which Pharaoh had sent to carry him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46006, 'So they took their livestock and their goods, which they had acquired in the land of Canaan, and went to Egypt, Jacob and all his descendants with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46007, 'His sons and his sons&rsquo; sons, his daughters and his sons&rsquo; daughters, and all his descendants he brought with him to Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46008, 'Now these were the names of the children of Israel, Jacob and his sons, who went to Egypt: Reuben was Jacob&rsquo;s firstborn.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46009, 'The sons of Reuben were Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46010, 'The sons of Simeon were Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul, the son of a Canaanite woman.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46011, 'The sons of Levi were Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46012, 'The sons of Judah were Er, Onan, Shelah, Perez, and Zerah (but Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan). The sons of Perez were Hezron and Hamul.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46013, 'The sons of Issachar were Tola, Puvah, Job, and Shimron.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46014, 'The sons of Zebulun were Sered, Elon, and Jahleel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46015, 'These were the sons of Leah, whom she bore to Jacob in Padan Aram, with his daughter Dinah. All the persons, his sons and his daughters, were thirty-three.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46016, 'The sons of Gad were Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi, and Areli.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46017, 'The sons of Asher were Jimnah, Ishuah, Isui, Beriah, and Serah, their sister. And the sons of Beriah were Heber and Malchiel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46018, 'These were the sons of Zilpah, whom Laban gave to Leah his daughter; and these she bore to Jacob: sixteen persons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46019, 'The sons of Rachel, Jacob&rsquo;s wife, were Joseph and Benjamin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46020, 'And to Joseph in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh and Ephraim, whom Asenath, the daughter of Poti-Pherah priest of On, bore to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46021, 'The sons of Benjamin were Belah, Becher, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi, Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, and Ard.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46022, 'These were the sons of Rachel, who were born to Jacob: fourteen persons in all.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46023, 'The son of Dan was Hushim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46024, 'The sons of Naphtali were Jahzeel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46025, 'These were the sons of Bilhah, whom Laban gave to Rachel his daughter, and she bore these to Jacob: seven persons in all.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46026, 'All the persons who went with Jacob to Egypt, who came from his body, besides Jacob&rsquo;s sons&rsquo; wives, were sixty-six persons in all.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46027, 'And the sons of Joseph who were born to him in Egypt were two persons. All the persons of the house of Jacob who went to Egypt were seventy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46028, 'Then he sent Judah before him to Joseph, to point out before him the way to Goshen. And they came to the land of Goshen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46029, 'So Joseph made ready his chariot and went up to Goshen to meet his father Israel; and he presented himself to him, and fell on his neck and wept on his neck a good while.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46030, 'And Israel said to Joseph, &ldquo;Now let me die, since I have seen your face, because you are still alive.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46031, 'Then Joseph said to his brothers and to his father&rsquo;s household, &ldquo;I will go up and tell Pharaoh, and say to him, &lsquo;My brothers and those of my father&rsquo;s house, who were in the land of Canaan, have come to me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46032, '&lsquo;And the men are shepherds, for their occupation has been to feed livestock; and they have brought their flocks, their herds, and all that they have.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46033, '&ldquo;So it shall be, when Pharaoh calls you and says, &lsquo;What is your occupation?&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 46034, '&ldquo;that you shall say, &lsquo;Your servants&rsquo; occupation has been with livestock from our youth even till now, both we and also our fathers,&rsquo; that you may dwell in the land of Goshen; for every shepherd is an abomination to the Egyptians.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47001, 'Then Joseph went and told Pharaoh, and said, &ldquo;My father and my brothers, their flocks and their herds and all that they possess, have come from the land of Canaan; and indeed they are in the land of Goshen.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47002, 'And he took five men from among his brothers and presented them to Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47003, 'Then Pharaoh said to his brothers, &ldquo;What is your occupation?&rdquo; And they said to Pharaoh, &ldquo;Your servants are shepherds, both we and also our fathers.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47004, 'And they said to Pharaoh, &ldquo;We have come to dwell in the land, because your servants have no pasture for their flocks, for the famine is severe in the land of Canaan. Now therefore, please let your servants dwell in the land of Goshen.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47005, 'Then Pharaoh spoke to Joseph, saying, &ldquo;Your father and your brothers have come to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47006, '&ldquo;The land of Egypt is before you. Have your father and brothers dwell in the best of the land; let them dwell in the land of Goshen. And if you know any competent men among them, then make them chief herdsmen over my livestock.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47007, 'Then Joseph brought in his father Jacob and set him before Pharaoh; and Jacob blessed Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47008, 'Pharaoh said to Jacob, &ldquo;How old are you?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47009, 'And Jacob said to Pharaoh, &ldquo;The days of the years of my pilgrimage are one hundred and thirty years; few and evil have been the days of the years of my life, and they have not attained to the days of the years of the life of my fathers in the days of thei');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47010, 'So Jacob blessed Pharaoh, and went out from before Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47011, 'And Joseph situated his father and his brothers, and gave them a possession in the land of Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of Rameses, as Pharaoh had commanded.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47012, 'Then Joseph provided his father, his brothers, and all his father&rsquo;s household with bread, according to the number in their families.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47013, 'Now there was no bread in all the land; for the famine was very severe, so that the land of Egypt and the land of Canaan languished because of the famine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47014, 'And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land of Egypt and in the land of Canaan, for the grain which they bought; and Joseph brought the money into Pharaoh&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47015, 'So when the money failed in the land of Egypt and in the land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came to Joseph and said, &ldquo;Give us bread, for why should we die in your presence? For the money has failed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47016, 'Then Joseph said, &ldquo;Give your livestock, and I will give you bread for your livestock, if the money is gone.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47017, 'So they brought their livestock to Joseph, and Joseph gave them bread in exchange for the horses, the flocks, the cattle of the herds, and for the donkeys. Thus he fed them with bread in exchange for all their livestock that year.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47018, 'When that year had ended, they came to him the next year and said to him, &ldquo;We will not hide from my lord that our money is gone; my lord also has our herds of livestock. There is nothing left in the sight of my lord but our bodies and our lands.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47019, '&ldquo;Why should we die before your eyes, both we and our land? Buy us and our land for bread, and we and our land will be servants of Pharaoh; give us seed, that we may live and not die, that the land may not be desolate.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47020, 'Then Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh; for every man of the Egyptians sold his field, because the famine was severe upon them. So the land became Pharaoh&rsquo;s.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47021, 'And as for the people, he moved them into the cities, from one end of the borders of Egypt to the other end.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47022, 'Only the land of the priests he did not buy; for the priests had rations allotted to them by Pharaoh, and they ate their rations which Pharaoh gave them; therefore they did not sell their lands.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47023, 'Then Joseph said to the people, &ldquo;Indeed I have bought you and your land this day for Pharaoh. Look, here is seed for you, and you shall sow the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47024, '&ldquo;And it shall come to pass in the harvest that you shall give one-fifth to Pharaoh. Four-fifths shall be your own, as seed for the field and for your food, for those of your households and as food for your little ones.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47025, 'So they said, &ldquo;You have saved our lives; let us find favor in the sight of my lord, and we will be Pharaoh&rsquo;s servants.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47026, 'And Joseph made it a law over the land of Egypt to this day, that Pharaoh should have one-fifth, except for the land of the priests only, which did not become Pharaoh&rsquo;s.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47027, 'So Israel dwelt in the land of Egypt, in the country of Goshen; and they had possessions there and grew and multiplied exceedingly.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47028, 'And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years. So the length of Jacob&rsquo;s life was one hundred and forty-seven years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47029, 'When the time drew near that Israel must die, he called his son Joseph and said to him, &ldquo;Now if I have found favor in your sight, please put your hand under my thigh, and deal kindly and truly with me. Please do not bury me in Egypt,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47030, '&ldquo;but let me lie with my fathers; you shall carry me out of Egypt and bury me in their burial place.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;I will do as you have said.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 47031, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Swear to me.&rdquo; And he swore to him. So Israel bowed himself on the head of the bed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48001, 'Now it came to pass after these things that Joseph was told, &ldquo;Indeed your father is sick&rdquo;; and he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and Ephraim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48002, 'And Jacob was told, &ldquo;Look, your son Joseph is coming to you&rdquo;; and Israel strengthened himself and sat up on the bed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48003, 'Then Jacob said to Joseph: &ldquo;God Almighty appeared to me at Luz in the land of Canaan and blessed me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48004, '&ldquo;and said to me, &lsquo;Behold, I will make you fruitful and multiply you, and I will make of you a multitude of people, and give this land to your descendants after you as an everlasting possession.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48005, '&ldquo;And now your two sons, Ephraim and Manasseh, who were born to you in the land of Egypt before I came to you in Egypt, are mine; as Reuben and Simeon, they shall be mine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48006, '&ldquo;Your offspring whom you beget after them shall be yours; they will be called by the name of their brothers in their inheritance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48007, '&ldquo;But as for me, when I came from Padan, Rachel died beside me in the land of Canaan on the way, when there was but a little distance to go to Ephrath; and I buried her there on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem).&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48008, 'Then Israel saw Joseph&rsquo;s sons, and said, &ldquo;Who are these?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48009, 'And Joseph said to his father, &ldquo;They are my sons, whom God has given me in this place.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Please bring them to me, and I will bless them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48010, 'Now the eyes of Israel were dim with age, so that he could not see. Then Joseph brought them near him, and he kissed them and embraced them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48011, 'And Israel said to Joseph, &ldquo;I had not thought to see your face; but in fact, God has also shown me your offspring!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48012, 'So Joseph brought them from beside his knees, and he bowed down with his face to the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48013, 'And Joseph took them both, Ephraim with his right hand toward Israel&rsquo;s left hand, and Manasseh with his left hand toward Israel&rsquo;s right hand, and brought them near him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48014, 'Then Israel stretched out his right hand and laid it on Ephraim&rsquo;s head, who was the younger, and his left hand on Manasseh&rsquo;s head, guiding his hands knowingly, for Manasseh was the firstborn.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48015, 'And he blessed Joseph, and said: &ldquo;God, before whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac walked, The God who has fed me all my life long to this day, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48016, 'The Angel who has redeemed me from all evil, Bless the lads; Let my name be named upon them, And the name of my fathers Abraham and Isaac; And let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48017, 'Now when Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand on the head of Ephraim, it displeased him; so he took hold of his father&rsquo;s hand to remove it from Ephraim&rsquo;s head to Manasseh&rsquo;s head.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48018, 'And Joseph said to his father, &ldquo;Not so, my father, for this one is the firstborn; put your right hand on his head.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48019, 'But his father refused and said, &ldquo;I know, my son, I know. He also shall become a people, and he also shall be great; but truly his younger brother shall be greater than he, and his descendants shall become a multitude of nations.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48020, 'So he blessed them that day, saying, &ldquo;By you Israel will bless, saying, &lsquo;May God make you as Ephraim and as Manasseh!&rsquo;&rdquo; And thus he set Ephraim before Manasseh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48021, 'Then Israel said to Joseph, &ldquo;Behold, I am dying, but God will be with you and bring you back to the land of your fathers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 48022, '&ldquo;Moreover I have given to you one portion above your brothers, which I took from the hand of the Amorite with my sword and my bow.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49001, 'And *Jacob called his sons and said, &ldquo;Gather together, that I may tell you what shall befall you in the last days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49002, 'Gather together and hear, you sons of Jacob, and listen to Israel your father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49003, '&ldquo;Reuben, you are my firstborn, My might and the beginning of my strength, The excellency of dignity and the excellency of power. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49004, 'Unstable as water, you shall not excel, Because you went up to your father&rsquo;s bed; Then you defiled it &ndash; He went up to my couch.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49005, '&ldquo;Simeon and Levi are brothers; Instruments of cruelty are in their dwelling place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49006, 'Let not my soul enter their council; Let not my honor be united to their assembly; For in their anger they slew a man, And in their self-will they hamstrung an ox.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49007, 'Cursed be their anger, for it is fierce; And their wrath, for it is cruel! I will divide them in Jacob And scatter them in Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49008, 'Judah, you are he whom your brothers shall praise; your hand shall be on the neck of your enemies; your father&rsquo;s children shall bow down before you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49009, 'Judah is a lion&rsquo;s whelp; from a tender sprout, my son, you have sprung up. He bows down, he lies down as a lion; and as a lion, who shall rouse him?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49010, 'A prince shall not fail from Judah, nor a ruler from his loins, until there comes the things stored up for him; he is the expectation of the nations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49011, 'Binding his donkey to the vine, and his donkey&rsquo;s colt to the choice vine, he shall wash his garments in wine, and his clothes in the blood of grapes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49012, 'His eyes shall bring joy more than wine, and his teeth are whiter than milk.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49013, '&ldquo;Zebulun shall dwell by the haven of the sea; He shall become a haven for ships, And his border shall adjoin Sidon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49014, '&ldquo;Issachar is a strong donkey, Lying down between two burdens; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49015, 'He saw that rest was good, And that the land was pleasant; He bowed his shoulder to bear a burden, And became a band of slaves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49016, '&ldquo;Dan shall judge his people As one of the tribes of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49017, 'Dan shall be a serpent by the way, A viper by the path, That bites the horse&rsquo;s heels So that its rider shall fall backward.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49018, 'I have waited for your salvation, O Lord! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49019, '&ldquo;Gad, a troop shall tramp upon him, But he shall triumph at last.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49020, '&ldquo;Bread from Asher shall be rich, And he shall yield royal dainties.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49021, '&ldquo;Naphtali is a deer let loose; He uses beautiful words.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49022, '&ldquo;Joseph is a fruitful bough, A fruitful bough by a well; His branches run over the wall.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49023, 'The archers have bitterly grieved him, Shot at him and hated him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49024, 'But his bow remained in strength, And the arms of his hands were made strong By the hands of the Mighty God of Jacob (From there is the Shepherd, the Stone of Israel),');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49025, 'By the God of your father who will help you, And by the Almighty who will bless you With blessings of heaven above, Blessings of the deep that lies beneath, Blessings of the breasts and of the womb.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49026, 'The blessings of your father Have excelled the blessings of my ancestors, Up to the utmost bound of the everlasting hills. They shall be on the head of Joseph, And on the crown of the head of him who was separate from his brothers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49027, '&ldquo;Benjamin is a ravenous wolf; In the morning he shall devour the prey, And at night he shall divide the spoil.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49028, 'All these are the twelve tribes of Israel, and this is what their father spoke to them. And he blessed them; he blessed each one according to his own blessing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49029, 'Then he charged them and said to them: &ldquo;I am to be gathered to my people; bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the Hittite,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49030, '&ldquo;in the cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre in the land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field of Ephron the Hittite as a possession for a burial place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49031, '&ldquo;There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife, there they buried Isaac and Rebekah his wife, and there I buried Leah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49032, '&ldquo;The field and the cave that is there were purchased from the sons of Heth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 49033, 'And when* Jacob had finished commanding his sons, he drew his feet up into the bed and breathed his last, and was gathered to his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50001, 'Then Joseph fell on his father&rsquo;s face, and wept over him, and kissed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50002, 'And Joseph commanded his servants the physicians to embalm his father. So the physicians embalmed Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50003, 'Forty days were required for him, for such are the days required for those who are embalmed; and the Egyptians mourned for him seventy days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50004, 'Now when the days of his mourning were past, Joseph spoke to the household of Pharaoh, saying, &ldquo;If now I have found favor in your eyes, please speak in the hearing of Pharaoh, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50005, '&lsquo;My father made me swear, saying, &ldquo;Behold, I am dying; in my grave which I dug for myself in the land of Canaan, there you shall bury me.&rdquo; Now therefore, please let me go up and bury my father, and I will come back.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50006, 'And Pharaoh said, &ldquo;Go up and bury your father, as he made you swear.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50007, 'So Joseph went up to bury his father; and with him went up all the servants of Pharaoh, the elders of his house, and all the elders of the land of Egypt,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50008, 'as well as all the house of Joseph, his brothers, and his father&rsquo;s house. Only their little ones, their flocks, and their herds they left in the land of Goshen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50009, 'And there went up with him both chariots and horsemen, and it was a very great gathering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50010, 'Then they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond the Jordan, and they mourned there with a great and very solemn lamentation. He observed seven days of mourning for his father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50011, 'And when the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning at the threshing floor of Atad, they said, &ldquo;This is a deep mourning of the Egyptians.&rdquo; Therefore its name was called Abel Mizraim, which is beyond the Jordan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50012, 'So his sons did for him just as he had commanded them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50013, 'For his sons carried him to the land of Canaan, and buried him in the cave of the field of Machpelah, before Mamre, which Abraham bought with the field from Ephron the Hittite as property for a burial place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50014, 'And after he had buried his father, Joseph returned to Egypt, he and his brothers and all who went up with him to bury his father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50015, 'When Joseph&rsquo;s brothers saw that their father was dead, they said, &ldquo;Perhaps Joseph will hate us, and may actually repay us for all the evil which we did to him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50016, 'So they sent messengers to Joseph, saying, &ldquo;Before your father died he commanded, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50017, '&lsquo;Thus you shall say to Joseph: &ldquo;I beg you, please forgive the trespass of your brothers and their sin; for they did evil to you.&rdquo;&rsquo; Now, please, forgive the trespass of the servants of the God of your father.&rdquo; And Joseph wept when they spoke to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50018, 'Then his brothers also went and fell down before his face, and they said, &ldquo;Behold, we are your servants.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50019, 'Joseph said to them, &ldquo;Do not be afraid, for am I in the place of God?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50020, '&ldquo;But as for you, you meant evil against me; but God meant it for good, in order to bring it about as it is this day, to save many people alive.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50021, '&ldquo;Now therefore, do not be afraid; I will provide for you and your little ones.&rdquo; And he comforted them and spoke kindly to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50022, 'So Joseph dwelt in Egypt, he and his father&rsquo;s household. And Joseph lived one hundred and ten years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50023, 'Joseph saw Ephraim&rsquo;s children to the third generation. The children of Machir, the son of Manasseh, were also brought up on Joseph&rsquo;s knees.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50024, 'And Joseph said to his brethren, &ldquo;I am dying; but God will surely visit you, and bring you out of this land to the land of which He swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50025, 'Then Joseph took an oath from the children of Israel, saying, &ldquo;God will surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones from here.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Gen', 50026, 'So Joseph died, being one hundred and ten years old; and they embalmed him, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1001, 'Now these* are the names of the children of Israel who came to Egypt; each man and his household came with Jacob:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1002, 'Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1003, 'Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1004, 'Dan, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1005, 'All those who were descendants of Jacob were seventy persons (for Joseph was in Egypt already).');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1006, 'And Joseph died, all his brothers, and all that generation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1007, 'But the children of Israel were fruitful and increased abundantly, multiplied and grew exceedingly mighty; and the land was filled with them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1008, 'Now there arose a new king over Egypt, who did not know Joseph.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1009, 'And he said to his people, &ldquo;Look, the people of the children of Israel are more and mightier than we;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1010, '&ldquo;come, let us deal shrewdly with them, lest they multiply, and it happen, in the event of war, that they also join our enemies and fight against us, and so go up out of the land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1011, 'Therefore they set taskmasters over them to afflict them with their burdens. And they built for Pharaoh supply cities, Pithom and Raamses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1012, 'But the more they afflicted them, the more they multiplied and grew. And they were in dread of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1013, 'So the Egyptians made the children of Israel serve with rigor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1014, 'And they made their lives bitter with hard bondage &ndash; in mortar, in brick, and in all manner of service in the field. All their service in which they made them serve was with rigor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1015, 'Then the king of Egypt spoke to the Hebrew midwives, of whom the name of one was Shiphrah and the name of the other Puah;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1016, 'and he said, &ldquo;When you do the duties of a midwife for the Hebrew women, and see them on the birthstools, if it is a son, then you shall kill him; but if it is a daughter, then she shall live.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1017, 'But the midwives feared God, and did not do as the king of Egypt commanded them, but saved the male children alive.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1018, 'So the king of Egypt called for the midwives and said to them, &ldquo;Why have you done this thing, and saved the male children alive?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1019, 'And the midwives said to Pharaoh, &ldquo;Because the Hebrew women are not like the Egyptian women; for they are lively and give birth before the midwives come to them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1020, 'Therefore God dealt well with the midwives, and the people multiplied and grew very mighty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1021, 'And so it was, because the midwives feared God, that He provided households for them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 1022, 'So Pharaoh commanded all his people, saying, &ldquo;Every son who is born you shall cast into the river, and every daughter you shall save alive.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2001, 'And a man of the house of Levi went and took as wife a daughter of Levi.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2002, 'So the woman conceived and bore a son. And when she saw that he was a beautiful child, she hid him three months.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2003, 'But when she could no longer hide him, she took an ark of bulrushes for him, daubed it with asphalt and pitch, put the child in it, and laid it in the reeds by the river&rsquo;s bank.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2004, 'And his sister stood afar off, to know what would be done to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2005, 'Then the* daughter of Pharaoh came down to bathe at the river. And her maidens walked along the riverside; and when she saw the ark among the reeds, she sent her maid to get it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2006, 'And when she opened it, she saw the child, and behold, the baby wept. So she had compassion on him, and said, &ldquo;This is one of the Hebrews&rsquo; children.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2007, 'Then his sister said to Pharaoh&rsquo;s daughter, &ldquo;Shall I go and call a nurse for you from the Hebrew women, that she may nurse the child for you?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2008, 'And Pharaoh&rsquo;s daughter said to her, &ldquo;Go.&rdquo; So the maiden went and called the child&rsquo;s mother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2009, 'Then Pharaoh&rsquo;s daughter said to her, &ldquo;Take this child away and nurse him for me, and I will give you your wages.&rdquo; So the woman took the child and nursed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2010, 'And the child grew, and she brought him to Pharaoh&rsquo;s daughter, and he became her son. So she called his name Moses, saying, &ldquo;Because I drew him out of the water.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2011, 'Now it* came to pass in those days, when Moses was grown, that he went out to his brethren and looked at their burdens. And he saw an Egyptian beating a Hebrew, one of his brethren.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2012, 'So he looked this way and that way, and when he saw no one, he killed the Egyptian and hid him in the sand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2013, 'And when he went out the second day, behold, two Hebrew men were fighting, and he said to the one who did the wrong, &ldquo;Why are you striking your companion?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2014, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Who made you a prince and a judge over us? Do you intend to kill me as you killed the Egyptian?&rdquo; So Moses feared and said, &ldquo;Surely this thing is known!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2015, 'When Pharaoh heard of this matter, he sought to kill Moses. But Moses fled from the face of Pharaoh and dwelt in the land of Midian; and he sat down by a well.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2016, 'Now the priest of Midian had seven daughters. And they came and drew water, and they filled the troughs to water their father&rsquo;s flock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2017, 'Then the shepherds came and drove them away; but Moses stood up and helped them, and watered their flock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2018, 'When they came to Reuel their father, he said, &ldquo;How is it that you have come so soon today?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2019, 'And they said, &ldquo;An Egyptian delivered us from the hand of the shepherds, and he also drew enough water for us and watered the flock.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2020, 'So he said to his daughters, &ldquo;And where is he? Why is it that you have left the man? Call him, that he may eat bread.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2021, 'Then Moses was content to live with the man, and he gave Zipporah his daughter to Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2022, 'And she bore him a son. He called his name Gershom, for he said, &ldquo;I have been a stranger in a foreign land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2023, 'Now it happened in the process of time that the king of Egypt died. Then the children of Israel groaned because of the bondage, and they cried out; and their cry came up to God because of the bondage.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2024, 'So God heard their groaning, and God remembered His covenant with Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 2025, 'And God looked upon the children of Israel, and God acknowledged them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3001, 'Now *Moses was tending the flock of Jethro his father-in-law, the priest of Midian. And he led the flock to the back of the desert, and came to Horeb, the mountain of God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3002, 'And the Angel of the Lord appeared to him in a flame of fire from the midst of a bush. So he looked, and behold, the bush was burning with fire, but the bush was not consumed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3003, 'Then Moses said, &ldquo;I will now turn aside and see this great sight, why the bush does not burn.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3004, 'So when the Lord saw that he turned aside to look, God called to him from the midst of the bush and said, &ldquo;Moses, Moses!&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Here I am.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3005, 'Then He said, &ldquo;Do not draw near this place. Take your sandals off your feet, for the place where you stand is holy ground.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3006, 'Moreover He said, &ldquo;I am the God of your father &ndash; the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.&rdquo; And Moses hid his face, for he was afraid to look upon God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3007, 'And the Lord said: &ldquo;I have surely seen the oppression of My people who are in Egypt, and have heard their cry because of their taskmasters, for I know their sorrows.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3008, '&ldquo;So I have come down to deliver them out of the hand of the Egyptians, and to bring them up from that land to a good and large land, to a land flowing with milk and honey|, to the place of the Canaanites and the Hittites and the Amorites and the Perizzites');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3009, '&ldquo;Now therefore, behold, the cry of the children of Israel has come to Me, and I have also seen the oppression with which the Egyptians oppress them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3010, '&ldquo;Come now, therefore, and I will send you to Pharaoh that you may bring My people, the children of Israel, out of Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3011, 'But Moses said to God, &ldquo;Who am I that I should go to Pharaoh, and that I should bring the children of Israel out of Egypt?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3012, 'So He said, &ldquo;I will certainly be with you. And this shall be a sign to you that I have sent you: When you have brought the people out of Egypt, you shall serve God on this mountain.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3013, 'Then Moses said to God, &ldquo;Indeed, when I come to the children of Israel and say to them, &lsquo;The God of your fathers has sent me to you,&rsquo; and they say to me, &lsquo;What is His name?&rsquo; what shall I say to them?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3014, 'And God said to Moses, &ldquo;I AM WHO I AM.&rdquo; And He said, &ldquo;Thus you shall say to the children of Israel, &lsquo;I AM has sent me to you.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3015, 'Moreover God said to Moses, &ldquo;Thus you shall say to the children of Israel: &lsquo;The Lord God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has sent me to you. This is My name forever, and this is My memorial to all generations.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3016, '&ldquo;Go and gather the elders of Israel together, and say to them, &lsquo;The Lord God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, of Isaac, and of Jacob, appeared to me, saying, &ldquo;I have surely visited you and seen what is done to you in Egypt;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3017, '&ldquo;and I have said I will bring you up out of the affliction of Egypt to the land of the Canaanites and the Hittites and the Amorites and the Perizzites and the Hivites and the Jebusites, to a land flowing with milk and honey.&rdquo;&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3018, '&ldquo;Then they will heed your voice; and you shall come, you and the elders of Israel, to the king of Egypt; and you shall say to him, &lsquo;The Lord God of the Hebrews has met with us; and now, please, let us go three days&rsquo; journey into the wilderness, that we ma');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3019, '&ldquo;But I am sure that the king of Egypt will not let you go, no, not even by a mighty hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3020, '&ldquo;So I will stretch out My hand and strike Egypt with all My wonders which I will do in its midst; and after that he will let you go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3021, '&ldquo;And I will give this people favor in the sight of the Egyptians; and it shall be, when you go, that you shall not go empty-handed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 3022, '&ldquo;But every woman shall ask of her neighbor, namely, of her who dwells near her house, articles of silver, articles of gold, and clothing; and you shall put them on your sons and on your daughters. So you shall plunder the Egyptians.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4001, 'Then Moses answered and said, &ldquo;But suppose they will not believe me or listen to my voice; suppose they say, &lsquo;The Lord has not appeared to you.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4002, 'So the Lord said to him, &ldquo;What is that in your hand?&rdquo; He said, &ldquo;A rod.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4003, 'And He said, &ldquo;Cast it on the ground.&rdquo; So he cast it on the ground, and it became a serpent; and Moses fled from it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4004, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Reach out your hand and take it by the tail&rdquo; (and he reached out his hand and caught it, and it became a rod in his hand),');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4005, '&ldquo;that they may believe that the Lord God of their fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has appeared to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4006, 'Furthermore the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Now put your hand in your bosom.&rdquo; And he put his hand in his bosom, and when he took it out, behold, his hand was leprous, like snow.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4007, 'And He said, &ldquo;Put your hand in your bosom again.&rdquo; So he put his hand in his bosom again, and drew it out of his bosom, and behold, it was restored like his other flesh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4008, '&ldquo;Then it will be, if they do not believe you, nor heed the message of the first sign, that they may believe the message of the latter sign.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4009, '&ldquo;And it shall be, if they do not believe even these two signs, or listen to your voice, that you shall take water from the river and pour it on the dry land. The water which you take from the river will become blood on the dry land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4010, 'Then Moses said to the Lord, &ldquo;O my Lord, I am not eloquent, neither before nor since You have spoken to Your servant; but I am slow of speech and slow of tongue.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4011, 'So the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Who has made man&rsquo;s mouth? Or who makes the mute, the deaf, the seeing, or the blind? Have not I, the Lord?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4012, '&ldquo;Now therefore, go, and I will be with your mouth and teach you what you shall say.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4013, 'But he said, &ldquo;O my Lord, please send by the hand of whomever else You may send.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4014, 'So the anger of the Lord was kindled against Moses, and He said: &ldquo;Is not Aaron the Levite your brother? I know that he can speak well. And look, he is also coming out to meet you. When he sees you, he will be glad in his heart.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4015, '&ldquo;Now you shall speak to him and put the words in his mouth. And I will be with your mouth and with his mouth, and I will teach you what you shall do.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4016, '&ldquo;So he shall be your spokesman to the people. And he himself shall be as a mouth for you, and you shall be to him as God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4017, '&ldquo;And you shall take this rod in your hand, with which you shall do the signs.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4018, 'So Moses went and returned to Jethro his father-in-law, and said to him, &ldquo;Please let me go and return to my brethren who are in Egypt, and see whether they are still alive.&rdquo; And Jethro said to Moses, &ldquo;Go in peace.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4019, 'Now the Lord said to Moses in Midian, &ldquo;Go, return to Egypt; for all the men who sought your life are dead.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4020, 'Then Moses took his wife and his sons and set them on a donkey, and he returned to the land of Egypt. And Moses took the rod of God in his hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4021, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;When you go back to Egypt, see that you do all those wonders before Pharaoh which I have put in your hand. But I will harden his heart, so that he will not let the people go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4022, '&ldquo;Then you shall say to Pharaoh, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: &ldquo;Israel is My son, My firstborn.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4023, '&ldquo;So I say to you, let My son go that he may serve Me. But if you refuse to let him go, indeed I will kill your son, your firstborn.&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4024, 'And it came to pass on the way, at the encampment, that the Lord met him and sought to kill him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4025, 'Then Zipporah took a sharp stone and cut off the foreskin of her son and cast it at Moses&rsquo; feet, and said, &ldquo;Surely you are a husband of blood to me!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4026, 'So He let him go. Then she said, &ldquo;You are a husband of blood!&rdquo; &ndash; because of the circumcision.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4027, 'And the Lord said to Aaron, &ldquo;Go into the wilderness to meet Moses.&rdquo; So he went and met him on the mountain of God, and kissed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4028, 'So Moses told Aaron all the words of the Lord who had sent him, and all the signs which He had commanded him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4029, 'Then Moses and Aaron went and gathered together all the elders of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4030, 'And Aaron spoke all the words which the Lord had spoken to Moses. Then he did the signs in the sight of the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 4031, 'So the people believed; and when they heard that the Lord had visited the children of Israel and that He had looked on their affliction, then they bowed their heads and worshiped.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5001, 'Afterward Moses and Aaron went in and told Pharaoh, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;Let My people go, that they may hold a feast to Me in the wilderness.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5002, 'And Pharaoh said, &ldquo;Who is the Lord, that I should obey His voice to let Israel go? I do not know the Lord, nor will I let Israel go.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5003, 'So they said, &ldquo;The God of the Hebrews has met with us. Please, let us go three days&rsquo; journey into the desert and sacrifice to the Lord our God, lest He fall upon us with pestilence or with the sword.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5004, 'Then the king of Egypt said to them, &ldquo;Moses and Aaron, why do you take the people from their work? Get back to your labor.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5005, 'And Pharaoh said, &ldquo;Look, the people of the land are many now, and you make them rest from their labor!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5006, 'So the same day Pharaoh commanded the taskmasters of the people and their officers, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5007, '&ldquo;You shall no longer give the people straw to make brick as before. Let them go and gather straw for themselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5008, '&ldquo;And you shall lay on them the quota of bricks which they made before. You shall not reduce it. For they are idle; therefore they cry out, saying, &lsquo;Let us go and sacrifice to our God.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5009, '&ldquo;Let more work be laid on the men, that they may labor in it, and let them not regard false words.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5010, 'And the taskmasters of the people and their officers went out and spoke to the people, saying, &ldquo;Thus says Pharaoh: &lsquo;I will not give you straw.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5011, '&lsquo;Go, get yourselves straw where you can find it; yet none of your work will be reduced.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5012, 'So the people were scattered abroad throughout all the land of Egypt to gather stubble instead of straw.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5013, 'And the taskmasters forced them to hurry, saying, &ldquo;Fulfill your work, your daily quota, as when there was straw.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5014, 'Also the officers of the children of Israel, whom Pharaoh&rsquo;s taskmasters had set over them, were beaten and were asked, &ldquo;Why have you not fulfilled your task in making brick both yesterday and today, as before?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5015, 'Then the officers of the children of Israel came and cried out to Pharaoh, saying, &ldquo;Why are you dealing thus with your servants?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5016, '&ldquo;There is no straw given to your servants, and they say to us, &lsquo;Make brick!&rsquo; And indeed your servants are beaten, but the fault is in your own people.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5017, 'But he said, &ldquo;You are idle! Idle! Therefore you say, &lsquo;Let us go and sacrifice to the Lord.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5018, '&ldquo;Therefore go now and work; for no straw shall be given you, yet you shall deliver the quota of bricks.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5019, 'And the officers of the children of Israel saw that they were in trouble after it was said, &ldquo;You shall not reduce any bricks from your daily quota.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5020, 'Then, as they came out from Pharaoh, they met Moses and Aaron who stood there to meet them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5021, 'And they said to them, &ldquo;Let the Lord look on you and judge, because you have made us abhorrent in the sight of Pharaoh and in the sight of his servants, to put a sword in their hand to kill us.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5022, 'So Moses returned to the Lord and said, &ldquo;Lord, why have You brought trouble on this people? Why is it You have sent me?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 5023, '&ldquo;For since I came to Pharaoh to speak in Your name, he has done evil to this people; neither have You delivered Your people at all.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6001, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Now you shall see what I will do to Pharaoh. For with a strong hand he will let them go, and with a strong hand he will drive them out of his land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6002, 'And God spoke to Moses and said to him: &ldquo;I am the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6003, '&ldquo;I appeared to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, as God Almighty, but by My name Lord I was not known to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6004, '&ldquo;I have also established My covenant with them, to give them the land of Canaan, the land of their pilgrimage, in which they were strangers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6005, '&ldquo;And I have also heard the groaning of the children of Israel whom the Egyptians keep in bondage, and I have remembered My covenant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6006, '&ldquo;Therefore say to the children of Israel: &lsquo;I am the Lord; I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, I will rescue you from their bondage, and I will redeem you with an outstretched arm and with great judgments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6007, '&lsquo;I will take you as My people, and I will be your God. Then you shall know that I am the Lord your God who brings you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6008, '&lsquo;And I will bring you into the land which I swore to give to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob; and I will give it to you as a heritage: I am the Lord.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6009, 'So Moses spoke thus to the children of Israel; but they did not heed Moses, because of anguish of spirit and cruel bondage.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6010, 'And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6011, '&ldquo;Go in, tell Pharaoh king of Egypt to let the children of Israel go out of his land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6012, 'And Moses spoke before the Lord, saying, &ldquo;The children of Israel have not heeded me. How then shall Pharaoh heed me, for I am of uncircumcised lips?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6013, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses and Aaron, and gave them a command for the children of Israel and for Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6014, 'These are the heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses: The sons of Reuben, the firstborn of Israel, were Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. These are the families of Reuben.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6015, 'And the sons of Simeon were Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul the son of a Canaanite woman. These are the families of Simeon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6016, 'These are the names of the sons of Levi according to their generations: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. And the years of the life of Levi were one hundred and thirty-seven.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6017, 'The sons of Gershon were Libni and Shimi according to their families.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6018, 'And the sons of Kohath were Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. And the years of the life of Kohath were one hundred and thirty-three.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6019, 'The sons of Merari were Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of Levi according to their generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6020, 'Now Amram took for himself Jochebed, his father&rsquo;s sister, as wife; and she bore him Aaron and Moses. And the years of the life of Amram were one hundred and thirty-seven.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6021, 'The sons of Izhar were Korah, Nepheg, and Zichri.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6022, 'And the sons of Uzziel were Mishael, Elzaphan, and Zithri.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6023, 'Aaron took to himself Elisheba, daughter of Amminadab, sister of Nahshon, as wife; and she bore him Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6024, 'And the sons of Korah were Assir, Elkanah, and Abiasaph. These are the families of the Korahites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6025, 'Eleazar, Aaron&rsquo;s son, took for himself one of the daughters of Putiel as wife; and she bore him Phinehas. These are the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the Levites according to their families.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6026, 'These are the same Aaron and Moses to whom the Lord said, &ldquo;Bring out the children of Israel from the land of Egypt according to their armies.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6027, 'These are the ones who spoke to Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring out the children of Israel from Egypt. These are the same Moses and Aaron.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6028, 'And it came to pass, on the day the Lord spoke to Moses in the land of Egypt,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6029, 'that the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, &ldquo;I am the Lord. Speak to Pharaoh king of Egypt all that I say to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 6030, 'But Moses said before the Lord, &ldquo;Behold, I am of uncircumcised lips, and how shall Pharaoh heed me?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7001, 'So the Lord said to Moses: &ldquo;See, I have made you as God to Pharaoh, and Aaron your brother shall be your prophet.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7002, '&ldquo;You shall speak all that I command you. And Aaron your brother shall tell Pharaoh to send the children of Israel out of his land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7003, '&ldquo;And I will harden Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart, and multiply My signs and My wonders in the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7004, '&ldquo;But Pharaoh will not heed you, so that I may lay My hand on Egypt and bring My armies and My people, the children of Israel, out of the land of Egypt by great judgments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7005, '&ldquo;And the Egyptians shall know that I am the Lord, when I stretch out My hand on Egypt and bring out the children of Israel from among them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7006, 'Then Moses and Aaron did so; just as the Lord commanded them, so they did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7007, 'And Moses was eighty years old and Aaron eighty-three years old when they spoke to Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7008, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7009, '&ldquo;When Pharaoh speaks to you, saying, &lsquo;Show a miracle for yourselves,&rsquo; then you shall say to Aaron, &lsquo;Take your rod and cast it before Pharaoh, and let it become a serpent.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7010, 'So Moses and Aaron went in to Pharaoh, and they did so, just as the Lord commanded. And Aaron cast down his rod before Pharaoh and before his servants, and it became a serpent.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7011, 'But Pharaoh also called the wise men and the sorcerers; so the magicians of Egypt, they also did in like manner with their enchantments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7012, 'For every man threw down his rod, and they became serpents. But Aaron&rsquo;s rod swallowed up their rods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7013, 'And Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart grew hard, and he did not heed them, as the Lord had said.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7014, 'So the Lord said to Moses: &ldquo;Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart is hard; he refuses to let the people go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7015, '&ldquo;Go to Pharaoh in the morning, when he goes out to the water, and you shall stand by the river&rsquo;s bank to meet him; and the rod which was turned to a serpent you shall take in your hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7016, '&ldquo;And you shall say to him, &lsquo;The Lord God of the Hebrews has sent me to you, saying, &ldquo;Let My people go, that they may serve Me in the wilderness&rdquo;; but indeed, until now you would not hear!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7017, '&lsquo;Thus says the Lord: &ldquo;By this you shall know that I am the Lord. Behold, I will strike the waters which are in the river with the rod that is in my hand, and they shall be turned to blood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7018, '&ldquo;And the fish that are in the river shall die, the river shall stink, and the Egyptians will loathe to drink the water of the river.&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7019, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, &ldquo;Say to Aaron, &lsquo;Take your rod and stretch out your hand over the waters of Egypt, over their streams, over their rivers, over their ponds, and over all their pools of water, that they may become blood. And there shall be bloo');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7020, 'And Moses and Aaron did so, just as the Lord commanded. So he lifted up the rod and struck the waters that were in the river, in the sight of Pharaoh and in the sight of his servants. And all the waters that were in the river were turned to blood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7021, 'The fish that were in the river died, the river stank, and the Egyptians could not drink the water of the river. So there was blood throughout all the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7022, 'Then the magicians of Egypt did so with their enchantments; and Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart grew hard, and he did not heed them, as the Lord had said.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7023, 'And Pharaoh turned and went into his house. Neither was his heart moved by this.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7024, 'So all the Egyptians dug all around the river for water to drink, because they could not drink the water of the river.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 7025, 'And seven days passed after the Lord had struck the river.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8001, 'And the Lord spoke to Moses, &ldquo;Go to Pharaoh and say to him, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: &ldquo;Let My people go, that they may serve Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8002, '&ldquo;But if you refuse to let them go, behold, I will smite all your territory with frogs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8003, '&ldquo;So the river shall bring forth frogs abundantly, which shall go up and come into your house, into your bedroom, on your bed, into the houses of your servants, on your people, into your ovens, and into your kneading bowls.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8004, '&ldquo;And the frogs shall come up on you, on your people, and on all your servants.&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8005, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, &ldquo;Say to Aaron, &lsquo;Stretch out your hand with your rod over the streams, over the rivers, and over the ponds, and cause frogs to come up on the land of Egypt.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8006, 'So Aaron stretched out his hand over the waters of Egypt, and the frogs came up and covered the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8007, 'And the magicians did so with their enchantments, and brought up frogs on the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8008, 'Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron, and said, &ldquo;Entreat the Lord that He may take away the frogs from me and from my people; and I will let the people go, that they may sacrifice to the Lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8009, 'And Moses said to Pharaoh, &ldquo;Accept the honor of saying when I shall intercede for you, for your servants, and for your people, to destroy the frogs from you and your houses, that they may remain in the river only.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8010, 'So he said, &ldquo;Tomorrow.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Let it be according to your word, that you may know that there is no one like the Lord our God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8011, '&ldquo;And the frogs shall depart from you, from your houses, from your servants, and from your people. They shall remain in the river only.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8012, 'Then Moses and Aaron went out from Pharaoh. And Moses cried out to the Lord concerning the frogs which He had brought against Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8013, 'So the Lord did according to the word of Moses. And the frogs died out of the houses, out of the courtyards, and out of the fields.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8014, 'They gathered them together in heaps, and the land stank.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8015, 'But when Pharaoh saw that there was relief, he hardened his heart and did not heed them, as the Lord had said.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8016, 'So the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Say to Aaron, &lsquo;Stretch out your rod, and strike the dust of the land, so that it may become lice throughout all the land of Egypt.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8017, 'And they did so. For Aaron stretched out his hand with his rod and struck the dust of the earth, and it became lice on man and beast. All the dust of the land became lice throughout all the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8018, 'Now the magicians so worked with their enchantments to bring forth lice, but they could not. So there were lice on man and beast.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8019, 'Then the magicians said to Pharaoh, &ldquo;This is the finger of God.&rdquo; But Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart grew hard, and he did not heed them, just as the Lord had said.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8020, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Rise early in the morning and stand before Pharaoh as he comes out to the water. Then say to him, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: &ldquo;Let My people go, that they may serve Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8021, '&ldquo;Or else, if you will not let My people go, behold, I will send swarms of flies on you and your servants, on your people and into your houses. The houses of the Egyptians shall be full of swarms of flies, and also the ground on which they stand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8022, '&ldquo;And in that day I will set apart the land of Goshen, in which My people dwell, that no swarms of flies shall be there, in order that you may know that I am the Lord in the midst of the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8023, '&ldquo;I will make a difference between My people and your people. Tomorrow this sign shall be.&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8024, 'And the Lord did so. Thick swarms of flies came into the house of Pharaoh, into his servants&rsquo; houses, and into all the land of Egypt. The land was corrupted because of the swarms of flies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8025, 'Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron, and said, &ldquo;Go, sacrifice to your God in the land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8026, 'And Moses said, &ldquo;It is not right to do so, for we would be sacrificing the abomination of the Egyptians to the Lord our God. If we sacrifice the abomination of the Egyptians before their eyes, then will they not stone us?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8027, '&ldquo;We will go three days&rsquo; journey into the wilderness and sacrifice to the Lord our God as He will command us.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8028, 'So Pharaoh said, &ldquo;I will let you go, that you may sacrifice to the Lord your God in the wilderness; only you shall not go very far away. Intercede for me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8029, 'Then Moses said, &ldquo;Indeed I am going out from you, and I will entreat the Lord, that the swarms of flies may depart tomorrow from Pharaoh, from his servants, and from his people. But let Pharaoh not deal deceitfully anymore in not letting the people go to ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8030, 'So Moses went out from Pharaoh and entreated the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8031, 'And the Lord did according to the word of Moses; He removed the swarms of flies from Pharaoh, from his servants, and from his people. Not one remained.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 8032, 'But Pharaoh hardened his heart at this time also; neither would he let the people go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9001, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Go in to Pharaoh and tell him, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord God of the Hebrews: &ldquo;Let My people go, that they may serve Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9002, '&ldquo;For if you refuse to let them go, and still hold them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9003, '&ldquo;behold, the hand of the Lord will be on your cattle in the field, on the horses, on the donkeys, on the camels, on the oxen, and on the sheep &ndash; a very severe pestilence.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9004, '&ldquo;And the Lord will make a difference between the livestock of Israel and the livestock of Egypt. So nothing shall die of all that belongs to the children of Israel.&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9005, 'Then the Lord appointed a set time, saying, &ldquo;Tomorrow the Lord will do this thing in the land.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9006, 'So the Lord did this thing on the next day, and all the livestock of Egypt died; but of the livestock of the children of Israel, not one died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9007, 'Then Pharaoh sent, and indeed, not even one of the livestock of the Israelites was dead. But the heart of Pharaoh became hard, and he did not let the people go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9008, 'So the Lord said to Moses and Aaron, &ldquo;Take for yourselves handfuls of ashes from a furnace, and let Moses scatter it toward the heavens in the sight of Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9009, '&ldquo;And it will become fine dust in all the land of Egypt, and it will cause boils that break out in sores on man and beast throughout all the land of Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9010, 'Then they took ashes from the furnace and stood before Pharaoh, and Moses scattered them toward heaven. And they caused boils that break out in sores on man and beast.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9011, 'And the magicians could not stand before Moses because of the boils, for the boils were on the magicians and on all the Egyptians.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9012, 'But the Lord hardened the heart of Pharaoh; and he did not heed them, just as the Lord had spoken to Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9013, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Rise early in the morning and stand before Pharaoh, and say to him, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord God of the Hebrews: &ldquo;Let My people go, that they may serve Me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9014, '&ldquo;for at this time I will send all My plagues to your very heart, and on your servants and on your people, that you may know that there is none like Me in all the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9015, '&ldquo;Now if I had stretched out My hand and struck you and your people with pestilence, then you would have been cut off from the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9016, '&ldquo;But indeed for this purpose I have raised you up, that I may show My power in you, and that My name may be declared in all the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9017, '&ldquo;As yet you exalt yourself against My people in that you will not let them go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9018, '&ldquo;Behold, tomorrow about this time I will cause very heavy hail to rain down, such as has not been in Egypt since its founding until now.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9019, '&ldquo;Therefore send now and gather your livestock and all that you have in the field, for the hail shall come down on every man and every animal which is found in the field and is not brought home; and they shall die.&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9020, 'He who feared the word of the Lord among the servants of Pharaoh made his servants and his livestock flee to the houses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9021, 'But he who did not regard the word of the Lord left his servants and his livestock in the field.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9022, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Stretch out your hand toward heaven, that there may be hail in all the land of Egypt &ndash; on man, on beast, and on every herb of the field, throughout the land of Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9023, 'And Moses stretched out his rod toward heaven; and the Lord sent thunder and hail, and fire darted to the ground. And the Lord rained hail on the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9024, 'So there was hail, and fire mingled with the hail, so very heavy that there was none like it in all the land of Egypt since it became a nation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9025, 'And the hail struck throughout the whole land of Egypt, all that was in the field, both man and beast; and the hail struck every herb of the field and broke every tree of the field.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9026, 'Only in the land of Goshen, where the children of Israel were, there was no hail.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9027, 'And Pharaoh sent and called for Moses and Aaron, and said to them, &ldquo;I have sinned this time. The Lord is righteous, and my people and I are wicked.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9028, '&ldquo;Entreat the Lord, that there may be no more mighty thundering and hail, for it is enough. I will let you go, and you shall stay no longer.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9029, 'So Moses said to him, &ldquo;As soon as I have gone out of the city, I will spread out my hands to the Lord; the thunder will cease, and there will be no more hail, that you may know that the earth is the Lord&rsquo;s.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9030, '&ldquo;But as for you and your servants, I know that you will not yet fear the Lord God.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9031, 'Now the flax and the barley were struck, for the barley was in the head and the flax was in bud.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9032, 'But the wheat and the spelt were not struck, for they are late crops.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9033, 'So Moses went out of the city from Pharaoh and spread out his hands to the Lord; then the thunder and the hail ceased, and the rain was not poured on the earth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9034, 'And when Pharaoh saw that the rain, the hail, and the thunder had ceased, he sinned yet more; and he hardened his heart, he and his servants.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 9035, 'So the heart of Pharaoh was hard; neither would he let the children of Israel go, as the Lord had spoken by Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10001, 'Now the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Go in to Pharaoh; for I have hardened his heart and the hearts of his servants, that I may show these signs of Mine before him,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10002, '&ldquo;and that you may tell in the hearing of your son and your son&rsquo;s son the mighty things I have done in Egypt, and My signs which I have done among them, that you may know that I am the Lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10003, 'So Moses and Aaron came in to Pharaoh and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of the Hebrews: &lsquo;How long will you refuse to humble yourself before Me? Let My people go, that they may serve Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10004, '&lsquo;Or else, if you refuse to let My people go, behold, tomorrow I will bring locusts into your territory.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10005, '&lsquo;And they shall cover the face of the earth, so that no one will be able to see the earth; and they shall eat the residue of what is left, which remains to you from the hail, and they shall eat every tree which grows up for you out of the field.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10006, '&lsquo;They shall fill your houses, the houses of all your servants, and the houses of all the Egyptians &ndash; which neither your fathers nor your fathers&rsquo; fathers have seen, since the day that they were on the earth to this day.&rsquo;&rdquo; And he turned and went out from Ph');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10007, 'Then Pharaoh&rsquo;s servants said to him, &ldquo;How long shall this man be a snare to us? Let the men go, that they may serve the Lord their God. Do you not yet know that Egypt is destroyed?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10008, 'So Moses and Aaron were brought again to Pharaoh, and he said to them, &ldquo;Go, serve the Lord your God. Who are the ones that are going?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10009, 'And Moses said, &ldquo;We will go with our young and our old; with our sons and our daughters, with our flocks and our herds we will go, for we must hold a feast to the Lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10010, 'Then he said to them, &ldquo;The Lord had better be with you when I let you and your little ones go! Beware, for evil is ahead of you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10011, '&ldquo;Not so! Go now, you who are men, and serve the Lord, for that is what you desired.&rdquo; And they were driven out from Pharaoh&rsquo;s presence.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10012, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Stretch out your hand over the land of Egypt for the locusts, that they may come upon the land of Egypt, and eat every herb of the land &ndash; all that the hail has left.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10013, 'So Moses stretched out his rod over the land of Egypt, and the Lord brought an east wind on the land all that day and all that night. When it was morning, the east wind brought the locusts.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10014, 'And the locusts went up over all the land of Egypt and rested on all the territory of Egypt. They were very severe; previously there had been no such locusts as they, nor shall there be such after them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10015, 'For they covered the face of the whole earth, so that the land was darkened; and they ate every herb of the land and all the fruit of the trees which the hail had left. So there remained nothing green on the trees or on the plants of the field throughout ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10016, 'Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron in haste, and said, &ldquo;I have sinned against the Lord your God and against you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10017, '&ldquo;Now therefore, please forgive my sin only this once, and entreat the Lord your God, that He may take away from me this death only.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10018, 'So he went out from Pharaoh and entreated the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10019, 'And the Lord turned a very strong west wind, which took the locusts away and blew them into the Red Sea. There remained not one locust in all the territory of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10020, 'But the Lord hardened Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart, and he did not let the children of Israel go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10021, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Stretch out your hand toward heaven, that there may be darkness over the land of Egypt, darkness which may even be felt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10022, 'So Moses stretched out his hand toward heaven, and there was thick darkness in all the land of Egypt three days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10023, 'They did not see one another; nor did anyone rise from his place for three days. But all the children of Israel had light in their dwellings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10024, 'Then Pharaoh called to Moses and said, &ldquo;Go, serve the Lord; only let your flocks and your herds be kept back. Let your little ones also go with you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10025, 'But Moses said, &ldquo;You must also give us sacrifices and burnt offerings, that we may sacrifice to the Lord our God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10026, '&ldquo;Our livestock also shall go with us; not a hoof shall be left behind. For we must take some of them to serve the Lord our God, and even we do not know with what we must serve the Lord until we arrive there.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10027, 'But the Lord hardened Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart, and he would not let them go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10028, 'Then Pharaoh said to him, &ldquo;Get away from me! Take heed to yourself and see my face no more! For in the day you see my face you shall die!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 10029, 'So Moses said, &ldquo;You have spoken well. I will never see your face again.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11001, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;I will bring one more plague on Pharaoh and on Egypt. Afterward he will let you go from here. When he lets you go, he will surely drive you out of here altogether.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11002, '&ldquo;Speak now in the hearing of the people, and let every man ask from his neighbor and every woman from her neighbor, articles of silver and articles of gold.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11003, 'And the Lord gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians. Moreover the man Moses was very great in the land of Egypt, in the sight of Pharaoh&rsquo;s servants and in the sight of the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11004, 'Then Moses said, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;About midnight I will go out into the midst of Egypt;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11005, '&lsquo;and all the firstborn in the land of Egypt shall die, from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sits on his throne, even to the firstborn of the female servant who is behind the handmill, and all the firstborn of the animals.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11006, '&lsquo;Then there shall be a great cry throughout all the land of Egypt, such as was not like it before, nor shall be like it again.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11007, '&lsquo;But against none of the children of Israel shall a dog move its tongue, against man or beast, that you may know that the Lord does make a difference between the Egyptians and Israel.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11008, '&ldquo;And all these your servants shall come down to me and bow down to me, saying, &lsquo;Get out, and all the people who follow you!&rsquo; After that I will go out.&rdquo; Then he went out from Pharaoh in great anger.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11009, 'But the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Pharaoh will not heed you, so that My wonders may be multiplied in the land of Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 11010, 'So Moses and Aaron did all these wonders before Pharaoh; and the Lord hardened Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart, and he did not let the children of Israel go out of his land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12001, 'Now the* Lord spoke to Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12002, '&ldquo;This month shall be your beginning of months; it shall be the first month of the year to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12003, '&ldquo;Speak to all the congregation of Israel, saying: &lsquo;On the tenth of this month every man shall take for himself a lamb, according to the house of his father, a lamb for a household.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12004, '&lsquo;And if the household is too small for the lamb, let him and his neighbor next to his house take it according to the number of the persons; according to each man&rsquo;s need you shall make your count for the lamb.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12005, '&lsquo;Your lamb shall be without blemish, a male of the first year. You may take it from the sheep or from the goats.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12006, '&lsquo;Now you shall keep it until the fourteenth day of the same month. Then the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel shall kill it at twilight.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12007, '&lsquo;And they shall take some of the blood and put it on the two doorposts and on the lintel of the houses where they eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12008, '&lsquo;Then they shall eat the flesh on that night; roasted in fire, with unleavened bread and with bitter herbs they shall eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12009, '&lsquo;Do not eat it raw, nor boiled at all with water, but roasted in fire &ndash; its head with its legs and its entrails.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12010, '&lsquo;You shall let none of it remain until morning, and what remains of it until morning you shall burn with fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12011, '&lsquo;And thus you shall eat it: with a belt on your waist, your sandals on your feet, and your staff in your hand. So you shall eat it in haste. It is the Lord&rsquo;s Passover.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12012, '&lsquo;For I will pass through the land of Egypt on that night, and will strike all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both man and beast; and against all the gods of Egypt I will execute judgment: I am the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12013, '&lsquo;Now the blood shall be a sign for you on the houses where you are. And when I see the blood, I will pass over you; and the plague shall not be on you to destroy you when I strike the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12014, '&lsquo;So this day shall be to you a memorial; and you shall keep it as a feast to the Lord throughout your generations. You shall keep it as a feast by an everlasting ordinance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12015, '&lsquo;Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread. On the first day you shall remove leaven from your houses. For whoever eats leavened bread from the first day until the seventh day, that person shall be cut off from Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12016, '&lsquo;On the first day there shall be a holy convocation, and on the seventh day there shall be a holy convocation for you. No manner of work shall be done on them; but that which everyone must eat &ndash; that only may be prepared by you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12017, '&lsquo;So you shall observe the Feast of Unleavened Bread, for on this same day I will have brought your armies out of the land of Egypt. Therefore you shall observe this day throughout your generations as an everlasting ordinance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12018, '&lsquo;In the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month at evening, you shall eat unleavened bread, until the twenty-first day of the month at evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12019, '&lsquo;For seven days no leaven shall be found in your houses, since whoever eats what is leavened, that same person shall be cut off from the congregation of Israel, whether he is a stranger or a native of the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12020, '&lsquo;You shall eat nothing leavened; in all your dwellings you shall eat unleavened bread.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12021, 'Then Moses called for all the elders of Israel and said to them, &ldquo;Pick out and take lambs for yourselves according to your families, and kill the Passover lamb.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12022, '&ldquo;And you shall take a bunch of hyssop, dip it in the blood that is in the basin, and strike the lintel and the two doorposts with the blood that is in the basin. And none of you shall go out of the door of his house until morning.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12023, '&ldquo;For the Lord will pass through to strike the Egyptians; and when He sees the blood on the lintel and on the two doorposts, the Lord will pass over the door and not allow the destroyer to come into your houses to strike you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12024, '&ldquo;And you shall observe this thing as an ordinance for you and your sons forever.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12025, '&ldquo;It will come to pass when you come to the land which the Lord will give you, just as He promised, that you shall keep this service.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12026, '&ldquo;And it shall be, when your children say to you, &lsquo;What do you mean by this service?&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12027, '&ldquo;that you shall say, &lsquo;It is the Passover sacrifice of the Lord, who passed over the houses of the children of Israel in Egypt when He struck the Egyptians and delivered our households.&rsquo;&rdquo; So the people bowed their heads and worshiped.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12028, 'Then the children of Israel went away and did so; just as the Lord had commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12029, 'And it came to pass at midnight that the Lord struck all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sat on his throne to the firstborn of the captive who was in the dungeon, and all the firstborn of livestock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12030, 'So Pharaoh rose in the night, he, all his servants, and all the Egyptians; and there was a great cry in Egypt, for there was not a house where there was not one dead.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12031, 'Then he called for Moses and Aaron by night, and said, &ldquo;Rise, go out from among my people, both you and the children of Israel. And go, serve the Lord as you have said.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12032, '&ldquo;Also take your flocks and your herds, as you have said, and be gone; and bless me also.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12033, 'And the Egyptians urged the people, that they might send them out of the land in haste. For they said, &ldquo;We shall all be dead.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12034, 'So the people took their dough before it was leavened, having their kneading bowls bound up in their clothes on their shoulders.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12035, 'Now the children of Israel had done according to the word of Moses, and they had asked from the Egyptians articles of silver, articles of gold, and clothing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12036, 'And the Lord had given the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians, so that they granted them what they requested. Thus they plundered the Egyptians.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12037, 'Then the children of Israel journeyed from Rameses to Succoth, about six hundred thousand men on foot, besides children.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12038, 'A mixed multitude went up with them also, and flocks and herds &ndash; a great deal of livestock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12039, 'And they baked unleavened cakes of the dough which they had brought out of Egypt; for it was not leavened, because they were driven out of Egypt and could not wait, nor had they prepared provisions for themselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12040, 'Now the sojourn of the children of Israel who lived in Egypt was four hundred and thirty years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12041, 'And it came to pass at the end of the four hundred and thirty years &ndash; on that very same day &ndash; it came to pass that all the armies of the Lord went out from the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12042, 'It is a night of solemn observance to the Lord for bringing them out of the land of Egypt. This is that night of the Lord, a solemn observance for all the children of Israel throughout their generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12043, 'And the Lord said to Moses and Aaron, &ldquo;This is the ordinance of the Passover: No foreigner shall eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12044, '&ldquo;But every man&rsquo;s servant who is bought for money, when you have circumcised him, then he may eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12045, '&ldquo;A sojourner and a hired servant shall not eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12046, '&ldquo;In one house it shall be eaten; you shall not carry any of the flesh outside the house, nor shall you break one of its bones.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12047, '&ldquo;All the congregation of Israel shall keep it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12048, '&ldquo;And when a stranger dwells with you and wants to keep the Passover to the Lord, let all his males be circumcised, and then let him come near and keep it; and he shall be as a native of the land. For no uncircumcised person shall eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12049, '&ldquo;One law shall be for the native-born and for the stranger who dwells among you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12050, 'Thus all the children of Israel did; as the Lord commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 12051, 'And it came to pass, on that very same day, that the Lord brought the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt according to their armies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13001, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13002, '&ldquo;Consecrate to Me all the firstborn, whatever opens the womb among the children of Israel, both of man and beast; it is Mine.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13003, 'And Moses said to the people: &ldquo;Remember this day in which you went out of Egypt, out of the house of bondage; for by strength of hand the Lord brought you out of this place. No leavened bread shall be eaten.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13004, '&ldquo;On this day you are going out, in the month Abib.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13005, '&ldquo;And it shall be, when the Lord brings you into the land of the Canaanites and the Hittites and the Amorites and the Hivites and the Jebusites, which He swore to your fathers to give you, a land flowing with milk and honey, that you shall keep this servic');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13006, '&ldquo;Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day there shall be a feast to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13007, '&ldquo;Unleavened bread shall be eaten seven days. And no leavened bread shall be seen among you, nor shall leaven be seen among you in all your quarters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13008, '&ldquo;And you shall tell your son in that day, saying, &lsquo;This is done because of what the Lord did for me when I came up from Egypt.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13009, '&ldquo;It shall be as a sign to you on your hand and as a memorial between your eyes, that the Lord&rsquo;s law may be in your mouth; for with a strong hand the Lord has brought you out of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13010, '&ldquo;You shall therefore keep this ordinance in its season from year to year.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13011, '&ldquo;And it shall be, when the Lord brings you into the land of the Canaanites, as He swore to you and your fathers, and gives it to you,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13012, '&ldquo;that you shall set apart to the Lord all that open the womb, that is, every firstborn that comes from an animal which you have; the males shall be the Lord&rsquo;s.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13013, '&ldquo;But every firstborn of a donkey you shall redeem with a lamb; and if you will not redeem it, then you shall break its neck. And all the firstborn of man among your sons you shall redeem.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13014, '&ldquo;So it shall be, when your son asks you in time to come, saying, &lsquo;What is this?&rsquo; that you shall say to him, &lsquo;By strength of hand the Lord brought us out of Egypt, out of the house of bondage.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13015, '&lsquo;And it came to pass, when Pharaoh was stubborn about letting us go, that the Lord killed all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both the firstborn of man and the firstborn of beast. Therefore I sacrifice to the Lord all males that open the womb, but all');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13016, '&ldquo;It shall be as a sign on your hand and as frontlets between your eyes, for by strength of hand the Lord brought us out of Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13017, 'Then it came to pass, when Pharaoh had let the people go, that God did not lead them by way of the land of the Philistines, although that was near; for God said, &ldquo;Lest perhaps the people change their minds when they see war, and return to Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13018, 'So God led the people around by way of the wilderness of the Red Sea. And the children of Israel went up in orderly ranks out of the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13019, 'And Moses took the bones of Joseph with him, for he had placed the children of Israel under solemn oath, saying, &ldquo;God will surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones from here with you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13020, 'So they* took their journey from Succoth and camped in Etham at the edge of the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13021, 'And the Lord went before them by day in a pillar of cloud to lead the way, and by night in a pillar of fire to give them light, so as to go by day and night.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 13022, 'He did not take away the pillar of cloud by day or the pillar of fire by night from before the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14001, 'Now the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, that they turn and camp before Pi Hahiroth, between Migdol and the sea, opposite Baal Zephon; you shall camp before it by the sea.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14003, '&ldquo;For Pharaoh will say of the children of Israel, &lsquo;They are bewildered by the land; the wilderness has closed them in.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14004, '&ldquo;Then I will harden Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart, so that he will pursue them; and I will gain honor over Pharaoh and over all his army, that the Egyptians may know that I am the Lord.&rdquo; And they did so.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14005, 'Now it was told the king of Egypt that the people had fled, and the heart of Pharaoh and his servants was turned against the people; and they said, &ldquo;Why have we done this, that we have let Israel go from serving us?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14006, 'So he made ready his chariot and took his people with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14007, 'Also, he took six hundred choice chariots, and all the chariots of Egypt with captains over every one of them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14008, 'And the Lord hardened the heart of Pharaoh king of Egypt, and he pursued the children of Israel; and the children of Israel went out with boldness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14009, 'So the Egyptians pursued them, all the horses and chariots of Pharaoh, his horsemen and his army, and overtook them camping by the sea beside Pi Hahiroth, before Baal Zephon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14010, 'And when Pharaoh drew near, the children of Israel lifted their eyes, and behold, the Egyptians marched after them. So they were very afraid, and the children of Israel cried out to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14011, 'Then they said to Moses, &ldquo;Because there were no graves in Egypt, have you taken us away to die in the wilderness? Why have you so dealt with us, to bring us up out of Egypt?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14012, '&ldquo;Is this not the word that we told you in Egypt, saying, &lsquo;Let us alone that we may serve the Egyptians&rsquo;? For it would have been better for us to serve the Egyptians than that we should die in the wilderness.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14013, 'And Moses said to the people, &ldquo;Do not be afraid. Stand still, and see the salvation of the Lord, which He will accomplish for you today. For the Egyptians whom you see today, you shall see again no more forever.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14014, '&ldquo;The Lord will fight for you, and you shall hold your peace.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14015, 'And the* Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Why do you cry to Me? Tell the children of Israel to go forward.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14016, '&ldquo;But lift up your rod, and stretch out your hand over the sea and divide it. And the children of Israel shall go on dry ground through the midst of the sea.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14017, '&ldquo;And I indeed will harden the hearts of the Egyptians, and they shall follow them. So I will gain honor over Pharaoh and over all his army, his chariots, and his horsemen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14018, '&ldquo;Then the Egyptians shall know that I am the Lord, when I have gained honor for Myself over Pharaoh, his chariots, and his horsemen.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14019, 'And the Angel of God, who went before the camp of Israel, moved and went behind them; and the pillar of cloud went from before them and stood behind them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14020, 'So it came between the camp of the Egyptians and the camp of Israel. Thus it was a cloud and darkness to the one, and it gave light by night to the other, so that the one did not come near the other all that night.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14021, 'Then Moses stretched out his hand over the sea; and the Lord caused the sea to go back by a strong east wind all that night, and made the sea into dry land, and the waters were divided.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14022, 'So the children of Israel went into the midst of the sea on the dry ground, and the waters were a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14023, 'And the Egyptians pursued and went after them into the midst of the sea, all Pharaoh&rsquo;s horses, his chariots, and his horsemen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14024, 'Now it came to pass, in the morning watch, that the Lord looked down upon the army of the Egyptians through the pillar of fire and cloud, and He troubled the army of the Egyptians.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14025, 'And He took offa their chariot wheels, so that they drove them with difficulty; and the Egyptians said, &ldquo;Let us flee from the face of Israel, for the Lord fights for them against the Egyptians.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14026, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Stretch out your hand over the sea, that the waters may come back upon the Egyptians, on their chariots, and on their horsemen.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14027, 'And Moses stretched out his hand over the sea; and when the morning appeared, the sea returned to its full depth, while the Egyptians were fleeing into it. So the Lord overthrew the Egyptians in the midst of the sea.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14028, 'Then the waters returned and covered the chariots, the horsemen, and all the army of Pharaoh that came into the sea after them. Not so much as one of them remained.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14029, 'But the children of Israel had walked on dry land in the midst of the sea|, and the waters were a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14030, 'So the Lord saved Israel that day out of the hand of the Egyptians, and Israel saw the Egyptians dead on the seashore.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 14031, 'Thus Israel saw the great work which the Lord had done in Egypt; so the people feared the Lord, and believed the Lord and His servant Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15001, 'Then Moses and the children of Israel sang this song to the Lord, and spoke, saying: &ldquo;I will sing to the Lord, For He has triumphed gloriously! The horse and its rider He has thrown into the sea!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15002, 'The Lord is my strength and song, And He has become my salvation; He is my God, and I will praise Him; My father&rsquo;s God, and I will exalt Him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15003, 'The Lord is a man of war; The Lord is His name.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15004, 'Pharaoh&rsquo;s chariots and his army He has cast into the sea; His chosen captains also are drowned in the Red Sea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15005, 'The depths have covered them; They sank to the bottom like a stone.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15006, '&ldquo;Your right hand, O Lord, has become glorious in power; Your right hand, O Lord, has dashed the enemy in pieces.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15007, 'And in the greatness of Your excellence You have overthrown those who rose against You; You sent forth Your wrath; It consumed them like stubble.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15008, 'And with the blast of Your nostrils The waters were gathered together; The floods stood upright like a heap; The depths congealed in the heart of the sea.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15009, 'The enemy said, &lsquo;I will pursue, I will overtake, I will divide the spoil; My desire shall be satisfied on them. I will draw my sword, My hand shall destroy them.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15010, 'You blew with Your wind, The sea covered them; They sank like lead in the mighty waters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15011, '&ldquo;Who is like You, O Lord, among the gods? Who is like You, glorious in holiness, Fearful in praises, doing wonders? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15012, 'You stretched out Your right hand; The earth swallowed them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15013, 'You in Your mercy have led forth The people whom You have redeemed; You have guided them in Your strength To Your holy habitation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15014, '&ldquo;The people will hear and be afraid; Sorrow will take hold of the inhabitants of Philistia.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15015, 'Then the chiefs of Edom will be dismayed; The mighty men of Moab, Trembling will take hold of them; All the inhabitants of Canaan will melt away.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15016, 'Fear and dread will fall on them; By the greatness of Your arm They will be as still as a stone, Till Your people pass over, O Lord, Till the people pass over Whom You have purchased.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15017, 'You will bring them in and plant them In the mountain of Your inheritance, In the place, O Lord, which You have made For Your own dwelling, The sanctuary, O Lord, which Your hands have established.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15018, '&ldquo;The Lord shall reign forever and ever.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15019, 'For the horses of Pharaoh went with his chariots and his horsemen into the sea, and the Lord brought back the waters of the sea upon them. But the children of Israel went on dry land in the midst of the sea.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15020, 'Then Miriam the prophetess, the sister of Aaron, took the timbrel in her hand; and all the women went out after her with timbrels and with dances.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15021, 'And Miriam answered them: &ldquo;Sing to the Lord, For He has triumphed gloriously! The horse and its rider He has thrown into the sea!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15022, 'So *Moses brought Israel from the Red Sea; then they went out into the Wilderness of Shur. And they went three days in the wilderness and found no water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15023, 'Now when they came to Marah, they could not drink the waters of Marah, for they were bitter. Therefore the name of it was called Marah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15024, 'And the people complained against Moses, saying, &ldquo;What shall we drink?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15025, 'So he cried out to the Lord, and the Lord showed him a tree. When he cast it into the waters, the waters were made sweet. There He made a statute and an ordinance for them, and there He tested them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15026, 'and said, &ldquo;If you diligently heed the voice of the Lord your God and do what is right in His sight, give ear to His commandments and keep all His statutes, I will put none of the diseases on you which I have brought on the Egyptians. For I am the Lord who heals you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 15027, 'Then they came to Elim, where there were twelve wells of water and seventy palm trees; so they camped there by the waters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16001, 'And they journeyed from Elim, and all the congregation of the children of Israel came to the Wilderness of Sin, which is between Elim and Sinai|, on the fifteenth day of the second month after they departed from the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16002, 'Then the whole congregation of the children of Israel complained against Moses and Aaron in the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16003, 'And the children of Israel said to them, &ldquo;Oh, that we had died by the hand of the Lord in the land of Egypt, when we sat by the pots of meat and when we ate bread to the full! For you have brought us out into this wilderness to kill this whole assembly wi');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16004, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Behold, I will rain bread from heaven for you. And the people shall go out and gather a certain quota every day, that I may test them, whether they will walk in My law or not.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16005, '&ldquo;And it shall be on the sixth day that they shall prepare what they bring in, and it shall be twice as much as they gather daily.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16006, 'Then Moses and Aaron said to all the children of Israel, &ldquo;At evening you shall know that the Lord has brought you out of the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16007, '&ldquo;And in the morning you shall see the glory of the Lord; for He hears your complaints against the Lord. But what are we, that you complain against us?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16008, 'Also Moses said, &ldquo;This shall be seen when the Lord gives you meat to eat in the evening, and in the morning bread to the full; for the Lord hears your complaints which you make against Him. And what are we? Your complaints are not against us but against t');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16009, 'Then Moses spoke to Aaron, &ldquo;Say to all the congregation of the children of Israel, &lsquo;Come near before the Lord, for He has heard your complaints.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16010, 'Now it came to pass, as Aaron spoke to the whole congregation of the children of Israel, that they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, the glory of the Lord appeared in the cloud.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16011, 'And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16012, '&ldquo;I have heard the complaints of the children of Israel. Speak to them, saying, &lsquo;At twilight you shall eat meat, and in the morning you shall be filled with bread. And you shall know that I am the Lord your God.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16013, 'So it was that quails came up at evening and covered the camp, and in the morning the dew lay all around the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16014, 'And when the layer of dew lifted, there, on the surface of the wilderness, was a small round substance, as fine as frost on the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16015, 'So when the children of Israel saw it, they said to one another, &ldquo;What is it?&rdquo; For they did not know what it was. And Moses said to them, &ldquo;This is the bread which the Lord has given you to eat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16016, '&ldquo;This is the thing which the Lord has commanded: &lsquo;Let every man gather it according to each one&rsquo;s need, one omer for each person, according to the number of persons; let every man take for those who are in his tent.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16017, 'Then the children of Israel did so and gathered, some more, some less.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16018, 'So when they measured it by omers, he who gathered much had nothing left over, and he who gathered little had no lack. Every man had gathered according to each one&rsquo;s need.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16019, 'And Moses said, &ldquo;Let no one leave any of it till morning.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16020, 'Notwithstanding they did not heed Moses. But some of them left part of it until morning, and it bred worms and stank. And Moses was angry with them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16021, 'So they gathered it every morning, every man according to his need. And when the sun became hot, it melted.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16022, 'And so it was, on the sixth day, that they gathered twice as much bread, two omers for each one. And all the rulers of the congregation came and told Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16023, 'Then he said to them, &ldquo;This is what the Lord has said: &lsquo;Tomorrow is a Sabbath rest, a holy Sabbath to the Lord. Bake what you will bake today, and boil what you will boil; and lay up for yourselves all that remains, to be kept until morning.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16024, 'So they laid it up till morning, as Moses commanded; and it did not stink, nor were there any worms in it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16025, 'Then Moses said, &ldquo;Eat that today, for today is a Sabbath to the Lord; today you will not find it in the field.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16026, '&ldquo;Six days you shall gather it, but on the seventh day, the Sabbath, there will be none.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16027, 'Now it happened that some of the people went out on the seventh day to gather, but they found none.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16028, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;How long do you refuse to keep My commandments and My laws?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16029, '&ldquo;See! For the Lord has given you the Sabbath; therefore He gives you on the sixth day bread for two days. Let every man remain in his place; let no man go out of his place on the seventh day.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16030, 'So the people rested on the seventh day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16031, 'And the house of Israel called its name Manna. And it was like white coriander seed, and the taste of it was like wafers made with honey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16032, 'Then Moses said, &ldquo;This is the thing which the Lord has commanded: &lsquo;Fill an omer with it, to be kept for your generations, that they may see the bread with which I fed you in the wilderness, when I brought you out of the land of Egypt.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16033, 'And Moses said to Aaron, &ldquo;Take a pot and put an omer of manna in it, and lay it up before the Lord, to be kept for your generations.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16034, 'As the Lord commanded Moses, so Aaron laid it up before the Testimony, to be kept.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16035, 'And the children of Israel ate manna forty years, until they came to an inhabited land; they ate manna until they came to the border of the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 16036, 'Now an omer is one-tenth of an ephah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17001, 'Then all the congregation of the children of Israel set out on their journey from the Wilderness of Sin, according to the commandment of the Lord, and camped in Rephidim; but there was no water for the people to drink.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17002, 'Therefore the people contended with Moses, and said, &ldquo;Give us water, that we may drink.&rdquo; So Moses said to them, &ldquo;Why do you contend with me? Why do you tempt the Lord?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17003, 'And the people thirsted there for water, and the people complained against Moses, and said, &ldquo;Why is it you have brought us up out of Egypt, to kill us and our children and our livestock with thirst?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17004, 'So Moses cried out to the Lord, saying, &ldquo;What shall I do with this people? They are almost ready to stone me!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17005, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Go on before the people, and take with you some of the elders of Israel. Also take in your hand your rod with which you struck the river, and go.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17006, '&ldquo;Behold, I will stand before you there on the rock in Horeb; and you shall strike the rock, and water will come out of it, that the people may drink.&rdquo; And Moses did so in the sight of the elders of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17007, 'So he called the name of the place Massah and Meribah, because of the contention of the children of Israel, and because they tempted the Lord, saying, &ldquo;Is the Lord among us or not?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17008, 'Now Amalek came and fought with Israel in Rephidim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17009, 'And Moses said to Joshua, &ldquo;Choose us some men and go out, fight with Amalek. Tomorrow I will stand on the top of the hill with the rod of God in my hand.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17010, 'So Joshua did as Moses said to him, and fought with Amalek. And Moses, Aaron, and Hur went up to the top of the hill.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17011, 'And so it was, when Moses held up his hand, that Israel prevailed; and when he let down his hand, Amalek prevailed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17012, 'But Moses&rsquo; hands became heavy; so they took a stone and put it under him, and he sat on it. And Aaron and Hur supported his hands, one on one side, and the other on the other side; and his hands were steady until the going down of the sun.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17013, 'So Joshua defeated Amalek and his people with the edge of the sword.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17014, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Write this for a memorial in the book and recount it in the hearing of Joshua, that I will utterly blot out the remembrance of Amalek from under heaven.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17015, 'And Moses built an altar and called its name, The-Lord-Is-My-Banner;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 17016, 'for he said, &ldquo;Because the Lord has sworn: the Lord will have war with Amalek from generation to generation.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18001, 'And Jethro, the priest of Midian, Moses&rsquo; father-in-law, heard of all that God had done for Moses and for Israel His people &ndash; that the Lord had brought Israel out of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18002, 'Then Jethro, Moses&rsquo; father-in-law, took Zipporah, Moses&rsquo; wife, after he had sent her back,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18003, 'with her two sons, of whom the name of one was Gershom (for he said, &ldquo;I have been a stranger in a foreign land&rdquo;)');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18004, 'and the name of the other was Eliezer (for he said, &ldquo;The God of my father was my help, and delivered me from the sword of Pharaoh&rdquo;);');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18005, 'and Jethro, Moses&rsquo; father-in-law, came with his sons and his wife to Moses in the wilderness, where he was encamped at the mountain of God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18006, 'Now he had said to Moses, &ldquo;I, your father-in-law Jethro, am coming to you with your wife and her two sons with her.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18007, 'So Moses went out to meet his father-in-law, bowed down, and kissed him. And they asked each other about their well-being, and they went into the tent.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18008, 'And Moses told his father-in-law all that the Lord had done to Pharaoh and to the Egyptians for Israel&rsquo;s sake, all the hardship that had come upon them on the way, and how the Lord had delivered them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18009, 'Then Jethro rejoiced for all the good which the Lord had done for Israel, whom He had delivered out of the hand of the Egyptians.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18010, 'And Jethro said, &ldquo;Blessed be the Lord, who has delivered you out of the hand of the Egyptians and out of the hand of Pharaoh, and who has delivered the people from under the hand of the Egyptians.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18011, '&ldquo;Now I know that the Lord is greater than all the gods; for in the very thing in which they behaved proudly, He was above them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18012, 'Then Jethro, Moses&rsquo; father-in-law, took a burnt offering and other sacrifices to offer to God. And Aaron came with all the elders of Israel to eat bread with Moses&rsquo; father-in-law before God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18013, 'And so it was, on the next day, that Moses sat to judge the people; and the people stood before Moses from morning until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18014, 'So when Moses&rsquo; father-in-law saw all that he did for the people, he said, &ldquo;What is this thing that you are doing for the people? Why do you alone sit, and all the people stand before you from morning until evening?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18015, 'And Moses said to his father-in-law, &ldquo;Because the people come to me to inquire of God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18016, '&ldquo;When they have a difficulty, they come to me, and I judge between one and another; and I make known the statutes of God and His laws.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18017, 'So Moses&rsquo; father-in-law said to him, &ldquo;The thing that you do is not good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18018, '&ldquo;Both you and these people who are with you will surely wear yourselves out. For this thing is too much for you; you are not able to perform it by yourself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18019, '&ldquo;Listen now to my voice; I will give you counsel, and God will be with you: Stand before God for the people, so that you may bring the difficulties to God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18020, '&ldquo;And you shall teach them the statutes and the laws, and show them the way in which they must walk and the work they must do.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18021, '&ldquo;Moreover you shall select from all the people able men, such as fear God, men of truth, hating covetousness; and place such over them to be rulers of thousands, rulers of hundreds, rulers of fifties, and rulers of tens.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18022, '&ldquo;And let them judge the people at all times. Then it will be that every great matter they shall bring to you, but every small matter they themselves shall judge. So it will be easier for you, for they will bear the burden with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18023, '&ldquo;If you do this thing, and God so commands you, then you will be able to endure, and all this people will also go to their place in peace.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18024, 'So Moses heeded the voice of his father-in-law and did all that he had said.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18025, 'And Moses chose able men out of all Israel, and made them heads over the people: rulers of thousands, rulers of hundreds, rulers of fifties, and rulers of tens.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18026, 'So they judged the people at all times; the hard cases they brought to Moses, but they judged every small case themselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 18027, 'Then Moses let his father-in-law depart, and he went his way to his own land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19001, 'In the third month after the children of Israel had gone out of the land of Egypt, on the same day, they came to the Wilderness of Sinai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19002, 'For they had departed from Rephidim, had come to the Wilderness of Sinai, and camped in the wilderness. So Israel camped there before the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19003, 'And Moses went up to God, and the Lord called to him from the mountain, saying, &ldquo;Thus you shall say to the house of Jacob, and tell the children of Israel:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19004, '&lsquo;You have seen what I did to the Egyptians, and how I bore you on eagles&rsquo; wings and brought you to Myself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19005, '&lsquo;Now therefore, if you will indeed obey My voice and keep My covenant, then you shall be a special treasure to Me above all people; for all the earth is Mine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19006, '&lsquo;And you shall be to Me a kingdom of priests and a holy nation.&rsquo; These are the words which you shall speak to the children of Israel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19007, 'So Moses came and called for the elders of the people, and laid before them all these words which the Lord commanded him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19008, 'Then all the people answered together and said, &ldquo;All that the Lord has spoken we will do.&rdquo; So Moses brought back the words of the people to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19009, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Behold, I come to you in the thick cloud, that the people may hear when I speak with you, and believe you forever.&rdquo; So Moses told the words of the people to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19010, 'Then the* Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Go to the people and consecrate them today and tomorrow, and let them wash their clothes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19011, '&ldquo;And let them be ready for the third day. For on the third day the Lord will come down upon Mount Sinai in the sight of all the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19012, '&ldquo;You shall set bounds for the people all around, saying, &lsquo;Take heed to yourselves that you do not go up to the mountain or touch its base. Whoever touches the mountain shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19013, '&lsquo;Not a hand shall touch him, but he shall surely be stoned or shot with an arrow; whether man or beast, he shall not live.&rsquo; When the trumpet sounds long, they shall come near the mountain.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19014, 'So Moses went down from the mountain to the people and sanctified the people, and they washed their clothes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19015, 'And he said to the people, &ldquo;Be ready for the third day; do not come near your wives.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19016, 'Then it came to pass on the third day, in the morning, that there were thunderings and lightnings, and a thick cloud on the mountain; and the sound of the trumpet was very loud, so that all the people who were in the camp trembled.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19017, 'And Moses brought the people out of the camp to meet with God, and they stood at the foot of the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19018, 'Now Mount Sinai was completely in smoke, because the Lord descended upon it in fire. Its smoke ascended like the smoke of a furnace, and the whole mountaina quaked greatly.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19019, 'And when the blast of the trumpet sounded long and became louder and louder, Moses spoke, and God answered him by voice.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19020, 'Then the Lord came down upon Mount Sinai, on the top of the mountain. And the Lord called Moses to the top of the mountain, and Moses went up.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19021, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Go down and warn the people, lest they break through to gaze at the Lord, and many of them perish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19022, '&ldquo;Also let the priests who come near the Lord consecrate themselves, lest the Lord break out against them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19023, 'But Moses said to the Lord, &ldquo;The people cannot come up to Mount Sinai; for You warned us, saying, &lsquo;Set bounds around the mountain and consecrate it.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19024, 'Then the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Away! Get down and then come up, you and Aaron with you. But do not let the priests and the people break through to come up to the Lord, lest He break out against them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 19025, 'So Moses went down to the people and spoke to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20001, 'And God spoke all these words, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20002, '&ldquo;I am the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of bondage.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20003, '&ldquo;You shall have no other gods before Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20004, '&ldquo;You shall not make for yourself a carved image &ndash; any likeness of anything that is in heaven above, or that is in the earth beneath, or that is in the water under the earth;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20005, 'you shall not bow down to them nor serve them. For I, the Lord your God, am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children to the third and fourth generations of those who hate Me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20006, 'but showing mercy to thousands, to those who love Me and keep My commandments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20007, '&ldquo;You shall not take the name of the Lord your God in vain, for the Lord will not hold him guiltless who takes His name in vain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20008, '&ldquo;Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20009, 'Six days you shall labor and do all your work,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20010, 'but the seventh day is the Sabbath of the Lord your God. In it you shall do no work: you, nor your son, nor your daughter, nor your male servant, nor your female servant, nor your cattle, nor your stranger who is within your gates.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20011, 'For in six days the Lord made the heavens and the earth, the sea, and all that is in them, and rested the seventh day. Therefore the Lord blessed the Sabbath day and hallowed it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20012, '&ldquo;Honor your father and your mother, that your days may be long upon the land which the Lord your God is giving you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20013, '&ldquo;You shall not murder.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20014, '&ldquo;You shall not commit adultery.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20015, '&ldquo;You shall not steal.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20016, '&ldquo;You shall not bear false witness against your neighbor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20017, '&ldquo;You shall not covet your neighbor&rsquo;s house; you shall not covet your neighbor&rsquo;s wife, nor his male servant, nor his female servant, nor his ox, nor his donkey, nor anything that is your neighbor&rsquo;s.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20018, 'Now all the people witnessed the thunderings, the lightning flashes, the sound of the trumpet, and the mountain smoking; and when the people saw it, they trembled and stood afar off.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20019, 'Then they said to Moses, &ldquo;You speak with us, and we will hear; but let not God speak with us, lest we die.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20020, 'And Moses said to the people, &ldquo;Do not fear; for God has come to test you, and that His fear may be before you, so that you may not sin.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20021, 'So the people stood afar off, but Moses drew near the thick darkness where God was.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20022, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Thus you shall say to the children of Israel: &lsquo;You have seen that I have talked with you from heaven.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20023, '&lsquo;You shall not make anything to be with Me &ndash; gods of silver or gods of gold you shall not make for yourselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20024, '&lsquo;An altar of earth you shall make for Me, and you shall sacrifice on it your burnt offerings and your peace offerings, your sheep and your oxen. In every place where I record My name I will come to you, and I will bless you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20025, '&lsquo;And if you make Me an altar of stone, you shall not build it of hewn stone; for if you use your tool on it, you have profaned it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 20026, '&lsquo;Nor shall you go up by steps to My altar, that your nakedness may not be exposed on it.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21001, '&ldquo;Now these are the judgments which you shall set before them:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21002, '&ldquo;If you buy a Hebrew servant, he shall serve six years; and in the seventh he shall go out free and pay nothing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21003, '&ldquo;If he comes in by himself, he shall go out by himself; if he comes in married, then his wife shall go out with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21004, '&ldquo;If his master has given him a wife, and she has borne him sons or daughters, the wife and her children shall be her master&rsquo;s, and he shall go out by himself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21005, '&ldquo;But if the servant plainly says, &lsquo;I love my master, my wife, and my children; I will not go out free,&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21006, '&ldquo;then his master shall bring him to the judges. He shall also bring him to the door, or to the doorpost, and his master shall pierce his ear with an awl; and he shall serve him forever.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21007, '&ldquo;And if a man sells his daughter to be a female slave, she shall not go out as the male slaves do.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21008, '&ldquo;If she does not please her master, who has betrothed her to himself, then he shall let her be redeemed. He shall have no right to sell her to a foreign people, since he has dealt deceitfully with her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21009, '&ldquo;And if he has betrothed her to his son, he shall deal with her according to the custom of daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21010, '&ldquo;If he takes another wife, he shall not diminish her food, her clothing, and her marriage rights.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21011, '&ldquo;And if he does not do these three for her, then she shall go out free, without paying money.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21012, '&ldquo;He who strikes a man so that he dies shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21013, '&ldquo;However, if he did not lie in wait, but God delivered him into his hand, then I will appoint for you a place where he may flee.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21014, '&ldquo;But if a man acts with premeditation against his neighbor, to kill him by treachery, you shall take him from My altar, that he may die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21015, '&ldquo;And he who strikes his father or his mother shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21016, '&ldquo;He who kidnaps a man and sells him, or if he is found in his hand, shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21017, '&ldquo;And he who curses his father or his mother shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21018, '&ldquo;If men contend with each other, and one strikes the other with a stone or with his fist, and he does not die but is confined to his bed,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21019, '&ldquo;if he rises again and walks about outside with his staff, then he who struck him shall be acquitted. He shall only pay for the loss of his time, and shall provide for him to be thoroughly healed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21020, '&ldquo;And if a man beats his male or female servant with a rod, so that he dies under his hand, he shall surely be punished.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21021, '&ldquo;Notwithstanding, if he remains alive a day or two, he shall not be punished; for he is his property.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21022, '&ldquo;If men fight, and hurt a woman with child, so that she gives birth prematurely, yet no harm follows, he shall surely be punished accordingly as the woman&rsquo;s husband imposes on him; and he shall pay as the judges determine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21023, '&ldquo;But if any harm follows, then you shall give life for life,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21024, '&ldquo;eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21025, '&ldquo;burn for burn, wound for wound, stripe for stripe.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21026, '&ldquo;If a man strikes the eye of his male or female servant, and destroys it, he shall let him go free for the sake of his eye.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21027, '&ldquo;And if he knocks out the tooth of his male or female servant, he shall let him go free for the sake of his tooth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21028, '&ldquo;If an ox gores a man or a woman to death, then the ox shall surely be stoned, and its flesh shall not be eaten; but the owner of the ox shall be acquitted.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21029, '&ldquo;But if the ox tended to thrust with its horn in times past, and it has been made known to his owner, and he has not kept it confined, so that it has killed a man or a woman, the ox shall be stoned and its owner also shall be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21030, '&ldquo;If there is imposed on him a sum of money, then he shall pay to redeem his life, whatever is imposed on him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21031, '&ldquo;Whether it has gored a son or gored a daughter, according to this judgment it shall be done to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21032, '&ldquo;If the ox gores a male or female servant, he shall give to their master thirty shekels of silver, and the ox shall be stoned.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21033, '&ldquo;And if a man opens a pit, or if a man digs a pit and does not cover it, and an ox or a donkey falls in it,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21034, '&ldquo;the owner of the pit shall make it good; he shall give money to their owner, but the dead animal shall be his.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21035, '&ldquo;If one man&rsquo;s ox hurts another&rsquo;s, so that it dies, then they shall sell the live ox and divide the money from it; and the dead ox they shall also divide.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 21036, '&ldquo;Or if it was known that the ox tended to thrust in time past, and its owner has not kept it confined, he shall surely pay ox for ox, and the dead animal shall be his own.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22001, '&ldquo;If a man steals an ox or a sheep, and slaughters it or sells it, he shall restore five oxen for an ox and four sheep for a sheep.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22002, '&ldquo;If the thief is found breaking in, and he is struck so that he dies, there shall be no guilt for his bloodshed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22003, '&ldquo;If the sun has risen on him, there shall be guilt for his bloodshed. He should make full restitution; if he has nothing, then he shall be sold for his theft.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22004, '&ldquo;If the theft is certainly found alive in his hand, whether it is an ox or donkey or sheep, he shall restore double.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22005, '&ldquo;If a man causes a field or vineyard to be grazed, and lets loose his animal, and it feeds in another man&rsquo;s field, he shall make restitution from the best of his own field and the best of his own vineyard.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22006, '&ldquo;If fire breaks out and catches in thorns, so that stacked grain, standing grain, or the field is consumed, he who kindled the fire shall surely make restitution.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22007, '&ldquo;If a man delivers to his neighbor money or articles to keep, and it is stolen out of the man&rsquo;s house, if the thief is found, he shall pay double.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22008, '&ldquo;If the thief is not found, then the master of the house shall be brought to the judges to see whether he has put his hand into his neighbor&rsquo;s goods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22009, '&ldquo;For any kind of trespass, whether it concerns an ox, a donkey, a sheep, or clothing, or for any kind of lost thing which another claims to be his, the cause of both parties shall come before the judges; and whomever the judges condemn shall pay double to');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22010, '&ldquo;If a man delivers to his neighbor a donkey, an ox, a sheep, or any animal to keep, and it dies, is hurt, or driven away, no one seeing it,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22011, '&ldquo;then an oath of the Lord shall be between them both, that he has not put his hand into his neighbor&rsquo;s goods; and the owner of it shall accept that, and he shall not make it good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22012, '&ldquo;But if, in fact, it is stolen from him, he shall make restitution to the owner of it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22013, '&ldquo;If it is torn to pieces by a beast, then he shall bring it as evidence, and he shall not make good what was torn.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22014, '&ldquo;And if a man borrows anything from his neighbor, and it becomes injured or dies, the owner of it not being with it, he shall surely make it good.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22015, '&ldquo;If its owner was with it, he shall not make it good; if it was hired, it came for its hire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22016, '&ldquo;If a man entices a virgin who is not betrothed, and lies with her, he shall surely pay the bride-price for her to be his wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22017, '&ldquo;If her father utterly refuses to give her to him, he shall pay money according to the bride-price of virgins.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22018, '&ldquo;You shall not permit a sorceress to live.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22019, '&ldquo;Whoever lies with an animal shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22020, '&ldquo;He who sacrifices to any god, except to the Lord only, he shall be utterly destroyed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22021, '&ldquo;You shall neither mistreat a stranger nor oppress him, for you were strangers in the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22022, '&ldquo;You shall not afflict any widow or fatherless child.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22023, '&ldquo;If you afflict them in any way, and they cry at all to Me, I will surely hear their cry;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22024, '&ldquo;and My wrath will become hot, and I will kill you with the sword; your wives shall be widows, and your children fatherless.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22025, '&ldquo;If you lend money to any of My people who are poor among you, you shall not be like a moneylender to him; you shall not charge him interest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22026, '&ldquo;If you ever take your neighbor&rsquo;s garment as a pledge, you shall return it to him before the sun goes down.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22027, '&ldquo;For that is his only covering, it is his garment for his skin. What will he sleep in? And it will be that when he cries to Me, I will hear, for I am gracious.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22028, '&ldquo;You shall not revile God, nor curse a ruler of your people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22029, '&ldquo;You shall not delay to offer the first of your ripe produce and your juices. The firstborn of your sons you shall give to Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22030, '&ldquo;Likewise you shall do with your oxen and your sheep. It shall be with its mother seven days; on the eighth day you shall give it to Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 22031, '&ldquo;And you shall be holy men to Me: you shall not eat meat torn by beasts in the field; you shall throw it to the dogs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23001, '&ldquo;You shall not circulate a false report. Do not put your hand with the wicked to be an unrighteous witness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23002, '&ldquo;You shall not follow a crowd to do evil; nor shall you testify in a dispute so as to turn aside after many to pervert justice.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23003, '&ldquo;You shall not show partiality to a poor man in his dispute.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23004, '&ldquo;If you meet your enemy&rsquo;s ox or his donkey going astray, you shall surely bring it back to him again.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23005, '&ldquo;If you see the donkey of one who hates you lying under its burden, and you would refrain from helping it, you shall surely help him with it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23006, '&ldquo;You shall not pervert the judgment of your poor in his dispute.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23007, '&ldquo;Keep yourself far from a false matter; do not kill the innocent and righteous. For I will not justify the wicked.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23008, '&ldquo;And you shall take no bribe, for a bribe blinds the discerning and perverts the words of the righteous.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23009, '&ldquo;Also you shall not oppress a stranger, for you know the heart of a stranger, because you were strangers in the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23010, '&ldquo;Six years you shall sow your land and gather in its produce,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23011, '&ldquo;but the seventh year you shall let it rest and lie fallow, that the poor of your people may eat; and what they leave, the beasts of the field may eat. In like manner you shall do with your vineyard and your olive grove.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23012, '&ldquo;Six days you shall do your work, and on the seventh day you shall rest, that your ox and your donkey may rest, and the son of your female servant and the stranger may be refreshed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23013, '&ldquo;And in all that I have said to you, be circumspect and make no mention of the name of other gods, nor let it be heard from your mouth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23014, '&ldquo;Three times you shall keep a feast to Me in the year:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23015, '&ldquo;You shall keep the Feast of Unleavened Bread (you shall eat unleavened bread seven days, as I commanded you, at the time appointed in the month of Abib, for in it you came out of Egypt; none shall appear before Me empty);');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23016, '&ldquo;and the Feast of Harvest, the firstfruits of your labors which you have sown in the field; and the Feast of Ingathering at the end of the year, when you have gathered in the fruit of your labors from the field.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23017, '&ldquo;Three times in the year all your males shall appear before the Lord God.a');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23018, '&ldquo;You shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leavened bread; nor shall the fat of My sacrifice remain until morning.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23019, '&ldquo;The first of the firstfruits of your land you shall bring into the house of the Lord your God. You shall not boil a young goat in its mother&rsquo;s milk.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23020, '&ldquo;Behold, I send an Angel before you to keep you in the way and to bring you into the place which I have prepared.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23021, '&ldquo;Beware of Him and obey His voice; do not provoke Him, for He will not pardon your transgressions; for My name is in Him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23022, '&ldquo;But if you indeed obey His voice and do all that I speak, then I will be an enemy to your enemies and an adversary to your adversaries.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23023, '&ldquo;For My Angel will go before you and bring you in to the Amorites and the Hittites and the Perizzites and the Canaanites and the Hivites and the Jebusites; and I will cut them off.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23024, '&ldquo;You shall not bow down to their gods, nor serve them, nor do according to their works; but you shall utterly overthrow them and completely break down their sacred pillars.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23025, '&ldquo;So you shall serve the Lord your God, and He will bless your bread and your water. And I will take sickness away from the midst of you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23026, '&ldquo;No one shall suffer miscarriage or be barren in your land; I will fulfill the number of your days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23027, '&ldquo;I will send My fear before you, I will cause confusion among all the people to whom you come, and will make all your enemies turn their backs to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23028, '&ldquo;And I will send hornets before you, which shall drive out the Hivite, the Canaanite, and the Hittite from before you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23029, '&ldquo;I will not drive them out from before you in one year, lest the land become desolate and the beasts of the field become too numerous for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23030, '&ldquo;Little by little I will drive them out from before you, until you have increased, and you inherit the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23031, '&ldquo;And I will set your bounds from the Red Sea to the sea, Philistia, and from the desert to the River. For I will deliver the inhabitants of the land into your hand, and you shall drive them out before you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23032, '&ldquo;You shall make no covenant with them, nor with their gods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 23033, '&ldquo;They shall not dwell in your land, lest they make you sin against Me. For if you serve their gods, it will surely be a snare to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24001, 'Now He said to Moses, &ldquo;Come up to the Lord, you and Aaron, Nadab and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel, and worship from afar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24002, '&ldquo;And Moses alone shall come near the Lord, but they shall not come near; nor shall the people go up with him.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24003, 'So Moses came and told the people all the words of the Lord and all the judgments. And all the people answered with one voice and said, &ldquo;All the words which the Lord has said we will do.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24004, 'And Moses wrote all the words of the Lord. And he rose early in the morning, and built an altar at the foot of the mountain, and twelve pillars according to the twelve tribes of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24005, 'Then he sent young men of the children of Israel, who offered burnt offerings and sacrificed peace offerings of oxen to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24006, 'And Moses took half the blood and put it in basins, and half the blood he sprinkled on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24007, 'Then he took the Book of the Covenant and read in the hearing of the people. And they said, &ldquo;All that the Lord has said we will do, and be obedient.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24008, 'And Moses took the blood, sprinkled it on the people, and said, &ldquo;This is the blood of the covenant which the Lord has made with you according to all these words.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24009, 'Then Moses went up, also Aaron, Nadab, and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24010, 'and they saw the God of Israel. And there was under His feet as it were a paved work of sapphire stone, and it was like the very heavens in its clarity.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24011, 'But on the nobles of the children of Israel He did not lay His hand. So they saw God, and they ate and drank.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24012, 'Then the* Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Come up to Me on the mountain and be there; and I will give you tablets of stone, and the law and commandments which I have written, that you may teach them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24013, 'So Moses arose with his assistant Joshua, and Moses went up to the mountain of God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24014, 'And he said to the elders, &ldquo;Wait here for us until we come back to you. Indeed, Aaron and Hur are with you. If any man has a difficulty, let him go to them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24015, 'Then Moses went up into the mountain, and a cloud covered the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24016, 'Now the glory of the Lord rested on Mount Sinai, and the cloud covered it six days. And on the seventh day He called to Moses out of the midst of the cloud.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24017, 'The sight of the glory of the Lord was like a consuming fire on the top of the mountain in the eyes of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 24018, 'So Moses went into the midst of the cloud and went up into the mountain. And Moses was on the mountain forty days and forty nights.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25001, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, that they bring Me an offering. From everyone who gives it willingly with his heart you shall take My offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25003, '&ldquo;And this is the offering which you shall take from them: gold, silver, and bronze;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25004, '&ldquo;blue, purple, and scarlet thread, fine linen, and goats&rsquo; hair;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25005, '&ldquo;ram skins dyed red, badger skins, and acacia wood;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25006, '&ldquo;oil for the light, and spices for the anointing oil and for the sweet incense;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25007, '&ldquo;onyx stones, and stones to be set in the ephod and in the breastplate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25008, '&ldquo;And let them make Me a sanctuary, that I may dwell among them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25009, '&ldquo;According to all that I show you, that is, the pattern of the tabernacle and the pattern of all its furnishings, just so you shall make it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25010, '&ldquo;And they shall make an ark of acacia wood; two and a half cubits shall be its length, a cubit and a half its width, and a cubit and a half its height.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25011, '&ldquo;And you shall overlay it with pure gold, inside and out you shall overlay it, and shall make on it a molding of gold all around.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25012, '&ldquo;You shall cast four rings of gold for it, and put them in its four corners; two rings shall be on one side, and two rings on the other side.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25013, '&ldquo;And you shall make poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25014, '&ldquo;You shall put the poles into the rings on the sides of the ark, that the ark may be carried by them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25015, '&ldquo;The poles shall be in the rings of the ark; they shall not be taken from it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25016, '&ldquo;And you shall put into the ark the Testimony which I will give you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25017, '&ldquo;You shall make a mercy seat of pure gold; two and a half cubits shall be its length and a cubit and a half its width.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25018, '&ldquo;And you shall make two cherubim of gold; of hammered work you shall make them at the two ends of the mercy seat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25019, '&ldquo;Make one cherub at one end, and the other cherub at the other end; you shall make the cherubim at the two ends of it of one piece with the mercy seat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25020, '&ldquo;And the cherubim shall stretch out their wings above, covering the mercy seat with their wings, and they shall face one another; the faces of the cherubim shall be toward the mercy seat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25021, '&ldquo;You shall put the mercy seat on top of the ark, and in the ark you shall put the Testimony that I will give you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25022, '&ldquo;And there I will meet with you, and I will speak with you from above the mercy seat, from between the two cherubim which are on the ark of the Testimony, about everything which I will give you in commandment to the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25023, '&ldquo;You shall also make a table of acacia wood; two cubits shall be its length, a cubit its width, and a cubit and a half its height.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25024, '&ldquo;And you shall overlay it with pure gold, and make a molding of gold all around.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25025, '&ldquo;You shall make for it a frame of a handbreadth all around, and you shall make a gold molding for the frame all around.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25026, '&ldquo;And you shall make for it four rings of gold, and put the rings on the four corners that are at its four legs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25027, '&ldquo;The rings shall be close to the frame, as holders for the poles to bear the table.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25028, '&ldquo;And you shall make the poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold, that the table may be carried with them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25029, '&ldquo;You shall make its dishes, its pans, its pitchers, and its bowls for pouring. You shall make them of pure gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25030, '&ldquo;And you shall set the showbread on the table before Me always.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25031, '&ldquo;You shall also make a lampstand of pure gold; the lampstand shall be of hammered work. Its shaft, its branches, its bowls, its ornamental knobs, and flowers shall be of one piece.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25032, '&ldquo;And six branches shall come out of its sides: three branches of the lampstand out of one side, and three branches of the lampstand out of the other side.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25033, '&ldquo;Three bowls shall be made like almond blossoms on one branch, with an ornamental knob and a flower, and three bowls made like almond blossoms on the other branch, with an ornamental knob and a flower &ndash; and so for the six branches that come out of the lamps');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25034, '&ldquo;On the lampstand itself four bowls shall be made like almond blossoms, each with its ornamental knob and flower.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25035, '&ldquo;And there shall be a knob under the first two branches of the same, a knob under the second two branches of the same, and a knob under the third two branches of the same, according to the six branches that extend from the lampstand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25036, '&ldquo;Their knobs and their branches shall be of one piece; all of it shall be one hammered piece of pure gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25037, '&ldquo;You shall make seven lamps for it, and they shall arrange its lamps so that they give light in front of it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25038, '&ldquo;And its wick-trimmers and their trays shall be of pure gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25039, '&ldquo;It shall be made of a talent of pure gold, with all these utensils.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 25040, '&ldquo;And see to it that you make them according to the pattern which was shown you on the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26001, '&ldquo;Moreover you shall make the tabernacle with ten curtains of fine woven linen, and blue, purple, and scarlet thread; with artistic designs of cherubim you shall weave them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26002, '&ldquo;The length of each curtain shall be twenty-eight cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits. And every one of the curtains shall have the same measurements.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26003, '&ldquo;Five curtains shall be coupled to one another, and the other five curtains shall be coupled to one another.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26004, '&ldquo;And you shall make loops of blue yarn on the edge of the curtain on the selvedge of one set, and likewise you shall do on the outer edge of the other curtain of the second set.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26005, '&ldquo;Fifty loops you shall make in the one curtain, and fifty loops you shall make on the edge of the curtain that is on the end of the second set, that the loops may be clasped to one another.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26006, '&ldquo;And you shall make fifty clasps of gold, and couple the curtains together with the clasps, so that it may be one tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26007, '&ldquo;You shall also make curtains of goats&rsquo; hair, to be a tent over the tabernacle. You shall make eleven curtains.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26008, '&ldquo;The length of each curtain shall be thirty cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits; and the eleven curtains shall all have the same measurements.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26009, '&ldquo;And you shall couple five curtains by themselves and six curtains by themselves, and you shall double over the sixth curtain at the forefront of the tent.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26010, '&ldquo;You shall make fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is outermost in one set, and fifty loops on the edge of the curtain of the second set.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26011, '&ldquo;And you shall make fifty bronze clasps, put the clasps into the loops, and couple the tent together, that it may be one.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26012, '&ldquo;The remnant that remains of the curtains of the tent, the half curtain that remains, shall hang over the back of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26013, '&ldquo;And a cubit on one side and a cubit on the other side, of what remains of the length of the curtains of the tent, shall hang over the sides of the tabernacle, on this side and on that side, to cover it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26014, '&ldquo;You shall also make a covering of ram skins dyed red for the tent, and a covering of badger skins above that.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26015, '&ldquo;And for the tabernacle you shall make the boards of acacia wood, standing upright.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26016, '&ldquo;Ten cubits shall be the length of a board, and a cubit and a half shall be the width of each board.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26017, '&ldquo;Two tenons shall be in each board for binding one to another. Thus you shall make for all the boards of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26018, '&ldquo;And you shall make the boards for the tabernacle, twenty boards for the south side.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26019, '&ldquo;You shall make forty sockets of silver under the twenty boards: two sockets under each of the boards for its two tenons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26020, '&ldquo;And for the second side of the tabernacle, the north side, there shall be twenty boards');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26021, '&ldquo;and their forty sockets of silver: two sockets under each of the boards.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26022, '&ldquo;For the far side of the tabernacle, westward, you shall make six boards.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26023, '&ldquo;And you shall also make two boards for the two back corners of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26024, '&ldquo;They shall be coupled together at the bottom and they shall be coupled together at the top by one ring. Thus it shall be for both of them. They shall be for the two corners.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26025, '&ldquo;So there shall be eight boards with their sockets of silver &ndash; sixteen sockets &ndash; two sockets under each of the boards.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26026, '&ldquo;And you shall make bars of acacia wood: five for the boards on one side of the tabernacle,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26027, '&ldquo;five bars for the boards on the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the side of the tabernacle, for the far side westward.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26028, '&ldquo;The middle bar shall pass through the midst of the boards from end to end.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26029, '&ldquo;You shall overlay the boards with gold, make their rings of gold as holders for the bars, and overlay the bars with gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26030, '&ldquo;And you shall raise up the tabernacle according to its pattern which you were shown on the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26031, '&ldquo;You shall make a veil woven of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen. It shall be woven with an artistic design of cherubim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26032, '&ldquo;You shall hang it upon the four pillars of acacia wood overlaid with gold. Their hooks shall be gold, upon four sockets of silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26033, '&ldquo;And you shall hang the veil from the clasps. Then you shall bring the ark of the Testimony in there, behind the veil. The veil shall be a divider for you between the holy place and the Most Holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26034, '&ldquo;You shall put the mercy seat upon the ark of the Testimony in the Most Holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26035, '&ldquo;You shall set the table outside the veil, and the lampstand across from the table on the side of the tabernacle toward the south; and you shall put the table on the north side.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26036, '&ldquo;You shall make a screen for the door of the tabernacle, woven of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen, made by a weaver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 26037, '&ldquo;And you shall make for the screen five pillars of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold; their hooks shall be gold, and you shall cast five sockets of bronze for them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27001, '&ldquo;You shall make an altar of acacia wood, five cubits long and five cubits wide &ndash; the altar shall be square &ndash; and its height shall be three cubits.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27002, '&ldquo;You shall make its horns on its four corners; its horns shall be of one piece with it. And you shall overlay it with bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27003, '&ldquo;Also you shall make its pans to receive its ashes, and its shovels and its basins and its forks and its firepans; you shall make all its utensils of bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27004, '&ldquo;You shall make a grate for it, a network of bronze; and on the network you shall make four bronze rings at its four corners.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27005, '&ldquo;You shall put it under the rim of the altar beneath, that the network may be midway up the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27006, '&ldquo;And you shall make poles for the altar, poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27007, '&ldquo;The poles shall be put in the rings, and the poles shall be on the two sides of the altar to bear it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27008, '&ldquo;You shall make it hollow with boards; as it was shown you on the mountain, so shall they make it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27009, '&ldquo;You shall also make the court of the tabernacle. For the south side there shall be hangings for the court made of fine woven linen, one hundred cubits long for one side.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27010, '&ldquo;And its twenty pillars and their twenty sockets shall be bronze. The hooks of the pillars and their bands shall be silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27011, '&ldquo;Likewise along the length of the north side there shall be hangings one hundred cubits long, with its twenty pillars and their twenty sockets of bronze, and the hooks of the pillars and their bands of silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27012, '&ldquo;And along the width of the court on the west side shall be hangings of fifty cubits, with their ten pillars and their ten sockets.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27013, '&ldquo;The width of the court on the east side shall be fifty cubits.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27014, '&ldquo;The hangings on one side of the gate shall be fifteen cubits, with their three pillars and their three sockets.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27015, '&ldquo;And on the other side shall be hangings of fifteen cubits, with their three pillars and their three sockets.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27016, '&ldquo;For the gate of the court there shall be a screen twenty cubits long, woven of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen, made by a weaver. It shall have four pillars and four sockets.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27017, '&ldquo;All the pillars around the court shall have bands of silver; their hooks shall be of silver and their sockets of bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27018, '&ldquo;The length of the court shall be one hundred cubits, the width fifty throughout, and the height five cubits, made of fine woven linen, and its sockets of bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27019, '&ldquo;All the utensils of the tabernacle for all its service, all its pegs, and all the pegs of the court, shall be of bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27020, '&ldquo;And you shall command the children of Israel that they bring you pure oil of pressed olives for the light, to cause the lamp to burn continually.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 27021, '&ldquo;In the tabernacle of meeting, outside the veil which is before the Testimony, Aaron and his sons shall tend it from evening until morning before the Lord. It shall be a statute forever to their generations on behalf of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28001, '&ldquo;Now take Aaron your brother, and his sons with him, from among the children of Israel, that he may minister to Me as priest, Aaron and Aaron&rsquo;s sons: Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28002, '&ldquo;And you shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother, for glory and for beauty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28003, '&ldquo;So you shall speak to all who are gifted artisans, whom I have filled with the spirit of wisdom, that they may make Aaron&rsquo;s garments, to consecrate him, that he may minister to Me as priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28004, '&ldquo;And these are the garments which they shall make: a breastplate, an ephod,a a robe, a skillfully woven tunic, a turban, and a sash. So they shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother and his sons, that he may minister to Me as priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28005, '&ldquo;They shall take the gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and the fine linen,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28006, '&ldquo;and they shall make the ephod of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen, artistically worked.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28007, '&ldquo;It shall have two shoulder straps joined at its two edges, and so it shall be joined together.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28008, '&ldquo;And the intricately woven band of the ephod, which is on it, shall be of the same workmanship, made of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28009, '&ldquo;Then you shall take two onyx stones and engrave on them the names of the sons of Israel:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28010, '&ldquo;six of their names on one stone and six names on the other stone, in order of their birth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28011, '&ldquo;With the work of an engraver in stone, like the engravings of a signet, you shall engrave the two stones with the names of the sons of Israel. You shall set them in settings of gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28012, '&ldquo;And you shall put the two stones on the shoulders of the ephod as memorial stones for the sons of Israel. So Aaron shall bear their names before the Lord on his two shoulders as a memorial.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28013, '&ldquo;You shall also make settings of gold,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28014, '&ldquo;and you shall make two chains of pure gold like braided cords, and fasten the braided chains to the settings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28015, '&ldquo;You shall make the breastplate of judgment. Artistically woven according to the workmanship of the ephod you shall make it: of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen, you shall make it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28016, '&ldquo;It shall be doubled into a square: a span shall be its length, and a span shall be its width.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28017, '&ldquo;And you shall put settings of stones in it, four rows of stones: The first row shall be a sardius, a topaz, and an emerald; this shall be the first row;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28018, '&ldquo;the second row shall be a turquoise, a sapphire, and a diamond;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28019, '&ldquo;the third row, a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28020, '&ldquo;and the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper. They shall be set in gold settings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28021, '&ldquo;And the stones shall have the names of the sons of Israel, twelve according to their names, like the engravings of a signet, each one with its own name; they shall be according to the twelve tribes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28022, '&ldquo;You shall make chains for the breastplate at the end, like braided cords of pure gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28023, '&ldquo;And you shall make two rings of gold for the breastplate, and put the two rings on the two ends of the breastplate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28024, '&ldquo;Then you shall put the two braided chains of gold in the two rings which are on the ends of the breastplate;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28025, '&ldquo;and the other two ends of the two braided chains you shall fasten to the two settings, and put them on the shoulder straps of the ephod in the front.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28026, '&ldquo;You shall make two rings of gold, and put them on the two ends of the breastplate, on the edge of it, which is on the inner side of the ephod.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28027, '&ldquo;And two other rings of gold you shall make, and put them on the two shoulder straps, underneath the ephod toward its front, right at the seam above the intricately woven band of the ephod.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28028, '&ldquo;They shall bind the breastplate by means of its rings to the rings of the ephod, using a blue cord, so that it is above the intricately woven band of the ephod, and so that the breastplate does not come loose from the ephod.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28029, '&ldquo;So Aaron shall bear the names of the sons of Israel on the breastplate of judgment over his heart, when he goes into the holy place, as a memorial before the Lord continually.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28030, '&ldquo;And you shall put in the breastplate of judgment the Urim and the Thummim,a and they shall be over Aaron&rsquo;s heart when he goes in before the Lord. So Aaron shall bear the judgment of the children of Israel over his heart before the Lord continually.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28031, '&ldquo;You shall make the robe of the ephod all of blue.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28032, '&ldquo;There shall be an opening for his head in the middle of it; it shall have a woven binding all around its opening, like the opening in a coat of mail, so that it does not tear.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28033, '&ldquo;And upon its hem you shall make pomegranates of blue, purple, and scarlet, all around its hem, and bells of gold between them all around:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28034, '&ldquo;a golden bell and a pomegranate, a golden bell and a pomegranate, upon the hem of the robe all around.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28035, '&ldquo;And it shall be upon Aaron when he ministers, and its sound will be heard when he goes into the holy place before the Lord and when he comes out, that he may not die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28036, '&ldquo;You shall also make a plate of pure gold and engrave on it, like the engraving of a signet:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28037, '&ldquo;And you shall put it on a blue cord, that it may be on the turban; it shall be on the front of the turban.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28038, '&ldquo;So it shall be on Aaron&rsquo;s forehead, that Aaron may bear the iniquity of the holy things which the children of Israel hallow in all their holy gifts; and it shall always be on his forehead, that they may be accepted before the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28039, '&ldquo;You shall skillfully weave the tunic of fine linen thread, you shall make the turban of fine linen, and you shall make the sash of woven work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28040, '&ldquo;For Aaron&rsquo;s sons you shall make tunics, and you shall make sashes for them. And you shall make hats for them, for glory and beauty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28041, '&ldquo;So you shall put them on Aaron your brother and on his sons with him. You shall anoint them, consecrate them, and sanctify them, that they may minister to Me as priests.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28042, '&ldquo;And you shall make for them linen trousers to cover their nakedness; they shall reach from the waist to the thighs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 28043, '&ldquo;They shall be on Aaron and on his sons when they come into the tabernacle of meeting, or when they come near the altar to minister in the holy place, that they do not incur iniquity and die. It shall be a statute forever to him and his descendants after ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29001, '&ldquo;And this is what you shall do to them to hallow them for ministering to Me as priests: Take one young bull and two rams without blemish,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29002, '&ldquo;and unleavened bread, unleavened cakes mixed with oil, and unleavened wafers anointed with oil (you shall make them of wheat flour).');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29003, '&ldquo;You shall put them in one basket and bring them in the basket, with the bull and the two rams.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29004, '&ldquo;And Aaron and his sons you shall bring to the door of the tabernacle of meeting, and you shall wash them with water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29005, '&ldquo;Then you shall take the garments, put the tunic on Aaron, and the robe of the ephod, the ephod, and the breastplate, and gird him with the intricately woven band of the ephod.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29006, '&ldquo;You shall put the turban on his head, and put the holy crown on the turban.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29007, '&ldquo;And you shall take the anointing oil, pour it on his head, and anoint him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29008, '&ldquo;Then you shall bring his sons and put tunics on them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29009, '&ldquo;And you shall gird them with sashes, Aaron and his sons, and put the hats on them. The priesthood shall be theirs for a perpetual statute. So you shall consecrate Aaron and his sons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29010, '&ldquo;You shall also have the bull brought before the tabernacle of meeting, and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands on the head of the bull.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29011, '&ldquo;Then you shall kill the bull before the Lord, by the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29012, '&ldquo;You shall take some of the blood of the bull and put it on the horns of the altar with your finger, and pour all the blood beside the base of the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29013, '&ldquo;And you shall take all the fat that covers the entrails, the fatty lobe attached to the liver, and the two kidneys and the fat that is on them, and burn them on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29014, '&ldquo;But the flesh of the bull, with its skin and its offal, you shall burn with fire outside the camp. It is a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29015, '&ldquo;You shall also take one ram, and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands on the head of the ram;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29016, '&ldquo;and you shall kill the ram, and you shall take its blood and sprinkle it all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29017, '&ldquo;Then you shall cut the ram in pieces, wash its entrails and its legs, and put them with its pieces and with its head.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29018, '&ldquo;And you shall burn the whole ram on the altar. It is a burnt offering to the Lord; it is a sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29019, '&ldquo;You shall also take the other ram, and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands on the head of the ram.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29020, '&ldquo;Then you shall kill the ram, and take some of its blood and put it on the tip of the right ear of Aaron and on the tip of the right ear of his sons, on the thumb of their right hand and on the big toe of their right foot, and sprinkle the blood all aroun');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29021, '&ldquo;And you shall take some of the blood that is on the altar, and some of the anointing oil, and sprinkle it on Aaron and on his garments, on his sons and on the garments of his sons with him; and he and his garments shall be hallowed, and his sons and his ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29022, '&ldquo;Also you shall take the fat of the ram, the fat tail, the fat that covers the entrails, the fatty lobe attached to the liver, the two kidneys and the fat on them, the right thigh (for it is a ram of consecration),');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29023, '&ldquo;one loaf of bread, one cake made with oil, and one wafer from the basket of the unleavened bread that is before the Lord;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29024, '&ldquo;and you shall put all these in the hands of Aaron and in the hands of his sons, and you shall wave them as a wave offering before the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29025, '&ldquo;You shall receive them back from their hands and burn them on the altar as a burnt offering, as a sweet aroma before the Lord. It is an offering made by fire to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29026, '&ldquo;Then you shall take the breast of the ram of Aaron&rsquo;s consecration and wave it as a wave offering before the Lord; and it shall be your portion.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29027, '&ldquo;And from the ram of the consecration you shall consecrate the breast of the wave offering which is waved, and the thigh of the heave offering which is raised, of that which is for Aaron and of that which is for his sons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29028, '&ldquo;It shall be from the children of Israel for Aaron and his sons by a statute forever. For it is a heave offering; it shall be a heave offering from the children of Israel from the sacrifices of their peace offerings, that is, their heave offering to the L');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29029, '&ldquo;And the holy garments of Aaron shall be his sons&rsquo; after him, to be anointed in them and to be consecrated in them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29030, '&ldquo;That son who becomes priest in his place shall put them on for seven days, when he enters the tabernacle of meeting to minister in the holy place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29031, '&ldquo;And you shall take the ram of the consecration and boil its flesh in the holy place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29032, '&ldquo;Then Aaron and his sons shall eat the flesh of the ram, and the bread that is in the basket, by the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29033, '&ldquo;They shall eat those things with which the atonement was made, to consecrate and to sanctify them; but an outsider shall not eat them, because they are holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29034, '&ldquo;And if any of the flesh of the consecration offerings, or of the bread, remains until the morning, then you shall burn the remainder with fire. It shall not be eaten, because it is holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29035, '&ldquo;Thus you shall do to Aaron and his sons, according to all that I have commanded you. Seven days you shall consecrate them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29036, '&ldquo;And you shall offer a bull every day as a sin offering for atonement. You shall cleanse the altar when you make atonement for it, and you shall anoint it to sanctify it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29037, '&ldquo;Seven days you shall make atonement for the altar and sanctify it. And the altar shall be most holy. Whatever touches the altar must be holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29038, '&ldquo;Now this is what you shall offer on the altar: two lambs of the first year, day by day continually.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29039, '&ldquo;One lamb you shall offer in the morning, and the other lamb you shall offer at twilight.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29040, '&ldquo;With the one lamb shall be one-tenth of an ephah of flour mixed with one-fourth of a hin of pressed oil, and one-fourth of a hin of wine as a drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29041, '&ldquo;And the other lamb you shall offer at twilight; and you shall offer with it the grain offering and the drink offering, as in the morning, for a sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29042, '&ldquo;This shall be a continual burnt offering throughout your generations at the door of the tabernacle of meeting before the Lord, where I will meet you to speak with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29043, '&ldquo;And there I will meet with the children of Israel, and the tabernacle shall be sanctified by My glory.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29044, '&ldquo;So I will consecrate the tabernacle of meeting and the altar. I will also consecrate both Aaron and his sons to minister to Me as priests.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29045, '&ldquo;I will dwell among the children of Israel and will be their God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 29046, '&ldquo;And they shall know that I am the Lord their God, who brought them up out of the land of Egypt, that I may dwell among them. I am the Lord their God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30001, '&ldquo;You shall make an altar to burn incense on; you shall make it of acacia wood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30002, '&ldquo;A cubit shall be its length and a cubit its width &ndash; it shall be square &ndash; and two cubits shall be its height. Its horns shall be of one piece with it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30003, '&ldquo;And you shall overlay its top, its sides all around, and its horns with pure gold; and you shall make for it a molding of gold all around.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30004, '&ldquo;Two gold rings you shall make for it, under the molding on both its sides. You shall place them on its two sides, and they will be holders for the poles with which to bear it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30005, '&ldquo;You shall make the poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30006, '&ldquo;And you shall put it before the veil that is before the ark of the Testimony, before the mercy seat that is over the Testimony, where I will meet with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30007, '&ldquo;Aaron shall burn on it sweet incense every morning; when he tends the lamps, he shall burn incense on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30008, '&ldquo;And when Aaron lights the lamps at twilight, he shall burn incense on it, a perpetual incense before the Lord throughout your generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30009, '&ldquo;You shall not offer strange incense on it, or a burnt offering, or a grain offering; nor shall you pour a drink offering on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30010, '&ldquo;And Aaron shall make atonement upon its horns once a year with the blood of the sin offering of atonement; once a year he shall make atonement upon it throughout your generations. It is most holy to the Lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30011, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30012, '&ldquo;When you take the census of the children of Israel for their number, then every man shall give a ransom for himself to the Lord, when you number them, that there may be no plague among them when you number them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30013, '&ldquo;This is what everyone among those who are numbered shall give: half a shekel according to the shekel of the sanctuary (a shekel is twenty gerahs). The half-shekel shall be an offering to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30014, '&ldquo;Everyone included among those who are numbered, from twenty years old and above, shall give an offering to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30015, '&ldquo;The rich shall not give more and the poor shall not give less than half a shekel, when you give an offering to the Lord, to make atonement for yourselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30016, '&ldquo;And you shall take the atonement money of the children of Israel, and shall appoint it for the service of the tabernacle of meeting, that it may be a memorial for the children of Israel before the Lord, to make atonement for yourselves.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30017, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30018, '&ldquo;You shall also make a laver of bronze, with its base also of bronze, for washing. You shall put it between the tabernacle of meeting and the altar. And you shall put water in it,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30019, '&ldquo;for Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet in water from it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30020, '&ldquo;When they go into the tabernacle of meeting, or when they come near the altar to minister, to burn an offering made by fire to the Lord, they shall wash with water, lest they die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30021, '&ldquo;So they shall wash their hands and their feet, lest they die. And it shall be a statute forever to them &ndash; to him and his descendants throughout their generations.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30022, 'Moreover the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30023, '&ldquo;Also take for yourself quality spices &ndash; five hundred shekels of liquid myrrh, half as much sweet-smelling cinnamon (two hundred and fifty shekels), two hundred and fifty shekels of sweet-smelling cane,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30024, '&ldquo;five hundred shekels of cassia, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, and a hin of olive oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30025, '&ldquo;And you shall make from these a holy anointing oil, an ointment compounded according to the art of the perfumer. It shall be a holy anointing oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30026, '&ldquo;With it you shall anoint the tabernacle of meeting and the ark of the Testimony;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30027, '&ldquo;the table and all its utensils, the lampstand and its utensils, and the altar of incense;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30028, '&ldquo;the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, and the laver and its base.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30029, '&ldquo;You shall consecrate them, that they may be most holy; whatever touches them must be holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30030, '&ldquo;And you shall anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that they may minister to Me as priests.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30031, '&ldquo;And you shall speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;This shall be a holy anointing oil to Me throughout your generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30032, '&lsquo;It shall not be poured on man&rsquo;s flesh; nor shall you make any other like it, according to its composition. It is holy, and it shall be holy to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30033, '&lsquo;Whoever compounds any like it, or whoever puts any of it on an outsider, shall be cut off from his people.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30034, 'And the Lord said to Moses: &ldquo;Take sweet spices, stacte and onycha and galbanum, and pure frankincense with these sweet spices; there shall be equal amounts of each.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30035, '&ldquo;You shall make of these an incense, a compound according to the art of the perfumer, salted, pure, and holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30036, '&ldquo;And you shall beat some of it very fine, and put some of it before the Testimony in the tabernacle of meeting where I will meet with you. It shall be most holy to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30037, '&ldquo;But as for the incense which you shall make, you shall not make any for yourselves, according to its composition. It shall be to you holy for the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 30038, '&ldquo;Whoever makes any like it, to smell it, he shall be cut off from his people.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31001, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31002, '&ldquo;See, I have called by name Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31003, '&ldquo;And I have filled him with the Spirit of God, in wisdom, in understanding, in knowledge, and in all manner of workmanship,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31004, '&ldquo;to design artistic works, to work in gold, in silver, in bronze,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31005, '&ldquo;in cutting jewels for setting, in carving wood, and to work in all manner of workmanship.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31006, '&ldquo;And I, indeed I, have appointed with him Aholiab the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan; and I have put wisdom in the hearts of all the gifted artisans, that they may make all that I have commanded you:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31007, '&ldquo;the tabernacle of meeting, the ark of the Testimony and the mercy seat that is on it, and all the furniture of the tabernacle &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31008, '&ldquo;the table and its utensils, the pure gold lampstand with all its utensils, the altar of incense,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31009, '&ldquo;the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, and the laver and its base &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31010, '&ldquo;the garments of ministry,a the holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments of his sons, to minister as priests,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31011, '&ldquo;and the anointing oil and sweet incense for the holy place. According to all that I have commanded you they shall do.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31012, 'And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31013, '&ldquo;Speak also to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;Surely My Sabbaths you shall keep, for it is a sign between Me and you throughout your generations, that you may know that I am the Lord who sanctifies you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31014, '&lsquo;You shall keep the Sabbath, therefore, for it is holy to you. Everyone who profanes it shall surely be put to death; for whoever does any work on it, that person shall be cut off from among his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31015, '&lsquo;Work shall be done for six days, but the seventh is the Sabbath of rest, holy to the Lord. Whoever does any work on the Sabbath day, he shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31016, '&lsquo;Therefore the children of Israel shall keep the Sabbath, to observe the Sabbath throughout their generations as a perpetual covenant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31017, '&lsquo;It is a sign between Me and the children of Israel forever; for in six days the Lord made the heavens and the earth, and on the seventh day He rested and was refreshed.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 31018, 'And when He had made an end of speaking with him on Mount Sinai, He gave Moses two tablets of the Testimony, tablets of stone, written with the finger of God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32001, 'Now when the people saw that Moses delayed coming down from the mountain, the people gathered together to Aaron, and said to him, &ldquo;Come, make us gods that shall go before us; for as for this Moses, the man who brought us up out of the land of Egypt, we do');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32002, 'And Aaron said to them, &ldquo;Break off the golden earrings which are in the ears of your wives, your sons, and your daughters, and bring them to me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32003, 'So all the people broke off the golden earrings which were in their ears, and brought them to Aaron.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32004, 'And he received the gold from their hand, and he fashioned it with an engraving tool, and made a molded calf. Then they said, &ldquo;This is your god, O Israel, that brought you out of the land of Egypt!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32005, 'So when Aaron saw it, he built an altar before it. And Aaron made a proclamation and said, &ldquo;Tomorrow is a feast to the Lord.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32006, 'Then they rose early on the next day, offered burnt offerings, and brought peace offerings; and the people sat down to eat and drink, and rose up to play.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32007, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Go, get down! For your people whom you brought out of the land of Egypt have corrupted themselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32008, '&ldquo;They have turned aside quickly out of the way which I commanded them. They have made themselves a molded calf, and worshiped it and sacrificed to it, and said, &lsquo;This is your god, O Israel, that brought you out of the land of Egypt!&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32009, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;I have seen this people, and indeed it is a stiff-necked people!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32010, '&ldquo;Now therefore, let Me alone, that My wrath may burn hot against them and I may consume them. And I will make of you a great nation.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32011, 'Then Moses pleaded with the Lord his God, and said: &ldquo;Lord, why does Your wrath burn hot against Your people whom You have brought out of the land of Egypt with great power and with a mighty hand?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32012, '&ldquo;Why should the Egyptians speak, and say, &lsquo;He brought them out to harm them, to kill them in the mountains, and to consume them from the face of the earth&rsquo;? Turn from Your fierce wrath, and relent from this harm to Your people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32013, '&ldquo;Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, Your servants, to whom You swore by Your own self, and said to them, &lsquo;I will multiply your descendants as the stars of heaven; and all this land that I have spoken of I give to your descendants, and they shall inherit');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32014, 'So the Lord relented from the harm which He said He would do to His people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32015, 'And Moses turned and went down from the mountain, and the two tablets of the Testimony were in his hand. The tablets were written on both sides; on the one side and on the other they were written.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32016, 'Now the tablets were the work of God, and the writing was the writing of God engraved on the tablets.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32017, 'And when Joshua heard the noise of the people as they shouted, he said to Moses, &ldquo;There is a noise of war in the camp.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32018, 'But he said: &ldquo;It is not the noise of the shout of victory, Nor the noise of the cry of defeat, But the sound of singing I hear.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32019, 'So it was, as soon as he came near the camp, that he saw the calf and the dancing. So Moses&rsquo; anger became hot, and he cast the tablets out of his hands and broke them at the foot of the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32020, 'Then he took the calf which they had made, burned it in the fire, and ground it to powder; and he scattered it on the water and made the children of Israel drink it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32021, 'And Moses said to Aaron, &ldquo;What did this people do to you that you have brought so great a sin upon them?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32022, 'So Aaron said, &ldquo;Do not let the anger of my lord become hot. You know the people, that they are set on evil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32023, '&ldquo;For they said to me, &lsquo;Make us gods that shall go before us; as for this Moses, the man who brought us out of the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32024, '&ldquo;And I said to them, &lsquo;Whoever has any gold, let them break it off.&rsquo; So they gave it to me, and I cast it into the fire, and this calf came out.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32025, 'Now when Moses saw that the people were unrestrained (for Aaron had not restrained them, to their shame among their enemies),');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32026, 'then Moses stood in the entrance of the camp, and said, &ldquo;Whoever is on the Lord&rsquo;s side &ndash; come to me!&rdquo; And all the sons of Levi gathered themselves together to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32027, 'And he said to them, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;Let every man put his sword on his side, and go in and out from entrance to entrance throughout the camp, and let every man kill his brother, every man his companion, and every man his neighbor.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32028, 'So the sons of Levi did according to the word of Moses. And about three thousand men of the people fell that day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32029, 'Then Moses said, &ldquo;Consecrate yourselves today to the Lord, that He may bestow on you a blessing this day, for every man has opposed his son and his brother.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32030, 'Now it came to pass on the next day that Moses said to the people, &ldquo;You have committed a great sin. So now I will go up to the Lord; perhaps I can make atonement for your sin.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32031, 'Then Moses returned to the Lord and said, &ldquo;Oh, these people have committed a great sin, and have made for themselves a god of gold!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32032, '&ldquo;Yet now, if You will forgive their sin &ndash; but if not, I pray, blot me out of Your book which You have written.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32033, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Whoever has sinned against Me, I will blot him out of My book.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32034, '&ldquo;Now therefore, go, lead the people to the place of which I have spoken to you. Behold, My Angel shall go before you. Nevertheless, in the day when I visit for punishment, I will visit punishment upon them for their sin.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 32035, 'So the Lord plagued the people because of what they did with the calf which Aaron made.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33001, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Depart and go up from here, you and the people whom you have brought out of the land of Egypt, to the land of which I swore to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, saying, &lsquo;To your descendants I will give it.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33002, '&ldquo;And I will send My Angel before you, and I will drive out the Canaanite and the Amorite and the Hittite and the Perizzite and the Hivite and the Jebusite.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33003, '&ldquo;Go up to a land flowing with milk and honey; for I will not go up in your midst, lest I consume you on the way, for you are a stiff-necked people.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33004, 'And when the people heard this bad news, they mourned, and no one put on his ornaments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33005, 'For the Lord had said to Moses, &ldquo;Say to the children of Israel, &lsquo;You are a stiff-necked people. I could come up into your midst in one moment and consume you. Now therefore, take off your ornaments, that I may know what to do to you.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33006, 'So the children of Israel stripped themselves of their ornaments by Mount Horeb.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33007, 'Moses took his tent and pitched it outside the camp, far from the camp, and called it the tabernacle of meeting. And it came to pass that everyone who sought the Lord went out to the tabernacle of meeting which was outside the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33008, 'So it was, whenever Moses went out to the tabernacle, that all the people rose, and each man stood at his tent door and watched Moses until he had gone into the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33009, 'And it came to pass, when Moses entered the tabernacle, that the pillar of cloud descended and stood at the door of the tabernacle, and the Lord talked with Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33010, 'All the people saw the pillar of cloud standing at the tabernacle door, and all the people rose and worshiped, each man in his tent door.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33011, 'So the* Lord spoke to Moses face to face, as a man speaks to his friend. And he would return to the camp, but his servant Joshua the son of Nun, a young man, did not depart from the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33012, 'Then Moses said to the Lord, &ldquo;See, You say to me, &lsquo;Bring up this people.&rsquo; But You have not let me know whom You will send with me. Yet You have said, &lsquo;I know you by name, and you have also found grace in My sight.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33013, '&ldquo;Now therefore, I pray, if I have found grace in Your sight, show me now Your way, that I may know You and that I may find grace in Your sight. And consider that this nation is Your people.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33014, 'And He said, &ldquo;My Presence will go with you, and I will give you rest.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33015, 'Then he said to Him, &ldquo;If Your Presence does not go with us, do not bring us up from here.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33016, '&ldquo;For how then will it be known that Your people and I have found grace in Your sight, except You go with us? So we shall be separate, Your people and I, from all the people who are upon the face of the earth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33017, 'So the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;I will also do this thing that you have spoken; for you have found grace in My sight, and I know you by name.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33018, 'And he said, &ldquo;Please, show me Your glory.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33019, 'Then He said, &ldquo;I will make all My goodness pass before you, and I will proclaim the name of the Lord before you. I will be gracious to whom I will be gracious, and I will have compassion on whom I will have compassion.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33020, 'But He said, &ldquo;You cannot see My face; for no man shall see Me, and live.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33021, 'And the Lord said, &ldquo;Here is a place by Me, and you shall stand on the rock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33022, '&ldquo;So it shall be, while My glory passes by, that I will put you in the cleft of the rock, and will cover you with My hand while I pass by.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 33023, '&ldquo;Then I will take away My hand, and you shall see My back; but My face shall not be seen.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34001, 'And the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Cut two tablets of stone like the first ones, and I will write on these tablets the words that were on the first tablets which you broke.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34002, '&ldquo;So be ready in the morning, and come up in the morning to Mount Sinai, and present yourself to Me there on the top of the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34003, '&ldquo;And no man shall come up with you, and let no man be seen throughout all the mountain; let neither flocks nor herds feed before that mountain.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34004, 'So he cut two tablets of stone like the first ones. Then Moses rose early in the morning and went up Mount Sinai, as the Lord had commanded him; and he took in his hand the two tablets of stone.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34005, 'Now the Lord descended in the cloud and stood with him there, and proclaimed the name of the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34006, 'And the Lord passed before him and proclaimed, &ldquo;The Lord, the Lord God, merciful and gracious, longsuffering, and abounding in goodness and truth,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34007, '&ldquo;keeping mercy for thousands, forgiving iniquity and transgression and sin, by no means clearing the guilty, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children and the children&rsquo;s children to the third and the fourth generation.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34008, 'So Moses made haste and bowed his head toward the earth, and worshiped.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34009, 'Then he said, &ldquo;If now I have found grace in Your sight, O Lord, let my Lord, I pray, go among us, even though we are a stiff-necked people; and pardon our iniquity and our sin, and take us as Your inheritance.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34010, 'And He said: &ldquo;Behold, I make a covenant. Before all your people I will do marvels such as have not been done in all the earth, nor in any nation; and all the people among whom you are shall see the work of the Lord. For it is an awesome thing that I will ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34011, '&ldquo;Observe what I command you this day. Behold, I am driving out from before you the Amorite and the Canaanite and the Hittite and the Perizzite and the Hivite and the Jebusite.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34012, '&ldquo;Take heed to yourself, lest you make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land where you are going, lest it be a snare in your midst.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34013, '&ldquo;But you shall destroy their altars, break their sacred pillars, and cut down their wooden images');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34014, '&ldquo;(for you shall worship no other god, for the Lord, whose name is Jealous, is a jealous God),');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34015, '&ldquo;lest you make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land, and they play the harlot with their gods and make sacrifice to their gods, and one of them invites you and you eat of his sacrifice,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34016, '&ldquo;and you take of his daughters for your sons, and his daughters play the harlot with their gods and make your sons play the harlot with their gods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34017, '&ldquo;You shall make no molded gods for yourselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34018, '&ldquo;The Feast of Unleavened Bread you shall keep. Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, in the appointed time of the month of Abib; for in the month of Abib you came out from Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34019, '&ldquo;All that open the womb are Mine, and every male firstborn among your livestock, whether ox or sheep.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34020, '&ldquo;But the firstborn of a donkey you shall redeem with a lamb. And if you will not redeem him, then you shall break his neck. All the firstborn of your sons you shall redeem. And none shall appear before Me empty-handed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34021, '&ldquo;Six days you shall work, but on the seventh day you shall rest; in plowing time and in harvest you shall rest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34022, '&ldquo;And you shall observe the Feast of Weeks, of the firstfruits of wheat harvest, and the Feast of Ingathering at the year&rsquo;s end.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34023, '&ldquo;Three times in the year all your men shall appear before the Lord, the Lord God of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34024, '&ldquo;For I will cast out the nations before you and enlarge your borders; neither will any man covet your land when you go up to appear before the Lord your God three times in the year.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34025, '&ldquo;You shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leaven, nor shall the sacrifice of the Feast of the Passover be left until morning.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34026, '&ldquo;The first of the firstfruits of your land you shall bring to the house of the Lord your God. You shall not boil a young goat in its mother&rsquo;s milk.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34027, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Write these words, for according to the tenor of these words I have made a covenant with you and with Israel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34028, 'So he was there with the Lord forty days and forty nights; he neither ate bread nor drank water. And He wrote on the tablets the words of the covenant, the Ten Commandments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34029, 'Now it was so, when Moses came down from Mount Sinai (and the two tablets of the Testimony were in Moses&rsquo; hand when he came down from the mountain), that Moses did not know that the skin of his face shone while he talked with Him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34030, 'So when Aaron and all the children of Israel saw Moses, behold, the skin of his face shone, and they were afraid to come near him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34031, 'Then Moses called to them, and Aaron and all the rulers of the congregation returned to him; and Moses talked with them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34032, 'Afterward all the children of Israel came near, and he gave them as commandments all that the Lord had spoken with him on Mount Sinai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34033, 'And when Moses had finished speaking with them, he put a veil on his face.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34034, 'But whenever Moses went in before the Lord to speak with Him, he would take the veil off until he came out; and he would come out and speak to the children of Israel whatever he had been commanded.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 34035, 'And whenever the children of Israel saw the face of Moses, that the skin of Moses&rsquo; face shone, then Moses would put the veil on his face again, until he went in to speak with Him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35001, 'Then Moses gathered all the congregation of the children of Israel together, and said to them, &ldquo;These are the words which the Lord has commanded you to do:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35002, '&ldquo;Work shall be done for six days, but the seventh day shall be a holy day for you, a Sabbath of rest to the Lord. Whoever does any work on it shall be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35003, '&ldquo;You shall kindle no fire throughout your dwellings on the Sabbath day.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35004, 'And Moses spoke to all the congregation of the children of Israel, saying, &ldquo;This is the thing which the Lord commanded, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35005, '&lsquo;Take from among you an offering to the Lord. Whoever is of a willing heart, let him bring it as an offering to the Lord: gold, silver, and bronze;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35006, '&lsquo;blue, purple, and scarlet thread, fine linen, and goats&rsquo; hair;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35007, '&lsquo;ram skins dyed red, badger skins, and acacia wood;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35008, '&lsquo;oil for the light, and spices for the anointing oil and for the sweet incense;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35009, '&lsquo;onyx stones, and stones to be set in the ephod and in the breastplate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35010, '&lsquo;All who are gifted artisans among you shall come and make all that the Lord has commanded:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35011, '&lsquo;the tabernacle, its tent, its covering, its clasps, its boards, its bars, its pillars, and its sockets;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35012, '&lsquo;the ark and its poles, with the mercy seat, and the veil of the covering;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35013, '&lsquo;the table and its poles, all its utensils, and the showbread;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35014, '&lsquo;also the lampstand for the light, its utensils, its lamps, and the oil for the light;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35015, '&lsquo;the incense altar, its poles, the anointing oil, the sweet incense, and the screen for the door at the entrance of the tabernacle;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35016, '&lsquo;the altar of burnt offering with its bronze grating, its poles, all its utensils, and the laver and its base;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35017, '&lsquo;the hangings of the court, its pillars, their sockets, and the screen for the gate of the court;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35018, '&lsquo;the pegs of the tabernacle, the pegs of the court, and their cords;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35019, '&lsquo;the garments of ministry, for ministering in the holy place &ndash; the holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments of his sons, to minister as priests.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35020, 'And all the congregation of the children of Israel departed from the presence of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35021, 'Then everyone came whose heart was stirred, and everyone whose spirit was willing, and they brought the Lord&rsquo;s offering for the work of the tabernacle of meeting, for all its service, and for the holy garments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35022, 'They came, both men and women, as many as had a willing heart, and brought earrings and nose rings, rings and necklaces, all jewelry of gold, that is, every man who made an offering of gold to the Lord.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35023, 'And every man, with whom was found blue, purple, and scarlet thread, fine linen, and goats&rsquo; hair, red skins of rams, and badger skins, brought them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35024, 'Everyone who offered an offering of silver or bronze brought the Lord&rsquo;s offering. And everyone with whom was found acacia wood for any work of the service, brought it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35025, 'All the women who were gifted artisans spun yarn with their hands, and brought what they had spun, of blue, purple, and scarlet, and fine linen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35026, 'And all the women whose hearts stirred with wisdom spun yarn of goats&rsquo; hair.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35027, 'The rulers brought onyx stones, and the stones to be set in the ephod and in the breastplate,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35028, 'and spices and oil for the light, for the anointing oil, and for the sweet incense.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35029, 'The children of Israel brought a freewill offering to the Lord, all the men and women whose hearts were willing to bring material for all kinds of work which the Lord, by the hand of Moses, had commanded to be done.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35030, 'And Moses said to the children of Israel, &ldquo;See, the Lord has called by name Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35031, '&ldquo;and He has filled him with the Spirit of God, in wisdom and understanding, in knowledge and all manner of workmanship,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35032, '&ldquo;to design artistic works, to work in gold and silver and bronze,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35033, '&ldquo;in cutting jewels for setting, in carving wood, and to work in all manner of artistic workmanship.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35034, '&ldquo;And He has put in his heart the ability to teach, in him and Aholiab the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 35035, '&ldquo;He has filled them with skill to do all manner of work of the engraver and the designer and the tapestry maker, in blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine linen, and of the weaver &ndash; those who do every work and those who design artistic works.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36001, '&ldquo;And Bezalel and Aholiab, and every gifted artisan in whom the Lord has put wisdom and understanding, to know how to do all manner of work for the service of the sanctuary, shall do according to all that the Lord has commanded.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36002, 'Then Moses called Bezalel and Aholiab, and every gifted artisan in whose heart the Lord had put wisdom, everyone whose heart was stirred, to come and do the work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36003, 'And they received from Moses all the offering which the children of Israel had brought for the work of the service of making the sanctuary. So they continued bringing to him freewill offerings every morning.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36004, 'Then all the craftsmen who were doing all the work of the sanctuary came, each from the work he was doing,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36005, 'and they spoke to Moses, saying, &ldquo;The people bring much more than enough for the service of the work which the Lord commanded us to do.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36006, 'So Moses gave a commandment, and they caused it to be proclaimed throughout the camp, saying, &ldquo;Let neither man nor woman do any more work for the offering of the sanctuary.&rdquo; And the people were restrained from bringing,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36007, 'for the material they had was sufficient for all the work to be done &ndash; indeed too much.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36008, 'Then all the gifted artisans among them who worked on the tabernacle made ten curtains woven of fine linen, and of blue, purple, and scarlet thread; with artistic designs of cherubim they made them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36009, 'The length of each curtain was twenty-eight cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits; the curtains were all the same size.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36010, 'And he coupled five curtains to one another, and the other five curtains he coupled to one another.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36011, 'He made loops of blue yarn on the edge of the curtain on the selvedge of one set; likewise he did on the outer edge of the other curtain of the second set.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36012, 'Fifty loops he made on one curtain, and fifty loops he made on the edge of the curtain on the end of the second set; the loops held one curtain to another.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36013, 'And he made fifty clasps of gold, and coupled the curtains to one another with the clasps, that it might be one tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36014, 'He made curtains of goats&rsquo; hair for the tent over the tabernacle; he made eleven curtains.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36015, 'The length of each curtain was thirty cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits; the eleven curtains were the same size.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36016, 'He coupled five curtains by themselves and six curtains by themselves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36017, 'And he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is outermost in one set, and fifty loops he made on the edge of the curtain of the second set.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36018, 'He also made fifty bronze clasps to couple the tent together, that it might be one.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36019, 'Then he made a covering for the tent of ram skins dyed red, and a covering of badger skins above that.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36020, 'For the tabernacle he made boards of acacia wood, standing upright.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36021, 'The length of each board was ten cubits, and the width of each board a cubit and a half.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36022, 'Each board had two tenons for binding one to another. Thus he made for all the boards of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36023, 'And he made boards for the tabernacle, twenty boards for the south side.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36024, 'Forty sockets of silver he made to go under the twenty boards: two sockets under each of the boards for its two tenons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36025, 'And for the other side of the tabernacle, the north side, he made twenty boards');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36026, 'and their forty sockets of silver: two sockets under each of the boards.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36027, 'For the west side of the tabernacle he made six boards.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36028, 'He also made two boards for the two back corners of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36029, 'And they were coupled at the bottom and coupled together at the top by one ring. Thus he made both of them for the two corners.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36030, 'So there were eight boards and their sockets &ndash; sixteen sockets of silver &ndash; two sockets under each of the boards.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36031, 'And he made bars of acacia wood: five for the boards on one side of the tabernacle,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36032, 'five bars for the boards on the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the tabernacle on the far side westward.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36033, 'And he made the middle bar to pass through the boards from one end to the other.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36034, 'He overlaid the boards with gold, made their rings of gold to be holders for the bars, and overlaid the bars with gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36035, 'And he made a veil of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen; it was worked with an artistic design of cherubim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36036, 'He made for it four pillars of acacia wood, and overlaid them with gold, with their hooks of gold; and he cast four sockets of silver for them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36037, 'He also made a screen for the tabernacle door, of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and fine woven linen, made by a weaver,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 36038, 'and its five pillars with their hooks. And he overlaid their capitals and their rings with gold, but their five sockets were bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37001, 'Then Bezalel made the ark of acacia wood; two and a half cubits was its length, a cubit and a half its width, and a cubit and a half its height.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37002, 'He overlaid it with pure gold inside and outside, and made a molding of gold all around it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37003, 'And he cast for it four rings of gold to be set in its four corners: two rings on one side, and two rings on the other side of it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37004, 'He made poles of acacia wood, and overlaid them with gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37005, 'And he put the poles into the rings at the sides of the ark, to bear the ark.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37006, 'He also made the mercy seat of pure gold; two and a half cubits was its length and a cubit and a half its width.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37007, 'He made two cherubim of beaten gold; he made them of one piece at the two ends of the mercy seat:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37008, 'one cherub at one end on this side, and the other cherub at the other end on that side. He made the cherubim at the two ends of one piece with the mercy seat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37009, 'The cherubim spread out their wings above, and covered the mercy seat with their wings. They faced one another; the faces of the cherubim were toward the mercy seat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37010, 'He made the table of acacia wood; two cubits was its length, a cubit its width, and a cubit and a half its height.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37011, 'And he overlaid it with pure gold, and made a molding of gold all around it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37012, 'Also he made a frame of a handbreadth all around it, and made a molding of gold for the frame all around it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37013, 'And he cast for it four rings of gold, and put the rings on the four corners that were at its four legs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37014, 'The rings were close to the frame, as holders for the poles to bear the table.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37015, 'And he made the poles of acacia wood to bear the table, and overlaid them with gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37016, 'He made of pure gold the utensils which were on the table: its dishes, its cups, its bowls, and its pitchers for pouring.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37017, 'He also made the lampstand of pure gold; of hammered work he made the lampstand. Its shaft, its branches, its bowls, its ornamental knobs, and its flowers were of the same piece.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37018, 'And six branches came out of its sides: three branches of the lampstand out of one side, and three branches of the lampstand out of the other side.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37019, 'There were three bowls made like almond blossoms on one branch, with an ornamental knob and a flower, and three bowls made like almond blossoms on the other branch, with an ornamental knob and a flower &ndash; and so for the six branches coming out of the lampsta');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37020, 'And on the lampstand itself were four bowls made like almond blossoms, each with its ornamental knob and flower.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37021, 'There was a knob under the first two branches of the same, a knob under the second two branches of the same, and a knob under the third two branches of the same, according to the six branches extending from it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37022, 'Their knobs and their branches were of one piece; all of it was one hammered piece of pure gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37023, 'And he made its seven lamps, its wick-trimmers, and its trays of pure gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37024, 'Of a talent of pure gold he made it, with all its utensils.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37025, 'He made the incense altar of acacia wood. Its length was a cubit and its width a cubit &ndash; it was square &ndash; and two cubits was its height. Its horns were of one piece with it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37026, 'And he overlaid it with pure gold: its top, its sides all around, and its horns. He also made for it a molding of gold all around it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37027, 'He made two rings of gold for it under its molding, by its two corners on both sides, as holders for the poles with which to bear it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37028, 'And he made the poles of acacia wood, and overlaid them with gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 37029, 'He also made the holy anointing oil and the pure incense of sweet spices, according to the work of the perfumer.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38001, 'He made the altar of burnt offering of acacia wood; five cubits was its length and five cubits its width &ndash; it was square &ndash; and its height was three cubits.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38002, 'He made its horns on its four corners; the horns were of one piece with it. And he overlaid it with bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38003, 'He made all the utensils for the altar: the pans, the shovels, the basins, the forks, and the firepans; all its utensils he made of bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38004, 'And he made a grate of bronze network for the altar, under its rim, midway from the bottom.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38005, 'He cast four rings for the four corners of the bronze grating, as holders for the poles.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38006, 'And he made the poles of acacia wood, and overlaid them with bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38007, 'Then he put the poles into the rings on the sides of the altar, with which to bear it. He made the altar hollow with boards.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38008, 'He made the laver of bronze and its base of bronze, from the bronze mirrors of the serving women who assembled at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38009, 'Then he made the court on the south side; the hangings of the court were of fine woven linen, one hundred cubits long.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38010, 'There were twenty pillars for them, with twenty bronze sockets. The hooks of the pillars and their bands were silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38011, 'On the north side the hangings were one hundred cubits long, with twenty pillars and their twenty bronze sockets. The hooks of the pillars and their bands were silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38012, 'And on the west side there were hangings of fifty cubits, with ten pillars and their ten sockets. The hooks of the pillars and their bands were silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38013, 'For the east side the hangings were fifty cubits.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38014, 'The hangings of one side of the gate were fifteen cubits long, with their three pillars and their three sockets,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38015, 'and the same for the other side of the court gate; on this side and that were hangings of fifteen cubits, with their three pillars and their three sockets.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38016, 'All the hangings of the court all around were of fine woven linen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38017, 'The sockets for the pillars were bronze, the hooks of the pillars and their bands were silver, and the overlay of their capitals was silver; and all the pillars of the court had bands of silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38018, 'The screen for the gate of the court was woven of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and of fine woven linen. The length was twenty cubits, and the height along its width was five cubits, corresponding to the hangings of the court.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38019, 'And there were four pillars with their four sockets of bronze; their hooks were silver, and the overlay of their capitals and their bands was silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38020, 'All the pegs of the tabernacle, and of the court all around, were bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38021, 'This is the inventory of the tabernacle, the tabernacle of the Testimony, which was counted according to the commandment of Moses, for the service of the Levites, by the hand of Ithamar, son of Aaron the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38022, 'Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah, made all that the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38023, 'And with him was Aholiab the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan, an engraver and designer, a weaver of blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and of fine linen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38024, 'All the gold that was used in all the work of the holy place, that is, the gold of the offering, was twenty-nine talents and seven hundred and thirty shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38025, 'And the silver from those who were numbered of the congregation was one hundred talents and one thousand seven hundred and seventy-five shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38026, 'a bekah for each man (that is, half a shekel, according to the shekel of the sanctuary), for everyone included in the numbering from twenty years old and above, for six hundred and three thousand, five hundred and fifty men.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38027, 'And from the hundred talents of silver were cast the sockets of the sanctuary and the bases of the veil: one hundred sockets from the hundred talents, one talent for each socket.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38028, 'Then from the one thousand seven hundred and seventy-five shekels he made hooks for the pillars, overlaid their capitals, and made bands for them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38029, 'The offering of bronze was seventy talents and two thousand four hundred shekels.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38030, 'And with it he made the sockets for the door of the tabernacle of meeting, the bronze altar, the bronze grating for it, and all the utensils for the altar,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 38031, 'the sockets for the court all around, the bases for the court gate, all the pegs for the tabernacle, and all the pegs for the court all around.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39001, 'Of the blue, purple, and scarlet thread they made garments of ministry, for ministering in the holy place, and made the holy garments for Aaron, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39002, 'He made the ephod of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and of fine woven linen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39003, 'And they beat the gold into thin sheets and cut it into threads, to work it in with the blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and the fine linen, into artistic designs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39004, 'They made shoulder straps for it to couple it together; it was coupled together at its two edges.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39005, 'And the intricately woven band of his ephod that was on it was of the same workmanship, woven of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and of fine woven linen, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39006, 'And they set onyx stones, enclosed in settings of gold; they were engraved, as signets are engraved, with the names of the sons of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39007, 'He put them on the shoulders of the ephod as memorial stones for the sons of Israel, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39008, 'And he made the breastplate, artistically woven like the workmanship of the ephod, of gold, blue, purple, and scarlet thread, and of fine woven linen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39009, 'They made the breastplate square by doubling it; a span was its length and a span its width when doubled.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39010, 'And they set in it four rows of stones: a row with a sardius, a topaz, and an emerald was the first row;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39011, 'the second row, a turquoise, a sapphire, and a diamond;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39012, 'the third row, a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39013, 'the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper. They were enclosed in settings of gold in their mountings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39014, 'There were twelve stones according to the names of the sons of Israel: according to their names, engraved like a signet, each one with its own name according to the twelve tribes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39015, 'And they made chains for the breastplate at the ends, like braided cords of pure gold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39016, 'They also made two settings of gold and two gold rings, and put the two rings on the two ends of the breastplate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39017, 'And they put the two braided chains of gold in the two rings on the ends of the breastplate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39018, 'The two ends of the two braided chains they fastened in the two settings, and put them on the shoulder straps of the ephod in the front.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39019, 'And they made two rings of gold and put them on the two ends of the breastplate, on the edge of it, which was on the inward side of the ephod.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39020, 'They made two other gold rings and put them on the two shoulder straps, underneath the ephod toward its front, right at the seam above the intricately woven band of the ephod.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39021, 'And they bound the breastplate by means of its rings to the rings of the ephod with a blue cord, so that it would be above the intricately woven band of the ephod, and that the breastplate would not come loose from the ephod, as the Lord had commanded Mos');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39022, 'He made the robe of the ephod of woven work, all of blue.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39023, 'And there was an opening in the middle of the robe, like the opening in a coat of mail, with a woven binding all around the opening, so that it would not tear.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39024, 'They made on the hem of the robe pomegranates of blue, purple, and scarlet, and of fine woven linen.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39025, 'And they made bells of pure gold, and put the bells between the pomegranates on the hem of the robe all around between the pomegranates:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39026, 'a bell and a pomegranate, a bell and a pomegranate, all around the hem of the robe to minister in, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39027, 'They made tunics, artistically woven of fine linen, for Aaron and his sons,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39028, 'a turban of fine linen, exquisite hats of fine linen, short trousers of fine woven linen,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39029, 'and a sash of fine woven linen with blue, purple, and scarlet thread, made by a weaver, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39030, 'Then they made the plate of the holy crown of pure gold, and wrote on it an inscription like the engraving of a signet:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39031, 'And they tied to it a blue cord, to fasten it above on the turban, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39032, 'Thus all the work of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting was finished. And the children of Israel did according to all that the Lord had commanded Moses; so they did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39033, 'And they brought the tabernacle to Moses, the tent and all its furnishings: its clasps, its boards, its bars, its pillars, and its sockets;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39034, 'the covering of ram skins dyed red, the covering of badger skins, and the veil of the covering;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39035, 'the ark of the Testimony with its poles, and the mercy seat;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39036, 'the table, all its utensils, and the showbread;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39037, 'the pure gold lampstand with its lamps (the lamps set in order), all its utensils, and the oil for light;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39038, 'the gold altar, the anointing oil, and the sweet incense; the screen for the tabernacle door;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39039, 'the bronze altar, its grate of bronze, its poles, and all its utensils; the laver with its base;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39040, 'the hangings of the court, its pillars and its sockets, the screen for the court gate, its cords, and its pegs; all the utensils for the service of the tabernacle, for the tent of meeting;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39041, 'and the garments of ministry, to minister in the holy place: the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and his sons&rsquo; garments, to minister as priests.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39042, 'According to all that the Lord had commanded Moses, so the children of Israel did all the work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 39043, 'Then Moses looked over all the work, and indeed they had done it; as the Lord had commanded, just so they had done it. And Moses blessed them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40001, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40002, '&ldquo;On the first day of the first month you shall set up the tabernacle of the tent of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40003, '&ldquo;You shall put in it the ark of the Testimony, and partition off the ark with the veil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40004, '&ldquo;You shall bring in the table and arrange the things that are to be set in order on it; and you shall bring in the lampstand and light its lamps.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40005, '&ldquo;You shall also set the altar of gold for the incense before the ark of the Testimony, and put up the screen for the door of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40006, '&ldquo;Then you shall set the altar of the burnt offering before the door of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40007, '&ldquo;And you shall set the laver between the tabernacle of meeting and the altar, and put water in it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40008, '&ldquo;You shall set up the court all around, and hang up the screen at the court gate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40009, '&ldquo;And you shall take the anointing oil, and anoint the tabernacle and all that is in it; and you shall hallow it and all its utensils, and it shall be holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40010, '&ldquo;You shall anoint the altar of the burnt offering and all its utensils, and consecrate the altar. The altar shall be most holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40011, '&ldquo;And you shall anoint the laver and its base, and consecrate it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40012, '&ldquo;Then you shall bring Aaron and his sons to the door of the tabernacle of meeting and wash them with water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40013, '&ldquo;You shall put the holy garments on Aaron, and anoint him and consecrate him, that he may minister to Me as priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40014, '&ldquo;And you shall bring his sons and clothe them with tunics.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40015, '&ldquo;You shall anoint them, as you anointed their father, that they may minister to Me as priests; for their anointing shall surely be an everlasting priesthood throughout their generations.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40016, 'Thus Moses did; according to all that the Lord had commanded him, so he did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40017, 'And it came to pass in the first month of the second year, on the first day of the month, that the tabernacle was raised up.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40018, 'So Moses raised up the tabernacle, fastened its sockets, set up its boards, put in its bars, and raised up its pillars.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40019, 'And he spread out the tent over the tabernacle and put the covering of the tent on top of it, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40020, 'He took the Testimony and put it into the ark, inserted the poles through the rings of the ark, and put the mercy seat on top of the ark.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40021, 'And he brought the ark into the tabernacle, hung up the veil of the covering, and partitioned off the ark of the Testimony, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40022, 'He put the table in the tabernacle of meeting, on the north side of the tabernacle, outside the veil;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40023, 'and he set the bread in order upon it before the Lord, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40024, 'He put the lampstand in the tabernacle of meeting, across from the table, on the south side of the tabernacle;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40025, 'and he lit the lamps before the Lord, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40026, 'He put the gold altar in the tabernacle of meeting in front of the veil;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40027, 'and he burned sweet incense on it, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40028, 'He hung up the screen at the door of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40029, 'And he put the altar of burnt offering before the door of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting, and offered upon it the burnt offering and the grain offering, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40030, 'He set the laver between the tabernacle of meeting and the altar, and put water there for washing;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40031, 'and Moses, Aaron, and his sons would wash their hands and their feet with water from it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40032, 'Whenever they went into the tabernacle of meeting, and when they came near the altar, they washed, as the Lord had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40033, 'And he raised up the court all around the tabernacle and the altar, and hung up the screen of the court gate. So Moses finished the work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40034, 'Then the cloud covered the tabernacle of meeting, and the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40035, 'And Moses was not able to enter the tabernacle of meeting, because the cloud rested above it, and the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40036, 'Whenever the cloud was taken up from above the tabernacle, the children of Israel would go onward in all their journeys.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40037, 'But if the cloud was not taken up, then they did not journey till the day that it was taken up.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Exod', 40038, 'For the cloud of the Lord was above the tabernacle by day, and fire was over it by night, in the sight of all the house of Israel, throughout all their journeys.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1001, 'Now the LORD called to Moses, and spoke to him from the tabernacle of meeting, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When any one of you brings an offering to the LORD, you shall bring your offering of the livestock &ndash; of the herd and of the flock.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1003, '&lsquo;If his offering is a burnt sacrifice of the herd, let him offer a male without blemish; he shall offer it of his own free will at the door of the tabernacle of meeting before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1004, 'Then he shall put his hand on the head of the burnt offering, and it will be accepted on his behalf to make atonement for him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1005, 'He shall kill the bull before the LORD; and the priests, Aaron&rsquo;s sons, shall bring the blood and sprinkle the blood all around on the altar that is by the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1006, 'And he shall skin the burnt offering and cut it into its pieces.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1007, 'The sons of Aaron the priest shall put fire on the altar, and lay the wood in order on the fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1008, 'Then the priests, Aaron&rsquo;s sons, shall lay the parts, the head, and the fat in order on the wood that is on the fire upon the altar;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1009, 'but he shall wash its entrails and its legs with water. And the priest shall burn all on the altar as a burnt sacrifice, an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1010, '&lsquo;If his offering is of the flocks &ndash; of the sheep or of the goats &ndash; as a burnt sacrifice, he shall bring a male without blemish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1011, 'He shall kill it on the north side of the altar before the LORD; and the priests, Aaron&rsquo;s sons, shall sprinkle its blood all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1012, 'And he shall cut it into its pieces, with its head and its fat; and the priest shall lay them in order on the wood that is on the fire upon the altar;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1013, 'but he shall wash the entrails and the legs with water. Then the priest shall bring it all and burn it on the altar; it is a burnt sacrifice, an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1014, '&lsquo;And if the burnt sacrifice of his offering to the LORD is of birds, then he shall bring his offering of turtledoves or young pigeons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1015, 'The priest shall bring it to the altar, wring off its head, and burn it on the altar; its blood shall be drained out at the side of the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1016, 'And he shall remove its crop with its feathers and cast it beside the altar on the east side, into the place for ashes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 1017, 'Then he shall split it at its wings, but shall not divide it completely; and the priest shall burn it on the altar, on the wood that is on the fire. It is a burnt sacrifice, an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2001, '&lsquo;When anyone offers a grain offering to the LORD, his offering shall be of fine flour. And he shall pour oil on it, and put frankincense on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2002, 'He shall bring it to Aaron&rsquo;s sons, the priests, one of whom shall take from it his handful of fine flour and oil with all the frankincense. And the priest shall burn it as a memorial on the altar, an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2003, 'The rest of the grain offering shall be Aaron&rsquo;s and his sons&rsquo;. It is most holy of the offerings to the LORD made by fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2004, '&lsquo;And if you bring as an offering a grain offering baked in the oven, it shall be unleavened cakes of fine flour mixed with oil, or unleavened wafers anointed with oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2005, 'But if your offering is a grain offering baked in a pan, it shall be of fine flour, unleavened, mixed with oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2006, 'You shall break it in pieces and pour oil on it; it is a grain offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2007, '&lsquo;If your offering is a grain offering baked in a covered pan, it shall be made of fine flour with oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2008, 'You shall bring the grain offering that is made of these things to the LORD. And when it is presented to the priest, he shall bring it to the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2009, 'Then the priest shall take from the grain offering a memorial portion, and burn it on the altar. It is an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2010, 'And what is left of the grain offering shall be Aaron&rsquo;s and his sons&rsquo;. It is most holy of the offerings to the LORD made by fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2011, 'No grain offering which you bring to the LORD shall be made with leaven, for you shall burn no leaven nor any honey in any offering to the LORD made by fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2012, 'As for the offering of the firstfruits, you shall offer them to the LORD, but they shall not be burned on the altar for a sweet aroma.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2013, 'And every offering of your grain offering you shall season with salt; you shall not allow the salt of the covenant of your God to be lacking from your grain offering. With all your offerings you shall offer salt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2014, '&lsquo;If you offer a grain offering of your firstfruits to the LORD, you shall offer for the grain offering of your firstfruits green heads of grain roasted on the fire, grain beaten from full heads.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2015, 'And you shall put oil on it, and lay frankincense on it. It is a grain offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 2016, 'Then the priest shall burn the memorial portion: part of its beaten grain and part of its oil, with all the frankincense, as an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3001, '&lsquo;When his offering is a sacrifice of a peace offering, if he offers it of the herd, whether male or female, he shall offer it without blemish before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3002, 'And he shall lay his hand on the head of his offering, and kill it at the door of the tabernacle of meeting; and Aaron&rsquo;s sons, the priests, shall sprinkle the blood all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3003, 'Then he shall offer from the sacrifice of the peace offering an offering made by fire to the LORD. The fat that covers the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3004, 'the two kidneys and the fat that is on them by the flanks, and the fatty lobe attached to the liver above the kidneys, he shall remove;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3005, 'and Aaron&rsquo;s sons shall burn it on the altar upon the burnt sacrifice, which is on the wood that is on the fire, as an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3006, '&lsquo;If his offering as a sacrifice of a peace offering to the LORD is of the flock, whether male or female, he shall offer it without blemish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3007, 'If he offers a lamb as his offering, then he shall offer it before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3008, 'And he shall lay his hand on the head of his offering, and kill it before the tabernacle of meeting; and Aaron&rsquo;s sons shall sprinkle its blood all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3009, '&lsquo;Then he shall offer from the sacrifice of the peace offering, as an offering made by fire to the LORD, its fat and the whole fat tail which he shall remove close to the backbone. And the fat that covers the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3010, 'the two kidneys and the fat that is on them by the flanks, and the fatty lobe attached to the liver above the kidneys, he shall remove;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3011, 'and the priest shall burn them on the altar as food, an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3012, '&lsquo;And if his offering is a goat, then he shall offer it before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3013, 'He shall lay his hand on its head and kill it before the tabernacle of meeting; and the sons of Aaron shall sprinkle its blood all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3014, 'Then he shall offer from it his offering, as an offering made by fire to the LORD. The fat that covers the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3015, 'the two kidneys and the fat that is on them by the flanks, and the fatty lobe attached to the liver above the kidneys, he shall remove;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3016, 'and the priest shall burn them on the altar as food, an offering made by fire for a sweet aroma; all the fat is the LORD&rsquo;s.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 3017, '&lsquo;This shall be a perpetual statute throughout your generations in all your dwellings: you shall eat neither fat nor blood.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4001, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;If a person sins unintentionally against any of the commandments of the LORD in anything which ought not to be done, and does any of them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4003, 'if the anointed priest sins, bringing guilt on the people, then let him offer to the LORD for his sin which he has sinned a young bull without blemish as a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4004, 'He shall bring the bull to the door of the tabernacle of meeting before the LORD, lay his hand on the bull&rsquo;s head, and kill the bull before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4005, 'Then the anointed priest shall take some of the bull&rsquo;s blood and bring it to the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4006, 'The priest shall dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle some of the blood seven times before the LORD, in front of the veil of the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4007, 'And the priest shall put some of the blood on the horns of the altar of sweet incense before the LORD, which is in the tabernacle of meeting; and he shall pour the remaining blood of the bull at the base of the altar of the burnt offering, which is at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4008, 'He shall take from it all the fat of the bull as the sin offering. The fat that covers the entrails and all the fat which is on the entrails,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4009, 'the two kidneys and the fat that is on them by the flanks, and the fatty lobe attached to the liver above the kidneys, he shall remove,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4010, 'as it was taken from the bull of the sacrifice of the peace offering; and the priest shall burn them on the altar of the burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4011, 'But the bull&rsquo;s hide and all its flesh, with its head and legs, its entrails and offal &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4012, 'the whole bull he shall carry outside the camp to a clean place, where the ashes are poured out, and burn it on wood with fire; where the ashes are poured out it shall be burned.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4013, '&lsquo;Now if the whole congregation of Israel sins unintentionally, and the thing is hidden from the eyes of the assembly, and they have done something against any of the commandments of the LORD in anything which should not be done, and are guilty;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4014, 'when the sin which they have committed becomes known, then the assembly shall offer a young bull for the sin, and bring it before the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4015, 'And the elders of the congregation shall lay their hands on the head of the bull before the LORD. Then the bull shall be killed before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4016, 'The anointed priest shall bring some of the bull&rsquo;s blood to the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4017, 'Then the priest shall dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle it seven times before the LORD, in front of the veil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4018, 'And he shall put some of the blood on the horns of the altar which is before the LORD, which is in the tabernacle of meeting; and he shall pour the remaining blood at the base of the altar of burnt offering, which is at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4019, 'He shall take all the fat from it and burn it on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4020, 'And he shall do with the bull as he did with the bull as a sin offering; thus he shall do with it. So the priest shall make atonement for them, and it shall be forgiven them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4021, 'Then he shall carry the bull outside the camp, and burn it as he burned the first bull. It is a sin offering for the assembly.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4022, '&lsquo;When a ruler has sinned, and done something unintentionally against any of the commandments of the LORD his God in anything which should not be done, and is guilty,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4023, 'or if his sin which he has committed comes to his knowledge, he shall bring as his offering a kid of the goats, a male without blemish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4024, 'And he shall lay his hand on the head of the goat, and kill it at the place where they kill the burnt offering before the LORD. It is a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4025, 'The priest shall take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger, put it on the horns of the altar of burnt offering, and pour its blood at the base of the altar of burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4026, 'And he shall burn all its fat on the altar, like the fat of the sacrifice of the peace offering. So the priest shall make atonement for him concerning his sin, and it shall be forgiven him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4027, '&lsquo;If anyone of the common people sins unintentionally by doing something against any of the commandments of the LORD in anything which ought not to be done, and is guilty,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4028, 'or if his sin which he has committed comes to his knowledge, then he shall bring as his offering a kid of the goats, a female without blemish, for his sin which he has committed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4029, 'And he shall lay his hand on the head of the sin offering, and kill the sin offering at the place of the burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4030, 'Then the priest shall take some of its blood with his finger, put it on the horns of the altar of burnt offering, and pour all the remaining blood at the base of the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4031, 'He shall remove all its fat, as fat is removed from the sacrifice of the peace offering; and the priest shall burn it on the altar for a sweet aroma to the LORD. So the priest shall make atonement for him, and it shall be forgiven him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4032, '&lsquo;If he brings a lamb as his sin offering, he shall bring a female without blemish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4033, 'Then he shall lay his hand on the head of the sin offering, and kill it as a sin offering at the place where they kill the burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4034, 'The priest shall take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger, put it on the horns of the altar of burnt offering, and pour all the remaining blood at the base of the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 4035, 'He shall remove all its fat, as the fat of the lamb is removed from the sacrifice of the peace offering. Then the priest shall burn it on the altar, according to the offerings made by fire to the LORD. So the priest shall make atonement for his sin that he has committed, and it shall be forgiven him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5001, '&lsquo;If a person sins in hearing the utterance of an oath, and is a witness, whether he has seen or known of the matter &ndash; if he does not tell it, he bears guilt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5002, '&lsquo;Or if a person touches any unclean thing, whether it is the carcass of an unclean beast, or the carcass of unclean livestock, or the carcass of unclean creeping things, and he is unaware of it, he also shall be unclean and guilty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5003, 'Or if he touches human uncleanness &ndash; whatever uncleanness with which a man may be defiled, and he is unaware of it &ndash; when he realizes it, then he shall be guilty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5004, '&lsquo;Or if a person swears, speaking thoughtlessly with his lips to do evil or to do good, whatever it is that a man may pronounce by an oath, and he is unaware of it &ndash; when he realizes it, then he shall be guilty in any of these matters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5005, '&lsquo;And it shall be, when he is guilty in any of these matters, that he shall confess that he has sinned in that thing;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5006, 'and he shall bring his trespass offering to the LORD for his sin which he has committed, a female from the flock, a lamb or a kid of the goats as a sin offering. So the priest shall make atonement for him concerning his sin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5007, '&lsquo;If he is not able to bring a lamb, then he shall bring to the LORD, for his trespass which he has committed, two turtledoves or two young pigeons: one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5008, 'And he shall bring them to the priest, who shall offer that which is for the sin offering first, and wring off its head from its neck, but shall not divide it completely.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5009, 'Then he shall sprinkle some of the blood of the sin offering on the side of the altar, and the rest of the blood shall be drained out at the base of the altar. It is a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5010, 'And he shall offer the second as a burnt offering according to the prescribed manner. So the priest shall make atonement on his behalf for his sin which he has committed, and it shall be forgiven him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5011, '&lsquo;But if he is not able to bring two turtledoves or two young pigeons, then he who sinned shall bring for his offering one-tenth of an ephah of fine flour as a sin offering. He shall put no oil on it, nor shall he put frankincense on it, for it is a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5012, 'Then he shall bring it to the priest, and the priest shall take his handful of it as a memorial portion, and burn it on the altar according to the offerings made by fire to the LORD. It is a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5013, 'The priest shall make atonement for him, for his sin that he has committed in any of these matters; and it shall be forgiven him. The rest shall be the priest&rsquo;s as a grain offering.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5014, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5015, '&ldquo;If a person commits a trespass, and sins unintentionally in regard to the holy things of the LORD, then he shall bring to the LORD as his trespass offering a ram without blemish from the flocks, with your valuation in shekels of silver according to the shekel of the sanctuary, as a trespass offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5016, 'And he shall make restitution for the harm that he has done in regard to the holy thing, and shall add one-fifth to it and give it to the priest. So the priest shall make atonement for him with the ram of the trespass offering, and it shall be forgiven him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5017, '&ldquo;If a person sins, and commits any of these things which are forbidden to be done by the commandments of the LORD, though he does not know it, yet he is guilty and shall bear his iniquity.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5018, 'And he shall bring to the priest a ram without blemish from the flock, with your valuation, as a trespass offering. So the priest shall make atonement for him regarding his ignorance in which he erred and did not know it, and it shall be forgiven him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 5019, 'It is a trespass offering; he has certainly trespassed against the LORD.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6002, '&ldquo;If a person sins and commits a trespass against the LORD by lying to his neighbor about what was delivered to him for safekeeping, or about a pledge, or about a robbery, or if he has extorted from his neighbor,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6003, 'or if he has found what was lost and lies concerning it, and swears falsely &ndash; in any one of these things that a man may do in which he sins:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6004, 'then it shall be, because he has sinned and is guilty, that he shall restore what he has stolen, or the thing which he has extorted, or what was delivered to him for safekeeping, or the lost thing which he found,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6005, 'or all that about which he has sworn falsely. He shall restore its full value, add one-fifth more to it, and give it to whomever it belongs, on the day of his trespass offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6006, 'And he shall bring his trespass offering to the LORD, a ram without blemish from the flock, with your valuation, as a trespass offering, to the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6007, 'So the priest shall make atonement for him before the LORD, and he shall be forgiven for any one of these things that he may have done in which he trespasses.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6008, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6009, '&ldquo;Command Aaron and his sons, saying, &lsquo;This is the law of the burnt offering: The burnt offering shall be on the hearth upon the altar all night until morning, and the fire of the altar shall be kept burning on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6010, 'And the priest shall put on his linen garment, and his linen trousers he shall put on his body, and take up the ashes of the burnt offering which the fire has consumed on the altar, and he shall put them beside the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6011, 'Then he shall take off his garments, put on other garments, and carry the ashes outside the camp to a clean place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6012, 'And the fire on the altar shall be kept burning on it; it shall not be put out. And the priest shall burn wood on it every morning, and lay the burnt offering in order on it; and he shall burn on it the fat of the peace offerings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6013, 'A fire shall always be burning on the altar; it shall never go out.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6014, '&lsquo;This is the law of the grain offering: The sons of Aaron shall offer it on the altar before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6015, 'He shall take from it his handful of the fine flour of the grain offering, with its oil, and all the frankincense which is on the grain offering, and shall burn it on the altar for a sweet aroma, as a memorial to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6016, 'And the remainder of it Aaron and his sons shall eat; with unleavened bread it shall be eaten in a holy place; in the court of the tabernacle of meeting they shall eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6017, 'It shall not be baked with leaven. I have given it as their portion of My offerings made by fire; it is most holy, like the sin offering and the trespass offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6018, 'All the males among the children of Aaron may eat it. It shall be a statute forever in your generations concerning the offerings made by fire to the LORD. Everyone who touches them must be holy.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6019, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6020, '&ldquo;This is the offering of Aaron and his sons, which they shall offer to the LORD, beginning on the day when he is anointed: one-tenth of an ephah of fine flour as a daily grain offering, half of it in the morning and half of it at night.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6021, 'It shall be made in a pan with oil. When it is mixed, you shall bring it in. The baked pieces of the grain offering you shall offer for a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6022, 'The priest from among his sons, who is anointed in his place, shall offer it. It is a statute forever to the LORD. It shall be wholly burned.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6023, 'For every grain offering for the priest shall be wholly burned. It shall not be eaten.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6024, 'Also the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6025, '&ldquo;Speak to Aaron and to his sons, saying, &lsquo;This is the law of the sin offering: In the place where the burnt offering is killed, the sin offering shall be killed before the LORD. It is most holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6026, 'The priest who offers it for sin shall eat it. In a holy place it shall be eaten, in the court of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6027, 'Everyone who touches its flesh must be holy. And when its blood is sprinkled on any garment, you shall wash that on which it was sprinkled, in a holy place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6028, 'But the earthen vessel in which it is boiled shall be broken. And if it is boiled in a bronze pot, it shall be both scoured and rinsed in water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6029, 'All the males among the priests may eat it. It is most holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 6030, 'But no sin offering from which any of the blood is brought into the tabernacle of meeting, to make atonement in the holy place, shall be eaten. It shall be burned in the fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7001, '&lsquo;Likewise this is the law of the trespass offering (it is most holy):');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7002, 'In the place where they kill the burnt offering they shall kill the trespass offering. And its blood he shall sprinkle all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7003, 'And he shall offer from it all its fat. The fat tail and the fat that covers the entrails,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7004, 'the two kidneys and the fat that is on them by the flanks, and the fatty lobe attached to the liver above the kidneys, he shall remove;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7005, 'and the priest shall burn them on the altar as an offering made by fire to the LORD. It is a trespass offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7006, 'Every male among the priests may eat it. It shall be eaten in a holy place. It is most holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7007, 'The trespass offering is like the sin offering; there is one law for them both: the priest who makes atonement with it shall have it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7008, 'And the priest who offers anyone&rsquo;s burnt offering, that priest shall have for himself the skin of the burnt offering which he has offered.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7009, 'Also every grain offering that is baked in the oven and all that is prepared in the covered pan, or in a pan, shall be the priest&rsquo;s who offers it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7010, 'Every grain offering, whether mixed with oil or dry, shall belong to all the sons of Aaron, to one as much as the other.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7011, '&lsquo;This is the law of the sacrifice of peace offerings which he shall offer to the LORD:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7012, 'If he offers it for a thanksgiving, then he shall offer, with the sacrifice of thanksgiving, unleavened cakes mixed with oil, unleavened wafers anointed with oil, or cakes of blended flour mixed with oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7013, 'Besides the cakes, as his offering he shall offer leavened bread with the sacrifice of thanksgiving of his peace offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7014, 'And from it he shall offer one cake from each offering as a heave offering to the LORD. It shall belong to the priest who sprinkles the blood of the peace offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7015, '&lsquo;The flesh of the sacrifice of his peace offering for thanksgiving shall be eaten the same day it is offered. He shall not leave any of it until morning.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7016, 'But if the sacrifice of his offering is a vow or a voluntary offering, it shall be eaten the same day that he offers his sacrifice; but on the next day the remainder of it also may be eaten;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7017, 'the remainder of the flesh of the sacrifice on the third day must be burned with fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7018, 'And if any of the flesh of the sacrifice of his peace offering is eaten at all on the third day, it shall not be accepted, nor shall it be imputed to him; it shall be an abomination to him who offers it, and the person who eats of it shall bear guilt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7019, '&lsquo;The flesh that touches any unclean thing shall not be eaten. It shall be burned with fire. And as for the clean flesh, all who are clean may eat of it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7020, 'But the person who eats the flesh of the sacrifice of the peace offering that belongs to the LORD, while he is unclean, that person shall be cut off from his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7021, 'Moreover the person who touches any unclean thing, such as human uncleanness, an unclean animal, or any abominable unclean thing, and who eats the flesh of the sacrifice of the peace offering that belongs to the LORD, that person shall be cut off from his people.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7022, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7023, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;You shall not eat any fat, of ox or sheep or goat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7024, 'And the fat of an animal that dies naturally, and the fat of what is torn by wild beasts, may be used in any other way; but you shall by no means eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7025, 'For whoever eats the fat of the animal of which men offer an offering made by fire to the LORD, the person who eats it shall be cut off from his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7026, 'Moreover you shall not eat any blood in any of your dwellings, whether of bird or beast.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7027, 'Whoever eats any blood, that person shall be cut off from his people.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7028, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7029, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;He who offers the sacrifice of his peace offering to the LORD shall bring his offering to the LORD from the sacrifice of his peace offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7030, 'His own hands shall bring the offerings made by fire to the LORD. The fat with the breast he shall bring, that the breast may be waved as a wave offering before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7031, 'And the priest shall burn the fat on the altar, but the breast shall be Aaron&rsquo;s and his sons&rsquo;.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7032, 'Also the right thigh you shall give to the priest as a heave offering from the sacrifices of your peace offerings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7033, 'He among the sons of Aaron, who offers the blood of the peace offering and the fat, shall have the right thigh for his part.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7034, 'For the breast of the wave offering and the thigh of the heave offering I have taken from the children of Israel, from the sacrifices of their peace offerings, and I have given them to Aaron the priest and to his sons from the children of Israel by a statute forever.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7035, 'This is the consecrated portion for Aaron and his sons, from the offerings made by fire to the LORD, on the day when Moses presented them to minister to the LORD as priests.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7036, 'The LORD commanded this to be given to them by the children of Israel, on the day that He anointed them, by a statute forever throughout their generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7037, 'This is the law of the burnt offering, the grain offering, the sin offering, the trespass offering, the consecrations, and the sacrifice of the peace offering,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 7038, 'which the LORD commanded Moses on Mount Sinai, on the day when He commanded the children of Israel to offer their offerings to the LORD in the Wilderness of Sinai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8002, '&ldquo;Take Aaron and his sons with him, and the garments, the anointing oil, a bull as the sin offering, two rams, and a basket of unleavened bread;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8003, 'and gather all the congregation together at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8004, 'So Moses did as the LORD commanded him. And the congregation was gathered together at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8005, 'And Moses said to the congregation, &ldquo;This is what the LORD commanded to be done.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8006, 'Then Moses brought Aaron and his sons and washed them with water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8007, 'And he put the tunic on him, girded him with the sash, clothed him with the robe, and put the ephod on him; and he girded him with the intricately woven band of the ephod, and with it tied the ephod on him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8008, 'Then he put the breastplate on him, and he put the Urim and the Thummim in the breastplate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8009, 'And he put the turban on his head. Also on the turban, on its front, he put the golden plate, the holy crown, as the LORD had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8010, 'Also Moses took the anointing oil, and anointed the tabernacle and all that was in it, and consecrated them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8011, 'He sprinkled some of it on the altar seven times, anointed the altar and all its utensils, and the laver and its base, to consecrate them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8012, 'And he poured some of the anointing oil on Aaron&rsquo;s head and anointed him, to consecrate him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8013, 'Then Moses brought Aaron&rsquo;s sons and put tunics on them, girded them with sashes, and put hats on them, as the LORD had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8014, 'And he brought the bull for the sin offering. Then Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the bull for the sin offering,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8015, 'and Moses killed it. Then he took the blood, and put some on the horns of the altar all around with his finger, and purified the altar. And he poured the blood at the base of the altar, and consecrated it, to make atonement for it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8016, 'Then he took all the fat that was on the entrails, the fatty lobe attached to the liver, and the two kidneys with their fat, and Moses burned them on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8017, 'But the bull, its hide, its flesh, and its offal, he burned with fire outside the camp, as the LORD had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8018, 'Then he brought the ram as the burnt offering. And Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8019, 'and Moses killed it. Then he sprinkled the blood all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8020, 'And he cut the ram into pieces; and Moses burned the head, the pieces, and the fat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8021, 'Then he washed the entrails and the legs in water. And Moses burned the whole ram on the altar. It was a burnt sacrifice for a sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the LORD, as the LORD had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8022, 'And he brought the second ram, the ram of consecration. Then Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8023, 'and Moses killed it. Also he took some of its blood and put it on the tip of Aaron&rsquo;s right ear, on the thumb of his right hand, and on the big toe of his right foot.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8024, 'Then he brought Aaron&rsquo;s sons. And Moses put some of the blood on the tips of their right ears, on the thumbs of their right hands, and on the big toes of their right feet. And Moses sprinkled the blood all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8025, 'Then he took the fat and the fat tail, all the fat that was on the entrails, the fatty lobe attached to the liver, the two kidneys and their fat, and the right thigh;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8026, 'and from the basket of unleavened bread that was before the LORD he took one unleavened cake, a cake of bread anointed with oil, and one wafer, and put them on the fat and on the right thigh;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8027, 'and he put all these in Aaron&rsquo;s hands and in his sons&rsquo; hands, and waved them as a wave offering before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8028, 'Then Moses took them from their hands and burned them on the altar, on the burnt offering. They were consecration offerings for a sweet aroma. That was an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8029, 'And Moses took the breast and waved it as a wave offering before the LORD. It was Moses&rsquo; part of the ram of consecration, as the LORD had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8030, 'Then Moses took some of the anointing oil and some of the blood which was on the altar, and sprinkled it on Aaron, on his garments, on his sons, and on the garments of his sons with him; and he consecrated Aaron, his garments, his sons, and the garments of his sons with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8031, 'And Moses said to Aaron and his sons, &ldquo;Boil the flesh at the door of the tabernacle of meeting, and eat it there with the bread that is in the basket of consecration offerings, as I commanded, saying, &lsquo;Aaron and his sons shall eat it.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8032, 'What remains of the flesh and of the bread you shall burn with fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8033, 'And you shall not go outside the door of the tabernacle of meeting for seven days, until the days of your consecration are ended. For seven days he shall consecrate you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8034, 'As he has done this day, so the LORD has commanded to do, to make atonement for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8035, 'Therefore you shall stay at the door of the tabernacle of meeting day and night for seven days, and keep the charge of the LORD, so that you may not die; for so I have been commanded.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 8036, 'So Aaron and his sons did all the things that the LORD had commanded by the hand of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9001, 'It came to pass on the eighth day that Moses called Aaron and his sons and the elders of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9002, 'And he said to Aaron, &ldquo;Take for yourself a young bull as a sin offering and a ram as a burnt offering, without blemish, and offer them before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9003, 'And to the children of Israel you shall speak, saying, &lsquo;Take a kid of the goats as a sin offering, and a calf and a lamb, both of the first year, without blemish, as a burnt offering,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9004, 'also a bull and a ram as peace offerings, to sacrifice before the LORD, and a grain offering mixed with oil; for today the LORD will appear to you.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9005, 'So they brought what Moses commanded before the tabernacle of meeting. And all the congregation drew near and stood before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9006, 'Then Moses said, &ldquo;This is the thing which the LORD commanded you to do, and the glory of the LORD will appear to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9007, 'And Moses said to Aaron, &ldquo;Go to the altar, offer your sin offering and your burnt offering, and make atonement for yourself and for the people. Offer the offering of the people, and make atonement for them, as the LORD commanded.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9008, 'Aaron therefore went to the altar and killed the calf of the sin offering, which was for himself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9009, 'Then the sons of Aaron brought the blood to him. And he dipped his finger in the blood, put it on the horns of the altar, and poured the blood at the base of the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9010, 'But the fat, the kidneys, and the fatty lobe from the liver of the sin offering he burned on the altar, as the LORD had commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9011, 'The flesh and the hide he burned with fire outside the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9012, 'And he killed the burnt offering; and Aaron&rsquo;s sons presented to him the blood, which he sprinkled all around on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9013, 'Then they presented the burnt offering to him, with its pieces and head, and he burned them on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9014, 'And he washed the entrails and the legs, and burned them with the burnt offering on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9015, 'Then he brought the people&rsquo;s offering, and took the goat, which was the sin offering for the people, and killed it and offered it for sin, like the first one.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9016, 'And he brought the burnt offering and offered it according to the prescribed manner.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9017, 'Then he brought the grain offering, took a handful of it, and burned it on the altar, besides the burnt sacrifice of the morning.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9018, 'He also killed the bull and the ram as sacrifices of peace offerings, which were for the people. And Aaron&rsquo;s sons presented to him the blood, which he sprinkled all around on the altar,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9019, 'and the fat from the bull and the ram &ndash; the fatty tail, what covers the entrails and the kidneys, and the fatty lobe attached to the liver;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9020, 'and they put the fat on the breasts. Then he burned the fat on the altar;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9021, 'but the breasts and the right thigh Aaron waved as a wave offering before the LORD, as Moses had commanded.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9022, 'Then Aaron lifted his hand toward the people, blessed them, and came down from offering the sin offering, the burnt offering, and peace offerings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9023, 'And Moses and Aaron went into the tabernacle of meeting, and came out and blessed the people. Then the glory of the LORD appeared to all the people,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 9024, 'and fire came out from before the LORD and consumed the burnt offering and the fat on the altar. When all the people saw it, they shouted and fell on their faces.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10001, 'Then Nadab and Abihu, the sons of Aaron, each took his censer and put fire in it, put incense on it, and offered profane fire before the LORD, which He had not commanded them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10002, 'So fire went out from the LORD and devoured them, and they died before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10003, 'And Moses said to Aaron, &ldquo;This is what the LORD spoke, saying: &lsquo;By those who come near Me, I must be regarded as holy; And before all the people, I must be glorified.&rsquo;&rdquo; So Aaron held his peace.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10004, 'Then Moses called Mishael and Elzaphan, the sons of Uzziel the uncle of Aaron, and said to them, &ldquo;Come near, carry your brethren from before the sanctuary out of the camp.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10005, 'So they went near and carried them by their tunics out of the camp, as Moses had said.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10006, 'And Moses said to Aaron, and to Elemazar and Ithamar, his sons, &ldquo;Do not uncover your heads nor tear your clothes, lest you die, and wrath come upon all the people. But let your brethren, the whole house of Israel, bewail the burning which the LORD has kindled.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10007, 'You shall not go out from the door of the tabernacle of meeting, lest you die, for the anointing oil of the LORD is upon you.&rdquo; And they did according to the word of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10008, 'Then the LORD spoke to Aaron, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10009, '&ldquo;Do not drink wine or intoxicating drink, you, nor your sons with you, when you go into the tabernacle of meeting, lest you die. It shall be a statute forever throughout your generations,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10010, 'that you may distinguish between holy and unholy, and between unclean and clean,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10011, 'and that you may teach the children of Israel all the statutes which the LORD has spoken to them by the hand of Moses.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10012, 'And Moses spoke to Aaron, and to Elemazar and Ithamar, his sons who were left: &ldquo;Take the grain offering that remains of the offerings made by fire to the LORD, and eat it without leaven beside the altar; for it is most holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10013, 'You shall eat it in a holy place, because it is your due and your sons&rsquo; due, of the sacrifices made by fire to the LORD; for so I have been commanded.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10014, 'The breast of the wave offering and the thigh of the heave offering you shall eat in a clean place, you, your sons, and your daughters with you; for they are your due and your sons&rsquo; due, which are given from the sacrifices of peace offerings of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10015, 'The thigh of the heave offering and the breast of the wave offering they shall bring with the offerings of fat made by fire, to offer as a wave offering before the LORD. And it shall be yours and your sons&rsquo; with you, by a statute forever, as the LORD has commanded.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10016, 'Then Moses made careful inquiry about the goat of the sin offering, and there it was &ndash; burned up. And he was angry with Elemazar and Ithamar, the sons of Aaron who were left, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10017, '&ldquo;Why have you not eaten the sin offering in a holy place, since it is most holy, and God has given it to you to bear the guilt of the congregation, to make atonement for them before the LORD?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10018, 'See! Its blood was not brought inside the holy place; indeed you should have eaten it in a holy place, as I commanded.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10019, 'And Aaron said to Moses, &ldquo;Look, this day they have offered their sin offering and their burnt offering before the LORD, and such things have befallen me! If I had eaten the sin offering today, would it have been accepted in the sight of the LORD?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 10020, 'So when Moses heard that, he was content.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11001, 'The LORD said to Moses and Aaron,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11002, 'Say to the Israelites: &lsquo;Of all the animals that live on land, these are the ones you may eat:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11003, 'You may eat any animal that has a split hoof completely divided and that chews the cud.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11004, ' &lsquo;There are some that only chew the cud or only have a split hoof, but you must not eat them. The camel, though it chews the cud, does not have a split hoof; it is ceremonially unclean for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11005, 'The coney, though it chews the cud, does not have a split hoof; it is unclean for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11006, 'The rabbit, though it chews the cud, does not have a split hoof; it is unclean for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11007, 'And the pig, though it has a split hoof completely divided, does not chew the cud; it is unclean for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11008, 'You must not eat their meat or touch their carcasses; they are unclean for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11009, ' &lsquo;Of all the creatures living in the water of the seas and the streams, you may eat any that have fins and scales.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11010, 'But all creatures in the seas or streams that do not have fins and scales &ndash; whether among all the swarming things or among all the other living creatures in the water &ndash; you are to detest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11011, 'And since you are to detest them, you must not eat their meat and you must detest their carcasses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11012, 'Anything living in the water that does not have fins and scales is to be detestable to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11013, ' &lsquo;These are the birds you are to detest and not eat because they are detestable: the eagle, the vulture, the black vulture,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11014, 'the red kite, any kind of black kite,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11015, 'any kind of raven,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11016, 'the horned owl, the screech owl, the gull, any kind of hawk,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11017, 'the little owl, the cormorant, the great owl,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11018, 'the white owl, the desert owl, the osprey,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11019, 'the stork, any kind of heron, the hoopoe and the bat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11020, ' &lsquo;All flying insects that walk on all fours are to be detestable to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11021, 'There are, however, some winged creatures that walk on all fours that you may eat: those that have jointed legs for hopping on the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11022, 'Of these you may eat any kind of locust, katydid, cricket or grasshopper.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11023, 'But all other winged creatures that have four legs you are to detest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11024, ' &lsquo;You will make yourselves unclean by these; whoever touches their carcasses will be unclean till evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11025, 'Whoever picks up one of their carcasses must wash his clothes, and he will be unclean till evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11026, ' &lsquo;Every animal that has a split hoof not completely divided or that does not chew the cud is unclean for you; whoever touches the carcass of any of them will be unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11027, 'Of all the animals that walk on all fours, those that walk on their paws are unclean for you; whoever touches their carcasses will be unclean till evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11028, 'Anyone who picks up their carcasses must wash his clothes, and he will be unclean till evening. They are unclean for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11029, ' &lsquo;Of the animals that move about on the ground, these are unclean for you: the weasel, the rat, any kind of great lizard,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11030, 'the gecko, the monitor lizard, the wall lizard, the skink and the chameleon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11031, 'Of all those that move along the ground, these are unclean for you. Whoever touches them when they are dead will be unclean till evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11032, 'When one of them dies and falls on something, that article, whatever its use, will be unclean, whether it is made of wood, cloth, hide or sackcloth. Put it in water; it will be unclean till evening, and then it will be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11033, 'If one of them falls into a clay pot, everything in it will be unclean, and you must break the pot.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11034, 'Any food that could be eaten but has water on it from such a pot is unclean, and any liquid that could be drunk from it is unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11035, 'Anything that one of their carcasses falls on becomes unclean; an oven or cooking pot must be broken up. They are unclean, and you are to regard them as unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11036, 'A spring, however, or a cistern for collecting water remains clean, but anyone who touches one of these carcasses is unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11037, 'If a carcass falls on any seeds that are to be planted, they remain clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11038, 'But if water has been put on the seed and a carcass falls on it, it is unclean for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11039, ' &lsquo;If an animal that you are allowed to eat dies, anyone who touches the carcass will be unclean till evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11040, 'Anyone who eats some of the carcass must wash his clothes, and he will be unclean till evening. Anyone who picks up the carcass must wash his clothes, and he will be unclean till evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11041, ' &lsquo;Every creature that moves about on the ground is detestable; it is not to be eaten.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11042, 'You are not to eat any creature that moves about on the ground, whether it moves on its belly or walks on all fours or on many feet; it is detestable.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11043, 'Do not defile yourselves by any of these creatures. Do not make yourselves unclean by means of them or be made unclean by them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11044, 'I am the LORD your God; consecrate yourselves and be holy, because I am holy. Do not make yourselves unclean by any creature that moves about on the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11045, 'I am the LORD who brought you up out of Egypt to be your God; therefore be holy, because I am holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11046, ' &lsquo;These are the regulations concerning animals, birds, every living thing that moves in the water and every creature that moves about on the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 11047, 'You must distinguish between the unclean and the clean, between living creatures that may be eaten and those that may not be eaten.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 12001, 'The LORD said to Moses,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 12002, 'Say to the Israelites: &lsquo;A woman who becomes pregnant and gives birth to a son will be ceremonially unclean for seven days, just as she is unclean during her monthly period.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 12003, 'On the eighth day the boy is to be circumcised.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 12004, 'Then the woman must wait thirty-three days to be purified from her bleeding. She must not touch anything sacred or go to the sanctuary until the days of her purification are over.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 12005, 'If she gives birth to a daughter, for two weeks the woman will be unclean, as during her period. Then she must wait sixty-six days to be purified from her bleeding.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 12006, ' &lsquo;When the days of her purification for a son or daughter are over, she is to bring to the priest at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting a year-old lamb for a burnt offering and a young pigeon or a dove for a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 12007, 'He shall offer them before the LORD to make atonement for her, and then she will be ceremonially clean from her flow of blood. &ldquo; &lsquo;These are the regulations for the woman who gives birth to a boy or a girl.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 12008, 'If she cannot afford a lamb, she is to bring two doves or two young pigeons, one for a burnt offering and the other for a sin offering. In this way the priest will make atonement for her, and she will be clean.&rsquo; &ldquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13001, 'The LORD said to Moses and Aaron,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13002, 'When anyone has a swelling or a rash or a bright spot on his skin that may become an infectious skin disease, he must be brought to Aaron the priest or to one of his sons [b] who is a priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13003, 'The priest is to examine the sore on his skin, and if the hair in the sore has turned white and the sore appears to be more than skin deep, it is an infectious skin disease. When the priest examines him, he shall pronounce him ceremonially unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13004, 'If the spot on his skin is white but does not appear to be more than skin deep and the hair in it has not turned white, the priest is to put the infected person in isolation for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13005, 'On the seventh day the priest is to examine him, and if he sees that the sore is unchanged and has not spread in the skin, he is to keep him in isolation another seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13006, 'On the seventh day the priest is to examine him again, and if the sore has faded and has not spread in the skin, the priest shall pronounce him clean; it is only a rash. The man must wash his clothes, and he will be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13007, 'But if the rash does spread in his skin after he has shown himself to the priest to be pronounced clean, he must appear before the priest again.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13008, 'The priest is to examine him, and if the rash has spread in the skin, he shall pronounce him unclean; it is an infectious disease.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13009, 'When anyone has an infectious skin disease, he must be brought to the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13010, 'The priest is to examine him, and if there is a white swelling in the skin that has turned the hair white and if there is raw flesh in the swelling,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13011, 'it is a chronic skin disease and the priest shall pronounce him unclean. He is not to put him in isolation, because he is already unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13012, 'If the disease breaks out all over his skin and, so far as the priest can see, it covers all the skin of the infected person from head to foot,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13013, 'the priest is to examine him, and if the disease has covered his whole body, he shall pronounce that person clean. Since it has all turned white, he is clean');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13014, 'But whenever raw flesh appears on him, he will be unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13015, 'When the priest sees the raw flesh, he shall pronounce him unclean. The raw flesh is unclean; he has an infectious disease.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13016, 'Should the raw flesh change and turn white, he must go to the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13017, 'The priest is to examine him, and if the sores have turned white, the priest shall pronounce the infected person clean; then he will be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13018, 'When someone has a boil on his skin and it heals,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13019, 'and in the place where the boil was, a white swelling or reddish-white spot appears, he must present himself to the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13020, 'The priest is to examine it, and if it appears to be more than skin deep and the hair in it has turned white, the priest shall pronounce him unclean. It is an infectious skin disease that has broken out where the boil was.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13021, 'But if, when the priest examines it, there is no white hair in it and it is not more than skin deep and has faded, then the priest is to put him in isolation for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13022, 'If it is spreading in the skin, the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is infectious.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13023, 'But if the spot is unchanged and has not spread, it is only a scar from the boil, and the priest shall pronounce him clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13024, 'When someone has a burn on his skin and a reddish-white or white spot appears in the raw flesh of the burn,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13025, 'the priest is to examine the spot, and if the hair in it has turned white, and it appears to be more than skin deep, it is an infectious disease that has broken out in the burn. The priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is an infectious skin disease.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13026, 'But if the priest examines it and there is no white hair in the spot and if it is not more than skin deep and has faded, then the priest is to put him in isolation for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13027, 'On the seventh day the priest is to examine him, and if it is spreading in the skin, the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is an infectious skin disease.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13028, 'If, however, the spot is unchanged and has not spread in the skin but has faded, it is a swelling from the burn, and the priest shall pronounce him clean; it is only a scar from the burn.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13029, 'If a man or woman has a sore on the head or on the chin,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13030, 'the priest is to examine the sore, and if it appears to be more than skin deep and the hair in it is yellow and thin, the priest shall pronounce that person unclean; it is an itch, an infectious disease of the head or chin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13031, 'But if, when the priest examines this kind of sore, it does not seem to be more than skin deep and there is no black hair in it, then the priest is to put the infected person in isolation for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13032, 'On the seventh day the priest is to examine the sore, and if the itch has not spread and there is no yellow hair in it and it does not appear to be more than skin deep,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13033, 'he must be shaved except for the diseased area, and the priest is to keep him in isolation another seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13034, 'On the seventh day the priest is to examine the itch, and if it has not spread in the skin and appears to be no more than skin deep, the priest shall pronounce him clean. He must wash his clothes, and he will be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13035, 'But if the itch does spread in the skin after he is pronounced clean,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13036, 'the priest is to examine him, and if the itch has spread in the skin, the priest does not need to look for yellow hair; the person is unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13037, 'If, however, in his judgment it is unchanged and black hair has grown in it, the itch is healed. He is clean, and the priest shall pronounce him clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13038, 'When a man or woman has white spots on the skin,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13039, 'the priest is to examine them, and if the spots are dull white, it is a harmless rash that has broken out on the skin; that person is clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13040, 'When a man has lost his hair and is bald, he is clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13041, 'If he has lost his hair from the front of his scalp and has a bald forehead, he is clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13042, 'But if he has a reddish-white sore on his bald head or forehead, it is an infectious disease breaking out on his head or forehead.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13043, 'The priest is to examine him, and if the swollen sore on his head or forehead is reddish-white like an infectious skin disease,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13044, 'the man is diseased and is unclean. The priest shall pronounce him unclean because of the sore on his head.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13045, 'The person with such an infectious disease must wear torn clothes, let his hair be unkempt, cover the lower part of his face and cry out, &lsquo;Unclean! Unclean!&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13046, 'As long as he has the infection he remains unclean. He must live alone; he must live outside the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13047, 'If any clothing is contaminated with mildew &ndash; any woolen or linen clothing,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13048, 'any woven or knitted material of linen or wool, any leather or anything made of leather &ndash;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13049, 'and if the contamination in the clothing, or leather, or woven or knitted material, or any leather article, is greenish or reddish, it is a spreading mildew and must be shown to the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13050, 'The priest is to examine the mildew and isolate the affected article for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13051, 'On the seventh day he is to examine it, and if the mildew has spread in the clothing, or the woven or knitted material, or the leather, whatever its use, it is a destructive mildew; the article is unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13052, 'He must burn up the clothing, or the woven or knitted material of wool or linen, or any leather article that has the contamination in it, because the mildew is destructive; the article must be burned up.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13053, 'But if, when the priest examines it, the mildew has not spread in the clothing, or the woven or knitted material, or the leather article,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13054, 'he shall order that the contaminated article be washed. Then he is to isolate it for another seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13055, 'After the affected article has been washed, the priest is to examine it, and if the mildew has not changed its appearance, even though it has not spread, it is unclean. Burn it with fire, whether the mildew has affected one side or the other.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13056, 'If, when the priest examines it, the mildew has faded after the article has been washed, he is to tear the contaminated part out of the clothing, or the leather, or the woven or knitted material.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13057, 'But if it reappears in the clothing, or in the woven or knitted material, or in the leather article, it is spreading, and whatever has the mildew must be burned with fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13058, 'The clothing, or the woven or knitted material, or any leather article that has been washed and is rid of the mildew, must be washed again, and it will be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 13059, 'These are the regulations concerning contamination by mildew in woolen or linen clothing, woven or knitted material, or any leather article, for pronouncing them clean or unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14001, 'The LORD said to Moses,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14002, 'These are the regulations for the diseased person at the time of his ceremonial cleansing, when he is brought to the priest:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14003, 'The priest is to go outside the camp and examine him. If the person has been healed of his infectious skin disease,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14004, 'the priest shall order that two live clean birds and some cedar wood, scarlet yarn and hyssop be brought for the one to be cleansed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14005, 'Then the priest shall order that one of the birds be killed over fresh water in a clay pot.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14006, 'He is then to take the live bird and dip it, together with the cedar wood, the scarlet yarn and the hyssop, into the blood of the bird that was killed over the fresh water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14007, 'Seven times he shall sprinkle the one to be cleansed of the infectious disease and pronounce him clean. Then he is to release the live bird in the open fields.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14008, 'The person to be cleansed must wash his clothes, shave off all his hair and bathe with water; then he will be ceremonially clean. After this he may come into the camp, but he must stay outside his tent for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14009, 'On the seventh day he must shave off all his hair; he must shave his head, his beard, his eyebrows and the rest of his hair. He must wash his clothes and bathe himself with water, and he will be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14010, 'On the eighth day he must bring two male lambs and one ewe lamb a year old, each without defect, along with three-tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering, and one log of oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14011, 'The priest who pronounces him clean shall present both the one to be cleansed and his offerings before the LORD at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14012, 'Then the priest is to take one of the male lambs and offer it as a guilt offering, along with the log of oil; he shall wave them before the LORD as a wave offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14013, 'He is to slaughter the lamb in the holy place where the sin offering and the burnt offering are slaughtered. Like the sin offering, the guilt offering belongs to the priest; it is most holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14014, 'The priest is to take some of the blood of the guilt offering and put it on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14015, 'The priest shall then take some of the log of oil, pour it in the palm of his own left hand,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14016, 'dip his right forefinger into the oil in his palm, and with his finger sprinkle some of it before the LORD seven times.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14017, 'The priest is to put some of the oil remaining in his palm on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot, on top of the blood of the guilt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14018, 'The rest of the oil in his palm the priest shall put on the head of the one to be cleansed and make atonement for him before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14019, 'Then the priest is to sacrifice the sin offering and make atonement for the one to be cleansed from his uncleanness. After that, the priest shall slaughter the burnt offering');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14020, 'and offer it on the altar, together with the grain offering, and make atonement for him, and he will be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14021, 'If, however, he is poor and cannot afford these, he must take one male lamb as a guilt offering to be waved to make atonement for him, together with a tenth of an ephah of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering, a log of oil,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14022, 'and two doves or two young pigeons, which he can afford, one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14023, 'On the eighth day he must bring them for his cleansing to the priest at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting, before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14024, 'The priest is to take the lamb for the guilt offering, together with the log of oil, and wave them before the LORD as a wave offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14025, 'He shall slaughter the lamb for the guilt offering and take some of its blood and put it on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14026, 'The priest is to pour some of the oil into the palm of his own left hand,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14027, 'and with his right forefinger sprinkle some of the oil from his palm seven times before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14028, 'Some of the oil in his palm he is to put on the same places he put the blood of the guilt offering &ndash; on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14029, 'The rest of the oil in his palm the priest shall put on the head of the one to be cleansed, to make atonement for him before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14030, 'Then he shall sacrifice the doves or the young pigeons, which the person can afford,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14031, 'one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering, together with the grain offering. In this way the priest will make atonement before the LORD on behalf of the one to be cleansed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14032, 'These are the regulations for anyone who has an infectious skin disease and who cannot afford the regular offerings for his cleansing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14033, 'The LORD said to Moses and Aaron,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14034, 'When you enter the land of Canaan, which I am giving you as your possession, and I put a spreading mildew in a house in that land,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14035, 'the owner of the house must go and tell the priest, &lsquo;I have seen something that looks like mildew in my house.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14036, 'The priest is to order the house to be emptied before he goes in to examine the mildew, so that nothing in the house will be pronounced unclean. After this the priest is to go in and inspect the house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14037, 'He is to examine the mildew on the walls, and if it has greenish or reddish depressions that appear to be deeper than the surface of the wall,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14038, 'the priest shall go out the doorway of the house and close it up for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14039, 'On the seventh day the priest shall return to inspect the house. If the mildew has spread on the walls,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14040, 'he is to order that the contaminated stones be torn out and thrown into an unclean place outside the town.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14041, 'He must have all the inside walls of the house scraped and the material that is scraped off dumped into an unclean place outside the town.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14042, 'Then they are to take other stones to replace these and take new clay and plaster the house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14043, 'If the mildew reappears in the house after the stones have been torn out and the house scraped and plastered,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14044, 'the priest is to go and examine it and, if the mildew has spread in the house, it is a destructive mildew; the house is unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14045, 'It must be torn down &ndash; its stones, timbers and all the plaster &ndash; and taken out of the town to an unclean place.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14046, 'Anyone who goes into the house while it is closed up will be unclean till evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14047, 'Anyone who sleeps or eats in the house must wash his clothes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14048, 'But if the priest comes to examine it and the mildew has not spread after the house has been plastered, he shall pronounce the house clean, because the mildew is gone.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14049, 'To purify the house he is to take two birds and some cedar wood, scarlet yarn and hyssop.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14050, 'He shall kill one of the birds over fresh water in a clay pot.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14051, 'Then he is to take the cedar wood, the hyssop, the scarlet yarn and the live bird, dip them into the blood of the dead bird and the fresh water, and sprinkle the house seven times.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14052, 'He shall purify the house with the bird&rsquo;s blood, the fresh water, the live bird, the cedar wood, the hyssop and the scarlet yarn.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14053, 'Then he is to release the live bird in the open fields outside the town. In this way he will make atonement for the house, and it will be clean.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14054, 'These are the regulations for any infectious skin disease, for an itch,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14055, 'for mildew in clothing or in a house,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14056, 'and for a swelling, a rash or a bright spot,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 14057, 'to determine when something is clean or unclean. These are the regulations for infectious skin diseases and mildew.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When any man has a discharge from his body, his discharge is unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15003, 'And this shall be his uncleanness in regard to his discharge &ndash; whether his body runs with his discharge, or his body is stopped up by his discharge, it is his uncleanness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15004, 'Every bed is unclean on which he who has the discharge lies, and everything on which he sits shall be unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15005, 'And whoever touches his bed shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15006, 'He who sits on anything on which he who has the discharge sat shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15007, 'And he who touches the body of him who has the discharge shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15008, 'If he who has the discharge spits on him who is clean, then he shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15009, 'Any saddle on which he who has the discharge rides shall be unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15010, 'Whoever touches anything that was under him shall be unclean until evening. He who carries any of those things shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15011, 'And whomever the one who has the discharge touches, and has not rinsed his hands in water, he shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15012, 'The vessel of earth that he who has the discharge touches shall be broken, and every vessel of wood shall be rinsed in water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15013, '&lsquo;And when he who has a discharge is cleansed of his discharge, then he shall count for himself seven days for his cleansing, wash his clothes, and bathe his body in running water; then he shall be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15014, 'On the eighth day he shall take for himself two turtledoves or two young pigeons, and come before the LORD, to the door of the tabernacle of meeting, and give them to the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15015, 'Then the priest shall offer them, the one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering. So the priest shall make atonement for him before the LORD because of his discharge.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15016, '&lsquo;If any man has an emission of semen, then he shall wash all his body in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15017, 'And any garment and any leather on which there is semen, it shall be washed with water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15018, 'Also, when a woman lies with a man, and there is an emission of semen, they shall bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15019, '&lsquo;If a woman has a discharge, and the discharge from her body is blood, she shall be set apart seven days; and whoever touches her shall be unclean until evening');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15020, 'Everything that she lies on during her impurity shall be unclean; also everything that she sits on shall be unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15021, 'Whoever touches her bed shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15022, 'And whoever touches anything that she sat on shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15023, 'If anything is on her bed or on anything on which she sits, when he touches it, he shall be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15024, 'And if any man lies with her at all, so that her impurity is on him, he shall be unclean seven days; and every bed on which he lies shall be unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15025, '&lsquo;If a woman has a discharge of blood for many days, other than at the time of her customary impurity, or if it runs beyond her usual time of impurity, all the days of her unclean discharge shall be as the days of her customary impurity. She shall be unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15026, 'Every bed on which she lies all the days of her discharge shall be to her as the bed of her impurity; and whatever she sits on shall be unclean, as the uncleanness of her impurity.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15027, 'Whoever touches those things shall be unclean; he shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15028, '&lsquo;But if she is cleansed of her discharge, then she shall count for herself seven days, and after that she shall be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15029, 'And on the eighth day she shall take for herself two turtledoves or two young pigeons, and bring them to the priest, to the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15030, 'Then the priest shall offer the one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering, and the priest shall make atonement for her before the LORD for the discharge of her uncleanness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15031, '&lsquo;Thus you shall separate the children of Israel from their uncleanness, lest they die in their uncleanness when they defile My tabernacle that is among them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15032, 'This is the law for one who has a discharge, and for him who emits semen and is unclean thereby,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 15033, 'and for her who is indisposed because of her customary impurity, and for one who has a discharge, either man or woman, and for him who lies with her who is unclean.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16001, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses after the death of the two sons of Aaron, when they offered profane fire before the LORD, and died;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16002, 'and the LORD said to Moses: &ldquo;Tell Aaron your brother not to come at just any time into the Holy Place inside the veil, before the mercy seat which is on the ark, lest he die; for I will appear in the cloud above the mercy seat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16003, '&ldquo;Thus Aaron shall come into the Holy Place: with the blood of a young bull as a sin offering, and of a ram as a burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16004, 'He shall put the holy linen tunic and the linen trousers on his body; he shall be girded with a linen sash, and with the linen turban he shall be attired. These are holy garments. Therefore he shall wash his body in water, and put them on.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16005, 'And he shall take from the congregation of the children of Israel two kids of the goats as a sin offering, and one ram as a burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16006, '&ldquo;Aaron shall offer the bull as a sin offering, which is for himself, and make atonement for himself and for his house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16007, 'He shall take the two goats and present them before the LORD at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16008, 'Then Aaron shall cast lots for the two goats: one lot for the LORD and the other lot for the scapegoat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16009, 'And Aaron shall bring the goat on which the LORD&rsquo;s lot fell, and offer it as a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16010, 'But the goat on which the lot fell to be the scapegoat shall be presented alive before the LORD, to make atonement upon it, and to let it go as the scapegoat into the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16011, '&ldquo;And Aaron shall bring the bull of the sin offering, which is for himself, and make atonement for himself and for his house, and shall kill the bull as the sin offering which is for himself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16012, 'Then he shall take a censer full of burning coals of fire from the altar before the LORD, with his hands full of sweet incense beaten fine, and bring it inside the veil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16013, 'And he shall put the incense on the fire before the LORD, that the cloud of incense may cover the mercy seat that is on the Testimony, lest he die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16014, 'He shall take some of the blood of the bull and sprinkle it with his finger on the mercy seat on the east side; and before the mercy seat he shall sprinkle some of the blood with his finger seven times.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16015, '&ldquo;Then he shall kill the goat of the sin offering, which is for the people, bring its blood inside the veil, do with that blood as he did with the blood of the bull, and sprinkle it on the mercy seat and before the mercy seat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16016, 'So he shall make atonement for the Holy Place, because of the uncleanness of the children of Israel, and because of their transgressions, for all their sins; and so he shall do for the tabernacle of meeting which remains among them in the midst of their uncleanness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16017, 'There shall be no man in the tabernacle of meeting when he goes in to make atonement in the Holy Place, until he comes out, that he may make atonement for himself, for his household, and for all the assembly of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16018, 'And he shall go out to the altar that is before the LORD, and make atonement for it, and shall take some of the blood of the bull and some of the blood of the goat, and put it on the horns of the altar all around.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16019, 'Then he shall sprinkle some of the blood on it with his finger seven times, cleanse it, and consecrate it from the uncleanness of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16020, '&ldquo;And when he has made an end of atoning for the Holy Place, the tabernacle of meeting, and the altar, he shall bring the live goat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16021, 'Aaron shall lay both his hands on the head of the live goat, confess over it all the iniquities of the children of Israel, and all their transgressions, concerning all their sins, putting them on the head of the goat, and shall send it away into the wilderness by the hand of a suitable man.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16022, 'The goat shall bear on itself all their iniquities to an uninhabited land; and he shall release the goat in the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16023, '&ldquo;Then Aaron shall come into the tabernacle of meeting, shall take off the linen garments which he put on when he went into the Holy Place, and shall leave them there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16024, 'And he shall wash his body with water in a holy place, put on his garments, come out and offer his burnt offering and the burnt offering of the people, and make atonement for himself and for the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16025, 'The fat of the sin offering he shall burn on the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16026, 'And he who released the goat as the scapegoat shall wash his clothes and bathe his body in water, and afterward he may come into the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16027, 'The bull for the sin offering and the goat for the sin offering, whose blood was brought in to make atonement in the Holy Place, shall be carried outside the camp. And they shall burn in the fire their skins, their flesh, and their offal.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16028, 'Then he who burns them shall wash his clothes and bathe his body in water, and afterward he may come into the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16029, '&ldquo;This shall be a statute forever for you: In the seventh month, on the tenth day of the month, you shall afflict your souls, and do no work at all, whether a native of your own country or a stranger who dwells among you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16030, 'For on that day the priest shall make atonement for you, to cleanse you, that you may be clean from all your sins before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16031, 'It is a sabbath of solemn rest for you, and you shall afflict your souls. It is a statute forever.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16032, 'And the priest, who is anointed and consecrated to minister as priest in his father&rsquo;s place, shall make atonement, and put on the linen clothes, the holy garments;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16033, 'then he shall make atonement for the Holy Sanctuary, and he shall make atonement for the tabernacle of meeting and for the altar, and he shall make atonement for the priests and for all the people of the assembly.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 16034, 'This shall be an everlasting statute for you, to make atonement for the children of Israel, for all their sins, once a year.&rdquo; And he did as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17002, '&ldquo;Speak to Aaron, to his sons, and to all the children of Israel, and say to them, &lsquo;This is the thing which the LORD has commanded, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17003, '&ldquo;Whatever man of the house of Israel who kills an ox or lamb or goat in the camp, or who kills it outside the camp,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17004, 'and does not bring it to the door of the tabernacle of meeting to offer an offering to the LORD before the tabernacle of the LORD, the guilt of bloodshed shall be imputed to that man. He has shed blood; and that man shall be cut off from among his people,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17005, 'to the end that the children of Israel may bring their sacrifices which they offer in the open field, that they may bring them to the LORD at the door of the tabernacle of meeting, to the priest, and offer them as peace offerings to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17006, 'And the priest shall sprinkle the blood on the altar of the LORD at the door of the tabernacle of meeting, and burn the fat for a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17007, 'They shall no more offer their sacrifices to demons, after whom they have played the harlot. This shall be a statute forever for them throughout their generations.&rdquo;&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17008, '&ldquo;Also you shall say to them: &lsquo;Whatever man of the house of Israel, or of the strangers who dwell among you, who offers a burnt offering or sacrifice,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17009, 'and does not bring it to the door of the tabernacle of meeting, to offer it to the LORD, that man shall be cut off from among his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17010, '&lsquo;And whatever man of the house of Israel, or of the strangers who dwell among you, who eats any blood, I will set My face against that person who eats blood, and will cut him off from among his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17011, 'For the life of the flesh is in the blood, and I have given it to you upon the altar to make atonement for your souls; for it is the blood that makes atonement for the soul.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17012, 'Therefore I said to the children of Israel, &lsquo;No one among you shall eat blood, nor shall any stranger who dwells among you eat blood.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17013, '&ldquo;Whatever man of the children of Israel, or of the strangers who dwell among you, who hunts and catches any animal or bird that may be eaten, he shall pour out its blood and cover it with dust;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17014, 'for it is the life of all flesh. Its blood sustains its life. Therefore I said to the children of Israel, &lsquo;You shall not eat the blood of any flesh, for the life of all flesh is its blood. Whoever eats it shall be cut off.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17015, '&ldquo;And every person who eats what died naturally or what was torn by beasts, whether he is a native of your own country or a stranger, he shall both wash his clothes and bathe in water, and be unclean until evening. Then he shall be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 17016, 'But if he does not wash them or bathe his body, then he shall bear his guilt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18001, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18003, 'According to the doings of the land of Egypt, where you dwelt, you shall not do; and according to the doings of the land of Canaan, where I am bringing you, you shall not do; nor shall you walk in their ordinances.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18004, 'You shall observe My judgments and keep My ordinances, to walk in them: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18005, 'You shall therefore keep My statutes and My judgments, which if a man does, he shall live by them: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18006, '&lsquo;None of you shall approach anyone who is near of kin to him, to uncover his nakedness: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18007, 'The nakedness of your father or the nakedness of your mother you shall not uncover. She is your mother; you shall not uncover her nakedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18008, 'The nakedness of your father&rsquo;s wife you shall not uncover; it is your father&rsquo;s nakedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18009, 'The nakedness of your sister, the daughter of your father, or the daughter of your mother, whether born at home or elsewhere, their nakedness you shall not uncover.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18010, 'The nakedness of your son&rsquo;s daughter or your daughter&rsquo;s daughter, their nakedness you shall not uncover; for theirs is your own nakedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18011, 'The nakedness of your father&rsquo;s wife&rsquo;s daughter, begotten by your father &ndash; she is your sister &ndash; you shall not uncover her nakedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18012, 'You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father&rsquo;s sister; she is near of kin to your father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18013, 'You shall not uncover the nakedness of your mother&rsquo;s sister, for she is near of kin to your mother.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18014, 'You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father&rsquo;s brother. You shall not approach his wife; she is your aunt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18015, 'You shall not uncover the nakedness of your daughter-in-law &ndash; she is your son&rsquo;s wife &ndash; you shall not uncover her nakedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18016, 'You shall not uncover the nakedness of your brother&rsquo;s wife; it is your brother&rsquo;s nakedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18017, 'You shall not uncover the nakedness of a woman and her daughter, nor shall you take her son&rsquo;s daughter or her daughter&rsquo;s daughter, to uncover her nakedness. They are near of kin to her. It is wickedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18018, 'Nor shall you take a woman as a rival to her sister, to uncover her nakedness while the other is alive.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18019, '&lsquo;Also you shall not approach a woman to uncover her nakedness as long as she is in her customary impurity.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18020, 'Moreover you shall not lie carnally with your neighbor&rsquo;s wife, to defile yourself with her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18021, 'And you shall not let any of your descendants pass through the fire to Molech, nor shall you profane the name of your God: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18022, 'You shall not lie with a male as with a woman. It is an abomination.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18023, 'Nor shall you mate with any animal, to defile yourself with it. Nor shall any woman stand before an animal to mate with it. It is perversion.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18024, '&lsquo;Do not defile yourselves with any of these things; for by all these the nations are defiled, which I am casting out before you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18025, 'For the land is defiled; therefore I visit the punishment of its iniquity upon it, and the land vomits out its inhabitants.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18026, 'You shall therefore keep My statutes and My judgments, and shall not commit any of these abominations, either any of your own nation or any stranger who dwells among you');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18027, '(for all these abominations the men of the land have done, who were before you, and thus the land is defiled),');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18028, 'lest the land vomit you out also when you defile it, as it vomited out the nations that were before you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18029, 'For whoever commits any of these abominations, the persons who commit them shall be cut off from among their people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 18030, '&lsquo;Therefore you shall keep My ordinance, so that you do not commit any of these abominable customs which were committed before you, and that you do not defile yourselves by them: I am the LORD your God.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19002, '&ldquo;Speak to all the congregation of the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;You shall be holy, for I the LORD your God am holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19003, '&lsquo;Every one of you shall revere his mother and his father, and keep My Sabbaths: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19004, '&lsquo;Do not turn to idols, nor make for yourselves molded gods: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19005, '&lsquo;And if you offer a sacrifice of a peace offering to the LORD, you shall offer it of your own free will.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19006, 'It shall be eaten the same day you offer it, and on the next day. And if any remains until the third day, it shall be burned in the fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19007, 'And if it is eaten at all on the third day, it is an abomination. It shall not be accepted.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19008, 'Therefore everyone who eats it shall bear his iniquity, because he has profaned the hallowed offering of the LORD; and that person shall be cut off from his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19009, '&lsquo;When you reap the harvest of your land, you shall not wholly reap the corners of your field, nor shall you gather the gleanings of your harvest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19010, 'And you shall not glean your vineyard, nor shall you gather every grape of your vineyard; you shall leave them for the poor and the stranger: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19011, '&lsquo;You shall not steal, nor deal falsely, nor lie to one another.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19012, 'And you shall not swear by My name falsely, nor shall you profane the name of your God: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19013, '&lsquo;You shall not cheat your neighbor, nor rob him. The wages of him who is hired shall not remain with you all night until morning.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19014, 'You shall not curse the deaf, nor put a stumbling block before the blind, but shall fear your God: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19015, '&lsquo;You shall do no injustice in judgment. You shall not be partial to the poor, nor honor the person of the mighty. In righteousness you shall judge your neighbor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19016, 'You shall not go about as a talebearer among your people; nor shall you take a stand against the life of your neighbor: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19017, '&lsquo;You shall not hate your brother in your heart. You shall surely rebuke your neighbor, and not bear sin because of him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19018, 'You shall not take vengeance, nor bear any grudge against the children of your people, but you shall love your neighbor as yourself: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19019, '&lsquo;You shall keep My statutes. You shall not let your livestock breed with another kind. You shall not sow your field with mixed seed. Nor shall a garment of mixed linen and wool come upon you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19020, '&lsquo;Whoever lies carnally with a woman who is betrothed to a man as a concubine, and who has not at all been redeemed nor given her freedom, for this there shall be scourging; but they shall not be put to death, because she was not free.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19021, 'And he shall bring his trespass offering to the LORD, to the door of the tabernacle of meeting, a ram as a trespass offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19022, 'The priest shall make atonement for him with the ram of the trespass offering before the LORD for his sin which he has committed. And the sin which he has committed shall be forgiven him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19023, '&lsquo;When you come into the land, and have planted all kinds of trees for food, then you shall count their fruit as uncircumcised. Three years it shall be as uncircumcised to you. It shall not be eaten.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19024, 'But in the fourth year all its fruit shall be holy, a praise to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19025, 'And in the fifth year you may eat its fruit, that it may yield to you its increase: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19026, '&lsquo;You shall not eat anything with the blood, nor shall you practice divination or soothsaying.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19027, 'You shall not shave around the sides of your head, nor shall you disfigure the edges of your beard.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19028, 'You shall not make any cuttings in your flesh for the dead, nor tattoo any marks on you: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19029, '&lsquo;Do not prostitute your daughter, to cause her to be a harlot, lest the land fall into harlotry, and the land become full of wickedness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19030, '&lsquo;You shall keep My Sabbaths and reverence My sanctuary: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19031, '&lsquo;Give no regard to mediums and familiar spirits; do not seek after them, to be defiled by them: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19032, '&lsquo;You shall rise before the gray headed and honor the presence of an old man, and fear your God: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19033, '&lsquo;And if a stranger dwells with you in your land, you shall not mistreat him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19034, 'The stranger who dwells among you shall be to you as one born among you, and you shall love him as yourself; for you were strangers in the land of Egypt: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19035, '&lsquo;You shall do no injustice in judgment, in measurement of length, weight, or volume.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19036, 'You shall have honest scales, honest weights, an honest ephah, and an honest hin: I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 19037, '&lsquo;Therefore you shall observe all My statutes and all My judgments, and perform them: I am the LORD.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20001, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20002, '&ldquo;Again, you shall say to the children of Israel: &lsquo;Whoever of the children of Israel, or of the strangers who dwell in Israel, who gives any of his descendants to Molech, he shall surely be put to death. The people of the land shall stone him with stones.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20003, 'I will set My face against that man, and will cut him off from his people, because he has given some of his descendants to Molech, to defile My sanctuary and profane My holy name.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20004, 'And if the people of the land should in any way hide their eyes from the man, when he gives some of his descendants to Molech, and they do not kill him,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20005, 'then I will set My face against that man and against his family; and I will cut him off from his people, and all who prostitute themselves with him to commit harlotry with Molech.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20006, '&lsquo;And the person who turns to mediums and familiar spirits, to prostitute himself with them, I will set My face against that person and cut him off from his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20007, 'Consecrate yourselves therefore, and be holy, for I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20008, 'And you shall keep My statutes, and perform them: I am the LORD who sanctifies you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20009, '&lsquo;For everyone who curses his father or his mother shall surely be put to death. He has cursed his father or his mother. His blood shall be upon him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20010, '&lsquo;The man who commits adultery with another man&rsquo;s wife, he who commits adultery with his neighbor&rsquo;s wife, the adulterer and the adulteress, shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20011, 'The man who lies with his father&rsquo;s wife has uncovered his father&rsquo;s nakedness; both of them shall surely be put to death. Their blood shall be upon them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20012, 'If a man lies with his daughter-in-law, both of them shall surely be put to death. They have committed perversion. Their blood shall be upon them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20013, 'If a man lies with a male as he lies with a woman, both of them have committed an abomination. They shall surely be put to death. Their blood shall be upon them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20014, 'If a man marries a woman and her mother, it is wickedness. They shall be burned with fire, both he and they, that there may be no wickedness among you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20015, 'If a man mates with an animal, he shall surely be put to death, and you shall kill the animal.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20016, 'If a woman approaches any animal and mates with it, you shall kill the woman and the animal. They shall surely be put to death. Their blood is upon them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20017, '&lsquo;If a man takes his sister, his father&rsquo;s daughter or his mother&rsquo;s daughter, and sees her nakedness and she sees his nakedness, it is a wicked thing. And they shall be cut off in the sight of their people. He has uncovered his sister&rsquo;s nakedness. He shall bear his guilt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20018, 'If a man lies with a woman during her sickness and uncovers her nakedness, he has exposed her flow, and she has uncovered the flow of her blood. Both of them shall be cut off from their people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20019, '&lsquo;You shall not uncover the nakedness of your mother&rsquo;s sister nor of your father&rsquo;s sister, for that would uncover his near of kin. They shall bear their guilt.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20020, 'If a man lies with his uncle&rsquo;s wife, he has uncovered his uncle&rsquo;s nakedness. They shall bear their sin; they shall die childless.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20021, 'If a man takes his brother&rsquo;s wife, it is an unclean thing. He has uncovered his brother&rsquo;s nakedness. They shall be childless.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20022, '&lsquo;You shall therefore keep all My statutes and all My judgments, and perform them, that the land where I am bringing you to dwell may not vomit you out.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20023, 'And you shall not walk in the statutes of the nation which I am casting out before you; for they commit all these things, and therefore I abhor them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20024, 'But I have said to you, &ldquo;You shall inherit their land, and I will give it to you to possess, a land flowing with milk and honey.&rdquo; I am the LORD your God, who has separated you from the peoples.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20025, 'You shall therefore distinguish between clean animals and unclean, between unclean birds and clean, and you shall not make yourselves abominable by beast or by bird, or by any kind of living thing that creeps on the ground, which I have separated from you as unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20026, 'And you shall be holy to Me, for I the LORD am holy, and have separated you from the peoples, that you should be Mine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 20027, '&lsquo;A man or a woman who is a medium, or who has familiar spirits, shall surely be put to death; they shall stone them with stones. Their blood shall be upon them.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21001, 'And the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;Speak to the priests, the sons of Aaron, and say to them: &lsquo;None shall defile himself for the dead among his people,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21002, 'except for his relatives who are nearest to him: his mother, his father, his son, his daughter, and his brother;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21003, 'also his virgin sister who is near to him, who has had no husband, for her he may defile himself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21004, 'Otherwise he shall not defile himself, being a chief man among his people, to profane himself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21005, '&lsquo;They shall not make any bald place on their heads, nor shall they shave the edges of their beards nor make any cuttings in their flesh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21006, 'They shall be holy to their God and not profane the name of their God, for they offer the offerings of the LORD made by fire, and the bread of their God; therefore they shall be holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21007, 'They shall not take a wife who is a harlot or a defiled woman, nor shall they take a woman divorced from her husband; for the priest is holy to his God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21008, 'Therefore you shall consecrate him, for he offers the bread of your God. He shall be holy to you, for I the LORD, who sanctify you, am holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21009, 'The daughter of any priest, if she profanes herself by playing the harlot, she profanes her father. She shall be burned with fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21010, '&lsquo;He who is the high priest among his brethren, on whose head the anointing oil was poured and who is consecrated to wear the garments, shall not uncover his head nor tear his clothes;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21011, 'nor shall he go near any dead body, nor defile himself for his father or his mother;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21012, 'nor shall he go out of the sanctuary, nor profane the sanctuary of his God; for the consecration of the anointing oil of his God is upon him: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21013, 'And he shall take a wife in her virginity.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21014, 'A widow or a divorced woman or a defiled woman or a harlot &ndash; these he shall not marry; but he shall take a virgin of his own people as wife.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21015, 'Nor shall he profane his posterity among his people, for I the LORD sanctify him.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21016, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21017, '&ldquo;Speak to Aaron, saying: &lsquo;No man of your descendants in succeeding generations, who has any defect, may approach to offer the bread of his God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21018, 'For any man who has a defect shall not approach: a man blind or lame, who has a marred face or any limb too long,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21019, 'a man who has a broken foot or broken hand,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21020, 'or is a hunchback or a dwarf, or a man who has a defect in his eye, or eczema or scab, or is a eunuch.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21021, 'No man of the descendants of Aaron the priest, who has a defect, shall come near to offer the offerings made by fire to the LORD. He has a defect; he shall not come near to offer the bread of his God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21022, 'He may eat the bread of his God, both the most holy and the holy;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21023, 'only he shall not go near the veil or approach the altar, because he has a defect, lest he profane My sanctuaries; for I the LORD sanctify them.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 21024, 'And Moses told it to Aaron and his sons, and to all the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22001, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22002, '&ldquo;Speak to Aaron and his sons, that they separate themselves from the holy things of the children of Israel, and that they do not profane My holy name by what they dedicate to Me: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22003, 'Say to them: &lsquo;Whoever of all your descendants throughout your generations, who goes near the holy things which the children of Israel dedicate to the LORD, while he has uncleanness upon him, that person shall be cut off from My presence: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22004, 'Whatever man of the descendants of Aaron, who is a leper or has a discharge, shall not eat the holy offerings until he is clean. And whoever touches anything made unclean by a corpse, or a man who has had an emission of semen,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22005, 'or whoever touches any creeping thing by which he would be made unclean, or any person by whom he would become unclean, whatever his uncleanness may be &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22006, 'the person who has touched any such thing shall be unclean until evening, and shall not eat the holy offerings unless he washes his body with water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22007, 'And when the sun goes down he shall be clean; and afterward he may eat the holy offerings, because it is his food.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22008, 'Whatever dies naturally or is torn by beasts he shall not eat, to defile himself with it: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22009, '&lsquo;They shall therefore keep My ordinance, lest they bear sin for it and die thereby, if they profane it: I the LORD sanctify them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22010, '&lsquo;No outsider shall eat the holy offering; one who dwells with the priest, or a hired servant, shall not eat the holy thing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22011, 'But if the priest buys a person with his money, he may eat it; and one who is born in his house may eat his food.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22012, 'If the priest&rsquo;s daughter is married to an outsider, she may not eat of the holy offerings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22013, 'But if the priest&rsquo;s daughter is a widow or divorced, and has no child, and has returned to her father&rsquo;s house as in her youth, she may eat her father&rsquo;s food; but no outsider shall eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22014, '&lsquo;And if a man eats the holy offering unintentionally, then he shall restore a holy offering to the priest, and add one-fifth to it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22015, 'They shall not profane the holy offerings of the children of Israel, which they offer to the LORD,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22016, 'or allow them to bear the guilt of trespass when they eat their holy offerings; for I the LORD sanctify them.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22017, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22018, '&ldquo;Speak to Aaron and his sons, and to all the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;Whatever man of the house of Israel, or of the strangers in Israel, who offers his sacrifice for any of his vows or for any of his freewill offerings, which they offer to the LORD as a burnt offering &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22019, 'you shall offer of your own free will a male without blemish from the cattle, from the sheep, or from the goats.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22020, 'Whatever has a defect, you shall not offer, for it shall not be acceptable on your behalf.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22021, 'And whoever offers a sacrifice of a peace offering to the LORD, to fulfill his vow, or a freewill offering from the cattle or the sheep, it must be perfect to be accepted; there shall be no defect in it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22022, 'Those that are blind or broken or maimed, or have an ulcer or eczema or scabs, you shall not offer to the LORD, nor make an offering by fire of them on the altar to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22023, 'Either a bull or a lamb that has any limb too long or too short you may offer as a freewill offering, but for a vow it shall not be accepted.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22024, '&lsquo;You shall not offer to the LORD what is bruised or crushed, or torn or cut; nor shall you make any offering of them in your land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22025, 'Nor from a foreigner&rsquo;s hand shall you offer any of these as the bread of your God, because their corruption is in them, and defects are in them. They shall not be accepted on your behalf.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22026, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22027, '&ldquo;When a bull or a sheep or a goat is born, it shall be seven days with its mother; and from the eighth day and thereafter it shall be accepted as an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22028, 'Whether it is a cow or ewe, do not kill both her and her young on the same day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22029, 'And when you offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving to the LORD, offer it of your own free will.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22030, 'On the same day it shall be eaten; you shall leave none of it until morning: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22031, '&ldquo;Therefore you shall keep My commandments, and perform them: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22032, 'You shall not profane My holy name, but I will be hallowed among the children of Israel. I am the LORD who sanctifies you,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 22033, 'who brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: I am the LORD.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;The feasts of the LORD, which you shall proclaim to be holy convocations, these are My feasts.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23003, '&lsquo;Six days shall work be done, but the seventh day is a Sabbath of solemn rest, a holy convocation. You shall do no work on it; it is the Sabbath of the LORD in all your dwellings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23004, '&lsquo;These are the feasts of the LORD, holy convocations which you shall proclaim at their appointed times.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23005, 'On the fourteenth day of the first month at twilight is the LORD&rsquo;s Passover.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23006, 'And on the fifteenth day of the same month is the Feast of Unleavened Bread to the LORD; seven days you must eat unleavened bread.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23007, 'On the first day you shall have a holy convocation; you shall do no customary work on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23008, 'But you shall offer an offering made by fire to the LORD for seven days. The seventh day shall be a holy convocation; you shall do no customary work on it.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23009, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23010, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When you come into the land which I give to you, and reap its harvest, then you shall bring a sheaf of the firstfruits of your harvest to the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23011, 'He shall wave the sheaf before the LORD, to be accepted on your behalf; on the day after the Sabbath the priest shall wave it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23012, 'And you shall offer on that day, when you wave the sheaf, a male lamb of the first year, without blemish, as a burnt offering to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23013, 'Its grain offering shall be two-tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with oil, an offering made by fire to the LORD, for a sweet aroma; and its drink offering shall be of wine, one-fourth of a hin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23014, 'You shall eat neither bread nor parched grain nor fresh grain until the same day that you have brought an offering to your God; it shall be a statute forever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23015, '&lsquo;And you shall count for yourselves from the day after the Sabbath, from the day that you brought the sheaf of the wave offering: seven Sabbaths shall be completed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23016, 'Count fifty days to the day after the seventh Sabbath; then you shall offer a new grain offering to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23017, 'You shall bring from your dwellings two wave loaves of two-tenths of an ephah. They shall be of fine flour; they shall be baked with leaven. They are the firstfruits to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23018, 'And you shall offer with the bread seven lambs of the first year, without blemish, one young bull, and two rams. They shall be as a burnt offering to the LORD, with their grain offering and their drink offerings, an offering made by fire for a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23019, 'Then you shall sacrifice one kid of the goats as a sin offering, and two male lambs of the first year as a sacrifice of a peace offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23020, 'The priest shall wave them with the bread of the firstfruits as a wave offering before the LORD, with the two lambs. They shall be holy to the LORD for the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23021, 'And you shall proclaim on the same day that it is a holy convocation to you. You shall do no customary work on it. It shall be a statute forever in all your dwellings throughout your generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23022, '&lsquo;When you reap the harvest of your land, you shall not wholly reap the corners of your field when you reap, nor shall you gather any gleaning from your harvest. You shall leave them for the poor and for the stranger: I am the LORD your God.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23023, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23024, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;In the seventh month, on the first day of the month, you shall have a sabbath-rest, a memorial of blowing of trumpets, a holy convocation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23025, 'You shall do no customary work on it; and you shall offer an offering made by fire to the LORD.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23026, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23027, '&ldquo;Also the tenth day of this seventh month shall be the Day of Atonement. It shall be a holy convocation for you; you shall afflict your souls, and offer an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23028, 'And you shall do no work on that same day, for it is the Day of Atonement, to make atonement for you before the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23029, 'For any person who is not afflicted in soul on that same day shall be cut off from his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23030, 'And any person who does any work on that same day, that person I will destroy from among his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23031, 'You shall do no manner of work; it shall be a statute forever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23032, 'It shall be to you a sabbath of solemn rest, and you shall afflict your souls; on the ninth day of the month at evening, from evening to evening, you shall celebrate your sabbath.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23033, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23034, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;The fifteenth day of this seventh month shall be the Feast of Tabernacles for seven days to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23035, 'On the first day there shall be a holy convocation. You shall do no customary work on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23036, 'For seven days you shall offer an offering made by fire to the LORD. On the eighth day you shall have a holy convocation, and you shall offer an offering made by fire to the LORD. It is a sacred assembly, and you shall do no customary work on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23037, '&lsquo;These are the feasts of the LORD which you shall proclaim to be holy convocations, to offer an offering made by fire to the LORD, a burnt offering and a grain offering, a sacrifice and drink offerings, everything on its day &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23038, 'besides the Sabbaths of the LORD, besides your gifts, besides all your vows, and besides all your freewill offerings which you give to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23039, '&lsquo;Also on the fifteenth day of the seventh month, when you have gathered in the fruit of the land, you shall keep the feast of the LORD for seven days; on the first day there shall be a sabbath-rest, and on the eighth day a sabbath-rest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23040, 'And you shall take for yourselves on the first day the fruit of beautiful trees, branches of palm trees, the boughs of leafy trees, and willows of the brook; and you shall rejoice before the LORD your God for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23041, 'You shall keep it as a feast to the LORD for seven days in the year. It shall be a statute forever in your generations. You shall celebrate it in the seventh month.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23042, 'You shall dwell in booths for seven days. All who are native Israelites shall dwell in booths,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23043, 'that your generations may know that I made the children of Israel dwell in booths when I brought them out of the land of Egypt: I am the LORD your God.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 23044, 'So Moses declared to the children of Israel the feasts of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24001, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24002, '&ldquo;Command the children of Israel that they bring to you pure oil of pressed olives for the light, to make the lamps burn continually.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24003, 'Outside the veil of the Testimony, in the tabernacle of meeting, Aaron shall be in charge of it from evening until morning before the LORD continually; it shall be a statute forever in your generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24004, 'He shall be in charge of the lamps on the pure gold lampstand before the LORD continually.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24005, '&ldquo;And you shall take fine flour and bake twelve cakes with it. Two-tenths of an ephah shall be in each cake.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24006, 'You shall set them in two rows, six in a row, on the pure gold table before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24007, 'And you shall put pure frankincense on each row, that it may be on the bread for a memorial, an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24008, 'Every Sabbath he shall set it in order before the LORD continually, being taken from the children of Israel by an everlasting covenant.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24009, 'And it shall be for Aaron and his sons, and they shall eat it in a holy place; for it is most holy to him from the offerings of the LORD made by fire, by a perpetual statute.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24010, 'Now the son of an Israelite woman, whose father was an Egyptian, went out among the children of Israel; and this Israelite woman&rsquo;s son and a man of Israel fought each other in the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24011, 'And the Israelite woman&rsquo;s son blasphemed the name of the LORD and cursed; and so they brought him to Moses. (His mother&rsquo;s name was Shelomith the daughter of Dibri, of the tribe of Dan.)');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24012, 'Then they put him in custody, that the mind of the LORD might be shown to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24013, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24014, '&ldquo;Take outside the camp him who has cursed; then let all who heard him lay their hands on his head, and let all the congregation stone him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24015, '&ldquo;Then you shall speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;Whoever curses his God shall bear his sin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24016, 'And whoever blasphemes the name of the LORD shall surely be put to death. All the congregation shall certainly stone him, the stranger as well as him who is born in the land. When he blasphemes the name of the LORD, he shall be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24017, '&lsquo;Whoever kills any man shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24018, 'Whoever kills an animal shall make it good, animal for animal.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24019, '&lsquo;If a man causes disfigurement of his neighbor, as he has done, so shall it be done to him &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24020, 'fracture for fracture, eye for eye, tooth for tooth; as he has caused disfigurement of a man, so shall it be done to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24021, 'And whoever kills an animal shall restore it; but whoever kills a man shall be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24022, 'You shall have the same law for the stranger and for one from your own country; for I am the LORD your God.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 24023, 'Then Moses spoke to the children of Israel; and they took outside the camp him who had cursed, and stoned him with stones. So the children of Israel did as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses on Mount Sinai, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When you come into the land which I give you, then the land shall keep a sabbath to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25003, 'Six years you shall sow your field, and six years you shall prune your vineyard, and gather its fruit;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25004, 'but in the seventh year there shall be a sabbath of solemn rest for the land, a sabbath to the LORD. You shall neither sow your field nor prune your vineyard.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25005, 'What grows of its own accord of your harvest you shall not reap, nor gather the grapes of your untended vine, for it is a year of rest for the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25006, 'And the sabbath produce of the land shall be food for you: for you, your male and female servants, your hired man, and the stranger who dwells with you,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25007, 'for your livestock and the beasts that are in your land &ndash; all its produce shall be for food.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25008, '&lsquo;And you shall count seven sabbaths of years for yourself, seven times seven years; and the time of the seven sabbaths of years shall be to you forty-nine years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25009, 'Then you shall cause the trumpet of the Jubilee to sound on the tenth day of the seventh month; on the Day of Atonement you shall make the trumpet to sound throughout all your land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25010, 'And you shall consecrate the fiftieth year, and proclaim liberty throughout all the land to all its inhabitants. It shall be a Jubilee for you; and each of you shall return to his possession, and each of you shall return to his family.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25011, 'That fiftieth year shall be a Jubilee to you; in it you shall neither sow nor reap what grows of its own accord, nor gather the grapes of your untended vine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25012, 'For it is the Jubilee; it shall be holy to you; you shall eat its produce from the field.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25013, '&lsquo;In this Year of Jubilee, each of you shall return to his possession.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25014, 'And if you sell anything to your neighbor or buy from your neighbor&rsquo;s hand, you shall not oppress one another.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25015, 'According to the number of years after the Jubilee you shall buy from your neighbor, and according to the number of years of crops he shall sell to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25016, 'According to the multitude of years you shall increase its price, and according to the fewer number of years you shall diminish its price; for he sells to you according to the number of the years of the crops.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25017, 'Therefore you shall not oppress one another, but you shall fear your God; for I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25018, '&lsquo;So you shall observe My statutes and keep My judgments, and perform them; and you will dwell in the land in safety.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25019, 'Then the land will yield its fruit, and you will eat your fill, and dwell there in safety.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25020, '&lsquo;And if you say, &ldquo;What shall we eat in the seventh year, since we shall not sow nor gather in our produce?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25021, 'Then I will command My blessing on you in the sixth year, and it will bring forth produce enough for three years.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25022, 'And you shall sow in the eighth year, and eat old produce until the ninth year; until its produce comes in, you shall eat of the old harvest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25023, '&lsquo;The land shall not be sold permanently, for the land is Mine; for you are strangers and sojourners with Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25024, 'And in all the land of your possession you shall grant redemption of the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25025, '&lsquo;If one of your brethren becomes poor, and has sold some of his possession, and if his redeeming relative comes to redeem it, then he may redeem what his brother sold.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25026, 'Or if the man has no one to redeem it, but he himself becomes able to redeem it,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25027, 'then let him count the years since its sale, and restore the remainder to the man to whom he sold it, that he may return to his possession.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25028, 'But if he is not able to have it restored to himself, then what was sold shall remain in the hand of him who bought it until the Year of Jubilee; and in the Jubilee it shall be released, and he shall return to his possession.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25029, '&lsquo;If a man sells a house in a walled city, then he may redeem it within a whole year after it is sold; within a full year he may redeem it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25030, 'But if it is not redeemed within the space of a full year, then the house in the walled city shall belong permanently to him who bought it, throughout his generations. It shall not be released in the Jubilee.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25031, 'However the houses of villages which have no wall around them shall be counted as the fields of the country. They may be redeemed, and they shall be released in the Jubilee.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25032, 'Nevertheless the cities of the Lemvites, and the houses in the cities of their possession, the Lemvites may redeem at any time.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25033, 'And if a man purchases a house from the Lemvites, then the house that was sold in the city of his possession shall be released in the Jubilee; for the houses in the cities of the Lemvites are their possession among the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25034, 'But the field of the common-land of their cities may not be sold, for it is their perpetual possession.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25035, '&lsquo;If one of your brethren becomes poor, and falls into poverty among you, then you shall help him, like a stranger or a sojourner, that he may live with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25036, 'no usury or interest from him; but fear your God, that your brother may live with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25037, 'You shall not lend him your money for usury, nor lend him your food at a profit.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25038, 'I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, to give you the land of Canaan and to be your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25039, '&lsquo;And if one of your brethren who dwells by you becomes poor, and sells himself to you, you shall not compel him to serve as a slave.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25040, 'As a hired servant and a sojourner he shall be with you, and shall serve you until the Year of Jubilee.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25041, 'And then he shall depart from you &ndash; he and his children with him &ndash; and shall return to his own family. He shall return to the possession of his fathers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25042, 'For they are My servants, whom I brought out of the land of Egypt; they shall not be sold as slaves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25043, 'You shall not rule over him with rigor, but you shall fear your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25044, 'And as for your male and female slaves whom you may have &ndash; from the nations that are around you, from them you may buy male and female slaves.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25045, 'Moreover you may buy the children of the strangers who dwell among you, and their families who are with you, which they beget in your land; and they shall become your property.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25046, 'And you may take them as an inheritance for your children after you, to inherit them as a possession; they shall be your permanent slaves. But regarding your brethren, the children of Israel, you shall not rule over one another with rigor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25047, '&lsquo;Now if a sojourner or stranger close to you becomes rich, and one of your brethren who dwells by him becomes poor, and sells himself to the stranger or sojourner close to you, or to a member of the stranger&rsquo;s family,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25048, 'after he is sold he may be redeemed again. One of his brothers may redeem him;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25049, 'or his uncle or his uncle&rsquo;s son may redeem him; or anyone who is near of kin to him in his family may redeem him; or if he is able he may redeem himself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25050, 'Thus he shall reckon with him who bought him: The price of his release shall be according to the number of years, from the year that he was sold to him until the Year of Jubilee; it shall be according to the time of a hired servant for him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25051, 'If there are still many years remaining, according to them he shall repay the price of his redemption from the money with which he was bought.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25052, 'And if there remain but a few years until the Year of Jubilee, then he shall reckon with him, and according to his years he shall repay him the price of his redemption.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25053, 'He shall be with him as a yearly hired servant, and he shall not rule with rigor over him in your sight.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25054, 'And if he is not redeemed in these years, then he shall be released in the Year of Jubilee &ndash; he and his children with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 25055, 'For the children of Israel are servants to Me; they are My servants whom I brought out of the land of Egypt: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26001, '&lsquo;You shall not make idols for yourselves; neither a carved image nor a sacred pillar shall you rear up for yourselves; nor shall you set up an engraved stone in your land, to bow down to it; for I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26002, 'You shall keep My Sabbaths and reverence My sanctuary: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26003, '&lsquo;If you walk in My statutes and keep My commandments, and perform them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26004, 'then I will give you rain in its season, the land shall yield its produce, and the trees of the field shall yield their fruit.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26005, 'Your threshing shall last till the time of vintage, and the vintage shall last till the time of sowing; you shall eat your bread to the full, and dwell in your land safely.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26006, 'I will give peace in the land, and you shall lie down, and none will make you afraid; I will rid the land of evil beasts, and the sword will not go through your land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26007, 'You will chase your enemies, and they shall fall by the sword before you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26008, 'Five of you shall chase a hundred, and a hundred of you shall put ten thousand to flight; your enemies shall fall by the sword before you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26009, '&lsquo;For I will look on you favorably and make you fruitful, multiply you and confirm My covenant with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26010, 'You shall eat the old harvest, and clear out the old because of the new.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26011, 'I will set My tabernacle among you, and My soul shall not abhor you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26012, 'I will walk among you and be your God, and you shall be My people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26013, 'I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, that you should not be their slaves; I have broken the bands of your yoke and made you walk upright.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26014, '&lsquo;But if you do not obey Me, and do not observe all these commandments,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26015, 'and if you despise My statutes, or if your soul abhors My judgments, so that you do not perform all My commandments, but break My covenant,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26016, 'I also will do this to you: I will even appoint terror over you, wasting disease and fever which shall consume the eyes and cause sorrow of heart. And you shall sow your seed in vain, for your enemies shall eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26017, 'I will set My face against you, and you shall be defeated by your enemies. Those who hate you shall reign over you, and you shall flee when no one pursues you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26018, '&lsquo;And after all this, if you do not obey Me, then I will punish you seven times more for your sins.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26019, 'I will break the pride of your power; I will make your heavens like iron and your earth like bronze.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26020, 'And your strength shall be spent in vain; for your land shall not yield its produce, nor shall the trees of the land yield their fruit.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26021, '&lsquo;Then, if you walk contrary to Me, and are not willing to obey Me, I will bring on you seven times more plagues, according to your sins.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26022, 'I will also send wild beasts among you, which shall rob you of your children, destroy your livestock, and make you few in number; and your highways shall be desolate.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26023, '&lsquo;And if by these things you are not reformed by Me, but walk contrary to Me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26024, 'then I also will walk contrary to you, and I will punish you yet seven times for your sins.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26025, 'And I will bring a sword against you that will execute the vengeance of the covenant; when you are gathered together within your cities I will send pestilence among you; and you shall be delivered into the hand of the enemy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26026, 'When I have cut off your supply of bread, ten women shall bake your bread in one oven, and they shall bring back your bread by weight, and you shall eat and not be satisfied.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26027, '&lsquo;And after all this, if you do not obey Me, but walk contrary to Me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26028, 'then I also will walk contrary to you in fury; and I, even I, will chastise you seven times for your sins.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26029, 'You shall eat the flesh of your sons, and you shall eat the flesh of your daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26030, 'I will destroy your high places, cut down your incense altars, and cast your carcasses on the lifeless forms of your idols; and My soul shall abhor you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26031, 'I will lay your cities waste and bring your sanctuaries to desolation, and I will not smell the fragrance of your sweet aromas.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26032, 'I will bring the land to desolation, and your enemies who dwell in it shall be astonished at it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26033, 'I will scatter you among the nations and draw out a sword after you; your land shall be desolate and your cities waste.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26034, 'Then the land shall enjoy its sabbaths as long as it lies desolate and you are in your enemies&rsquo; land; then the land shall rest and enjoy its sabbaths.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26035, 'As long as it lies desolate it shall rest &ndash; for the time it did not rest on your sabbaths when you dwelt in it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26036, '&lsquo;And as for those of you who are left, I will send faintness into their hearts in the lands of their enemies; the sound of a shaken leaf shall cause them to flee; they shall flee as though fleeing from a sword, and they shall fall when no one pursues.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26037, 'They shall stumble over one another, as it were before a sword, when no one pursues; and you shall have no power to stand before your enemies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26038, 'You shall perish among the nations, and the land of your enemies shall eat you up.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26039, 'And those of you who are left shall waste away in their iniquity in your enemies&rsquo; lands; also in their fathers&rsquo; iniquities, which are with them, they shall waste away.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26040, '&lsquo;But if they confess their iniquity and the iniquity of their fathers, with their unfaithfulness in which they were unfaithful to Me, and that they also have walked contrary to Me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26041, 'and that I also have walked contrary to them and have brought them into the land of their enemies; if their uncircumcised hearts are humbled, and they accept their guilt &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26042, 'then I will remember My covenant with Jacob, and My covenant with Isaac and My covenant with Abraham I will remember; I will remember the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26043, 'The land also shall be left empty by them, and will enjoy its sabbaths while it lies desolate without them; they will accept their guilt, because they despised My judgments and because their soul abhorred My statutes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26044, 'Yet for all that, when they are in the land of their enemies, I will not cast them away, nor shall I abhor them, to utterly destroy them and break My covenant with them; for I am the LORD their God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26045, 'But for their sake I will remember the covenant of their ancestors, whom I brought out of the land of Egypt in the sight of the nations, that I might be their God: I am the LORD.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 26046, 'These are the statutes and judgments and laws which the LORD made between Himself and the children of Israel on Mount Sinai by the hand of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27001, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When a man consecrates by a vow certain persons to the LORD, according to your valuation,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27003, 'if your valuation is of a male from twenty years old up to sixty years old, then your valuation shall be fifty shekels of silver, according to the shekel of the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27004, 'If it is a female, then your valuation shall be thirty shekels;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27005, 'and if from five years old up to twenty years old, then your valuation for a male shall be twenty shekels, and for a female ten shekels;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27006, 'and if from a month old up to five years old, then your valuation for a male shall be five shekels of silver, and for a female your valuation shall be three shekels of silver;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27007, 'and if from sixty years old and above, if it is a male, then your valuation shall be fifteen shekels, and for a female ten shekels.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27008, '&lsquo;But if he is too poor to pay your valuation, then he shall present himself before the priest, and the priest shall set a value for him; according to the ability of him who vowed, the priest shall value him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27009, '&lsquo;If it is an animal that men may bring as an offering to the LORD, all that anyone gives to the LORD shall be holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27010, 'He shall not substitute it or exchange it, good for bad or bad for good; and if he at all exchanges animal for animal, then both it and the one exchanged for it shall be holy.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27011, 'If it is an unclean animal which they do not offer as a sacrifice to the LORD, then he shall present the animal before the priest;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27012, 'and the priest shall set a value for it, whether it is good or bad; as you, the priest, value it, so it shall be.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27013, 'But if he wants at all to redeem it, then he must add one-fifth to your valuation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27014, '&lsquo;And when a man dedicates his house to be holy to the LORD, then the priest shall set a value for it, whether it is good or bad; as the priest values it, so it shall stand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27015, 'If he who dedicated it wants to redeem his house, then he must add one-fifth of the money of your valuation to it, and it shall be his.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27016, '&lsquo;If a man dedicates to the LORD part of a field of his possession, then your valuation shall be according to the seed for it. A homer of barley seed shall be valued at fifty shekels of silver.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27017, 'If he dedicates his field from the Year of Jubilee, according to your valuation it shall stand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27018, 'But if he dedicates his field after the Jubilee, then the priest shall reckon to him the money due according to the years that remain till the Year of Jubilee, and it shall be deducted from your valuation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27019, 'And if he who dedicates the field ever wishes to redeem it, then he must add one-fifth of the money of your valuation to it, and it shall belong to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27020, 'But if he does not want to redeem the field, or if he has sold the field to another man, it shall not be redeemed anymore;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27021, 'but the field, when it is released in the Jubilee, shall be holy to the LORD, as a devoted field; it shall be the possession of the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27022, '&lsquo;And if a man dedicates to the LORD a field which he has bought, which is not the field of his possession,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27023, 'then the priest shall reckon to him the worth of your valuation, up to the Year of Jubilee, and he shall give your valuation on that day as a holy offering to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27024, 'In the Year of Jubilee the field shall return to him from whom it was bought, to the one who owned the land as a possession.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27025, 'And all your valuations shall be according to the shekel of the sanctuary: twenty gerahs to the shekel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27026, '&lsquo;But the firstborn of the animals, which should be the LORD&rsquo;s firstborn, no man shall dedicate; whether it is an ox or sheep, it is the LORD&rsquo;s.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27027, 'And if it is an unclean animal, then he shall redeem it according to your valuation, and shall add one-fifth to it; or if it is not redeemed, then it shall be sold according to your valuation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27028, '&lsquo;Nevertheless no devoted offering that a man may devote to the LORD of all that he has, both man and beast, or the field of his possession, shall be sold or redeemed; every devoted offering is most holy to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27029, 'No person under the ban, who may become doomed to destruction among men, shall be redeemed, but shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27030, 'And all the tithe of the land, whether of the seed of the land or of the fruit of the tree, is the LORD&rsquo;s. It is holy to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27031, 'If a man wants at all to redeem any of his tithes, he shall add one-fifth to it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27032, 'And concerning the tithe of the herd or the flock, of whatever passes under the rod, the tenth one shall be holy to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27033, 'He shall not inquire whether it is good or bad, nor shall he exchange it; and if he exchanges it at all, then both it and the one exchanged for it shall be holy; it shall not be redeemed.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Lev', 27034, 'These are the commandments which the LORD commanded Moses for the children of Israel on Mount Sinai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1001, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses in the Wilderness of Sinai, in the tabernacle of meeting, on the first day of the second month, in the second year after they had come out of the land of Egypt, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1002, '&ldquo;Take a census of all the congregation of the children of Israel, by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; houses, according to the number of names, every male individually,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1003, 'from twenty years old and above &ndash; all who are able to go to war in Israel. You and Aaron shall number them by their armies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1004, 'And with you there shall be a man from every tribe, each one the head of his father&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1005, '&ldquo;These are the names of the men who shall stand with you: from Reuben, Elizur the son of Shedeur;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1006, 'from Simeon, Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1007, 'from Judah, Nahshon the son of Amminadab;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1008, 'from Issachar, Nethanel the son of Zuar;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1009, 'from Zebulun, Eliab the son of Helon;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1010, 'from the sons of Joseph: from Ephraim, Elishama the son of Ammihud; from Manasseh, Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1011, 'from Benjamin, Abidan the son of Gideoni;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1012, 'from Dan, Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1013, 'from Asher, Pagiel the son of Ocran;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1014, 'from Gad, Eliasaph the son of Deuel;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1015, 'from Naphtali, Ahira the son of Enan.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1016, 'These were chosen from the congregation, leaders of their fathers&rsquo; tribes, heads of the divisions in Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1017, 'Then Moses and Aaron took these men who had been mentioned by name,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1018, 'and they assembled all the congregation together on the first day of the second month; and they recited their ancestry by families, by their fathers&rsquo; houses, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, each one individually.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1019, 'As the LORD commanded Moses, so he numbered them in the Wilderness of Sinai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1020, 'Now the children of Reuben, Israel&rsquo;s oldest son, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, every male individually, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1021, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Reuben were forty-six thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1022, 'From the children of Simeon, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, of those who were numbered, according to the number of names, every male individually, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1023, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Simeon were fifty-nine thousand three hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1024, 'From the children of Gad, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1025, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Gad were forty-five thousand six hundred and fifty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1026, 'From the children of Judah, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1027, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Judah were seventy-four thousand six hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1028, 'From the children of Issachar, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1029, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Issachar were fifty-four thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1030, 'From the children of Zebulun, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1031, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Zebulun were fifty-seven thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1032, 'From the sons of Joseph, the children of Ephraim, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1033, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Ephraim were forty thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1034, 'From the children of Manasseh, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1035, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Manasseh were thirty-two thousand two hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1036, 'From the children of Benjamin, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1037, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Benjamin were thirty-five thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1038, 'From the children of Dan, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1039, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Dan were sixty-two thousand seven hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1040, 'From the children of Asher, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1041, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Asher were forty-one thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1042, 'From the children of Naphtali, their genealogies by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, according to the number of names, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1043, 'those who were numbered of the tribe of Naphtali were fifty-three thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1044, 'These are the ones who were numbered, whom Moses and Aaron numbered, with the leaders of Israel, twelve men, each one representing his father&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1045, 'So all who were numbered of the children of Israel, by their fathers&rsquo; houses, from twenty years old and above, all who were able to go to war in Israel &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1046, 'all who were numbered were six hundred and three thousand five hundred and fifty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1047, 'But the Levites were not numbered among them by their fathers&rsquo; tribe;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1048, 'for the LORD had spoken to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1049, '&ldquo;Only the tribe of Levi you shall not number, nor take a census of them among the children of Israel;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1050, 'but you shall appoint the Levites over the tabernacle of the Testimony, over all its furnishings, and over all things that belong to it; they shall carry the tabernacle and all its furnishings; they shall attend to it and camp around the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1051, 'And when the tabernacle is to go forward, the Levites shall take it down; and when the tabernacle is to be set up, the Levites shall set it up. The outsider who comes near shall be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1052, 'The children of Israel shall pitch their tents, everyone by his own camp, everyone by his own standard, according to their armies;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1053, 'but the Levites shall camp around the tabernacle of the Testimony, that there may be no wrath on the congregation of the children of Israel; and the Levites shall keep charge of the tabernacle of the Testimony.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 1054, 'Thus the children of Israel did; according to all that the LORD commanded Moses, so they did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2002, '&ldquo;Everyone of the children of Israel shall camp by his own standard, beside the emblems of his father&rsquo;s house; they shall camp some distance from the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2003, 'On the east side, toward the rising of the sun, those of the standard of the forces with Judah shall camp according to their armies; and Nahshon the son of Amminadab shall be the leader of the children of Judah.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2004, 'And his army was numbered at seventy-four thousand six hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2005, '&ldquo;Those who camp next to him shall be the tribe of Issachar, and Nethanel the son of Zuar shall be the leader of the children of Issachar.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2006, 'And his army was numbered at fifty-four thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2007, '&ldquo;Then comes the tribe of Zebulun, and Eliab the son of Helon shall be the leader of the children of Zebulun.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2008, 'And his army was numbered at fifty-seven thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2009, '&ldquo;All who were numbered according to their armies of the forces with Judah, one hundred and eighty-six thousand four hundred &ndash; these shall break camp first.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2010, '&ldquo;On the south side shall be the standard of the forces with Reuben according to their armies, and the leader of the children of Reuben shall be Elizur the son of Shedeur.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2011, 'And his army was numbered at forty-six thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2012, '&ldquo;Those who camp next to him shall be the tribe of Simeon, and the leader of the children of Simeon shall be Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2013, 'And his army was numbered at fifty-nine thousand three hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2014, '&ldquo;Then comes the tribe of Gad, and the leader of the children of Gad shall be Eliasaph the son of Reuel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2015, 'And his army was numbered at forty-five thousand six hundred and fifty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2016, '&ldquo;All who were numbered according to their armies of the forces with Reuben, one hundred and fifty-one thousand four hundred and fifty &ndash; they shall be the second to break camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2017, '&ldquo;And the tabernacle of meeting shall move out with the camp of the Levites in the middle of the camps; as they camp, so they shall move out, everyone in his place, by their standards.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2018, '&ldquo;On the west side shall be the standard of the forces with Ephraim according to their armies, and the leader of the children of Ephraim shall be Elishama the son of Ammihud.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2019, 'And his army was numbered at forty thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2020, '&ldquo;Next to him comes the tribe of Manasseh, and the leader of the children of Manasseh shall be Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2021, 'And his army was numbered at thirty-two thousand two hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2022, '&ldquo;Then comes the tribe of Benjamin, and the leader of the children of Benjamin shall be Abidan the son of Gideoni.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2023, 'And his army was numbered at thirty-five thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2024, '&ldquo;All who were numbered according to their armies of the forces with Ephraim, one hundred and eight thousand one hundred &ndash; they shall be the third to break camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2025, '&ldquo;The standard of the forces with Dan shall be on the north side according to their armies, and the leader of the children of Dan shall be Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2026, 'And his army was numbered at sixty-two thousand seven hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2027, '&ldquo;Those who camp next to him shall be the tribe of Asher, and the leader of the children of Asher shall be Pagiel the son of Ocran.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2028, 'And his army was numbered at forty-one thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2029, '&ldquo;Then comes the tribe of Naphtali, and the leader of the children of Naphtali shall be Ahira the son of Enan.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2030, 'And his army was numbered at fifty-three thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2031, '&ldquo;All who were numbered of the forces with Dan, one hundred and fifty-seven thousand six hundred &ndash; they shall break camp last, with their standards.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2032, 'These are the ones who were numbered of the children of Israel by their fathers&rsquo; houses. All who were numbered according to their armies of the forces were six hundred and three thousand five hundred and fifty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2033, 'But the Levites were not numbered among the children of Israel, just as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 2034, 'Thus the children of Israel did according to all that the LORD commanded Moses; so they camped by their standards and so they broke camp, each one by his family, according to their fathers&rsquo; houses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3001, 'Now these are the records of Aaron and Moses when the LORD spoke with Moses on Mount Sinai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3002, 'And these are the names of the sons of Aaron: Nadab, the firstborn, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3003, 'These are the names of the sons of Aaron, the anointed priests, whom he consecrated to minister as priests.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3004, 'Nadab and Abihu had died before the LORD when they offered profane fire before the LORD in the Wilderness of Sinai; and they had no children. So Eleazar and Ithamar ministered as priests in the presence of Aaron their father.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3005, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3006, '&ldquo;Bring the tribe of Levi near, and present them before Aaron the priest, that they may serve him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3007, 'And they shall attend to his needs and the needs of the whole congregation before the tabernacle of meeting, to do the work of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3008, 'Also they shall attend to all the furnishings of the tabernacle of meeting, and to the needs of the children of Israel, to do the work of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3009, 'And you shall give the Levites to Aaron and his sons; they are given entirely to him from among the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3010, 'So you shall appoint Aaron and his sons, and they shall attend to their priesthood; but the outsider who comes near shall be put to death.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3011, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3012, '&ldquo;Now behold, I Myself have taken the Levites from among the children of Israel instead of every firstborn who opens the womb among the children of Israel. Therefore the Levites shall be Mine,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3013, 'because all the firstborn are Mine. On the day that I struck all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, I sanctified to Myself all the firstborn in Israel, both man and beast. They shall be Mine: I am the LORD.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3014, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses in the Wilderness of Sinai, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3015, '&ldquo;Number the children of Levi by their fathers&rsquo; houses, by their families; you shall number every male from a month old and above.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3016, 'So Moses numbered them according to the word of the LORD, as he was commanded.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3017, 'These were the sons of Levi by their names: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3018, 'And these are the names of the sons of Gershon by their families: Libni and Shimei.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3019, 'And the sons of Kohath by their families: Amram, Izehar, Hebron, and Uzziel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3020, 'And the sons of Merari by their families: Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of the Levites by their fathers&rsquo; houses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3021, 'From Gershon came the family of the Libnites and the family of the Shimites; these were the families of the Gershonites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3022, 'Those who were numbered, according to the number of all the males from a month old and above &ndash; of those who were numbered there were seven thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3023, 'The families of the Gershonites were to camp behind the tabernacle westward.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3024, 'And the leader of the father&rsquo;s house of the Gershonites was Eliasaph the son of Lael.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3025, 'The duties of the children of Gershon in the tabernacle of meeting included the tabernacle, the tent with its covering, the screen for the door of the tabernacle of meeting,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3026, 'the screen for the door of the court, the hangings of the court which are around the tabernacle and the altar, and their cords, according to all the work relating to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3027, 'From Kohath came the family of the Amramites, the family of the Izharites, the family of the Hebronites, and the family of the Uzzielites; these were the families of the Kohathites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3028, 'According to the number of all the males, from a month old and above, there were eight thousand six hundred keeping charge of the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3029, 'The families of the children of Kohath were to camp on the south side of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3030, 'And the leader of the fathers&rsquo; house of the families of the Kohathites was Elizaphan the son of Uzziel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3031, 'Their duty included the ark, the table, the lampstand, the altars, the utensils of the sanctuary with which they ministered, the screen, and all the work relating to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3032, 'And Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest was to be chief over the leaders of the Levites, with oversight of those who kept charge of the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3033, 'From Merari came the family of the Mahlites and the family of the Mushites; these were the families of Merari.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3034, 'And those who were numbered, according to the number of all the males from a month old and above, were six thousand two hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3035, 'The leader of the fathers&rsquo; house of the families of Merari was Zuriel the son of Abihail. These were to camp on the north side of the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3036, 'And the appointed duty of the children of Merari included the boards of the tabernacle, its bars, its pillars, its sockets, its utensils, all the work relating to them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3037, 'and the pillars of the court all around, with their sockets, their pegs, and their cords.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3038, 'Moreover those who were to camp before the tabernacle on the east, before the tabernacle of meeting, were Moses, Aaron, and his sons, keeping charge of the sanctuary, to meet the needs of the children of Israel; but the outsider who came near was to be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3039, 'All who were numbered of the Levites, whom Moses and Aaron numbered at the commandment of the LORD, by their families, all the males from a month old and above, were twenty-two thousand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3040, 'Then the LORD said to Moses: &ldquo;Number all the firstborn males of the children of Israel from a month old and above, and take the number of their names.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3041, 'And you shall take the Levites for Me &ndash; I am the LORD &ndash; instead of all the firstborn among the children of Israel, and the livestock of the Levites instead of all the firstborn among the livestock of the children of Israel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3042, 'So Moses numbered all the firstborn among the children of Israel, as the LORD commanded him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3043, 'And all the firstborn males, according to the number of names from a month old and above, of those who were numbered of them, were twenty-two thousand two hundred and seventy-three.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3044, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3045, '&ldquo;Take the Levites instead of all the firstborn among the children of Israel, and the livestock of the Levites instead of their livestock. The Levites shall be Mine: I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3046, 'And for the redemption of the two hundred and seventy-three of the firstborn of the children of Israel, who are more than the number of the Levites,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3047, 'you shall take five shekels for each one individually; you shall take them in the currency of the shekel of the sanctuary, the shekel of twenty gerahs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3048, 'And you shall give the money, with which the excess number of them is redeemed, to Aaron and his sons.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3049, 'So Moses took the redemption money from those who were over and above those who were redeemed by the Levites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3050, 'From the firstborn of the children of Israel he took the money, one thousand three hundred and sixty-five shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 3051, 'And Moses gave their redemption money to Aaron and his sons, according to the word of the LORD, as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4001, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4002, '&ldquo;Take a census of the sons of Kohath from among the children of Levi, by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4003, 'from thirty years old and above, even to fifty years old, all who enter the service to do the work in the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4004, '&ldquo;This is the service of the sons of Kohath in the tabernacle of meeting, relating to the most holy things:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4005, 'When the camp prepares to journey, Aaron and his sons shall come, and they shall take down the covering veil and cover the ark of the Testimony with it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4006, 'Then they shall put on it a covering of badger skins, and spread over that a cloth entirely of blue; and they shall insert its poles.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4007, '&ldquo;On the table of showbread they shall spread a blue cloth, and put on it the dishes, the pans, the bowls, and the pitchers for pouring; and the showbread shall be on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4008, 'They shall spread over them a scarlet cloth, and cover the same with a covering of badger skins; and they shall insert its poles.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4009, 'And they shall take a blue cloth and cover the lampstand of the light, with its lamps, its wick-trimmers, its trays, and all its oil vessels, with which they service it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4010, 'Then they shall put it with all its utensils in a covering of badger skins, and put it on a carrying beam.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4011, '&ldquo;Over the golden altar they shall spread a blue cloth, and cover it with a covering of badger skins; and they shall insert its poles.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4012, 'Then they shall take all the utensils of service with which they minister in the sanctuary, put them in a blue cloth, cover them with a covering of badger skins, and put them on a carrying beam.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4013, 'Also they shall take away the ashes from the altar, and spread a purple cloth over it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4014, 'They shall put on it all its implements with which they minister there &ndash; the firepans, the forks, the shovels, the basins, and all the utensils of the altar &ndash; and they shall spread on it a covering of badger skins, and insert its poles.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4015, 'And when Aaron and his sons have finished covering the sanctuary and all the furnishings of the sanctuary, when the camp is set to go, then the sons of Kohath shall come to carry them; but they shall not touch any holy thing, lest they die. &ldquo;These are the things in the tabernacle of meeting which the sons of Kohath are to carry.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4016, '&ldquo;The appointed duty of Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest is the oil for the light, the sweet incense, the daily grain offering, the anointing oil, the oversight of all the tabernacle, of all that is in it, with the sanctuary and its furnishings.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4017, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4018, '&ldquo;Do not cut off the tribe of the families of the Kohathites from among the Levites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4019, 'but do this in regard to them, that they may live and not die when they approach the most holy things: Aaron and his sons shall go in and appoint each of them to his service and his task.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4020, 'But they shall not go in to watch while the holy things are being covered, lest they die.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4021, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4022, '&ldquo;Also take a census of the sons of Gershon, by their fathers&rsquo; house, by their families.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4023, 'From thirty years old and above, even to fifty years old, you shall number them, all who enter to perform the service, to do the work in the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4024, 'This is the service of the families of the Gershonites, in serving and carrying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4025, 'They shall carry the curtains of the tabernacle and the tabernacle of meeting with its covering, the covering of badger skins that is on it, the screen for the door of the tabernacle of meeting,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4026, 'the screen for the door of the gate of the court, the hangings of the court which are around the tabernacle and altar, and their cords, all the furnishings for their service and all that is made for these things: so shall they serve.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4027, '&ldquo;Aaron and his sons shall assign all the service of the sons of the Gershonites, all their tasks and all their service. And you shall appoint to them all their tasks as their duty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4028, 'This is the service of the families of the sons of Gershon in the tabernacle of meeting. And their duties shall be under the authority of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4029, '&ldquo;As for the sons of Merari, you shall number them by their families and by their fathers&rsquo; house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4030, 'From thirty years old and above, even to fifty years old, you shall number them, everyone who enters the service to do the work of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4031, 'And this is what they must carry as all their service for the tabernacle of meeting: the boards of the tabernacle, its bars, its pillars, its sockets,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4032, 'and the pillars around the court with their sockets, pegs, and cords, with all their furnishings and all their service; and you shall assign to each man by name the items he must carry.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4033, 'This is the service of the families of the sons of Merari, as all their service for the tabernacle of meeting, under the authority of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4034, 'And Moses, Aaron, and the leaders of the congregation numbered the sons of the Kohathites by their families and by their fathers&rsquo; house,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4035, 'from thirty years old and above, even to fifty years old, everyone who entered the service for work in the tabernacle of meeting;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4036, 'and those who were numbered by their families were two thousand seven hundred and fifty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4037, 'These were the ones who were numbered of the families of the Kohathites, all who might serve in the tabernacle of meeting, whom Moses and Aaron numbered according to the commandment of the LORD by the hand of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4038, 'And those who were numbered of the sons of Gershon, by their families and by their fathers&rsquo; house,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4039, 'from thirty years old and above, even to fifty years old, everyone who entered the service for work in the tabernacle of meeting &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4040, 'those who were numbered by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house, were two thousand six hundred and thirty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4041, 'These are the ones who were numbered of the families of the sons of Gershon, of all who might serve in the tabernacle of meeting, whom Moses and Aaron numbered according to the commandment of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4042, 'Those of the families of the sons of Merari who were numbered, by their families, by their fathers&rsquo; house,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4043, 'from thirty years old and above, even to fifty years old, everyone who entered the service for work in the tabernacle of meeting &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4044, 'those who were numbered by their families were three thousand two hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4045, 'These are the ones who were numbered of the families of the sons of Merari, whom Moses and Aaron numbered according to the word of the LORD by the hand of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4046, 'All who were numbered of the Levites, whom Moses, Aaron, and the leaders of Israel numbered, by their families and by their fathers&rsquo; houses,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4047, 'from thirty years old and above, even to fifty years old, everyone who came to do the work of service and the work of bearing burdens in the tabernacle of meeting &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4048, 'those who were numbered were eight thousand five hundred and eighty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 4049, 'According to the commandment of the LORD they were numbered by the hand of Moses, each according to his service and according to his task; thus were they numbered by him, as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5002, '&ldquo;Command the children of Israel that they put out of the camp every leper, everyone who has a discharge, and whoever becomes defiled by a corpse.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5003, 'You shall put out both male and female; you shall put them outside the camp, that they may not defile their camps in the midst of which I dwell.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5004, 'And the children of Israel did so, and put them outside the camp; as the LORD spoke to Moses, so the children of Israel did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5005, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5006, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel: &lsquo;When a man or woman commits any sin that men commit in unfaithfulness against the LORD, and that person is guilty,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5007, 'then he shall confess the sin which he has committed. He shall make restitution for his trespass in full, plus one-fifth of it, and give it to the one he has wronged.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5008, 'But if the man has no relative to whom restitution may be made for the wrong, the restitution for the wrong must go to the LORD for the priest, in addition to the ram of the atonement with which atonement is made for him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5009, 'Every offering of all the holy things of the children of Israel, which they bring to the priest, shall be his.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5010, 'And every man&rsquo;s holy things shall be his; whatever any man gives the priest shall be his.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5011, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5012, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;If any man&rsquo;s wife goes astray and behaves unfaithfully toward him,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5013, 'and a man lies with her carnally, and it is hidden from the eyes of her husband, and it is concealed that she has defiled herself, and there was no witness against her, nor was she caught &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5014, 'if the spirit of jealousy comes upon him and he becomes jealous of his wife, who has defiled herself; or if the spirit of jealousy comes upon him and he becomes jealous of his wife, although she has not defiled herself &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5015, 'then the man shall bring his wife to the priest. He shall bring the offering required for her, one-tenth of an ephah of barley meal; he shall pour no oil on it and put no frankincense on it, because it is a grain offering of jealousy, an offering for remembering, for bringing iniquity to remembrance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5016, '&lsquo;And the priest shall bring her near, and set her before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5017, 'The priest shall take holy water in an earthen vessel, and take some of the dust that is on the floor of the tabernacle and put it into the water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5018, 'Then the priest shall stand the woman before the LORD, uncover the woman&rsquo;s head, and put the offering for remembering in her hands, which is the grain offering of jealousy. And the priest shall have in his hand the bitter water that brings a curse.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5019, 'And the priest shall put her under oath, and say to the woman, &ldquo;If no man has lain with you, and if you have not gone astray to uncleanness while under your husband&rsquo;s authority, be free from this bitter water that brings a curse.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5020, 'But if you have gone astray while under your husband&rsquo;s authority, and if you have defiled yourself and some man other than your husband has lain with you&rdquo; &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5021, 'then the priest shall put the woman under the oath of the curse, and he shall say to the woman &ndash; &ldquo;the LORD make you a curse and an oath among your people, when the LORD makes your thigh rot and your belly swell;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5022, 'and may this water that causes the curse go into your stomach, and make your belly swell and your thigh rot.&rdquo; Then the woman shall say, &ldquo;Amen, so be it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5023, '&lsquo;Then the priest shall write these curses in a book, and he shall scrape them off into the bitter water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5024, 'And he shall make the woman drink the bitter water that brings a curse, and the water that brings the curse shall enter her to become bitter.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5025, 'Then the priest shall take the grain offering of jealousy from the woman&rsquo;s hand, shall wave the offering before the LORD, and bring it to the altar;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5026, 'and the priest shall take a handful of the offering, as its memorial portion, burn it on the altar, and afterward make the woman drink the water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5027, 'When he has made her drink the water, then it shall be, if she has defiled herself and behaved unfaithfully toward her husband, that the water that brings a curse will enter her and become bitter, and her belly will swell, her thigh will rot, and the woman will become a curse among her people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5028, 'But if the woman has not defiled herself, and is clean, then she shall be free and may conceive children.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5029, '&lsquo;This is the law of jealousy, when a wife, while under her husband&rsquo;s authority, goes astray and defiles herself,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5030, 'or when the spirit of jealousy comes upon a man, and he becomes jealous of his wife; then he shall stand the woman before the LORD, and the priest shall execute all this law upon her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 5031, 'Then the man shall be free from iniquity, but that woman shall bear her guilt.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6001, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When either a man or woman consecrates an offering to take the vow of a Nazirite, to separate himself to the LORD,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6003, 'he shall separate himself from wine and similar drink; he shall drink neither vinegar made from wine nor vinegar made from similar drink; neither shall he drink any grape juice, nor eat fresh grapes or raisins.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6004, 'All the days of his separation he shall eat nothing that is produced by the grapevine, from seed to skin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6005, '&lsquo;All the days of the vow of his separation no razor shall come upon his head; until the days are fulfilled for which he separated himself to the LORD, he shall be holy. Then he shall let the locks of the hair of his head grow.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6006, 'All the days that he separates himself to the LORD he shall not go near a dead body.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6007, 'He shall not make himself unclean even for his father or his mother, for his brother or his sister, when they die, because his separation to God is on his head.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6008, 'All the days of his separation he shall be holy to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6009, '&lsquo;And if anyone dies very suddenly beside him, and he defiles his consecrated head, then he shall shave his head on the day of his cleansing; on the seventh day he shall shave it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6010, 'Then on the eighth day he shall bring two turtledoves or two young pigeons to the priest, to the door of the tabernacle of meeting;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6011, 'and the priest shall offer one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering, and make atonement for him, because he sinned in regard to the corpse; and he shall sanctify his head that same day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6012, 'He shall consecrate to the LORD the days of his separation, and bring a male lamb in its first year as a trespass offering; but the former days shall be lost, because his separation was defiled.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6013, '&lsquo;Now this is the law of the Nazirite: When the days of his separation are fulfilled, he shall be brought to the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6014, 'And he shall present his offering to the LORD: one male lamb in its first year without blemish as a burnt offering, one ewe lamb in its first year without blemish as a sin offering, one ram without blemish as a peace offering,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6015, 'a basket of unleavened bread, cakes of fine flour mixed with oil, unleavened wafers anointed with oil, and their grain offering with their drink offerings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6016, '&lsquo;Then the priest shall bring them before the LORD and offer his sin offering and his burnt offering;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6017, 'and he shall offer the ram as a sacrifice of a peace offering to the LORD, with the basket of unleavened bread; the priest shall also offer its grain offering and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6018, 'Then the Nazirite shall shave his consecrated head at the door of the tabernacle of meeting, and shall take the hair from his consecrated head and put it on the fire which is under the sacrifice of the peace offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6019, '&lsquo;And the priest shall take the boiled shoulder of the ram, one unleavened cake from the basket, and one unleavened wafer, and put them upon the hands of the Nazirite after he has shaved his consecrated hair,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6020, 'and the priest shall wave them as a wave offering before the LORD; they are holy for the priest, together with the breast of the wave offering and the thigh of the heave offering. After that the Nazirite may drink wine.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 6021, '&ldquo;This is the law of the Nazirite who vows to the LORD the offering for his separation, and besides that, whatever else his hand is able to provide; according to the vow which he takes, so he must do according to the law of his separation.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7001, 'Now it came to pass, when Moses had finished setting up the tabernacle, that he anointed it and consecrated it and all its furnishings, and the altar and all its utensils; so he anointed them and consecrated them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7002, 'Then the leaders of Israel, the heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses, who were the leaders of the tribes and over those who were numbered, made an offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7003, 'And they brought their offering before the LORD, six covered carts and twelve oxen, a cart for every two of the leaders, and for each one an ox; and they presented them before the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7004, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7005, '&ldquo;Accept these from them, that they may be used in doing the work of the tabernacle of meeting; and you shall give them to the Levites, to every man according to his service.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7006, 'So Moses took the carts and the oxen, and gave them to the Levites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7007, 'Two carts and four oxen he gave to the sons of Gershon, according to their service;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7008, 'and four carts and eight oxen he gave to the sons of Merari, according to their service, under the authority of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7009, 'But to the sons of Kohath he gave none, because theirs was the service of the holy things, which they carried on their shoulders.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7010, 'Now the leaders offered the dedication offering for the altar when it was anointed; so the leaders offered their offering before the altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7011, 'For the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;They shall offer their offering, one leader each day, for the dedication of the altar.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7012, 'And the one who offered his offering on the first day was Nahshon the son of Amminadab, from the tribe of Judah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7013, 'His offering was one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels, and one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7014, 'one gold pan of ten shekels, full of incense;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7015, 'one young bull, one ram, and one male lamb in its first year, as a burnt offering;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7016, 'one kid of the goats as a sin offering;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7017, 'and for the sacrifice of peace offerings: two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs in their first year. This was the offering of Nahshon the son of Amminadab.');
