INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7084, 'This was the dedication offering for the altar from the leaders of Israel, when it was anointed: twelve silver platters, twelve silver bowls, and twelve gold pans.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7085, 'Each silver platter weighed one hundred and thirty shekels and each bowl seventy shekels. All the silver of the vessels weighed two thousand four hundred shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7086, 'The twelve gold pans full of incense weighed ten shekels apiece, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; all the gold of the pans weighed one hundred and twenty shekels.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7087, 'All the oxen for the burnt offering were twelve young bulls, the rams twelve, the male lambs in their first year twelve, with their grain offering, and the kids of the goats as a sin offering twelve.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7088, 'And all the oxen for the sacrifice of peace offerings were twenty-four bulls, the rams sixty, the male goats sixty, and the lambs in their first year sixty. This was the dedication offering for the altar after it was anointed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 7089, 'Now when Moses went into the tabernacle of meeting to speak with Him, he heard the voice of One speaking to him from above the mercy seat that was on the ark of the Testimony, from between the two cherubim; thus He spoke to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8002, '&ldquo;Speak to Aaron, and say to him, &lsquo;When you arrange the lamps, the seven lamps shall give light in front of the lampstand.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8003, 'And Aaron did so; he arranged the lamps to face toward the front of the lampstand, as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8004, 'Now this workmanship of the lampstand was hammered gold; from its shaft to its flowers it was hammered work. According to the pattern which the LORD had shown Moses, so he made the lampstand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8005, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8006, '&ldquo;Take the Levites from among the children of Israel and cleanse them ceremonially.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8007, 'Thus you shall do to them to cleanse them: Sprinkle water of purification on them, and let them shave all their body, and let them wash their clothes, and so make themselves clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8008, 'Then let them take a young bull with its grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil, and you shall take another young bull as a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8009, 'And you shall bring the Levites before the tabernacle of meeting, and you shall gather together the whole congregation of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8010, 'So you shall bring the Levites before the LORD, and the children of Israel shall lay their hands on the Levites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8011, 'and Aaron shall offer the Levites before the LORD like a wave offering from the children of Israel, that they may perform the work of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8012, 'Then the Levites shall lay their hands on the heads of the young bulls, and you shall offer one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering to the LORD, to make atonement for the Levites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8013, '&ldquo;And you shall stand the Levites before Aaron and his sons, and then offer them like a wave offering to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8014, 'Thus you shall separate the Levites from among the children of Israel, and the Levites shall be Mine.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8015, 'After that the Levites shall go in to service the tabernacle of meeting. So you shall cleanse them and offer them like a wave offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8016, 'For they are wholly given to Me from among the children of Israel; I have taken them for Myself instead of all who open the womb, the firstborn of all the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8017, 'For all the firstborn among the children of Israel are Mine, both man and beast; on the day that I struck all the firstborn in the land of Egypt I sanctified them to Myself.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8018, 'I have taken the Levites instead of all the firstborn of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8019, 'And I have given the Levites as a gift to Aaron and his sons from among the children of Israel, to do the work for the children of Israel in the tabernacle of meeting, and to make atonement for the children of Israel, that there be no plague among the children of Israel when the children of Israel come near the sanctuary.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8020, 'Thus Moses and Aaron and all the congregation of the children of Israel did to the Levites; according to all that the LORD commanded Moses concerning the Levites, so the children of Israel did to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8021, 'And the Levites purified themselves and washed their clothes; then Aaron presented them like a wave offering before the LORD, and Aaron made atonement for them to cleanse them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8022, 'After that the Levites went in to do their work in the tabernacle of meeting before Aaron and his sons; as the LORD commanded Moses concerning the Levites, so they did to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8023, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8024, '&ldquo;This is what pertains to the Levites: From twenty-five years old and above one may enter to perform service in the work of the tabernacle of meeting;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8025, 'and at the age of fifty years they must cease performing this work, and shall work no more.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 8026, 'They may minister with their brethren in the tabernacle of meeting, to attend to needs, but they themselves shall do no work. Thus you shall do to the Levites regarding their duties.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9001, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses in the Wilderness of Sinai, in the first month of the second year after they had come out of the land of Egypt, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9002, '&ldquo;Let the children of Israel keep the Passover at its appointed time.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9003, 'On the fourteenth day of this month, at twilight, you shall keep it at its appointed time. According to all its rites and ceremonies you shall keep it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9004, 'So Moses told the children of Israel that they should keep the Passover.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9005, 'And they kept the Passover on the fourteenth day of the first month, at twilight, in the Wilderness of Sinai; according to all that the LORD commanded Moses, so the children of Israel did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9006, 'Now there were certain men who were defiled by a human corpse, so that they could not keep the Passover on that day; and they came before Moses and Aaron that day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9007, 'And those men said to him, &ldquo;We became defiled by a human corpse. Why are we kept from presenting the offering of the LORD at its appointed time among the children of Israel?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9008, 'And Moses said to them, &ldquo;Stand still, that I may hear what the LORD will command concerning you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9009, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9010, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;If anyone of you or your posterity is unclean because of a corpse, or is far away on a journey, he may still keep the LORD&rsquo;s Passover.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9011, 'On the fourteenth day of the second month, at twilight, they may keep it. They shall eat it with unleavened bread and bitter herbs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9012, 'They shall leave none of it until morning, nor break one of its bones. According to all the ordinances of the Passover they shall keep it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9013, 'But the man who is clean and is not on a journey, and ceases to keep the Passover, that same person shall be cut off from among his people, because he did not bring the offering of the LORD at its appointed time; that man shall bear his sin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9014, '&lsquo;And if a stranger dwells among you, and would keep the LORD&rsquo;s Passover, he must do so according to the rite of the Passover and according to its ceremony; you shall have one ordinance, both for the stranger and the native of the land.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9015, 'Now on the day that the tabernacle was raised up, the cloud covered the tabernacle, the tent of the Testimony; from evening until morning it was above the tabernacle like the appearance of fire.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9016, 'So it was always: the cloud covered it by day, and the appearance of fire by night.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9017, 'Whenever the cloud was taken up from above the tabernacle, after that the children of Israel would journey; and in the place where the cloud settled, there the children of Israel would pitch their tents.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9018, 'At the command of the LORD the children of Israel would journey, and at the command of the LORD they would camp; as long as the cloud stayed above the tabernacle they remained encamped.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9019, 'Even when the cloud continued long, many days above the tabernacle, the children of Israel kept the charge of the LORD and did not journey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9020, 'So it was, when the cloud was above the tabernacle a few days: according to the command of the LORD they would remain encamped, and according to the command of the LORD they would journey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9021, 'So it was, when the cloud remained only from evening until morning: when the cloud was taken up in the morning, then they would journey; whether by day or by night, whenever the cloud was taken up, they would journey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9022, 'Whether it was two days, a month, or a year that the cloud remained above the tabernacle, the children of Israel would remain encamped and not journey; but when it was taken up, they would journey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 9023, 'At the command of the LORD they remained encamped, and at the command of the LORD they journeyed; they kept the charge of the LORD, at the command of the LORD by the hand of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10002, '&ldquo;Make two silver trumpets for yourself; you shall make them of hammered work; you shall use them for calling the congregation and for directing the movement of the camps.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10003, 'When they blow both of them, all the congregation shall gather before you at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10004, 'But if they blow only one, then the leaders, the heads of the divisions of Israel, shall gather to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10005, 'When you sound the advance, the camps that lie on the east side shall then begin their journey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10006, 'When you sound the advance the second time, then the camps that lie on the south side shall begin their journey; they shall sound the call for them to begin their journeys.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10007, 'And when the assembly is to be gathered together, you shall blow, but not sound the advance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10008, 'The sons of Aaron, the priests, shall blow the trumpets; and these shall be to you as an ordinance forever throughout your generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10009, '&ldquo;When you go to war in your land against the enemy who oppresses you, then you shall sound an alarm with the trumpets, and you will be remembered before the LORD your God, and you will be saved from your enemies.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10010, 'Also in the day of your gladness, in your appointed feasts, and at the beginning of your months, you shall blow the trumpets over your burnt offerings and over the sacrifices of your peace offerings; and they shall be a memorial for you before your God: I am the LORD your God.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10011, 'Now it came to pass on the twentieth day of the second month, in the second year, that the cloud was taken up from above the tabernacle of the Testimony.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10012, 'And the children of Israel set out from the Wilderness of Sinai on their journeys; then the cloud settled down in the Wilderness of Paran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10013, 'So they started out for the first time according to the command of the LORD by the hand of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10014, 'The standard of the camp of the children of Judah set out first according to their armies; over their army was Nahshon the son of Amminadab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10015, 'Over the army of the tribe of the children of Issachar was Nethanel the son of Zuar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10016, 'And over the army of the tribe of the children of Zebulun was Eliab the son of Helon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10017, 'Then the tabernacle was taken down; and the sons of Gershon and the sons of Merari set out, carrying the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10018, 'And the standard of the camp of Reuben set out according to their armies; over their army was Elizur the son of Shedeur.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10019, 'Over the army of the tribe of the children of Simeon was Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10020, 'And over the army of the tribe of the children of Gad was Eliasaph the son of Deuel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10021, 'Then the Kohathites set out, carrying the holy things. (The tabernacle would be prepared for their arrival.)');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10022, 'And the standard of the camp of the children of Ephraim set out according to their armies; over their army was Elishama the son of Ammihud.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10023, 'Over the army of the tribe of the children of Manasseh was Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10024, 'And over the army of the tribe of the children of Benjamin was Abidan the son of Gideoni.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10025, 'Then the standard of the camp of the children of Dan (the rear guard of all the camps) set out according to their armies; over their army was Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10026, 'Over the army of the tribe of the children of Asher was Pagiel the son of Ocran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10027, 'And over the army of the tribe of the children of Naphtali was Ahira the son of Enan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10028, 'Thus was the order of march of the children of Israel, according to their armies, when they began their journey.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10029, 'Now Moses said to Hobab the son of Reuel the Midianite, Moses&rsquo; father-in-law, &ldquo;We are setting out for the place of which the LORD said, &lsquo;I will give it to you.&rsquo; Come with us, and we will treat you well; for the LORD has promised good things to Israel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10030, 'And he said to him, &ldquo;I will not go, but I will depart to my own land and to my relatives.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10031, 'So Moses said, &ldquo;Please do not leave, inasmuch as you know how we are to camp in the wilderness, and you can be our eyes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10032, 'And it shall be, if you go with us &ndash; indeed it shall be &ndash; that whatever good the LORD will do to us, the same we will do to you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10033, 'So they departed from the mountain of the LORD on a journey of three days; and the ark of the covenant of the LORD went before them for the three days&rsquo; journey, to search out a resting place for them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10034, 'And the cloud of the LORD was above them by day when they went out from the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10035, 'So it was, whenever the ark set out, that Moses said: &ldquo;Rise up, O LORD! Let Your enemies be scattered, And let those who hate You flee before You.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 10036, 'And when it rested, he said: &ldquo; Return, O LORD, To the many thousands of Israel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11001, 'Now when the people complained, it displeased the LORD; for the LORD heard it, and His anger was aroused. So the fire of the LORD burned among them, and consumed some in the outskirts of the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11002, 'Then the people cried out to Moses, and when Moses prayed to the LORD, the fire was quenched.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11003, 'So he called the name of the place Taberah,[a] because the fire of the LORD had burned among them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11004, 'Now the mixed multitude who were among them yielded to intense craving; so the children of Israel also wept again and said: &ldquo;Who will give us meat to eat?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11005, 'We remember the fish which we ate freely in Egypt, the cucumbers, the melons, the leeks, the onions, and the garlic;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11006, 'but now our whole being is dried up; there is nothing at all except this manna before our eyes!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11007, 'Now the manna was like coriander seed, and its color like the color of bdellium.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11008, 'The people went about and gathered it, ground it on millstones or beat it in the mortar, cooked it in pans, and made cakes of it; and its taste was like the taste of pastry prepared with oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11009, 'And when the dew fell on the camp in the night, the manna fell on it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11010, 'Then Moses heard the people weeping throughout their families, everyone at the door of his tent; and the anger of the LORD was greatly aroused; Moses also was displeased.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11011, 'So Moses said to the LORD, &ldquo;Why have You afflicted Your servant? And why have I not found favor in Your sight, that You have laid the burden of all these people on me?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11012, 'Did I conceive all these people? Did I beget them, that You should say to me, &lsquo;Carry them in your bosom, as a guardian carries a nursing child,&rsquo; to the land which You swore to their fathers?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11013, 'Where am I to get meat to give to all these people? For they weep all over me, saying, &lsquo;Give us meat, that we may eat.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11014, 'I am not able to bear all these people alone, because the burden is too heavy for me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11015, 'If You treat me like this, please kill me here and now &ndash; if I have found favor in Your sight &ndash; and do not let me see my wretchedness!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11016, 'So* the LORD said to Moses: &ldquo;Gather to Me seventy men of the elders of Israel, whom you know to be the elders of the people and officers over them; bring them to the tabernacle of meeting, that they may stand there with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11017, 'Then I will come down and talk with you there. I will take of the Spirit that is upon you and will put the same upon them; and they shall bear the burden of the people with you, that you may not bear it yourself alone.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11018, 'Then you shall say to the people, &lsquo;Consecrate yourselves for tomorrow, and you shall eat meat; for you have wept in the hearing of the LORD, saying, &ldquo;Who will give us meat to eat? For it was well with us in Egypt.&rdquo; Therefore the LORD will give you meat, and you shall eat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11019, 'You shall eat, not one day, nor two days, nor five days, nor ten days, nor twenty days,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11020, 'but for a whole month, until it comes out of your nostrils and becomes loathsome to you, because you have despised the LORD who is among you, and have wept before Him, saying, &ldquo;Why did we ever come up out of Egypt?&rdquo;&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11021, 'And Moses said, &ldquo;The people whom I am among are six hundred thousand men on foot; yet You have said, &lsquo;I will give them meat, that they may eat for a whole month.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11022, 'Shall flocks and herds be slaughtered for them, to provide enough for them? Or shall all the fish of the sea be gathered together for them, to provide enough for them?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11023, 'And the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;Has the LORD&rsquo;s arm been shortened? Now you shall see whether what I say will happen to you or not.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11024, 'So Moses went out and told the people the words of the LORD, and he gathered the seventy men of the elders of the people and placed them around the tabernacle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11025, 'Then the LORD came down in the cloud, and spoke to him, and took of the Spirit that was upon him, and placed the same upon the seventy elders; and it happened, when the Spirit rested upon them, that they prophesied, although they never did so again.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11026, 'But two men had remained in the camp: the name of one was Eldad, and the name of the other Medad. And the Spirit rested upon them. Now they were among those listed, but who had not gone out to the tabernacle; yet they prophesied in the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11027, 'And a young man ran and told Moses, and said, &ldquo;Eldad and Medad are prophesying in the camp.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11028, 'So Joshua the son of Nun, Moses&rsquo; assistant, one of his choice men, answered and said, &ldquo;Moses my lord, forbid them!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11029, 'Then Moses said to him, &ldquo;Are you zealous for my sake? Oh, that all the LORD&rsquo;s people were prophets and that the LORD would put His Spirit upon them!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11030, 'And Moses returned to the camp, he and the elders of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11031, 'Now a wind went out from the LORD, and it brought quail from the sea and left them fluttering near the camp, about a day&rsquo;s journey on this side and about a day&rsquo;s journey on the other side, all around the camp, and about two cubits above the surface of the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11032, 'And the people stayed up all that day, all night, and all the next day, and gathered the quail (he who gathered least gathered ten homers); and they spread them out for themselves all around the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11033, 'But while the meat was still between their teeth, before it was chewed, the wrath of the LORD was aroused against the people, and the LORD struck the people with a very great plague.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11034, 'So he called the name of that place Kibroth Hattaavah, because there they buried the people who had yielded to craving.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 11035, 'From Kibroth Hattaavah the people moved to Hazeroth, and camped at Hazeroth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12001, 'Then Miriam and Aaron spoke against Moses because of the Ethiopian woman whom he had married; for he had married an Ethiopian woman.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12002, 'So they said, &ldquo;Has the LORD indeed spoken only through Moses? Has He not spoken through us also?&rdquo; And the LORD heard it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12003, '(Now the man Moses was very humble, more than all men who were on the face of the earth.)');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12004, 'Suddenly the LORD said to Moses, Aaron, and Miriam, &ldquo;Come out, you three, to the tabernacle of meeting!&rdquo; So the three came out.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12005, 'Then the LORD came down in the pillar of cloud and stood in the door of the tabernacle, and called Aaron and Miriam. And they both went forward.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12006, 'Then He said, &ldquo;Hear now My words: If there is a prophet among you, I, the LORD, make Myself known to him in a vision; I speak to him in a dream.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12007, 'Not so with My servant Moses; He is faithful in all My house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12008, 'I speak with him face to face, Even plainly, and not in dark sayings; And he sees the form of the LORD. Why then were you not afraid To speak against My servant Moses?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12009, 'So the anger of the LORD was aroused against them, and He departed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12010, 'And when the cloud departed from above the tabernacle, suddenly Miriam became leprous, as white as snow. Then Aaron turned toward Miriam, and there she was, a leper.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12011, 'So Aaron said to Moses, &ldquo;Oh, my lord! Please do not lay this sin on us, in which we have done foolishly and in which we have sinned.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12012, 'Please do not let her be as one dead, whose flesh is half consumed when he comes out of his mother&rsquo;s womb!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12013, 'So Moses cried out to the LORD, saying, &ldquo;Please heal her, O God, I pray!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12014, 'Then the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;If her father had but spit in her face, would she not be shamed seven days? Let her be shut out of the camp seven days, and afterward she may be received again.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12015, 'So Miriam was shut out of the camp seven days, and the people did not journey till Miriam was brought in again.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 12016, 'And afterward the people moved from Hazeroth and camped in the Wilderness of Paran.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13002, '&ldquo;Send men to spy out the land of Canaan, which I am giving to the children of Israel; from each tribe of their fathers you shall send a man, every one a leader among them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13003, 'So Moses sent them from the Wilderness of Paran according to the command of the LORD, all of them men who were heads of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13004, 'Now these were their names: from the tribe of Reuben, Shammua the son of Zaccur;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13005, 'from the tribe of Simeon, Shaphat the son of Hori;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13006, 'from the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13007, 'from the tribe of Issachar, Igal the son of Joseph;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13008, 'from the tribe of Ephraim, Hoshea the son of Nun;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13009, 'from the tribe of Benjamin, Palti the son of Raphu;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13010, 'from the tribe of Zebulun, Gaddiel the son of Sodi;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13011, 'from the tribe of Joseph, that is, from the tribe of Manasseh, Gaddi the son of Susi;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13012, 'from the tribe of Dan, Ammiel the son of Gemalli;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13013, 'from the tribe of Asher, Sethur the son of Michael;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13014, 'from the tribe of Naphtali, Nahbi the son of Vophsi;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13015, 'from the tribe of Gad, Geuel the son of Machi.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13016, 'These are the names of the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land. And Moses called Hoshea the son of Nun, Joshua.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13017, 'Then Moses sent them to spy out the land of Canaan, and said to them, &ldquo;Go up this way into the South, and go up to the mountains,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13018, 'and see what the land is like: whether the people who dwell in it are strong or weak, few or many;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13019, 'whether the land they dwell in is good or bad; whether the cities they inhabit are like camps or strongholds;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13020, 'whether the land is rich or poor; and whether there are forests there or not. Be of good courage. And bring some of the fruit of the land.&rdquo; Now the time was the season of the first ripe grapes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13021, 'So they went up and spied out the land from the Wilderness of Zin as far as Rehob, near the entrance of Hamath.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13022, 'And they went up through the South and came to Hebron; Ahiman, Sheshai, and Talmai, the descendants of Anak, were there. (Now Hebron was built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.)');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13023, 'Then they came to the Valley of Eshcol, and there cut down a branch with one cluster of grapes; they carried it between two of them on a pole. They also brought some of the pomegranates and figs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13024, 'The place was called the Valley of Eshcol, because of the cluster which the men of Israel cut down there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13025, 'And they returned from spying out the land after forty days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13026, 'Now they departed and came back to Moses and Aaron and all the congregation of the children of Israel in the Wilderness of Paran, at Kadesh; they brought back word to them and to all the congregation, and showed them the fruit of the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13027, 'Then they told him, and said: &ldquo;We went to the land where you sent us. It truly flows with milk and honey, and this is its fruit.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13028, 'Nevertheless the people who dwell in the land are strong; the cities are fortified and very large; moreover we saw the descendants of Anak there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13029, 'The Amalekites dwell in the land of the South; the Hittites, the Jebusites, and the Amorites dwell in the mountains; and the Canaanites dwell by the sea and along the banks of the Jordan.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13030, 'Then Caleb quieted the people before Moses, and said, &ldquo;Let us go up at once and take possession, for we are well able to overcome it.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13031, 'But the men who had gone up with him said, &ldquo;We are not able to go up against the people, for they are stronger than we.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13032, 'And they gave the children of Israel a bad report of the land which they had spied out, saying, &ldquo;The land through which we have gone as spies is a land that devours its inhabitants, and all the people whom we saw in it are men of great stature.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 13033, 'There we saw the giants (the descendants of Anak came from the giants); and we were like grasshoppers in our own sight, and so we were in their sight.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14001, 'So all the congregation lifted up their voices and cried, and the people wept that night.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14002, 'And all the children of Israel complained against Moses and Aaron, and the whole congregation said to them, &ldquo;If only we had died in the land of Egypt! Or if only we had died in this wilderness!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14003, 'Why has the LORD brought us to this land to fall by the sword, that our wives and children should become victims? Would it not be better for us to return to Egypt?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14004, 'So they said to one another, &ldquo;Let us select a leader and return to Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14005, 'Then Moses and Aaron fell on their faces before all the assembly of the congregation of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14006, 'But Joshua the son of Nun and Caleb the son of Jephunneh, who were among those who had spied out the land, tore their clothes;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14007, 'and they spoke to all the congregation of the children of Israel, saying: &ldquo;The land we passed through to spy out is an exceedingly good land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14008, 'If the LORD delights in us, then He will bring us into this land and give it to us, &lsquo;a land which flows with milk and honey.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14009, 'Only do not rebel against the LORD, nor fear the people of the land, for they are our bread; their protection has departed from them, and the LORD is with us. Do not fear them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14010, 'And all the congregation said to stone them with stones. Now the glory of the LORD appeared in the tabernacle of meeting before all the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14011, 'Then the LORD said to Moses: &ldquo;How long will these people reject Me? And how long will they not believe Me, with all the signs which I have performed among them?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14012, 'I will strike them with the pestilence and disinherit them, and I will make of you a nation greater and mightier than they.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14013, 'And Moses said to the LORD: &ldquo;Then the Egyptians will hear it, for by Your might You brought these people up from among them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14014, 'and they will tell it to the inhabitants of this land. They have heard that You, LORD, are among these people; that You, LORD, are seen face to face and Your cloud stands above them, and You go before them in a pillar of cloud by day and in a pillar of fire by night.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14015, 'Now if You kill these people as one man, then the nations which have heard of Your fame will speak, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14016, '&lsquo;Because the LORD was not able to bring this people to the land which He swore to give them, therefore He killed them in the wilderness.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14017, 'And now, I pray, let the power of my Lord be great, just as You have spoken, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14018, '&lsquo;The LORD is longsuffering and abundant in mercy, forgiving iniquity and transgression; but He by no means clears the guilty, visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children to the third and fourth generation.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14019, 'Pardon the iniquity of this people, I pray, according to the greatness of Your mercy, just as You have forgiven this people, from Egypt even until now.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14020, 'Then the LORD said: &ldquo;I have pardoned, according to your word;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14021, 'but truly, as I live, all the earth shall be filled with the glory of the LORD &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14022, 'because all these men who have seen My glory and the signs which I did in Egypt and in the wilderness, and have put Me to the test now these ten times, and have not heeded My voice,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14023, 'they certainly shall not see the land of which I swore to their fathers, nor shall any of those who rejected Me see it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14024, 'But My servant Caleb, because he has a different spirit in him and has followed Me fully, I will bring into the land where he went, and his descendants shall inherit it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14025, 'Now the Amalekites and the Canaanites dwell in the valley; tomorrow turn and move out into the wilderness by the Way of the Red Sea.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14026, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14027, '&ldquo;How long shall I bear with this evil congregation who complain against Me? I have heard the complaints which the children of Israel make against Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14028, 'Say to them, &lsquo;As I live,&rsquo; says the LORD, &lsquo;just as you have spoken in My hearing, so I will do to you:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14029, 'The carcasses of you who have complained against Me shall fall in this wilderness, all of you who were numbered, according to your entire number, from twenty years old and above.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14030, 'Except for Caleb the son of Jephunneh and Joshua the son of Nun, you shall by no means enter the land which I swore I would make you dwell in.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14031, 'But your little ones, whom you said would be victims, I will bring in, and they shall know the land which you have despised.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14032, 'But as for you, your carcasses shall fall in this wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14033, 'And your sons shall be shepherds in the wilderness forty years, and bear the brunt of your infidelity, until your carcasses are consumed in the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14034, 'According to the number of the days in which you spied out the land, forty days, for each day you shall bear your guilt one year, namely forty years, and you shall know My rejection.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14035, 'I the LORD have spoken this. I will surely do so to all this evil congregation who are gathered together against Me. In this wilderness they shall be consumed, and there they shall die.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14036, 'Now the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land, who returned and made all the congregation complain against him by bringing a bad report of the land,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14037, 'those very men who brought the evil report about the land, died by the plague before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14038, 'But Joshua the son of Nun and Caleb the son of Jephunneh remained alive, of the men who went to spy out the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14039, 'Then Moses told these words to all the children of Israel, and the people mourned greatly.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14040, 'And they rose early in the morning and went up to the top of the mountain, saying, &ldquo;Here we are, and we will go up to the place which the LORD has promised, for we have sinned!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14041, 'And Moses said, &ldquo;Now why do you transgress the command of the LORD? For this will not succeed.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14042, 'Do not go up, lest you be defeated by your enemies, for the LORD is not among you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14043, 'For the Amalekites and the Canaanites are there before you, and you shall fall by the sword; because you have turned away from the LORD, the LORD will not be with you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14044, 'But they presumed to go up to the mountaintop. Nevertheless, neither the ark of the covenant of the LORD nor Moses departed from the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 14045, 'Then the Amalekites and the Canaanites who dwelt in that mountain came down and attacked them, and drove them back as far as Hormah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When you have come into the land you are to inhabit, which I am giving to you,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15003, 'and you make an offering by fire to the LORD, a burnt offering or a sacrifice, to fulfill a vow or as a freewill offering or in your appointed feasts, to make a sweet aroma to the LORD, from the herd or the flock,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15004, 'then he who presents his offering to the LORD shall bring a grain offering of one-tenth of an ephah of fine flour mixed with one-fourth of a hin of oil;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15005, 'and one-fourth of a hin of wine as a drink offering you shall prepare with the burnt offering or the sacrifice, for each lamb.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15006, 'Or for a ram you shall prepare as a grain offering two-tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with one-third of a hin of oil;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15007, 'and as a drink offering you shall offer one-third of a hin of wine as a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15008, 'And when you prepare a young bull as a burnt offering, or as a sacrifice to fulfill a vow, or as a peace offering to the LORD,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15009, 'then shall be offered with the young bull a grain offering of three-tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with half a hin of oil;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15010, 'and you shall bring as the drink offering half a hin of wine as an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15011, '&lsquo;Thus it shall be done for each young bull, for each ram, or for each lamb or young goat.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15012, 'According to the number that you prepare, so you shall do with everyone according to their number.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15013, 'All who are native-born shall do these things in this manner, in presenting an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15014, 'And if a stranger dwells with you, or whoever is among you throughout your generations, and would present an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD, just as you do, so shall he do.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15015, 'One ordinance shall be for you of the assembly and for the stranger who dwells with you, an ordinance forever throughout your generations; as you are, so shall the stranger be before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15016, 'One law and one custom shall be for you and for the stranger who dwells with you.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15017, 'Again the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15018, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When you come into the land to which I bring you,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15019, 'then it will be, when you eat of the bread of the land, that you shall offer up a heave offering to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15020, 'You shall offer up a cake of the first of your ground meal as a heave offering; as a heave offering of the threshing floor, so shall you offer it up.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15021, 'Of the first of your ground meal you shall give to the LORD a heave offering throughout your generations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15022, '&lsquo;If you sin unintentionally, and do not observe all these commandments which the LORD has spoken to Moses &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15023, 'all that the LORD has commanded you by the hand of Moses, from the day the LORD gave commandment and onward throughout your generations &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15024, 'then it will be, if it is unintentionally committed, without the knowledge of the congregation, that the whole congregation shall offer one young bull as a burnt offering, as a sweet aroma to the LORD, with its grain offering and its drink offering, according to the ordinance, and one kid of the goats as a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15025, 'So the priest shall make atonement for the whole congregation of the children of Israel, and it shall be forgiven them, for it was unintentional; they shall bring their offering, an offering made by fire to the LORD, and their sin offering before the LORD, for their unintended sin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15026, 'It shall be forgiven the whole congregation of the children of Israel and the stranger who dwells among them, because all the people did it unintentionally.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15027, '&lsquo;And if a person sins unintentionally, then he shall bring a female goat in its first year as a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15028, 'So the priest shall make atonement for the person who sins unintentionally, when he sins unintentionally before the LORD, to make atonement for him; and it shall be forgiven him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15029, 'You shall have one law for him who sins unintentionally, for him who is native-born among the children of Israel and for the stranger who dwells among them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15030, '&lsquo;But the person who does anything presumptuously, whether he is native-born or a stranger, that one brings reproach on the LORD, and he shall be cut off from among his people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15031, 'Because he has despised the word of the LORD, and has broken His commandment, that person shall be completely cut off; his guilt shall be upon him.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15032, 'Now while the children of Israel were in the wilderness, they found a man gathering sticks on the Sabbath day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15033, 'And those who found him gathering sticks brought him to Moses and Aaron, and to all the congregation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15034, 'They put him under guard, because it had not been explained what should be done to him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15035, 'Then the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;The man must surely be put to death; all the congregation shall stone him with stones outside the camp.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15036, 'So, as the LORD commanded Moses, all the congregation brought him outside the camp and stoned him with stones, and he died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15037, 'Again the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15038, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel: Tell them to make tassels on the corners of their garments throughout their generations, and to put a blue thread in the tassels of the corners.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15039, 'And you shall have the tassel, that you may look upon it and remember all the commandments of the LORD and do them, and that you may not follow the harlotry to which your own heart and your own eyes are inclined,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15040, 'and that you may remember and do all My commandments, and be holy for your God.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 15041, 'I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: I am the LORD your God.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16001, 'Now Korah the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, with Dathan and Abiram the sons of Eliab, and On the son of Peleth, sons of Reuben, took men;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16002, 'and they rose up before Moses with some of the children of Israel, two hundred and fifty leaders of the congregation, representatives of the congregation, men of renown.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16003, 'They gathered together against Moses and Aaron, and said to them, &ldquo;You take too much upon yourselves, for all the congregation is holy, every one of them, and the LORD is among them. Why then do you exalt yourselves above the assembly of the LORD?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16004, 'So when Moses heard it, he fell on his face;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16005, 'and he spoke to Korah and all his company, saying, &ldquo;Tomorrow morning the LORD will show who is His and who is holy, and will cause him to come near to Him. That one whom He chooses He will cause to come near to Him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16006, 'Do this: Take censers, Korah and all your company;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16007, 'put fire in them and put incense in them before the LORD tomorrow, and it shall be that the man whom the LORD chooses is the holy one. You take too much upon yourselves, you sons of Levi!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16008, 'Then Moses said to Korah, &ldquo;Hear now, you sons of Levi:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16009, 'Is it a small thing to you that the God of Israel has separated you from the congregation of Israel, to bring you near to Himself, to do the work of the tabernacle of the LORD, and to stand before the congregation to serve them;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16010, 'and that He has brought you near to Himself, you and all your brethren, the sons of Levi, with you? And are you seeking the priesthood also?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16011, 'Therefore you and all your company are gathered together against the LORD. And what is Aaron that you complain against him?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16012, 'And Moses sent to call Dathan and Abiram the sons of Eliab, but they said, &ldquo;We will not come up!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16013, 'Is it a small thing that you have brought us up out of a land flowing with milk and honey, to kill us in the wilderness, that you should keep acting like a prince over us?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16014, 'Moreover you have not brought us into a land flowing with milk and honey, nor given us inheritance of fields and vineyards. Will you put out the eyes of these men? We will not come up!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16015, 'Then Moses was very angry, and said to the LORD, &ldquo;Do not respect their offering. I have not taken one donkey from them, nor have I hurt one of them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16016, 'And Moses said to Korah, &ldquo;Tomorrow, you and all your company be present before the LORD &ndash; you and they, as well as Aaron.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16017, 'Let each take his censer and put incense in it, and each of you bring his censer before the LORD, two hundred and fifty censers; both you and Aaron, each with his censer.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16018, 'So every man took his censer, put fire in it, laid incense on it, and stood at the door of the tabernacle of meeting with Moses and Aaron.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16019, 'And Korah gathered all the congregation against them at the door of the tabernacle of meeting. Then the glory of the LORD appeared to all the congregation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16020, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16021, '&ldquo;Separate yourselves from among this congregation, that I may consume them in a moment.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16022, 'Then they fell on their faces, and said, &ldquo;O God, the God of the spirits of all flesh, shall one man sin, and You be angry with all the congregation?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16023, 'So the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16024, '&ldquo;Speak to the congregation, saying, &lsquo;Get away from the tents of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16025, 'Then Moses rose and went to Dathan and Abiram, and the elders of Israel followed him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16026, 'And he spoke to the congregation, saying, &ldquo;Depart now from the tents of these wicked men! Touch nothing of theirs, lest you be consumed in all their sins.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16027, 'So they got away from around the tents of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram; and Dathan and Abiram came out and stood at the door of their tents, with their wives, their sons, and their little children.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16028, 'And Moses said: &ldquo;By this you shall know that the LORD has sent me to do all these works, for I have not done them of my own will.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16029, 'If these men die naturally like all men, or if they are visited by the common fate of all men, then the LORD has not sent me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16030, 'But if the LORD creates a new thing, and the earth opens its mouth and swallows them up with all that belongs to them, and they go down alive into the pit, then you will understand that these men have rejected the LORD.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16031, 'Now it came to pass, as he finished speaking all these words, that the ground split apart under them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16032, 'and the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up, with their households and all the men with Korah, with all their goods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16033, 'So they and all those with them went down alive into the pit; the earth closed over them, and they perished from among the assembly.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16034, 'Then all Israel who were around them fled at their cry, for they said, &ldquo;Lest the earth swallow us up also!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16035, 'And a fire came out from the LORD and consumed the two hundred and fifty men who were offering incense.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16036, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16037, '&ldquo;Tell Eleazar, the son of Aaron the priest, to pick up the censers out of the blaze, for they are holy, and scatter the fire some distance away.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16038, 'The censers of these men who sinned against their own souls, let them be made into hammered plates as a covering for the altar. Because they presented them before the LORD, therefore they are holy; and they shall be a sign to the children of Israel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16039, 'So Eleazar the priest took the bronze censers, which those who were burned up had presented, and they were hammered out as a covering on the altar,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16040, 'to be a memorial to the children of Israel that no outsider, who is not a descendant of Aaron, should come near to offer incense before the LORD, that he might not become like Korah and his companions, just as the LORD had said to him through Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16041, 'On the next day all the congregation of the children of Israel complained against Moses and Aaron, saying, &ldquo;You have killed the people of the LORD.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16042, 'Now it happened, when the congregation had gathered against Moses and Aaron, that they turned toward the tabernacle of meeting; and suddenly the cloud covered it, and the glory of the LORD appeared.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16043, 'Then Moses and Aaron came before the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16044, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16045, '&ldquo;Get away from among this congregation, that I may consume them in a moment.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16046, 'And they fell on their faces.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16047, 'So Moses said to Aaron, &ldquo;Take a censer and put fire in it from the altar, put incense on it, and take it quickly to the congregation and make atonement for them; for wrath has gone out from the LORD. The plague has begun.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16048, 'Then Aaron took it as Moses commanded, and ran into the midst of the assembly; and already the plague had begun among the people. So he put in the incense and made atonement for the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16049, 'And he stood between the dead and the living; so the plague was stopped.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 16050, 'Now those who died in the plague were fourteen thousand seven hundred, besides those who died in the Korah incident.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17002, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and get from them a rod from each father&rsquo;s house, all their leaders according to their fathers&rsquo; houses &ndash; twelve rods. Write each man&rsquo;s name on his rod.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17003, 'And you shall write Aaron&rsquo;s name on the rod of Levi. For there shall be one rod for the head of each father&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17004, 'Then you shall place them in the tabernacle of meeting before the Testimony, where I meet with you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17005, 'And it shall be that the rod of the man whom I choose will blossom; thus I will rid Myself of the complaints of the children of Israel, which they make against you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17006, 'So Moses spoke to the children of Israel, and each of their leaders gave him a rod apiece, for each leader according to their fathers&rsquo; houses, twelve rods; and the rod of Aaron was among their rods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17007, 'And Moses placed the rods before the LORD in the tabernacle of witness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17008, 'Now it came to pass on the next day that Moses went into the tabernacle of witness, and behold, the rod of Aaron, of the house of Levi, had sprouted and put forth buds, had produced blossoms and yielded ripe almonds.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17009, 'Then Moses brought out all the rods from before the LORD to all the children of Israel; and they looked, and each man took his rod.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17010, 'And the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;Bring Aaron&rsquo;s rod back before the Testimony, to be kept as a sign against the rebels, that you may put their complaints away from Me, lest they die.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17011, 'Thus did Moses; just as the LORD had commanded him, so he did.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 17012, 'So the children of Israel spoke to Moses, saying, &ldquo;Surely we die, we perish, we all perish!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18001, 'Then the LORD said to Aaron: &ldquo;You and your sons and your father&rsquo;s house with you shall bear the iniquity related to the sanctuary, and you and your sons with you shall bear the iniquity associated with your priesthood.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18002, 'Also bring with you your brethren of the tribe of Levi, the tribe of your father, that they may be joined with you and serve you while you and your sons are with you before the tabernacle of witness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18003, 'They shall attend to your needs and all the needs of the tabernacle; but they shall not come near the articles of the sanctuary and the altar, lest they die &ndash; they and you also.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18004, 'They shall be joined with you and attend to the needs of the tabernacle of meeting, for all the work of the tabernacle; but an outsider shall not come near you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18005, 'And you shall attend to the duties of the sanctuary and the duties of the altar, that there may be no more wrath on the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18006, 'Behold, I Myself have taken your brethren the Levites from among the children of Israel; they are a gift to you, given by the LORD, to do the work of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18007, 'Therefore you and your sons with you shall attend to your priesthood for everything at the altar and behind the veil; and you shall serve. I give your priesthood to you as a gift for service, but the outsider who comes near shall be put to death.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18008, 'And the LORD spoke to Aaron: &ldquo;Here, I Myself have also given you charge of My heave offerings, all the holy gifts of the children of Israel; I have given them as a portion to you and your sons, as an ordinance forever.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18009, 'This shall be yours of the most holy things reserved from the fire: every offering of theirs, every grain offering and every sin offering and every trespass offering which they render to Me, shall be most holy for you and your sons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18010, 'In a most holy place you shall eat it; every male shall eat it. It shall be holy to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18011, '&ldquo;This also is yours: the heave offering of their gift, with all the wave offerings of the children of Israel; I have given them to you, and your sons and daughters with you, as an ordinance forever. Everyone who is clean in your house may eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18012, '&ldquo;All the best of the oil, all the best of the new wine and the grain, their firstfruits which they offer to the LORD, I have given them to you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18013, 'Whatever first ripe fruit is in their land, which they bring to the LORD, shall be yours. Everyone who is clean in your house may eat it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18014, '&ldquo;Every devoted thing in Israel shall be yours.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18015, '&ldquo;Everything that first opens the womb of all flesh, which they bring to the LORD, whether man or beast, shall be yours; nevertheless the firstborn of man you shall surely redeem, and the firstborn of unclean animals you shall redeem.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18016, 'And those redeemed of the devoted things you shall redeem when one month old, according to your valuation, for five shekels of silver, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, which is twenty gerahs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18017, 'But the firstborn of a cow, the firstborn of a sheep, or the firstborn of a goat you shall not redeem; they are holy. You shall sprinkle their blood on the altar, and burn their fat as an offering made by fire for a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18018, 'And their flesh shall be yours, just as the wave breast and the right thigh are yours.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18019, '&ldquo;All the heave offerings of the holy things, which the children of Israel offer to the LORD, I have given to you and your sons and daughters with you as an ordinance forever; it is a covenant of salt forever before the LORD with you and your descendants with you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18020, 'Then the LORD said to Aaron: &ldquo;You shall have no inheritance in their land, nor shall you have any portion among them; I am your portion and your inheritance among the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18021, '&ldquo;Behold, I have given the children of Levi all the tithes in Israel as an inheritance in return for the work which they perform, the work of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18022, 'Hereafter the children of Israel shall not come near the tabernacle of meeting, lest they bear sin and die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18023, 'But the Levites shall perform the work of the tabernacle of meeting, and they shall bear their iniquity; it shall be a statute forever, throughout your generations, that among the children of Israel they shall have no inheritance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18024, 'For the tithes of the children of Israel, which they offer up as a heave offering to the LORD, I have given to the Levites as an inheritance; therefore I have said to them, &lsquo;Among the children of Israel they shall have no inheritance.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18025, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18026, '&ldquo;Speak thus to the Levites, and say to them: &lsquo;When you take from the children of Israel the tithes which I have given you from them as your inheritance, then you shall offer up a heave offering of it to the LORD, a tenth of the tithe.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18027, 'And your heave offering shall be reckoned to you as though it were the grain of the threshing floor and as the fullness of the winepress.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18028, 'Thus you shall also offer a heave offering to the LORD from all your tithes which you receive from the children of Israel, and you shall give the LORD&rsquo;s heave offering from it to Aaron the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18029, 'Of all your gifts you shall offer up every heave offering due to the LORD, from all the best of them, the consecrated part of them.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18030, 'Therefore you shall say to them: &lsquo;When you have lifted up the best of it, then the rest shall be accounted to the Levites as the produce of the threshing floor and as the produce of the winepress.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18031, 'You may eat it in any place, you and your households, for it is your reward for your work in the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 18032, 'And you shall bear no sin because of it, when you have lifted up the best of it. But you shall not profane the holy gifts of the children of Israel, lest you die.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19001, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19002, '&ldquo;This is the ordinance of the law which the LORD has commanded, saying: &lsquo;Speak to the children of Israel, that they bring you a red heifer without blemish, in which there is no defect and on which a yoke has never come.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19003, 'You shall give it to Eleazar the priest, that he may take it outside the camp, and it shall be slaughtered before him;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19004, 'and Eleazar the priest shall take some of its blood with his finger, and sprinkle some of its blood seven times directly in front of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19005, 'Then the heifer shall be burned in his sight: its hide, its flesh, its blood, and its offal shall be burned.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19006, 'And the priest shall take cedar wood and hyssop and scarlet, and cast them into the midst of the fire burning the heifer.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19007, 'Then the priest shall wash his clothes, he shall bathe in water, and afterward he shall come into the camp; the priest shall be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19008, 'And the one who burns it shall wash his clothes in water, bathe in water, and shall be unclean until evening.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19009, 'Then a man who is clean shall gather up the ashes of the heifer, and store them outside the camp in a clean place; and they shall be kept for the congregation of the children of Israel for the water of purification; it is for purifying from sin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19010, 'And the one who gathers the ashes of the heifer shall wash his clothes, and be unclean until evening. It shall be a statute forever to the children of Israel and to the stranger who dwells among them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19011, '&lsquo;He who touches the dead body of anyone shall be unclean seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19012, 'He shall purify himself with the water on the third day and on the seventh day; then he will be clean. But if he does not purify himself on the third day and on the seventh day, he will not be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19013, 'Whoever touches the body of anyone who has died, and does not purify himself, defiles the tabernacle of the LORD. That person shall be cut off from Israel. He shall be unclean, because the water of purification was not sprinkled on him; his uncleanness is still on him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19014, '&lsquo;This is the law when a man dies in a tent: All who come into the tent and all who are in the tent shall be unclean seven days;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19015, 'and every open vessel, which has no cover fastened on it, is unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19016, 'Whoever in the open field touches one who is slain by a sword or who has died, or a bone of a man, or a grave, shall be unclean seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19017, '&lsquo;And for an unclean person they shall take some of the ashes of the heifer burnt for purification from sin, and running water shall be put on them in a vessel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19018, 'A clean person shall take hyssop and dip it in the water, sprinkle it on the tent, on all the vessels, on the persons who were there, or on the one who touched a bone, the slain, the dead, or a grave.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19019, 'The clean person shall sprinkle the unclean on the third day and on the seventh day; and on the seventh day he shall purify himself, wash his clothes, and bathe in water; and at evening he shall be clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19020, '&lsquo;But the man who is unclean and does not purify himself, that person shall be cut off from among the assembly, because he has defiled the sanctuary of the LORD. The water of purification has not been sprinkled on him; he is unclean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 19021, 'It shall be a perpetual statute for them. He who sprinkles the water of purification shall wash his clothes; and he who touches the water of purification shall be unclean until evening. 22 Whatever the unclean person touches shall be unclean; and the person who touches it shall be unclean until evening.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20001, 'Then the children of Israel, the whole congregation, came into the Wilderness of Zin in the first month, and the people stayed in Kadesh; and Miriam died there and was buried there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20002, 'Now there was no water for the congregation; so they gathered together against Moses and Aaron.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20003, 'And the people contended with Moses and spoke, saying: &ldquo;If only we had died when our brethren died before the LORD!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20004, 'Why have you brought up the assembly of the LORD into this wilderness, that we and our animals should die here?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20005, 'And why have you made us come up out of Egypt, to bring us to this evil place? It is not a place of grain or figs or vines or pomegranates; nor is there any water to drink.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20006, 'So Moses and Aaron went from the presence of the assembly to the door of the tabernacle of meeting, and they fell on their faces. And the glory of the LORD appeared to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20007, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20008, '&ldquo;Take the rod; you and your brother Aaron gather the congregation together. Speak to the rock before their eyes, and it will yield its water; thus you shall bring water for them out of the rock, and give drink to the congregation and their animals.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20009, 'So Moses took the rod from before the LORD as He commanded him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20010, 'And Moses and Aaron gathered the assembly together before the rock; and he said to them, &ldquo;Hear now, you rebels! Must we bring water for you out of this rock?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20011, 'Then Moses lifted his hand and struck the rock twice with his rod; and water came out abundantly, and the congregation and their animals drank.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20012, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, &ldquo;Because you did not believe Me, to hallow Me in the eyes of the children of Israel, therefore you shall not bring this assembly into the land which I have given them.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20013, 'This was the water of Meribah, because the children of Israel contended with the LORD, and He was hallowed among them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20014, 'Now Moses sent messengers from Kadesh to the king of Edom. &ldquo;Thus says your brother Israel: &lsquo;You know all the hardship that has befallen us,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20015, 'how our fathers went down to Egypt, and we dwelt in Egypt a long time, and the Egyptians afflicted us and our fathers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20016, 'When we cried out to the LORD, He heard our voice and sent the Angel and brought us up out of Egypt; now here we are in Kadesh, a city on the edge of your border.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20017, 'Please let us pass through your country. We will not pass through fields or vineyards, nor will we drink water from wells; we will go along the King&rsquo;s Highway; we will not turn aside to the right hand or to the left until we have passed through your territory.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20018, 'Then Edom said to him, &ldquo;You shall not pass through my land, lest I come out against you with the sword.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20019, 'So the children of Israel said to him, &ldquo;We will go by the Highway, and if I or my livestock drink any of your water, then I will pay for it; let me only pass through on foot, nothing more.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20020, 'Then he said, &ldquo;You shall not pass through.&rdquo; So Edom came out against them with many men and with a strong hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20021, 'Thus Edom refused to give Israel passage through his territory; so Israel turned away from him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20022, 'Now the children of Israel, the whole congregation, journeyed from Kadesh and came to Mount Hor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20023, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron in Mount Hor by the border of the land of Edom, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20024, '&ldquo;Aaron shall be gathered to his people, for he shall not enter the land which I have given to the children of Israel, because you rebelled against My word at the water of Meribah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20025, 'Take Aaron and Eleazar his son, and bring them up to Mount Hor;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20026, 'and strip Aaron of his garments and put them on Eleazar his son; for Aaron shall be gathered to his people and die there.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20027, 'So Moses did just as the LORD commanded, and they went up to Mount Hor in the sight of all the congregation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20028, 'Moses stripped Aaron of his garments and put them on Eleazar his son; and Aaron died there on the top of the mountain. Then Moses and Eleazar came down from the mountain.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 20029, 'Now when all the congregation saw that Aaron was dead, all the house of Israel mourned for Aaron thirty days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21001, 'The king of Arad, the Canaanite, who dwelt in the South, heard that Israel was coming on the road to Atharim. Then he fought against Israel and took some of them prisoners.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21002, 'So Israel made a vow to the LORD, and said, &ldquo;If You will indeed deliver this people into my hand, then I will utterly destroy their cities.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21003, 'And the LORD listened to the voice of Israel and delivered up the Canaanites, and they utterly destroyed them and their cities. So the name of that place was called Hormah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21004, 'Then they journeyed from Mount Hor by the Way of the Red Sea, to go around the land of Edom; and the soul of the people became very discouraged on the way.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21005, 'And the people spoke against God and against Moses: &ldquo;Why have you brought us up out of Egypt to die in the wilderness? For there is no food and no water, and our soul loathes this worthless bread.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21006, 'So the LORD sent fiery serpents among the people, and they bit the people; and many of the people of Israel died.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21007, 'Therefore the people came to Moses, and said, &ldquo;We have sinned, for we have spoken against the LORD and against you; pray to the LORD that He take away the serpents from us.&rdquo; So Moses prayed for the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21008, 'Then the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;Make a fiery serpent, and set it on a pole; and it shall be that everyone who is bitten, when he looks at it, shall live.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21009, 'So Moses made a bronze serpent, and put it on a pole; and so it was, if a serpent had bitten anyone, when he looked at the bronze serpent, he lived.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21010, 'Now the children of Israel moved on and camped in Oboth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21011, 'And they journeyed from Oboth and camped at Ije Abarim, in the wilderness which is east of Moab, toward the sunrise.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21012, 'From there they moved and camped in the Valley of Zered.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21013, 'From there they moved and camped on the other side of the Arnon, which is in the wilderness that extends from the border of the Amorites; for the Arnon is the border of Moab, between Moab and the Amorites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21014, 'Therefore it is said in the Book of the Wars of the LORD: &ldquo; Waheb in Suphah, The brooks of the Arnon,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21015, 'And the slope of the brooks That reaches to the dwelling of Ar, And lies on the border of Moab.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21016, 'From there they went to Beer, which is the well where the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;Gather the people together, and I will give them water.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21017, 'Then Israel sang this song: &ldquo; Spring up, O well! All of you sing to it &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21018, 'The well the leaders sank, Dug by the nation&rsquo;s nobles, By the lawgiver, with their staves.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21019, 'And from the wilderness they went to Mattanah,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21020, 'from Mattanah to Nahaliel, from Nahaliel to Bamoth,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21021, 'and from Bamoth, in the valley that is in the country of Moab, to the top of Pisgah which looks down on the wasteland.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21022, 'Then Israel sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21023, '&ldquo;Let me pass through your land. We will not turn aside into fields or vineyards; we will not drink water from wells. We will go by the King&rsquo;s Highway until we have passed through your territory.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21024, 'But Sihon would not allow Israel to pass through his territory. So Sihon gathered all his people together and went out against Israel in the wilderness, and he came to Jahaz and fought against Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21025, 'Then Israel defeated him with the edge of the sword, and took possession of his land from the Arnon to the Jabbok, as far as the people of Ammon; for the border of the people of Ammon was fortified.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21026, 'So Israel took all these cities, and Israel dwelt in all the cities of the Amorites, in Heshbon and in all its villages.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21027, 'For Heshbon was the city of Sihon king of the Amorites, who had fought against the former king of Moab, and had taken all his land from his hand as far as the Arnon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21028, 'Therefore those who speak in proverbs say: &ldquo;Come to Heshbon, let it be built; Let the city of Sihon be repaired.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21029, '&ldquo;For fire went out from Heshbon, A flame from the city of Sihon; It consumed Ar of Moab, The lords of the heights of the Arnon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21030, 'Woe to you, Moab! You have perished, O people of Chemosh! He has given his sons as fugitives, And his daughters into captivity, To Sihon king of the Amorites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21031, '&ldquo;But we have shot at them; Heshbon has perished as far as Dibon. Then we laid waste as far as Nophah, Which reaches to Medeba.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21032, 'Thus Israel dwelt in the land of the Amorites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21033, 'Then Moses sent to spy out Jazer; and they took its villages and drove out the Amorites who were there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21034, 'And they turned and went up by the way to Bashan. So Og king of Bashan went out against them, he and all his people, to battle at Edrei.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 21035, 'Then the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;Do not fear him, for I have delivered him into your hand, with all his people and his land; and you shall do to him as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who dwelt at Heshbon.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22001, 'Then the children of Israel moved, and camped in the plains of Moab on the side of the Jordan across from Jericho.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22002, 'Now Balak the son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22003, 'And Moab was exceedingly afraid of the people because they were many, and Moab was sick with dread because of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22004, 'So Moab said to the elders of Midian, &ldquo;Now this company will lick up everything around us, as an ox licks up the grass of the field.&rdquo; And Balak the son of Zippor was king of the Moabites at that time.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22005, 'Then he sent messengers to Balaam the son of Beor at Pethor, which is near the River in the land of the sons of his people, to call him, saying: &ldquo;Look, a people has come from Egypt. See, they cover the face of the earth, and are settling next to me!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22006, 'Therefore please come at once, curse this people for me, for they are too mighty for me. Perhaps I shall be able to defeat them and drive them out of the land, for I know that he whom you bless is blessed, and he whom you curse is cursed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22007, 'So the elders of Moab and the elders of Midian departed with the diviner&rsquo;s fee in their hand, and they came to Balaam and spoke to him the words of Balak.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22008, 'And he said to them, &ldquo;Lodge here tonight, and I will bring back word to you, as the LORD speaks to me.&rdquo; So the princes of Moab stayed with Balaam.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22009, 'Then God came to Balaam and said, &ldquo;Who are these men with you?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22010, 'So Balaam said to God, &ldquo;Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, has sent to me, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22011, '&lsquo;Look, a people has come out of Egypt, and they cover the face of the earth. Come now, curse them for me; perhaps I shall be able to overpower them and drive them out.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22012, 'And God said to Balaam, &ldquo;You shall not go with them; you shall not curse the people, for they are blessed.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22013, 'So Balaam rose in the morning and said to the princes of Balak, &ldquo;Go back to your land, for the LORD has refused to give me permission to go with you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22014, 'And the princes of Moab rose and went to Balak, and said, &ldquo;Balaam refuses to come with us.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22015, 'Then Balak again sent princes, more numerous and more honorable than they.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22016, 'And they came to Balaam and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says Balak the son of Zippor: &lsquo;Please let nothing hinder you from coming to me;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22017, 'for I will certainly honor you greatly, and I will do whatever you say to me. Therefore please come, curse this people for me.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22018, 'Then Balaam answered and said to the servants of Balak, &ldquo;Though Balak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, I could not go beyond the word of the LORD my God, to do less or more.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22019, 'Now therefore, please, you also stay here tonight, that I may know what more the LORD will say to me.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22020, 'And God came to Balaam at night and said to him, &ldquo;If the men come to call you, rise and go with them; but only the word which I speak to you &ndash; that you shall do.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22021, 'So Balaam rose in the morning, saddled his donkey, and went with the princes of Moab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22022, 'Then God&rsquo;s anger was aroused because he went, and the Angel of the LORD took His stand in the way as an adversary against him. And he was riding on his donkey, and his two servants were with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22023, 'Now the donkey saw the Angel of the LORD standing in the way with His drawn sword in His hand, and the donkey turned aside out of the way and went into the field. So Balaam struck the donkey to turn her back onto the road.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22024, 'Then the Angel of the LORD stood in a narrow path between the vineyards, with a wall on this side and a wall on that side.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22025, 'And when the donkey saw the Angel of the LORD, she pushed herself against the wall and crushed Balaam&rsquo;s foot against the wall; so he struck her again.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22026, 'Then the Angel of the LORD went further, and stood in a narrow place where there was no way to turn either to the right hand or to the left.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22027, 'And when the donkey saw the Angel of the LORD, she lay down under Balaam; so Balaam&rsquo;s anger was aroused, and he struck the donkey with his staff.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22028, 'Then the LORD opened the mouth of the donkey, and she said to Balaam, &ldquo;What have I done to you, that you have struck me these three times?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22029, 'And Balaam said to the donkey, &ldquo;Because you have abused me. I wish there were a sword in my hand, for now I would kill you!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22030, 'So the donkey said to Balaam, &ldquo;Am I not your donkey on which you have ridden, ever since I became yours, to this day? Was I ever disposed to do this to you?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;No.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22031, 'Then the LORD opened Balaam&rsquo;s eyes, and he saw the Angel of the LORD standing in the way with His drawn sword in His hand; and he bowed his head and fell flat on his face.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22032, 'And the Angel of the LORD said to him, &ldquo;Why have you struck your donkey these three times? Behold, I have come out to stand against you, because your way is perverse before Me.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22033, 'The donkey saw Me and turned aside from Me these three times. If she had not turned aside from Me, surely I would also have killed you by now, and let her live.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22034, 'And Balaam said to the Angel of the LORD, &ldquo;I have sinned, for I did not know You stood in the way against me. Now therefore, if it displeases You, I will turn back.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22035, 'Then the Angel of the LORD said to Balaam, &ldquo;Go with the men, but only the word that I speak to you, that you shall speak.&rdquo; So Balaam went with the princes of Balak.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22036, 'Now when Balak heard that Balaam was coming, he went out to meet him at the city of Moab, which is on the border at the Arnon, the boundary of the territory.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22037, 'Then Balak said to Balaam, &ldquo;Did I not earnestly send to you, calling for you? Why did you not come to me? Am I not able to honor you?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22038, 'And Balaam said to Balak, &ldquo;Look, I have come to you! Now, have I any power at all to say anything? The word that God puts in my mouth, that I must speak.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22039, 'So Balaam went with Balak, and they came to Kirjath Huzoth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22040, 'Then Balak offered oxen and sheep, and he sent some to Balaam and to the princes who were with him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 22041, 'So it was, the next day, that Balak took Balaam and brought him up to the high places of Baal, that from there he might observe the extent of the people.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23001, 'Then Balaam said to Balak, &ldquo;Build seven altars for me here, and prepare for me here seven bulls and seven rams.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23002, 'And Balak did just as Balaam had spoken, and Balak and Balaam offered a bull and a ram on each altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23003, 'Then Balaam said to Balak, &ldquo;Stand by your burnt offering, and I will go; perhaps the LORD will come to meet me, and whatever He shows me I will tell you.&rdquo; So he went to a desolate height.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23004, 'And God met Balaam, and he said to Him, &ldquo;I have prepared the seven altars, and I have offered on each altar a bull and a ram.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23005, 'Then the LORD put a word in Balaam&rsquo;s mouth, and said, &ldquo;Return to Balak, and thus you shall speak.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23006, 'So he returned to him, and there he was, standing by his burnt offering, he and all the princes of Moab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23007, 'And he took up his oracle and said: &ldquo;Balak the king of Moab has brought me from Aram, From the mountains of the east. &lsquo; Come, curse Jacob for me, And come, denounce Israel!&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23008, '&ldquo;How shall I curse whom God has not cursed? And how shall I denounce whom the LORD has not denounced?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23009, 'For from the top of the rocks I see him, And from the hills I behold him; There! A people dwelling alone, Not reckoning itself among the nations.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23010, '&ldquo;Who can count the dust of Jacob, Or number one-fourth of Israel? Let me die the death of the righteous, And let my end be like his!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23011, 'Then Balak said to Balaam, &ldquo;What have you done to me? I took you to curse my enemies, and look, you have blessed them bountifully!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23012, 'So he answered and said, &ldquo;Must I not take heed to speak what the LORD has put in my mouth?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23013, 'Then Balak said to him, &ldquo;Please come with me to another place from which you may see them; you shall see only the outer part of them, and shall not see them all; curse them for me from there.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23014, 'So he brought him to the field of Zophim, to the top of Pisgah, and built seven altars, and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23015, 'And he said to Balak, &ldquo;Stand here by your burnt offering while I meet the LORD over there.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23016, 'Then the LORD met Balaam, and put a word in his mouth, and said, &ldquo;Go back to Balak, and thus you shall speak.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23017, 'So he came to him, and there he was, standing by his burnt offering, and the princes of Moab were with him. And Balak said to him, &ldquo;What has the LORD spoken?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23018, 'Then he took up his oracle and said: &ldquo;Rise up, Balak, and hear! Listen to me, son of Zippor!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23019, '&ldquo;God is not a man, that He should lie, Nor a son of man, that He should repent. Has He said, and will He not do? Or has He spoken, and will He not make it good?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23020, 'Behold, I have received a command to bless; He has blessed, and I cannot reverse it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23021, '&ldquo;He has not observed iniquity in Jacob, Nor has He seen wickedness in Israel. The LORD his God is with him, And the shout of a King is among them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23022, 'God brings them out of Egypt; He has strength like a wild ox.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23023, '&ldquo;For there is no sorcery against Jacob, Nor any divination against Israel. It now must be said of Jacob And of Israel, &lsquo;Oh, what God has done!&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23024, 'Look, a people rises like a lioness, And lifts itself up like a lion; It shall not lie down until it devours the prey, And drinks the blood of the slain.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23025, 'Then Balak said to Balaam, &ldquo;Neither curse them at all, nor bless them at all!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23026, 'So Balaam answered and said to Balak, &ldquo;Did I not tell you, saying, &lsquo;All that the LORD speaks, that I must do&rsquo;?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23027, 'Then Balak said to Balaam, &ldquo;Please come, I will take you to another place; perhaps it will please God that you may curse them for me from there.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23028, 'So Balak took Balaam to the top of Peor, that overlooks the wasteland.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23029, 'Then Balaam said to Balak, &ldquo;Build for me here seven altars, and prepare for me here seven bulls and seven rams.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 23030, 'And Balak did as Balaam had said, and offered a bull and a ram on every altar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24001, 'Now when Balaam saw that it pleased the LORD to bless Israel, he did not go as at other times, to seek to use sorcery, but he set his face toward the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24002, 'And Balaam raised his eyes, and saw Israel encamped according to their tribes; and the Spirit of God came upon him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24003, 'Then he took up his oracle and said: &ldquo;The utterance of Balaam the son of Beor, The utterance of the man whose eyes are opened,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24004, 'The utterance of him who hears the words of God, Who sees the vision of the Almighty, Who falls down, with eyes wide open:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24005, '&ldquo;How lovely are your tents, O Jacob! Your dwellings, O Israel!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24006, 'Like valleys that stretch out, Like gardens by the riverside, Like aloes planted by the LORD, Like cedars beside the waters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24007, 'He shall pour water from his buckets, And his seed shall be in many waters. &ldquo;His king shall be higher than Agag, And his kingdom shall be exalted.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24008, '&ldquo;God brings him out of Egypt; He has strength like a wild ox; He shall consume the nations, his enemies; He shall break their bones And pierce them with his arrows.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24009, '&lsquo;He bows down, he lies down as a lion; And as a lion, who shall rouse him?&rsquo; &ldquo; Blessed is he who blesses you, And cursed is he who curses you.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24010, 'Then Balak&rsquo;s anger was aroused against Balaam, and he struck his hands together; and Balak said to Balaam, &ldquo;I called you to curse my enemies, and look, you have bountifully blessed them these three times!');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24011, 'Now therefore, flee to your place. I said I would greatly honor you, but in fact, the LORD has kept you back from honor.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24012, 'So Balaam said to Balak, &ldquo;Did I not also speak to your messengers whom you sent to me, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24013, '&lsquo;If Balak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, I could not go beyond the word of the LORD, to do good or bad of my own will. What the LORD says, that I must speak&rsquo;?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24014, 'And now, indeed, I am going to my people. Come, I will advise you what this people will do to your people in the latter days.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24015, 'So he took up his oracle and said: &ldquo;The utterance of Balaam the son of Beor, And the utterance of the man whose eyes are opened;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24016, 'The utterance of him who hears the words of God, And has the knowledge of the Most High, Who sees the vision of the Almighty, Who falls down, with eyes wide open:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24017, '&ldquo;I see Him, but not now; I behold Him, but not near; A Star shall come out of Jacob; A Scepter shall rise out of Israel, And batter the brow of Moab, And destroy all the sons of tumult.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24018, '&ldquo;And Edom shall be a possession; Seir also, his enemies, shall be a possession, While Israel does valiantly.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24019, 'Out of Jacob One shall have dominion, And destroy the remains of the city.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24020, 'Then he looked on Amalek, and he took up his oracle and said: &ldquo; Amalek was first among the nations, But shall be last until he perishes.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24021, 'Then he looked on the Kenites, and he took up his oracle and said: &ldquo;Firm is your dwelling place, And your nest is set in the rock;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24022, 'Nevertheless Kain shall be burned. How long until Asshur carries you away captive?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24023, 'Then he took up his oracle and said: &ldquo;Alas! Who shall live when God does this?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24024, 'But ships shall come from the coasts of Cyprus, And they shall afflict Asshur and afflict Eber, And so shall Amalek, until he perishes.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 24025, 'So Balaam rose and departed and returned to his place; Balak also went his way.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25001, 'Now Israel remained in Acacia Grove, and the people began to commit harlotry with the women of Moab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25002, 'They invited the people to the sacrifices of their gods, and the people ate and bowed down to their gods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25003, 'So Israel was joined to Baal of Peor, and the anger of the LORD was aroused against Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25004, 'Then the LORD said to Moses, &ldquo;Take all the leaders of the people and hang the offenders before the LORD, out in the sun, that the fierce anger of the LORD may turn away from Israel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25005, 'So Moses said to the judges of Israel, &ldquo;Every one of you kill his men who were joined to Baal of Peor.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25006, 'And indeed, one of the children of Israel came and presented to his brethren a Midianite woman in the sight of Moses and in the sight of all the congregation of the children of Israel, who were weeping at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25007, 'Now when Phinehas the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron the priest, saw it, he rose from among the congregation and took a javelin in his hand;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25008, 'and he went after the man of Israel into the tent and thrust both of them through, the man of Israel, and the woman through her body. So the plague was stopped among the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25009, 'And those who died in the plague were twenty-four thousand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25010, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25011, '&ldquo;Phinehas the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron the priest, has turned back My wrath from the children of Israel, because he was zealous with My zeal among them, so that I did not consume the children of Israel in My zeal.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25012, 'Therefore say, &lsquo;Behold, I give to him My covenant of peace;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25013, 'and it shall be to him and his descendants after him a covenant of an everlasting priesthood, because he was zealous for his God, and made atonement for the children of Israel.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25014, 'Now the name of the Israelite who was killed, who was killed with the Midianite woman, was Zimri the son of Salu, a leader of a father&rsquo;s house among the Simeonites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25015, 'And the name of the Midianite woman who was killed was Cozbi the daughter of Zur; he was head of the people of a father&rsquo;s house in Midian.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25016, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 25017, '&ldquo;Harass the Midianites, and attack them; 18 for they harassed you with their schemes by which they seduced you in the matter of Peor and in the matter of Cozbi, the daughter of a leader of Midian, their sister, who was killed in the day of the plague because of Peor.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26001, 'And it came to pass, after the plague, that the LORD spoke to Moses and Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26002, '&ldquo;Take a census of all the congregation of the children of Israel from twenty years old and above, by their fathers&rsquo; houses, all who are able to go to war in Israel.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26003, 'So Moses and Eleazar the priest spoke with them in the plains of Moab by the Jordan, across from Jericho, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26004, '&ldquo;Take a census of the people from twenty years old and above, just as the LORD commanded Moses and the children of Israel who came out of the land of Egypt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26005, 'Reuben was the firstborn of Israel. The children of Reuben were: of Hanoch, the family of the Hanochites; of Pallu, the family of the Palluites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26006, 'of Hezron, the family of the Hezronites; of Carmi, the family of the Carmites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26007, 'These are the families of the Reubenites: those who were numbered of them were forty-three thousand seven hundred and thirty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26008, 'And the son of Pallu was Eliab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26009, 'The sons of Eliab were Nemuel, Dathan, and Abiram. These are the Dathan and Abiram, representatives of the congregation, who contended against Moses and Aaron in the company of Korah, when they contended against the LORD;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26010, 'and the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up together with Korah when that company died, when the fire devoured two hundred and fifty men; and they became a sign.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26011, 'Nevertheless the children of Korah did not die.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26012, 'The sons of Simeon according to their families were: of Nemuel, the family of the Nemuelites; of Jamin, the family of the Jaminites; of Jachin, the family of the Jachinites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26013, 'of Zerah, the family of the Zarhites; of Shaul, the family of the Shaulites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26014, 'These are the families of the Simeonites: twenty-two thousand two hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26015, 'The sons of Gad according to their families were: of Zephon, the family of the Zephonites; of Haggi, the family of the Haggites; of Shuni, the family of the Shunites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26016, 'of Ozni, the family of the Oznites; of Eri, the family of the Erites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26017, 'of Arod, the family of the Arodites; of Areli, the family of the Arelites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26018, 'These are the families of the sons of Gad according to those who were numbered of them: forty thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26019, 'The sons of Judah were Er and Onan; and Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26020, 'And the sons of Judah according to their families were: of Shelah, the family of the Shelanites; of Perez, the family of the Parzites; of Zerah, the family of the Zarhites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26021, 'And the sons of Perez were: of Hezron, the family of the Hezronites; of Hamul, the family of the Hamulites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26022, 'These are the families of Judah according to those who were numbered of them: seventy-six thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26023, 'The sons of Issachar according to their families were: of Tola, the family of the Tolaites; of Puah, the family of the Punites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26024, 'of Jashub, the family of the Jashubites; of Shimron, the family of the Shimronites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26025, 'These are the families of Issachar according to those who were numbered of them: sixty-four thousand three hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26026, 'The sons of Zebulun according to their families were: of Sered, the family of the Sardites; of Elon, the family of the Elonites; of Jahleel, the family of the Jahleelites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26027, 'These are the families of the Zebulunites according to those who were numbered of them: sixty thousand five hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26028, 'The sons of Joseph according to their families, by Manasseh and Ephraim, were:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26029, 'The sons of Manasseh: of Machir, the family of the Machirites; and Machir begot Gilead; of Gilead, the family of the Gileadites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26030, 'These are the sons of Gilead: of Jeezer, the family of the Jeezerites; of Helek, the family of the Helekites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26031, 'of Asriel, the family of the Asrielites; of Shechem, the family of the Shechemites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26032, 'of Shemida, the family of the Shemidaites; of Hepher, the family of the Hepherites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26033, 'Now Zelophehad the son of Hepher had no sons, but daughters; and the names of the daughters of Zelophehad were Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26034, 'These are the families of Manasseh; and those who were numbered of them were fifty-two thousand seven hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26035, 'These are the sons of Ephraim according to their families: of Shuthelah, the family of the Shuthalhites; of Becher, the family of the Bachrites; of Tahan, the family of the Tahanites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26036, 'And these are the sons of Shuthelah: of Eran, the family of the Eranites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26037, 'These are the families of the sons of Ephraim according to those who were numbered of them: thirty-two thousand five hundred. These are the sons of Joseph according to their families.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26038, 'The sons of Benjamin according to their families were: of Bela, the family of the Belaites; of Ashbel, the family of the Ashbelites; of Ahiram, the family of the Ahiramites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26039, 'of Shupham, the family of the Shuphamites; of Hupham, the family of the Huphamites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26040, 'And the sons of Bela were Ard and Naaman: of Ard, the family of the Ardites; of Naaman, the family of the Naamites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26041, 'These are the sons of Benjamin according to their families; and those who were numbered of them were forty-five thousand six hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26042, 'These are the sons of Dan according to their families: of Shuham, the family of the Shuhamites. These are the families of Dan according to their families.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26043, 'All the families of the Shuhamites, according to those who were numbered of them, were sixty-four thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26044, 'The sons of Asher according to their families were: of Jimna, the family of the Jimnites; of Jesui, the family of the Jesuites; of Beriah, the family of the Beriites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26045, 'Of the sons of Beriah: of Heber, the family of the Heberites; of Malchiel, the family of the Malchielites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26046, 'And the name of the daughter of Asher was Serah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26047, 'These are the families of the sons of Asher according to those who were numbered of them: fifty-three thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26048, 'The sons of Naphtali according to their families were: of Jahzeel, the family of the Jahzeelites; of Guni, the family of the Gunites;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26049, 'of Jezer, the family of the Jezerites; of Shillem, the family of the Shillemites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26050, 'These are the families of Naphtali according to their families; and those who were numbered of them were forty-five thousand four hundred.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26051, 'These are those who were numbered of the children of Israel: six hundred and one thousand seven hundred and thirty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26052, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26053, '&ldquo;To these the land shall be divided as an inheritance, according to the number of names.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26054, 'To a large tribe you shall give a larger inheritance, and to a small tribe you shall give a smaller inheritance. Each shall be given its inheritance according to those who were numbered of them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26055, 'But the land shall be divided by lot; they shall inherit according to the names of the tribes of their fathers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26056, 'According to the lot their inheritance shall be divided between the larger and the smaller.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26057, 'And these are those who were numbered of the Levites according to their families: of Gershon, the family of the Gershonites; of Kohath, the family of the Kohathites; of Merari, the family of the Merarites.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26058, 'These are the families of the Levites: the family of the Libnites, the family of the Hebronites, the family of the Mahlites, the family of the Mushites, and the family of the Korathites. And Kohath begot Amram.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26059, 'The name of Amram&rsquo;s wife was Jochebed the daughter of Levi, who was born to Levi in Egypt; and to Amram she bore Aaron and Moses and their sister Miriam.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26060, 'To Aaron were born Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26061, 'And Nadab and Abihu died when they offered profane fire before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26062, 'Now those who were numbered of them were twenty-three thousand, every male from a month old and above; for they were not numbered among the other children of Israel, because there was no inheritance given to them among the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26063, 'These are those who were numbered by Moses and Eleazar the priest, who numbered the children of Israel in the plains of Moab by the Jordan, across from Jericho.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26064, 'But among these there was not a man of those who were numbered by Moses and Aaron the priest when they numbered the children of Israel in the Wilderness of Sinai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 26065, 'For the LORD had said of them, &ldquo;They shall surely die in the wilderness.&rdquo; So there was not left a man of them, except Caleb the son of Jephunneh and Joshua the son of Nun.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27001, 'Then came the daughters of Zelophehad the son of Hepher, the son of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, from the families of Manasseh the son of Joseph; and these were the names of his daughters: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27002, 'And they stood before Moses, before Eleazar the priest, and before the leaders and all the congregation, by the doorway of the tabernacle of meeting, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27003, '&ldquo;Our father died in the wilderness; but he was not in the company of those who gathered together against the LORD, in company with Korah, but he died in his own sin; and he had no sons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27004, 'Why should the name of our father be removed from among his family because he had no son? Give us a possession among our father&rsquo;s brothers.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27005, 'So Moses brought their case before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27006, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27007, '&ldquo;The daughters of Zelophehad speak what is right; you shall surely give them a possession of inheritance among their father&rsquo;s brothers, and cause the inheritance of their father to pass to them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27008, 'And you shall speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;If a man dies and has no son, then you shall cause his inheritance to pass to his daughter.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27009, 'If he has no daughter, then you shall give his inheritance to his brothers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27010, 'If he has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to his father&rsquo;s brothers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27011, 'And if his father has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to the relative closest to him in his family, and he shall possess it.&rsquo;&rdquo; And it shall be to the children of Israel a statute of judgment, just as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27012, 'Now the LORD said to Moses: &ldquo;Go up into this Mount Abarim, and see the land which I have given to the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27013, 'And when you have seen it, you also shall be gathered to your people, as Aaron your brother was gathered.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27014, 'For in the Wilderness of Zin, during the strife of the congregation, you rebelled against My command to hallow Me at the waters before their eyes.&rdquo; (These are the waters of Meribah, at Kadesh in the Wilderness of Zin.)');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27015, 'Then Moses spoke to the LORD, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27016, '&ldquo;Let the LORD, the God of the spirits of all flesh, set a man over the congregation,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27017, 'who may go out before them and go in before them, who may lead them out and bring them in, that the congregation of the LORD may not be like sheep which have no shepherd.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27018, 'And the LORD said to Moses: &ldquo;Take Joshua the son of Nun with you, a man in whom is the Spirit, and lay your hand on him;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27019, 'set him before Eleazar the priest and before all the congregation, and inaugurate him in their sight.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27020, 'And you shall give some of your authority to him, that all the congregation of the children of Israel may be obedient.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27021, 'He shall stand before Eleazar the priest, who shall inquire before the LORD for him by the judgment of the Urim. At his word they shall go out, and at his word they shall come in, he and all the children of Israel with him &ndash; all the congregation.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27022, 'So Moses did as the LORD commanded him. He took Joshua and set him before Eleazar the priest and before all the congregation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 27023, 'And he laid his hands on him and inaugurated him, just as the LORD commanded by the hand of Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28001, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28002, '&ldquo;Command the children of Israel, and say to them, &lsquo;My offering, My food for My offerings made by fire as a sweet aroma to Me, you shall be careful to offer to Me at their appointed time.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28003, '&ldquo;And you shall say to them, &lsquo;This is the offering made by fire which you shall offer to the LORD: two male lambs in their first year without blemish, day by day, as a regular burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28004, 'The one lamb you shall offer in the morning, the other lamb you shall offer in the evening,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28005, 'and one-tenth of an ephah of fine flour as a grain offering mixed with one-fourth of a hin of pressed oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28006, 'It is a regular burnt offering which was ordained at Mount Sinai for a sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28007, 'And its drink offering shall be one-fourth of a hin for each lamb; in a holy place you shall pour out the drink to the LORD as an offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28008, 'The other lamb you shall offer in the evening; as the morning grain offering and its drink offering, you shall offer it as an offering made by fire, a sweet aroma to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28009, '&lsquo;And on the Sabbath day two lambs in their first year, without blemish, and two-tenths of an ephah of fine flour as a grain offering, mixed with oil, with its drink offering &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28010, 'this is the burnt offering for every Sabbath, besides the regular burnt offering with its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28011, '&lsquo;At the beginnings of your months you shall present a burnt offering to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, and seven lambs in their first year, without blemish;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28012, 'three-tenths of an ephah of fine flour as a grain offering, mixed with oil, for each bull; two-tenths of an ephah of fine flour as a grain offering, mixed with oil, for the one ram;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28013, 'and one-tenth of an ephah of fine flour, mixed with oil, as a grain offering for each lamb, as a burnt offering of sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28014, 'Their drink offering shall be half a hin of wine for a bull, one-third of a hin for a ram, and one-fourth of a hin for a lamb; this is the burnt offering for each month throughout the months of the year.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28015, 'Also one kid of the goats as a sin offering to the LORD shall be offered, besides the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28016, '&lsquo;On the fourteenth day of the first month is the Passover of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28017, 'And on the fifteenth day of this month is the feast; unleavened bread shall be eaten for seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28018, 'On the first day you shall have a holy convocation. You shall do no customary work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28019, 'And you shall present an offering made by fire as a burnt offering to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, and seven lambs in their first year. Be sure they are without blemish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28020, 'Their grain offering shall be of fine flour mixed with oil: three-tenths of an ephah you shall offer for a bull, and two-tenths for a ram;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28021, 'you shall offer one-tenth of an ephah for each of the seven lambs;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28022, 'also one goat as a sin offering, to make atonement for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28023, 'You shall offer these besides the burnt offering of the morning, which is for a regular burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28024, 'In this manner you shall offer the food of the offering made by fire daily for seven days, as a sweet aroma to the LORD; it shall be offered besides the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28025, 'And on the seventh day you shall have a holy convocation. You shall do no customary work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28026, '&lsquo;Also on the day of the firstfruits, when you bring a new grain offering to the LORD at your Feast of Weeks, you shall have a holy convocation. You shall do no customary work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28027, 'You shall present a burnt offering as a sweet aroma to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, and seven lambs in their first year,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28028, 'with their grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil: three-tenths of an ephah for each bull, two-tenths for the one ram,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28029, 'and one-tenth for each of the seven lambs;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28030, 'also one kid of the goats, to make atonement for you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 28031, 'Be sure they are without blemish. You shall present them with their drink offerings, besides the regular burnt offering with its grain offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29001, '&lsquo;And in the seventh month, on the first day of the month, you shall have a holy convocation. You shall do no customary work. For you it is a day of blowing the trumpets.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29002, 'You shall offer a burnt offering as a sweet aroma to the LORD: one young bull, one ram, and seven lambs in their first year, without blemish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29003, 'Their grain offering shall be fine flour mixed with oil: three-tenths of an ephah for the bull, two-tenths for the ram,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29004, 'and one-tenth for each of the seven lambs;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29005, 'also one kid of the goats as a sin offering, to make atonement for you;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29006, 'besides the burnt offering with its grain offering for the New Moon, the regular burnt offering with its grain offering, and their drink offerings, according to their ordinance, as a sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29007, '&lsquo;On the tenth day of this seventh month you shall have a holy convocation. You shall afflict your souls; you shall not do any work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29008, 'You shall present a burnt offering to the LORD as a sweet aroma: one young bull, one ram, and seven lambs in their first year. Be sure they are without blemish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29009, 'Their grain offering shall be of fine flour mixed with oil: three-tenths of an ephah for the bull, two-tenths for the one ram,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29010, 'and one-tenth for each of the seven lambs;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29011, 'also one kid of the goats as a sin offering, besides the sin offering for atonement, the regular burnt offering with its grain offering, and their drink offerings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29012, '&lsquo;On the fifteenth day of the seventh month you shall have a holy convocation. You shall do no customary work, and you shall keep a feast to the LORD seven days.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29013, 'You shall present a burnt offering, an offering made by fire as a sweet aroma to the LORD: thirteen young bulls, two rams, and fourteen lambs in their first year. They shall be without blemish.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29014, 'Their grain offering shall be of fine flour mixed with oil: three-tenths of an ephah for each of the thirteen bulls, two-tenths for each of the two rams,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29015, 'and one-tenth for each of the fourteen lambs;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29016, 'also one kid of the goats as a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29017, '&lsquo;On the second day present twelve young bulls, two rams, fourteen lambs in their first year without blemish,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29018, 'and their grain offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, by their number, according to the ordinance;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29019, 'also one kid of the goats as a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering with its grain offering, and their drink offerings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29020, '&lsquo;On the third day present eleven bulls, two rams, fourteen lambs in their first year without blemish,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29021, 'and their grain offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, by their number, according to the ordinance;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29022, 'also one goat as a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29023, '&lsquo;On the fourth day present ten bulls, two rams, and fourteen lambs in their first year, without blemish,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29024, 'and their grain offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, by their number, according to the ordinance;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29025, 'also one kid of the goats as a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29026, '&lsquo;On the fifth day present nine bulls, two rams, and fourteen lambs in their first year without blemish,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29027, 'and their grain offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, by their number, according to the ordinance;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29028, 'also one goat as a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29029, '&lsquo;On the sixth day present eight bulls, two rams, and fourteen lambs in their first year without blemish,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29030, 'and their grain offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, by their number, according to the ordinance;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29031, 'also one goat as a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29032, '&lsquo;On the seventh day present seven bulls, two rams, and fourteen lambs in their first year without blemish,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29033, 'and their grain offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, by their number, according to the ordinance;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29034, 'also one goat as a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29035, '&lsquo;On the eighth day you shall have a sacred assembly. You shall do no customary work.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29036, 'You shall present a burnt offering, an offering made by fire as a sweet aroma to the LORD: one bull, one ram, seven lambs in their first year without blemish,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29037, 'and their grain offering and their drink offerings for the bull, for the ram, and for the lambs, by their number, according to the ordinance;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29038, 'also one goat as a sin offering, besides the regular burnt offering, its grain offering, and its drink offering.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29039, '&lsquo;These you shall present to the LORD at your appointed feasts (besides your vowed offerings and your freewill offerings) as your burnt offerings and your grain offerings, as your drink offerings and your peace offerings.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 29040, 'So Moses told the children of Israel everything, just as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30001, 'Then Moses spoke to the heads of the tribes concerning the children of Israel, saying, &ldquo;This is the thing which the LORD has commanded:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30002, 'If a man makes a vow to the LORD, or swears an oath to bind himself by some agreement, he shall not break his word; he shall do according to all that proceeds out of his mouth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30003, '&ldquo;Or if a woman makes a vow to the LORD, and binds herself by some agreement while in her father&rsquo;s house in her youth,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30004, 'and her father hears her vow and the agreement by which she has bound herself, and her father holds his peace, then all her vows shall stand, and every agreement with which she has bound herself shall stand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30005, 'But if her father overrules her on the day that he hears, then none of her vows nor her agreements by which she has bound herself shall stand; and the LORD will release her, because her father overruled her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30006, '&ldquo;If indeed she takes a husband, while bound by her vows or by a rash utterance from her lips by which she bound herself,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30007, 'and her husband hears it, and makes no response to her on the day that he hears, then her vows shall stand, and her agreements by which she bound herself shall stand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30008, 'But if her husband overrules her on the day that he hears it, he shall make void her vow which she took and what she uttered with her lips, by which she bound herself, and the LORD will release her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30009, '&ldquo;Also any vow of a widow or a divorced woman, by which she has bound herself, shall stand against her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30010, '&ldquo;If she vowed in her husband&rsquo;s house, or bound herself by an agreement with an oath,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30011, 'and her husband heard it, and made no response to her and did not overrule her, then all her vows shall stand, and every agreement by which she bound herself shall stand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30012, 'But if her husband truly made them void on the day he heard them, then whatever proceeded from her lips concerning her vows or concerning the agreement binding her, it shall not stand; her husband has made them void, and the LORD will release her.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30013, 'Every vow and every binding oath to afflict her soul, her husband may confirm it, or her husband may make it void.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30014, 'Now if her husband makes no response whatever to her from day to day, then he confirms all her vows or all the agreements that bind her; he confirms them, because he made no response to her on the day that he heard them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30015, 'But if he does make them void after he has heard them, then he shall bear her guilt.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 30016, 'These are the statutes which the LORD commanded Moses, between a man and his wife, and between a father and his daughter in her youth in her father&rsquo;s house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31002, '&ldquo;Take vengeance on the Midianites for the children of Israel. Afterward you shall be gathered to your people.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31003, 'So Moses spoke to the people, saying, &ldquo;Arm some of yourselves for war, and let them go against the Midianites to take vengeance for the LORD on Midian.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31004, 'A thousand from each tribe of all the tribes of Israel you shall send to the war.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31005, 'So there were recruited from the divisions of Israel one thousand from each tribe, twelve thousand armed for war.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31006, 'Then Moses sent them to the war, one thousand from each tribe; he sent them to the war with Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, with the holy articles and the signal trumpets in his hand.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31007, 'And they warred against the Midianites, just as the LORD commanded Moses, and they killed all the males.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31008, 'They killed the kings of Midian with the rest of those who were killed &ndash; Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur, and Reba, the five kings of Midian. Balaam the son of Beor they also killed with the sword.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31009, 'And the children of Israel took the women of Midian captive, with their little ones, and took as spoil all their cattle, all their flocks, and all their goods.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31010, 'They also burned with fire all the cities where they dwelt, and all their forts.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31011, 'And they took all the spoil and all the booty &ndash; of man and beast.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31012, 'Then they brought the captives, the booty, and the spoil to Moses, to Eleazar the priest, and to the congregation of the children of Israel, to the camp in the plains of Moab by the Jordan, across from Jericho.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31013, 'And Moses, Eleazar the priest, and all the leaders of the congregation, went to meet them outside the camp.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31014, 'But Moses was angry with the officers of the army, with the captains over thousands and captains over hundreds, who had come from the battle.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31015, 'And Moses said to them: &ldquo;Have you kept all the women alive?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31016, 'Look, these women caused the children of Israel, through the counsel of Balaam, to trespass against the LORD in the incident of Peor, and there was a plague among the congregation of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31017, 'Now therefore, kill every male among the little ones, and kill every woman who has known a man intimately.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31018, 'But keep alive for yourselves all the young girls who have not known a man intimately.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31019, 'And as for you, remain outside the camp seven days; whoever has killed any person, and whoever has touched any slain, purify yourselves and your captives on the third day and on the seventh day.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31020, 'Purify every garment, everything made of leather, everything woven of goats&rsquo; hair, and everything made of wood.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31021, 'Then Eleazar the priest said to the men of war who had gone to the battle, &ldquo;This is the ordinance of the law which the LORD commanded Moses:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31022, 'Only the gold, the silver, the bronze, the iron, the tin, and the lead,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31023, 'everything that can endure fire, you shall put through the fire, and it shall be clean; and it shall be purified with the water of purification. But all that cannot endure fire you shall put through water.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31024, 'And you shall wash your clothes on the seventh day and be clean, and afterward you may come into the camp.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31025, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31026, '&ldquo;Count up the plunder that was taken &ndash; of man and beast &ndash; you and Eleazar the priest and the chief fathers of the congregation;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31027, 'and divide the plunder into two parts, between those who took part in the war, who went out to battle, and all the congregation.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31028, 'And levy a tribute for the LORD on the men of war who went out to battle: one of every five hundred of the persons, the cattle, the donkeys, and the sheep;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31029, 'take it from their half, and give it to Eleazar the priest as a heave offering to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31030, 'And from the children of Israel&rsquo;s half you shall take one of every fifty, drawn from the persons, the cattle, the donkeys, and the sheep, from all the livestock, and give them to the Levites who keep charge of the tabernacle of the LORD.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31031, 'So Moses and Eleazar the priest did as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31032, 'The booty remaining from the plunder, which the men of war had taken, was six hundred and seventy-five thousand sheep,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31033, 'seventy-two thousand cattle,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31034, 'sixty-one thousand donkeys,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31035, 'and thirty-two thousand persons in all, of women who had not known a man intimately.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31036, 'And the half, the portion for those who had gone out to war, was in number three hundred and thirty-seven thousand five hundred sheep;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31037, 'and the LORD&rsquo;s tribute of the sheep was six hundred and seventy-five.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31038, 'The cattle were thirty-six thousand, of which the LORD&rsquo;s tribute was seventy-two.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31039, 'The donkeys were thirty thousand five hundred, of which the LORD&rsquo;s tribute was sixty-one.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31040, 'The persons were sixteen thousand, of which the LORD&rsquo;s tribute was thirty-two persons.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31041, 'So Moses gave the tribute which was the LORD&rsquo;s heave offering to Eleazar the priest, as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31042, 'And from the children of Israel&rsquo;s half, which Moses separated from the men who fought &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31043, 'now the half belonging to the congregation was three hundred and thirty-seven thousand five hundred sheep,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31044, 'thirty-six thousand cattle,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31045, 'thirty thousand five hundred donkeys,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31046, 'and sixteen thousand persons &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31047, 'and from the children of Israel&rsquo;s half Moses took one of every fifty, drawn from man and beast, and gave them to the Levites, who kept charge of the tabernacle of the LORD, as the LORD commanded Moses.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31048, 'Then the officers who were over thousands of the army, the captains of thousands and captains of hundreds, came near to Moses;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31049, 'and they said to Moses, &ldquo;Your servants have taken a count of the men of war who are under our command, and not a man of us is missing.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31050, 'Therefore we have brought an offering for the LORD, what every man found of ornaments of gold: armlets and bracelets and signet rings and earrings and necklaces, to make atonement for ourselves before the LORD.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31051, 'So Moses and Eleazar the priest received the gold from them, all the fashioned ornaments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31052, 'And all the gold of the offering that they offered to the LORD, from the captains of thousands and captains of hundreds, was sixteen thousand seven hundred and fifty shekels.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31053, '(The men of war had taken spoil, every man for himself.)');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 31054, 'And Moses and Eleazar the priest received the gold from the captains of thousands and of hundreds, and brought it into the tabernacle of meeting as a memorial for the children of Israel before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32001, 'Now the children of Reuben and the children of Gad had a very great multitude of livestock; and when they saw the land of Jazer and the land of Gilead, that indeed the region was a place for livestock,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32002, 'the children of Gad and the children of Reuben came and spoke to Moses, to Eleazar the priest, and to the leaders of the congregation, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32003, '&ldquo;Ataroth, Dibon, Jazer, Nimrah, Heshbon, Elealeh, Shebam, Nebo, and Beon,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32004, 'the country which the LORD defeated before the congregation of Israel, is a land for livestock, and your servants have livestock.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32005, 'Therefore they said, &ldquo;If we have found favor in your sight, let this land be given to your servants as a possession. Do not take us over the Jordan.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32006, 'And Moses said to the children of Gad and to the children of Reuben: &ldquo;Shall your brethren go to war while you sit here?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32007, 'Now why will you discourage the heart of the children of Israel from going over into the land which the LORD has given them?');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32008, 'Thus your fathers did when I sent them away from Kadesh Barnea to see the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32009, 'For when they went up to the Valley of Eshcol and saw the land, they discouraged the heart of the children of Israel, so that they did not go into the land which the LORD had given them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32010, 'So the LORD&rsquo;s anger was aroused on that day, and He swore an oath, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32011, '&lsquo;Surely none of the men who came up from Egypt, from twenty years old and above, shall see the land of which I swore to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, because they have not wholly followed Me,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32012, 'except Caleb the son of Jephunneh, the Kenizzite, and Joshua the son of Nun, for they have wholly followed the LORD.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32013, 'So the LORD&rsquo;s anger was aroused against Israel, and He made them wander in the wilderness forty years, until all the generation that had done evil in the sight of the LORD was gone.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32014, 'And look! You have risen in your fathers&rsquo; place, a brood of sinful men, to increase still more the fierce anger of the LORD against Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32015, 'For if you turn away from following Him, He will once again leave them in the wilderness, and you will destroy all these people.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32016, 'Then they came near to him and said: &ldquo;We will build sheepfolds here for our livestock, and cities for our little ones,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32017, 'but we ourselves will be armed, ready to go before the children of Israel until we have brought them to their place; and our little ones will dwell in the fortified cities because of the inhabitants of the land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32018, 'We will not return to our homes until every one of the children of Israel has received his inheritance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32019, 'For we will not inherit with them on the other side of the Jordan and beyond, because our inheritance has fallen to us on this eastern side of the Jordan.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32020, 'Then Moses said to them: &ldquo;If you do this thing, if you arm yourselves before the LORD for the war,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32021, 'and all your armed men cross over the Jordan before the LORD until He has driven out His enemies from before Him,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32022, 'and the land is subdued before the LORD, then afterward you may return and be blameless before the LORD and before Israel; and this land shall be your possession before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32023, 'But if you do not do so, then take note, you have sinned against the LORD; and be sure your sin will find you out.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32024, 'Build cities for your little ones and folds for your sheep, and do what has proceeded out of your mouth.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32025, 'And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben spoke to Moses, saying: &ldquo;Your servants will do as my lord commands.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32026, 'Our little ones, our wives, our flocks, and all our livestock will be there in the cities of Gilead;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32027, 'but your servants will cross over, every man armed for war, before the LORD to battle, just as my lord says.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32028, 'So Moses gave command concerning them to Eleazar the priest, to Joshua the son of Nun, and to the chief fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32029, 'And Moses said to them: &ldquo;If the children of Gad and the children of Reuben cross over the Jordan with you, every man armed for battle before the LORD, and the land is subdued before you, then you shall give them the land of Gilead as a possession.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32030, 'But if they do not cross over armed with you, they shall have possessions among you in the land of Canaan.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32031, 'Then the children of Gad and the children of Reuben answered, saying: &ldquo;As the LORD has said to your servants, so we will do.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32032, 'We will cross over armed before the LORD into the land of Canaan, but the possession of our inheritance shall remain with us on this side of the Jordan.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32033, 'So Moses gave to the children of Gad, to the children of Reuben, and to half the tribe of Manasseh the son of Joseph, the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites and the kingdom of Og king of Bashan, the land with its cities within the borders, the cities of the surrounding country.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32034, 'And the children of Gad built Dibon and Ataroth and Aroer,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32035, 'Atroth and Shophan and Jazer and Jogbehah,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32036, 'Beth Nimrah and Beth Haran, fortified cities, and folds for sheep.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32037, 'And the children of Reuben built Heshbon and Elealeh and Kirjathaim,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32038, 'Nebo and Baal Meon (their names being changed) and Shibmah; and they gave other names to the cities which they built.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32039, 'And the children of Machir the son of Manasseh went to Gilead and took it, and dispossessed the Amorites who were in it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32040, 'So Moses gave Gilead to Machir the son of Manasseh, and he dwelt in it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32041, 'Also Jair the son of Manasseh went and took its small towns, and called them Havoth Jair.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 32042, 'Then Nobah went and took Kenath and its villages, and he called it Nobah, after his own name.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33001, 'These are the journeys of the children of Israel, who went out of the land of Egypt by their armies under the hand of Moses and Aaron.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33002, 'Now Moses wrote down the starting points of their journeys at the command of the LORD. And these are their journeys according to their starting points:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33003, 'They departed from Rameses in the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month; on the day after the Passover the children of Israel went out with boldness in the sight of all the Egyptians.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33004, 'For the Egyptians were burying all their firstborn, whom the LORD had killed among them. Also on their gods the LORD had executed judgments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33005, 'Then the children of Israel moved from Rameses and camped at Succoth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33006, 'They departed from Succoth and camped at Etham, which is on the edge of the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33007, 'They moved from Etham and turned back to Pi Hahiroth, which is east of Baal Zephon; and they camped near Migdol.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33008, 'They departed from before Hahiroth and passed through the midst of the sea into the wilderness, went three days&rsquo; journey in the Wilderness of Etham, and camped at Marah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33009, 'They moved from Marah and came to Elim. At Elim were twelve springs of water and seventy palm trees; so they camped there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33010, 'They moved from Elim and camped by the Red Sea.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33011, 'They moved from the Red Sea and camped in the Wilderness of Sin.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33012, 'They journeyed from the Wilderness of Sin and camped at Dophkah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33013, 'They departed from Dophkah and camped at Alush.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33014, 'They moved from Alush and camped at Rephidim, where there was no water for the people to drink.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33015, 'They departed from Rephidim and camped in the Wilderness of Sinai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33016, 'They moved from the Wilderness of Sinai and camped at Kibroth Hattaavah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33017, 'They departed from Kibroth Hattaavah and camped at Hazeroth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33018, 'They departed from Hazeroth and camped at Rithmah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33019, 'They departed from Rithmah and camped at Rimmon Perez.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33020, 'They departed from Rimmon Perez and camped at Libnah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33021, 'They moved from Libnah and camped at Rissah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33022, 'They journeyed from Rissah and camped at Kehelathah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33023, 'They went from Kehelathah and camped at Mount Shepher.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33024, 'They moved from Mount Shepher and camped at Haradah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33025, 'They moved from Haradah and camped at Makheloth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33026, 'They moved from Makheloth and camped at Tahath.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33027, 'They departed from Tahath and camped at Terah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33028, 'They moved from Terah and camped at Mithkah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33029, 'They went from Mithkah and camped at Hashmonah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33030, 'They departed from Hashmonah and camped at Moseroth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33031, 'They departed from Moseroth and camped at Bene Jaakan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33032, 'They moved from Bene Jaakan and camped at Hor Hagidgad.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33033, 'They went from Hor Hagidgad and camped at Jotbathah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33034, 'They moved from Jotbathah and camped at Abronah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33035, 'They departed from Abronah and camped at Ezion Geber.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33036, 'They moved from Ezion Geber and camped in the Wilderness of Zin, which is Kadesh.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33037, 'They moved from Kadesh and camped at Mount Hor, on the boundary of the land of Edom.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33038, 'Then Aaron the priest went up to Mount Hor at the command of the LORD, and died there in the fortieth year after the children of Israel had come out of the land of Egypt, on the first day of the fifth month.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33039, 'Aaron was one hundred and twenty-three years old when he died on Mount Hor.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33040, 'Now the king of Arad, the Canaanite, who dwelt in the South in the land of Canaan, heard of the coming of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33041, 'So they departed from Mount Hor and camped at Zalmonah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33042, 'They departed from Zalmonah and camped at Punon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33043, 'They departed from Punon and camped at Oboth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33044, 'They departed from Oboth and camped at Ije Abarim, at the border of Moab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33045, 'They departed from Ijim and camped at Dibon Gad.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33046, 'They moved from Dibon Gad and camped at Almon Diblathaim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33047, 'They moved from Almon Diblathaim and camped in the mountains of Abarim, before Nebo.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33048, 'They departed from the mountains of Abarim and camped in the plains of Moab by the Jordan, across from Jericho.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33049, 'They camped by the Jordan, from Beth Jesimoth as far as the Abel Acacia Grove in the plains of Moab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33050, 'Now the LORD spoke to Moses in the plains of Moab by the Jordan, across from Jericho, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33051, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When you have crossed the Jordan into the land of Canaan,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33052, 'then you shall drive out all the inhabitants of the land from before you, destroy all their engraved stones, destroy all their molded images, and demolish all their high places;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33053, 'you shall dispossess the inhabitants of the land and dwell in it, for I have given you the land to possess.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33054, 'And you shall divide the land by lot as an inheritance among your families; to the larger you shall give a larger inheritance, and to the smaller you shall give a smaller inheritance; there everyone&rsquo;s inheritance shall be whatever falls to him by lot. You shall inherit according to the tribes of your fathers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33055, 'But if you do not drive out the inhabitants of the land from before you, then it shall be that those whom you let remain shall be irritants in your eyes and thorns in your sides, and they shall harass you in the land where you dwell.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 33056, 'Moreover it shall be that I will do to you as I thought to do to them.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34001, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34002, '&ldquo;Command the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When you come into the land of Canaan, this is the land that shall fall to you as an inheritance &ndash; the land of Canaan to its boundaries.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34003, 'Your southern border shall be from the Wilderness of Zin along the border of Edom; then your southern border shall extend eastward to the end of the Salt Sea;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34004, 'your border shall turn from the southern side of the Ascent of Akrabbim, continue to Zin, and be on the south of Kadesh Barnea; then it shall go on to Hazar Addar, and continue to Azmon;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34005, 'the border shall turn from Azmon to the Brook of Egypt, and it shall end at the Sea.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34006, '&lsquo;As for the western border, you shall have the Great Sea for a border; this shall be your western border.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34007, '&lsquo;And this shall be your northern border: From the Great Sea you shall mark out your border line to Mount Hor;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34008, 'from Mount Hor you shall mark out your border to the entrance of Hamath; then the direction of the border shall be toward Zedad;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34009, 'the border shall proceed to Ziphron, and it shall end at Hazar Enan. This shall be your northern border.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34010, '&lsquo;You shall mark out your eastern border from Hazar Enan to Shepham;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34011, 'the border shall go down from Shepham to Riblah on the east side of Ain; the border shall go down and reach to the eastern side of the Sea of Chinnereth;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34012, 'the border shall go down along the Jordan, and it shall end at the Salt Sea. This shall be your land with its surrounding boundaries.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34013, 'Then Moses commanded the children of Israel, saying: &ldquo;This is the land which you shall inherit by lot, which the LORD has commanded to give to the nine tribes and to the half-tribe.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34014, 'For the tribe of the children of Reuben according to the house of their fathers, and the tribe of the children of Gad according to the house of their fathers, have received their inheritance; and the half-tribe of Manasseh has received its inheritance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34015, 'The two tribes and the half-tribe have received their inheritance on this side of the Jordan, across from Jericho eastward, toward the sunrise.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34016, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34017, '&ldquo;These are the names of the men who shall divide the land among you as an inheritance: Eleazar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34018, 'And you shall take one leader of every tribe to divide the land for the inheritance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34019, 'These are the names of the men: from the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34020, 'from the tribe of the children of Simeon, Shemuel the son of Ammihud;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34021, 'from the tribe of Benjamin, Elidad the son of Chislon;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34022, 'a leader from the tribe of the children of Dan, Bukki the son of Jogli;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34023, 'from the sons of Joseph: a leader from the tribe of the children of Manasseh, Hanniel the son of Ephod,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34024, 'and a leader from the tribe of the children of Ephraim, Kemuel the son of Shiphtan;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34025, 'a leader from the tribe of the children of Zebulun, Elizaphan the son of Parnach;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34026, 'a leader from the tribe of the children of Issachar, Paltiel the son of Azzan;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34027, 'a leader from the tribe of the children of Asher, Ahihud the son of Shelomi;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34028, 'and a leader from the tribe of the children of Naphtali, Pedahel the son of Ammihud.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 34029, 'These are the ones the LORD commanded to divide the inheritance among the children of Israel in the land of Canaan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35001, 'And the LORD spoke to Moses in the plains of Moab by the Jordan across from Jericho, saying:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35002, '&ldquo;Command the children of Israel that they give the Levites cities to dwell in from the inheritance of their possession, and you shall also give the Levites common-land around the cities.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35003, 'They shall have the cities to dwell in; and their common-land shall be for their cattle, for their herds, and for all their animals.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35004, 'The common-land of the cities which you will give the Levites shall extend from the wall of the city outward a thousand cubits all around.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35005, 'And you shall measure outside the city on the east side two thousand cubits, on the south side two thousand cubits, on the west side two thousand cubits, and on the north side two thousand cubits. The city shall be in the middle. This shall belong to them as common-land for the cities.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35006, '&ldquo;Now among the cities which you will give to the Levites you shall appoint six cities of refuge, to which a manslayer may flee. And to these you shall add forty-two cities.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35007, 'So all the cities you will give to the Levites shall be forty-eight; these you shall give with their common-land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35008, 'And the cities which you will give shall be from the possession of the children of Israel; from the larger tribe you shall give many, from the smaller you shall give few. Each shall give some of its cities to the Levites, in proportion to the inheritance that each receives.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35009, 'Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35010, '&ldquo;Speak to the children of Israel, and say to them: &lsquo;When you cross the Jordan into the land of Canaan,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35011, 'then you shall appoint cities to be cities of refuge for you, that the manslayer who kills any person accidentally may flee there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35012, 'They shall be cities of refuge for you from the avenger, that the manslayer may not die until he stands before the congregation in judgment.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35013, 'And of the cities which you give, you shall have six cities of refuge.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35014, 'You shall appoint three cities on this side of the Jordan, and three cities you shall appoint in the land of Canaan, which will be cities of refuge.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35015, 'These six cities shall be for refuge for the children of Israel, for the stranger, and for the sojourner among them, that anyone who kills a person accidentally may flee there.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35016, '&lsquo;But if he strikes him with an iron implement, so that he dies, he is a murderer; the murderer shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35017, 'And if he strikes him with a stone in the hand, by which one could die, and he does die, he is a murderer; the murderer shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35018, 'Or if he strikes him with a wooden hand weapon, by which one could die, and he does die, he is a murderer; the murderer shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35019, 'The avenger of blood himself shall put the murderer to death; when he meets him, he shall put him to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35020, 'If he pushes him out of hatred or, while lying in wait, hurls something at him so that he dies,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35021, 'or in enmity he strikes him with his hand so that he dies, the one who struck him shall surely be put to death. He is a murderer. The avenger of blood shall put the murderer to death when he meets him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35022, '&lsquo;However, if he pushes him suddenly without enmity, or throws anything at him without lying in wait,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35023, 'or uses a stone, by which a man could die, throwing it at him without seeing him, so that he dies, while he was not his enemy or seeking his harm,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35024, 'then the congregation shall judge between the manslayer and the avenger of blood according to these judgments.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35025, 'So the congregation shall deliver the manslayer from the hand of the avenger of blood, and the congregation shall return him to the city of refuge where he had fled, and he shall remain there until the death of the high priest who was anointed with the holy oil.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35026, 'But if the manslayer at any time goes outside the limits of the city of refuge where he fled,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35027, 'and the avenger of blood finds him outside the limits of his city of refuge, and the avenger of blood kills the manslayer, he shall not be guilty of blood,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35028, 'because he should have remained in his city of refuge until the death of the high priest. But after the death of the high priest the manslayer may return to the land of his possession.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35029, '&lsquo;And these things shall be a statute of judgment to you throughout your generations in all your dwellings.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35030, 'Whoever kills a person, the murderer shall be put to death on the testimony of witnesses; but one witness is not sufficient testimony against a person for the death penalty.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35031, 'Moreover you shall take no ransom for the life of a murderer who is guilty of death, but he shall surely be put to death.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35032, 'And you shall take no ransom for him who has fled to his city of refuge, that he may return to dwell in the land before the death of the priest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35033, 'So you shall not pollute the land where you are; for blood defiles the land, and no atonement can be made for the land, for the blood that is shed on it, except by the blood of him who shed it.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 35034, 'Therefore do not defile the land which you inhabit, in the midst of which I dwell; for I the LORD dwell among the children of Israel.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36001, 'Now the chief fathers of the families of the children of Gilead the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, of the families of the sons of Joseph, came near and spoke before Moses and before the leaders, the chief fathers of the children of Israel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36002, 'And they said: &ldquo;The LORD commanded my lord Moses to give the land as an inheritance by lot to the children of Israel, and my lord was commanded by the LORD to give the inheritance of our brother Zelophehad to his daughters.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36003, 'Now if they are married to any of the sons of the other tribes of the children of Israel, then their inheritance will be taken from the inheritance of our fathers, and it will be added to the inheritance of the tribe into which they marry; so it will be taken from the lot of our inheritance.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36004, 'And when the Jubilee of the children of Israel comes, then their inheritance will be added to the inheritance of the tribe into which they marry; so their inheritance will be taken away from the inheritance of the tribe of our fathers.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36005, 'Then Moses commanded the children of Israel according to the word of the LORD, saying: &ldquo;What the tribe of the sons of Joseph speaks is right.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36006, 'This is what the LORD commands concerning the daughters of Zelophehad, saying, &lsquo;Let them marry whom they think best, but they may marry only within the family of their father&rsquo;s tribe.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36007, 'So the inheritance of the children of Israel shall not change hands from tribe to tribe, for every one of the children of Israel shall keep the inheritance of the tribe of his fathers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36008, 'And every daughter who possesses an inheritance in any tribe of the children of Israel shall be the wife of one of the family of her father&rsquo;s tribe, so that the children of Israel each may possess the inheritance of his fathers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36009, 'Thus no inheritance shall change hands from one tribe to another, but every tribe of the children of Israel shall keep its own inheritance.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36010, 'Just as the LORD commanded Moses, so did the daughters of Zelophehad;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36011, 'for Mahlah, Tirzah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Noah, the daughters of Zelophehad, were married to the sons of their father&rsquo;s brothers.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36012, 'They were married into the families of the children of Manasseh the son of Joseph, and their inheritance remained in the tribe of their father&rsquo;s family.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Num', 36013, 'These are the commandments and the judgments which the LORD commanded the children of Israel by the hand of Moses in the plains of Moab by the Jordan, across from Jericho.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1001, 'These are the words which Moses spoke to all Israel on this side of the Jordan in the wilderness, in the plain opposite Suph, between Paran, Tophel, Laban, Hazeroth, and Dizahab.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1002, 'It is eleven days&rsquo; journey from Horeb by way of Mount Seir to Kadesh Barnea.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1003, 'Now it came to pass in the fortieth year, in the eleventh month, on the first day of the month, that Moses spoke to the children of Israel according to all that the Lord had given him as commandments to them,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1004, 'after he had killed Sihon king of the Amorites, who dwelt in Heshbon, and Og king of Bashan, who dwelt at Ashtaroth in Edrei.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1005, 'On this side of the Jordan in the land of Moab, Moses began to explain this law, saying,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1006, 'The Lord our God spoke to us in Horeb, saying: &lsquo;You have dwelt long enough at this mountain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1007, 'Turn and take your journey, and go to the mountains of the Amorites, to all the neighboring places in the plain, in the mountains and in the lowland, in the South and on the seacoast, to the land of the Canaanites and to Lebanon, as far as the great river, the River Euphrates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1007, 'Turn and take your journey, and go to the mountains of the Amorites, to all the neighboring places in the plain, F4 in the mountains and in the lowland, in the South and on the seacoast, to the land of the Canaanites and to Lebanon, as far as the great river, the River Euphrates.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1008, 'See, I have set the land before you; go in and possess the land which the Lord swore to your fathers &ndash; to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob &ndash; to give to them and their descendants after them.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1008, 'See, I have set the land before you; go in and possess the land which the Lord swore to your fathers &ndash; to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob &ndash; to give to them and their descendants after them.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1009, 'And I spoke to you at that time, saying: &lsquo;I alone am not able to bear you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1009, '&ldquo;And I spoke to you at that time, saying: &lsquo;I alone am not able to bear you.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1010, 'The Lord your God has multiplied you, and here you are today, as the stars of heaven in multitude. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1011, 'May the Lord God of your fathers make you a thousand times more numerous than you are, and bless you as He has promised you! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1012, 'How can I alone bear your problems and your burdens and your complaints? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1013, 'Choose wise, understanding, and knowledgeable men from among your tribes, and I will make them heads over you.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1014, 'And you answered me and said, &lsquo;The thing which you have told us to do is good.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1015, 'So I took the heads of your tribes, wise and knowledgeable men, and made them heads over you, leaders of thousands, leaders of hundreds, leaders of fifties, leaders of tens, and officers for your tribes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1016, 'Then I commanded your judges at that time, saying, &lsquo;Hear the cases between your brethren, and judge righteously between a man and his brother or the stranger who is with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1017, 'You shall not show partiality in judgment; you shall hear the small as well as the great; you shall not be afraid in any man&rsquo;s presence, for the judgment is God&rsquo;s.| The case that is too hard for you, bring to me, and I will hear it.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1018, 'And I commanded you at that time all the things which you should do. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1019, 'So we departed from Horeb, and went through all that great and terrible wilderness which you saw on the way to the mountains of the Amorites, as the Lord our God had commanded us. Then we came to Kadesh Barnea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1020, 'And I said to you, &lsquo;You have come to the mountains of the Amorites, which the Lord our God is giving us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1021, 'Look, the Lord your God has set the land before you; go up and possess it, as the Lord God of your fathers has spoken to you; do not fear or be discouraged.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1022, 'And everyone of you came near to me and said, &lsquo;Let us send men before us, and let them search out the land for us, and bring back word to us of the way by which we should go up, and of the cities into which we shall come.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1023, 'The plan pleased me well; so I took twelve of your men, one man from each tribe. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1024, 'And they departed and went up into the mountains, and came to the Valley of Eshcol, and spied it out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1025, 'They also took some of the fruit of the land in their hands and brought it down to us; and they brought back word to us, saying, &lsquo;It is a good land which the Lord our God is giving us.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1026, 'Nevertheless you would not go up, but rebelled against the command of the Lord your God; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1027, 'and you complained in your tents, and said, &lsquo;Because the Lord hates us, He has brought us out of the land of Egypt to deliver us into the hand of the Amorites, to destroy us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1028, 'Where can we go up? Our brethren have discouraged our hearts, saying, &ldquo;The people are greater and taller than we; the cities are great and fortified up to heaven; moreover we have seen the sons of the Anakim there.&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1029, 'Then I said to you, &lsquo;Do not be terrified, or afraid of them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1030, 'The Lord your God, who goes before you, He will fight for you, according to all He did for you in Egypt before your eyes, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1031, 'and in the wilderness where you saw how the Lord your God carried you, as a man carries his son, in all the way that you went until you came to this place.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1032, 'Yet, for all that, you did not believe the Lord your God, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1033, 'who went in the way before you to search out a place for you to pitch your tents, to show you the way you should go, in the fire by night and in the cloud by day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1034, 'And the Lord heard the sound of your words, and was angry, and took an oath, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1035, '&rsquo;Surely not one of these men of this evil generation shall see that good land of which I swore to give to your fathers, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1036, 'except Caleb the son of Jephunneh; he shall see it, and to him and his children I am giving the land on which he walked, because he wholly followed the Lord.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1037, 'The Lord was also angry with me for your sakes, saying, &lsquo;Even you shall not go in there; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1038, 'Joshua the son of Nun, who stands before you, he shall go in there. Encourage him, for he shall cause Israel to inherit it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1039, 'Moreover your little ones and your children, who you say will be victims, who today have no knowledge of good and evil, they shall go in there; to them I will give it, and they shall possess it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1040, 'But as for you, turn and take your journey into the wilderness by the Way of the Red Sea.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1041, 'Then you answered and said to me, &lsquo;We have sinned against the Lord; we will go up and fight, just as the Lord our God commanded us.&rsquo; And when everyone of you had girded on his weapons of war, you were ready to go up into the mountain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1042, 'And the Lord said to me, &lsquo;Tell them, &ldquo;Do not go up nor fight, for I am not among you; lest you be defeated before your enemies.&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1043, 'So I spoke to you; yet you would not listen, but rebelled against the command of the Lord, and presumptuously went up into the mountain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1044, 'And the Amorites who dwelt in that mountain came out against you and chased you as bees do, and drove you back from Seir to Hormah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1045, 'Then you returned and wept before the Lord, but the Lord would not listen to your voice nor give ear to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 1046, 'So you remained in Kadesh many days, according to the days that you spent there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2001, 'Then we turned and journeyed into the wilderness of the Way of the Red Sea, as the Lord spoke to me, and we skirted Mount Seir for many days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2002, 'And the Lord spoke to me, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2003, '&rsquo;You have skirted this mountain long enough; turn northward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2004, 'And command the people, saying, You are about to pass through the territory of your brethren, the descendants of Esau, who live in Seir; and they will be afraid of you. Therefore watch yourselves carefully. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2005, 'Do not meddle with them, for I will not give you any of their land, no, not so much as one footstep, because I have given Mount Seir to Esau as a possession. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2006, 'You shall buy food from them with money, that you may eat; and you shall also buy water from them with money, that you may drink. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2007, 'For the Lord your God has blessed you in all the work of your hand. He knows your trudging through this great wilderness. These forty years the Lord your God has been with you; you have lacked nothing.&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2008, 'And when we passed beyond our brethren, the descendants of Esau who dwell in Seir, away from the road of the plain, away from Elath and Ezion Geber, we turned and passed by way of the Wilderness of Moab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2009, 'Then the Lord said to me, &lsquo;Do not harass Moab, nor contend with them in battle, for I will not give you any of their land as a possession, because I have given Ar to the descendants of Lot as a possession.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2010, '(The Emim had dwelt there in times past, a people as great and numerous and tall as the Anakim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2011, 'They were also regarded as giants, like the Anakim, but the Moabites call them Emim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2012, 'The Horites formerly dwelt in Seir, but the descendants of Esau dispossessed them and destroyed them from before them, and dwelt in their place, just as Israel did to the land of their possession which the Lord gave them.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2013, ' &lsquo;Now rise and cross over the Valley of the Zered.&rsquo; So we crossed over the Valley of the Zered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2014, 'And the time we took to come from Kadesh Barnea until we crossed over the Valley of the Zered was thirty-eight years, until all the generation of the men of war was consumed from the midst of the camp, just as the Lord had sworn to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2015, 'For indeed the hand of the Lord was against them, to destroy them from the midst of the camp until they were consumed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2016, 'So it was, when all the men of war had finally perished from among the people, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2017, 'that the Lord spoke to me, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2018, '&rsquo;This day you are to cross over at Ar, the boundary of Moab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2019, 'And when you come near the people of Ammon, do not harass them or meddle with them, for I will not give you any of the land of the people of Ammon as a possession, because I have given it to the descendants of Lot as a possession.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2020, '(That was also regarded as a land of giants;* giants formerly dwelt there. But the Ammonites call them Zamzummim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2021, 'a people as great and numerous and tall as the Anakim. But the Lord destroyed them before them, and they dispossessed them and dwelt in their place, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2022, 'just as He had done for the descendants of Esau, who dwelt in Seir, when He destroyed the Horites from before them. They dispossessed them and dwelt in their place, even to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2023, 'And the Avim, who dwelt in villages as far as Gaza &ndash; the Caphtorim, who came from Caphtor, destroyed them and dwelt in their place.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2024, ' &lsquo;Rise, take your journey, and cross over the River Arnon. Look, I have given into your hand Sihon the Amorite, king of Heshbon, and his land. Begin to possess it, and engage him in battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2025, 'This day I will begin to put the dread and fear of you upon the nations under the whole heaven, who shall hear the report of you, and shall tremble and be in anguish because of you.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2026, 'And I sent messengers from the Wilderness of Kedemoth to Sihon king of Heshbon, with words of peace, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2027, '&rsquo;Let me pass through your land; I will keep strictly to the road, and I will turn neither to the right nor to the left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2028, 'You shall sell me food for money, that I may eat, and give me water for money, that I may drink; only let me pass through on foot, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2029, 'just as the descendants of Esau who dwell in Seir and the Moabites who dwell in Ar did for me, until I cross the Jordan to the land which the Lord our God is giving us.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2030, 'But Sihon king of Heshbon would not let us pass through, for the Lord your God hardened his spirit and made his heart obstinate, that He might deliver him into your hand, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2031, 'And the Lord said to me, &lsquo;See, I have begun to give Sihon and his land over to you. Begin to possess it, that you may inherit his land.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2032, 'Then Sihon and all his people came out against us to fight at Jahaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2033, 'And the Lord our God delivered him over to us; so we defeated him, his sons, and all his people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2034, 'We took all his cities at that time, and we utterly destroyed the men, women, and little ones of every city; we left none remaining. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2035, 'We took only the livestock as plunder for ourselves, with the spoil of the cities which we took. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2036, 'From Aroer, which is on the bank of the River Arnon, and from the city that is in the ravine, as far as Gilead, there was not one city too strong for us; the Lord our God delivered all to us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 2037, 'Only you did not go near the land of the people of Ammon &ndash; anywhere along the River Jabbok, or to the cities of the mountains, or wherever the Lord our God had forbidden us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3001, 'Then we turned and went up the road to Bashan; and Og king of Bashan came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at Edrei. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3002, 'And the Lord said to me, &lsquo;Do not fear him, for I have delivered him and all his people and his land into your hand; you shall do to him as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who dwelt at Heshbon.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3003, 'So the Lord our God also delivered into our hands Og king of Bashan, with all his people, and we attacked him until he had no survivors remaining. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3004, 'And we took all his cities at that time; there was not a city which we did not take from them: sixty cities, all the region of Argob, the kingdom of Og in Bashan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3005, 'All these cities were fortified with high walls, gates, and bars, besides a great many rural towns. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3006, 'And we utterly destroyed them, as we did to Sihon king of Heshbon, utterly destroying the men, women, and children of every city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3007, 'But all the livestock and the spoil of the cities we took as booty for ourselves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3008, 'And at that time we took the land from the hand of the two kings of the Amorites who were on this side of the Jordan, from the River Arnon to Mount Hermon ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3009, '(the Sidonians call Hermon Sirion, and the Amorites call it Senir), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3010, 'all the cities of the plain, all Gilead, and all Bashan, as far as Salcah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3011, 'For only Og king of Bashan remained of the remnant of the giants. Indeed his bedstead was an iron bedstead. (Is it not in Rabbah of the people of Ammon?) Nine cubits is its length and four cubits its width, according to the standard cubit. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3012, 'And this land, which we possessed at that time, from Aroer, which is by the River Arnon, and half the mountains of Gilead and its cities, I gave to the Reubenites and the Gadites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3013, 'The rest of Gilead, and all Bashan, the kingdom of Og, I gave to half the tribe of Manasseh. (All the region of Argob, with all Bashan, was called the land of the giants.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3014, 'Jair the son of Manasseh took all the region of Argob, as far as the border of the Geshurites and the Maachathites, and called Bashan after his own name, Havoth Jair, to this day.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3015, 'Also I gave Gilead to Machir. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3016, 'And to the Reubenites and the Gadites I gave from Gilead as far as the River Arnon, the middle of the river as the border, as far as the River Jabbok, the border of the people of Ammon; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3017, 'the plain also, with the Jordan as the border, from Chinnereth as far as the east side of the Sea of the Arabah (the Salt Sea), below the slopes of Pisgah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3018, 'Then I commanded you at that time, saying: &lsquo;The Lord your God has given you this land to possess. All you men of valor shall cross over armed before your brethren, the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3019, 'But your wives, your little ones, and your livestock (I know that you have much livestock) shall stay in your cities which I have given you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3020, 'until the Lord has given rest to your brethren as to you, and they also possess the land which the Lord your God is giving them beyond the Jordan. Then each of you may return to his possession which I have given you.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3021, 'And I commanded Joshua at that time, saying, &lsquo;Your eyes have seen all that the Lord your God has done to these two kings; so will the Lord do to all the kingdoms through which you pass. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3022, 'You must not fear them, for the Lord your God Himself fights for you.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3023, 'Then I pleaded with the Lord at that time, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3024, '&rsquo;O Lord God, You have begun to show Your servant Your greatness and Your mighty hand, for what god is there in heaven or on earth who can do anything like Your works and Your mighty deeds? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3025, 'I pray, let me cross over and see the good land beyond the Jordan, those pleasant mountains, and Lebanon.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3026, 'But the Lord was angry with me on your account, and would not listen to me. So the Lord said to me: &lsquo;Enough of that! Speak no more to Me of this matter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3027, 'Go up to the top of Pisgah, and lift your eyes toward the west, the north, the south, and the east; behold it with your eyes, for you shall not cross over this Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3028, 'But command Joshua, and encourage him and strengthen him; for he shall go over before this people, and he shall cause them to inherit the land which you will see.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 3029, 'So we stayed in the valley opposite Beth Peor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4001, 'Now, O Israel, listen to the statutes and the judgments which I teach you to observe, that you may live, and go in and possess the land which the Lord God of your fathers is giving you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4002, 'You shall not add to the word which I command you, nor take from it, that you may keep the commandments of the Lord your God which I command you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4003, 'Your eyes have seen what the Lord did at Baal Peor; for the Lord your God has destroyed from among you all the men who followed Baal of Peor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4004, 'But you who held fast to the Lord your God are alive today, every one of you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4005, 'Surely I have taught you statutes and judgments, just as the Lord my God commanded me, that you should act according to them in the land which you go to possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4006, 'Therefore be careful to observe them; for this is your wisdom and your understanding in the sight of the peoples who will hear all these statutes, and say, &lsquo;Surely this great nation is a wise and understanding people.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4007, 'For what great nation is there that has God so near to it, as the Lord our God is to us, for whatever reason we may call upon Him? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4008, 'And what great nation is there that has such statutes and righteous judgments as are in all this law which I set before you this day? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4009, 'Only take heed to yourself, and diligently keep yourself, lest you forget the things your eyes have seen, and lest they depart from your heart all the days of your life. And teach them to your children and your grandchildren, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4010, 'especially concerning the day you stood before the Lord your God in Horeb, when the Lord said to me, &lsquo;Gather the people to Me, and I will let them hear My words, that they may learn to fear Me all the days they live on the earth, and that they may teach their children.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4011, 'Then you came near and stood at the foot of the mountain, and the mountain burned with fire to the midst of heaven, with darkness, cloud, and thick darkness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4012, 'And the Lord spoke to you out of the midst of the fire. You heard the sound of the words, but saw no form; you only heard a voice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4013, 'So He declared to you His covenant which He commanded you to perform, the Ten Commandments; and He wrote them on two tablets of stone. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4014, 'And the Lord commanded me at that time to teach you statutes and judgments, that you might observe them in the land which you cross over to possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4015, 'Take careful heed to yourselves, for you saw no form when the Lord spoke to you at Horeb out of the midst of the fire, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4016, 'lest you act corruptly and make for yourselves a carved image in the form of any figure: the likeness of male or female, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4017, 'the likeness of any animal that is on the earth or the likeness of any winged bird that flies in the air, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4018, 'the likeness of anything that creeps on the ground or the likeness of any fish that is in the water beneath the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4019, 'And take heed, lest you lift your eyes to heaven, and when you see the sun, the moon, and the stars, all the host of heaven, you feel driven to worship them and serve them, which the Lord your God has given to all the peoples under the whole heaven as a heritage. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4020, 'But the Lord has taken you and brought you out of the iron furnace, out of Egypt, to be His people, an inheritance, as you are this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4021, 'Furthermore the Lord was angry with me for your sakes, and swore that I would not cross over the Jordan, and that I would not enter the good land which the Lord your God is giving you as an inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4022, 'But I must die in this land, I must not cross over the Jordan; but you shall cross over and possess that good land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4023, 'Take heed to yourselves, lest you forget the covenant of the Lord your God which He made with you, and make for yourselves a carved image in the form of anything which the Lord your God has forbidden you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4024, 'For the Lord your God is a consuming fire, a jealous God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4025, 'When you beget children and grandchildren and have grown old in the land, and act corruptly and make a carved image in the form of anything, and do evil in the sight of the Lord your God to provoke Him to anger, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4026, 'I call heaven and earth to witness against you this day, that you will soon utterly perish from the land which you cross over the Jordan to possess; you will not prolong your days in it, but will be utterly destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4027, 'And the Lord will scatter you among the peoples, and you will be left few in number among the nations where the Lord will drive you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4028, 'And there you will serve gods, the work of men&rsquo;s hands, wood and stone, which neither see nor hear nor eat nor smell. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4029, 'But from there you will seek the Lord your God, and you will find Him if you seek Him with all your heart and with all your soul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4030, 'When you are in distress, and all these things come upon you in the latter days, when you turn to the Lord your God and obey His voice ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4031, '(for the Lord your God is a merciful God), He will not forsake you nor destroy you, nor forget the covenant of your fathers which He swore to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4032, 'For ask now concerning the days that are past, which were before you, since the day that God created man on the earth, and ask from one end of heaven to the other, whether any great thing like this has happened, or anything like it has been heard. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4033, 'Did any people ever hear the voice of God speaking out of the midst of the fire, as you have heard, and live? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4034, 'Or did God ever try to go and take for Himself a nation from the midst of another nation, by trials, by signs, by wonders, by war, by a mighty hand and an outstretched arm, and by great terrors, according to all that the Lord your God did for you in Egypt before your eyes? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4035, 'To you it was shown, that you might know that the Lord Himself is God; there is none other besides Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4036, 'Out of heaven He let you hear His voice, that He might instruct you; on earth He showed you His great fire, and you heard His words out of the midst of the fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4037, 'And because He loved your fathers, therefore He chose their descendants after them; and He brought you out of Egypt with His Presence, with His mighty power, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4038, 'driving out from before you nations greater and mightier than you, to bring you in, to give you their land as an inheritance, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4039, 'Therefore know this day, and consider it in your heart, that the Lord Himself is God in heaven above and on the earth beneath; there is no other. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4040, 'You shall therefore keep His statutes and His commandments which I command you today, that it may go well with you and with your children after you, and that you may prolong your days in the land which the Lord your God is giving you for all time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4041, 'Then Moses set apart three cities on this side of the Jordan, toward the rising of the sun, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4042, 'that the manslayer might flee there, who kills his neighbor unintentionally, without having hated him in time past, and that by fleeing to one of these cities he might live: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4043, 'Bezer in the wilderness on the plateau for the Reubenites, Ramoth in Gilead for the Gadites, and Golan in Bashan for the Manassites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4044, 'Now this is the law which Moses set before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4045, 'These are the testimonies, the statutes, and the judgments which Moses spoke to the children of Israel after they came out of Egypt, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4046, 'on this side of the Jordan, in the valley opposite Beth Peor, in the land of Sihon king of the Amorites, who dwelt at Heshbon, whom Moses and the children of Israel defeated after they came out of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4047, 'And they took possession of his land and the land of Og king of Bashan, two kings of the Amorites, who were on this side of the Jordan, toward the rising of the sun, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4048, 'from Aroer, which is on the bank of the River Arnon, even to Mount Sion (that is, Hermon), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 4049, 'and all the plain on the east side of the Jordan as far as the Sea of the Arabah, below the slopes of Pisgah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5001, 'And Moses called all Israel, and said to them: &ldquo;Hear, O Israel, the statutes and judgments which I speak in your hearing today, that you may learn them and be careful to observe them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5002, 'The Lord our God made a covenant with us in Horeb. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5003, 'The Lord did not make this covenant with our fathers, but with us, those who are here today, all of us who are alive. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5004, 'The Lord talked with you face to face on the mountain from the midst of the fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5005, 'I stood between the Lord and you at that time, to declare to you the word of the Lord; for you were afraid because of the fire, and you did not go up the mountain. He said: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5006, '&rsquo;I am the Lord your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of bondage. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5007, '&rsquo;You shall have no other gods before Me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5008, '&rsquo;You shall not make for yourself a carved image &ndash; any likeness of anything that is in heaven above, or that is in the earth beneath, or that is in the water under the earth; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5009, 'you shall not bow down to them nor serve them. For I, the Lord your God, am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children to the third and fourth generations of those who hate Me, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5010, 'but showing mercy to thousands, to those who love Me and keep My commandments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5011, '&rsquo;You shall not take the name of the Lord your God in vain, for the Lord will not hold him guiltless who takes His name in vain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5012, '&rsquo;Observe the Sabbath day, to keep it holy, as the Lord your God commanded you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5013, 'Six days you shall labor and do all your work, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5014, 'but the seventh day is the Sabbath of the Lord your God. In it you shall do no work: you, nor your son, nor your daughter, nor your male servant, nor your female servant, nor your ox, nor your donkey, nor any of your cattle, nor your stranger who is within your gates, that your male servant and your female servant may rest as well as you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5015, 'And remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and the Lord your God brought you out from there by a mighty hand and by an outstretched arm; therefore the Lord your God commanded you to keep the Sabbath day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5016, '&rsquo;Honor your father and your mother, as the Lord your God has commanded you, that your days may be long, and that it may be well with you in the land which the Lord your God is giving you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5017, '&rsquo;You shall not murder. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5018, '&rsquo;You shall not commit adultery. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5019, '&rsquo;You shall not steal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5020, '&rsquo;You shall not bear false witness against your neighbor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5021, '&rsquo;You shall not covet your neighbor&rsquo;s wife; and you shall not desire your neighbor&rsquo;s house, his field, his male servant, his female servant, his ox, his donkey, or anything that is your neighbor&rsquo;s.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5022, 'These words the Lord spoke to all your assembly, in the mountain from the midst of the fire, the cloud, and the thick darkness, with a loud voice; and He added no more. And He wrote them on two tablets of stone and gave them to me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5023, 'So it was, when you heard the voice from the midst of the darkness, while the mountain was burning with fire, that you came near to me, all the heads of your tribes and your elders. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5024, 'And you said: &lsquo;Surely the Lord our God has shown us His glory and His greatness, and we have heard His voice from the midst of the fire. We have seen this day that God speaks with man; yet he still lives. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5025, 'Now therefore, why should we die? For this great fire will consume us; if we hear the voice of the Lord our God anymore, then we shall die. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5026, 'For who is there of all flesh who has heard the voice of the living God speaking from the midst of the fire, as we have, and lived? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5027, 'You go near and hear all that the Lord our God may say, and tell us all that the Lord our God says to you, and we will hear and do it.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5028, 'Then the Lord heard the voice of your words when you spoke to me, and the Lord said to me: &lsquo;I have heard the voice of the words of this people which they have spoken to you. They are right in all that they have spoken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5029, 'Oh, that they had such a heart in them that they would fear Me and always keep all My commandments, that it might be well with them and with their children forever! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5030, 'Go and say to them, &ldquo;Return to your tents.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5031, 'But as for you, stand here by Me, and I will speak to you all the commandments, the statutes, and the judgments which you shall teach them, that they may observe them in the land which I am giving them to possess.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5032, 'Therefore you shall be careful to do as the Lord your God has commanded you; you shall not turn aside to the right hand or to the left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 5033, 'You shall walk in all the ways which the Lord your God has commanded you, that you may live and that it may be well with you, and that you may prolong your days in the land which you shall possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6001, 'Now this is the commandment, and these are the statutes and judgments which the Lord your God has commanded to teach you, that you may observe them in the land which you are crossing over to possess, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6002, 'that you may fear the Lord your God, to keep all His statutes and His commandments which I command you, you and your son and your grandson, all the days of your life, and that your days may be prolonged. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6003, 'Therefore hear, O Israel, and be careful to observe it, that it may be well with you, and that you may multiply greatly as the Lord God of your fathers has promised you &ndash; &rsquo;a land flowing with milk and honey.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6004, 'Hear, O Israel: The Lord our God, the Lord is one! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6005, 'You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your strength. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6006, 'And these words which I command you today shall be in your heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6007, 'You shall teach them diligently to your children, and shall talk of them when you sit in your house, when you walk by the way, when you lie down, and when you rise up. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6008, 'You shall bind them as a sign on your hand, and they shall be as frontlets between your eyes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6009, 'You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6010, 'So it shall be, when the Lord your God brings you into the land of which He swore to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, to give you large and beautiful cities which you did not build, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6011, 'houses full of all good things, which you did not fill, hewn-out wells which you did not dig, vineyards and olive trees which you did not plant &ndash; when you have eaten and are full &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6012, 'then beware, lest you forget the Lord who brought you out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6013, 'You shall fear the Lord your God and serve Him, and shall take oaths in His name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6014, 'You shall not go after other gods, the gods of the peoples who are all around you ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6015, '(for the Lord your God is a jealous God among you), lest the anger of the Lord your God be aroused against you and destroy you from the face of the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6016, 'You shall not tempt the Lord your God as you tempted Him in Massah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6017, 'You shall diligently keep the commandments of the Lord your God, His testimonies, and His statutes which He has commanded you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6018, 'And you shall do what is right and good in the sight of the Lord, that it may be well with you, and that you may go in and possess the good land of which the Lord swore to your fathers, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6019, 'to cast out all your enemies from before you, as the Lord has spoken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6020, 'When your son asks you in time to come, saying, &lsquo;What is the meaning of the testimonies, the statutes, and the judgments which the Lord our God has commanded you?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6021, 'then you shall say to your son: &lsquo;We were slaves of Pharaoh in Egypt, and the Lord brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6022, 'and the Lord showed signs and wonders before our eyes, great and severe, against Egypt, Pharaoh, and all his household. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6023, 'Then He brought us out from there, that He might bring us in, to give us the land of which He swore to our fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6024, 'And the Lord commanded us to observe all these statutes, to fear the Lord our God, for our good always, that He might preserve us alive, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 6025, 'Then it will be righteousness for us, if we are careful to observe all these commandments before the Lord our God, as He has commanded us.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7001, 'When the Lord your God brings you into the land which you go to possess, and has cast out many nations before you, the Hittites and the Girgashites and the Amorites and the Canaanites and the Perizzites and the Hivites and the Jebusites, seven nations greater and mightier than you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7002, 'and when the Lord your God delivers them over to you, you shall conquer them and utterly destroy them. You shall make no covenant with them nor show mercy to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7003, 'Nor shall you make marriages with them. You shall not give your daughter to their son, nor take their daughter for your son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7004, 'For they will turn your sons away from following Me, to serve other gods; so the anger of the Lord will be aroused against you and destroy you suddenly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7005, 'But thus you shall deal with them: you shall destroy their altars, and break down their sacred pillars, and cut down their wooden images, and burn their carved images with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7006, 'For you are a holy people to the Lord your God; the Lord your God has chosen you to be a people for Himself, a special treasure above all the peoples on the face of the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7007, 'The Lord did not set His love on you nor choose you because you were more in number than any other people, for you were the least of all peoples; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7008, 'but because the Lord loves you, and because He would keep the oath which He swore to your fathers, the Lord has brought you out with a mighty hand, and redeemed you from the house of bondage, from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7009, 'Therefore know that the Lord your God, He is God, the faithful God who keeps covenant and mercy for a thousand generations with those who love Him and keep His commandments; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7010, 'and He repays those who hate Him to their face, to destroy them. He will not be slack with him who hates Him; He will repay him to his face. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7011, 'Therefore you shall keep the commandment, the statutes, and the judgments which I command you today, to observe them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7012, 'Then it shall come to pass, because you listen to these judgments, and keep and do them, that the Lord your God will keep with you the covenant and the mercy which He swore to your fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7013, 'And He will love you and bless you and multiply you; He will also bless the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your land, your grain and your new wine and your oil, the increase of your cattle and the offspring of your flock, in the land of which He swore to your fathers to give you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7014, 'You shall be blessed above all peoples; there shall not be a male or female barren among you or among your livestock. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7015, 'And the Lord will take away from you all sickness, and will afflict you with none of the terrible diseases of Egypt which you have known, but will lay them on all those who hate you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7016, 'And you shall destroy all the peoples whom the Lord your God delivers over to you; your eye shall have no pity on them; nor shall you serve their gods, for that will be a snare to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7017, 'If you should say in your heart, &lsquo;These nations are greater than I; how can I dispossess them?&rsquo; &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7018, 'you shall not be afraid of them, but you shall remember well what the Lord your God did to Pharaoh and to all Egypt: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7019, 'the great trials which your eyes saw, the signs and the wonders, the mighty hand and the outstretched arm, by which the Lord your God brought you out. So shall the Lord your God do to all the peoples of whom you are afraid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7020, 'Moreover the Lord your God will send the hornet among them until those who are left, who hide themselves from you, are destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7021, 'You shall not be terrified of them; for the Lord your God, the great and awesome God, is among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7022, 'And the Lord your God will drive out those nations before you little by little; you will be unable to destroy them at once, lest the beasts of the field become too numerous for you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7023, 'But the Lord your God will deliver them over to you, and will inflict defeat upon them until they are destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7024, 'And He will deliver their kings into your hand, and you will destroy their name from under heaven; no one shall be able to stand against you until you have destroyed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7025, 'You shall burn the carved images of their gods with fire; you shall not covet the silver or gold that is on them, nor take it for yourselves, lest you be snared by it; for it is an abomination to the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 7026, 'Nor shall you bring an abomination into your house, lest you be doomed to destruction like it. You shall utterly detest it and utterly abhor it, for it is an accursed thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8001, 'Every commandment which I command you today you must be careful to observe, that you may live and multiply, and go in and possess the land of which the Lord swore to your fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8002, 'And you shall remember that the Lord your God led you all the way these forty years in the wilderness, to humble you and test you, to know what was in your heart, whether you would keep His commandments or not. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8003, 'So He humbled you, allowed you to hunger, and fed you with manna which you did not know nor did your fathers know, that He might make you know that man shall not live by bread alone; but man lives by every word that proceeds from the mouth of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8004, 'Your garments did not wear out on you, nor did your foot swell these forty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8005, 'You should know in your heart that as a man chastens his son, so the Lord your God chastens you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8006, 'Therefore you shall keep the commandments of the Lord your God, to walk in His ways and to fear Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8007, 'For the Lord your God is bringing you into a good land, a land of brooks of water, of fountains and springs, that flow out of valleys and hills; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8008, 'a land of wheat and barley, of vines and fig trees and pomegranates, a land of olive oil and honey; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8009, 'a land in which you will eat bread without scarcity, in which you will lack nothing; a land whose stones are iron and out of whose hills you can dig copper. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8010, 'When you have eaten and are full, then you shall bless the Lord your God for the good land which He has given you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8011, 'Beware that you do not forget the Lord your God by not keeping His commandments, His judgments, and His statutes which I command you today, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8012, 'lest &ndash; when you have eaten and are full, and have built beautiful houses and dwell in them; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8013, 'and when your herds and your flocks multiply, and your silver and your gold are multiplied, and all that you have is multiplied; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8014, 'when your heart is lifted up, and you forget the Lord your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8015, 'who led you through that great and terrible wilderness, in which were fiery serpents and scorpions and thirsty land where there was no water; who brought water for you out of the flinty rock; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8016, 'who fed you in the wilderness with manna, which your fathers did not know, that He might humble you and that He might test you, to do you good in the end &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8017, 'then you say in your heart, &lsquo;My power and the might of my hand have gained me this wealth.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8018, 'And you shall remember the Lord your God, for it is He who gives you power to get wealth, that He may establish His covenant which He swore to your fathers, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8019, 'Then it shall be, if you by any means forget the Lord your God, and follow other gods, and serve them and worship them, I testify against you this day that you shall surely perish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 8020, 'As the nations which the Lord destroys before you, so you shall perish, because you would not be obedient to the voice of the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9001, 'Hear, O Israel: You are to cross over the Jordan today, and go in to dispossess nations greater and mightier than yourself, cities great and fortified up to heaven, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9002, 'a people great and tall, the descendants of the Anakim, whom you know, and of whom you heard it said, &lsquo;Who can stand before the descendants of Anak?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9003, 'Therefore understand today that the Lord your God is He who goes over before you as a consuming fire. He will destroy them and bring them down before you; so you shall drive them out and destroy them quickly, as the Lord has said to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9004, 'Do not think in your heart, after the Lord your God has cast them out before you, saying, &lsquo;Because of my righteousness the Lord has brought me in to possess this land&rsquo;; but it is because of the wickedness of these nations that the Lord is driving them out from before you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9005, 'It is not because of your righteousness or the uprightness of your heart that you go in to possess their land, but because of the wickedness of these nations that the Lord your God drives them out from before you, and that He may fulfill the word which the Lord swore to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9006, 'Therefore understand that the Lord your God is not giving you this good land to possess because of your righteousness, for you are a stiff-necked people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9007, 'Remember. Do not forget how you provoked the Lord your God to wrath in the wilderness. From the day that you departed from the land of Egypt until you came to this place, you have been rebellious against the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9008, 'Also in Horeb you provoked the Lord to wrath, so that the Lord was angry enough with you to have destroyed you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9009, 'When I went up into the mountain to receive the tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant which the Lord made with you, then I stayed on the mountain forty days and forty nights. I neither ate bread nor drank water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9010, 'Then the Lord delivered to me two tablets of stone written with the finger of God, and on them were all the words which the Lord had spoken to you on the mountain from the midst of the fire in the day of the assembly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9011, 'And it came to pass, at the end of forty days and forty nights, that the Lord gave me the two tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9012, 'Then the Lord said to me, &lsquo;Arise, go down quickly from here, for your people whom you brought out of Egypt have acted corruptly; they have quickly turned aside from the way which I commanded them; they have made themselves a molded image.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9013, 'Furthermore the Lord spoke to me, saying, &lsquo;I have seen this people, and indeed they are a stiff-necked people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9014, 'Let Me alone, that I may destroy them and blot out their name from under heaven; and I will make of you a nation mightier and greater than they.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9015, 'So I turned and came down from the mountain, and the mountain burned with fire; and the two tablets of the covenant were in my two hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9016, 'And I looked, and behold, you had sinned against the Lord your God &ndash; had made for yourselves a molded calf! You had turned aside quickly from the way which the Lord had commanded you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9017, 'Then I took the two tablets and threw them out of my two hands and broke them before your eyes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9018, 'And I fell down before the Lord, as at the first, forty days and forty nights; I neither ate bread nor drank water, because of all your sin which you committed in doing wickedly in the sight of the Lord, to provoke Him to anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9019, 'For I was afraid of the anger and hot displeasure with which the Lord was angry with you, to destroy you. But the Lord listened to me at that time also. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9020, 'And the Lord was very angry with Aaron and would have destroyed him; so I prayed for Aaron also at the same time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9021, 'Then I took your sin, the calf which you had made, and burned it with fire and crushed it and ground it very small, until it was as fine as dust; and I threw its dust into the brook that descended from the mountain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9022, 'Also at Taberah and Massah and Kibroth Hattaavah you provoked the Lord to wrath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9023, 'Likewise, when the Lord sent you from Kadesh Barnea, saying, &lsquo;Go up and possess the land which I have given you,&rsquo; then you rebelled against the commandment of the Lord your God, and you did not believe Him nor obey His voice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9024, 'You have been rebellious against the Lord from the day that I knew you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9025, 'Thus I prostrated myself before the Lord; forty days and forty nights I kept prostrating myself, because the Lord had said He would destroy you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9026, 'Therefore I prayed to the Lord, and said: &lsquo;O Lord God, do not destroy Your people and Your inheritance whom You have redeemed through Your greatness, whom You have brought out of Egypt with a mighty hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9027, 'Remember Your servants, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob; do not look on the stubbornness of this people, or on their wickedness or their sin, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9028, 'lest the land from which You brought us should say, Because the Lord was not able to bring them to the land which He promised them, and because He hated them, He has brought them out to kill them in the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 9029, 'Yet they are Your people and Your inheritance, whom You brought out by Your mighty power and by Your outstretched arm.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10001, 'At that time the Lord said to me, &lsquo;Hew for yourself two tablets of stone like the first, and come up to Me on the mountain and make yourself an ark of wood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10002, 'And I will write on the tablets the words that were on the first tablets, which you broke; and you shall put them in the ark.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10003, 'So I made an ark of acacia wood, hewed two tablets of stone like the first, and went up the mountain, having the two tablets in my hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10004, 'And He wrote on the tablets according to the first writing, the Ten Commandments, which the Lord had spoken to you in the mountain from the midst of the fire in the day of the assembly; and the Lord gave them to me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10005, 'Then I turned and came down from the mountain, and put the tablets in the ark which I had made; and there they are, just as the Lord commanded me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10006, '(Now the children of Israel journeyed from the wells of Bene Jaakan to Moserah, where Aaron died, and where he was buried; and Eleazar his son ministered as priest in his stead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10007, 'From there they journeyed to Gudgodah, and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah, a land of rivers of water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10008, 'At that time the Lord separated the tribe of Levi to bear the ark of the covenant of the Lord, to stand before the Lord to minister to Him and to bless in His name, to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10009, 'Therefore Levi has no portion nor inheritance with his brethren; the Lord is his inheritance, just as the Lord your God promised him.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10010, 'As at the first time, I stayed in the mountain forty days and forty nights; the Lord also heard me at that time, and the Lord chose not to destroy you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10011, 'Then the Lord said to me, &lsquo;Arise, begin your journey before the people, that they may go in and possess the land which I swore to their fathers to give them.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10012, 'And now, Israel, what does the Lord your God require of you, but to fear the Lord your God, to walk in all His ways and to love Him, to serve the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10013, 'and to keep the commandments of the Lord and His statutes which I command you today for your good? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10014, 'Indeed heaven and the highest heavens belong to the Lord your God, also the earth with all that is in it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10015, 'The Lord delighted only in your fathers, to love them; and He chose their descendants after them, you above all peoples, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10016, 'Therefore circumcise the foreskin of your heart, and be stiff-necked no longer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10017, 'For the Lord your God is God of gods and Lord of lords, the great God, mighty and awesome, who shows no partiality nor takes a bribe. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10018, 'He administers justice for the fatherless and the widow, and loves the stranger, giving him food and clothing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10019, 'Therefore love the stranger, for you were strangers in the land of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10020, 'You shall fear the Lord your God; you shall serve Him, and to Him you shall hold fast, and take oaths in His name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10021, 'He is your praise, and He is your God, who has done for you these great and awesome things which your eyes have seen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 10022, 'Your fathers went down to Egypt with seventy persons, and now the Lord your God has made you as the stars of heaven in multitude. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11001, 'Therefore you shall love the Lord your God, and keep His charge, His statutes, His judgments, and His commandments always. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11002, 'Know today that I do not speak with your children, who have not known and who have not seen the chastening of the Lord your God, His greatness and His mighty hand and His outstretched arm &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11003, 'His signs and His acts which He did in the midst of Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt, and to all his land; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11004, 'what He did to the army of Egypt, to their horses and their chariots: how He made the waters of the Red Sea overflow them as they pursued you, and how the Lord has destroyed them to this day; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11005, 'what He did for you in the wilderness until you came to this place; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11006, 'and what He did to Dathan and Abiram the sons of Eliab, the son of Reuben: how the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up, their households, their tents, and all the substance that was in their possession, in the midst of all Israel &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11007, 'but your eyes have seen every great act of the Lord which He did. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11008, 'Therefore you shall keep every commandment which I command you today, that you may be strong, and go in and possess the land which you cross over to possess, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11009, 'and that you may prolong your days in the land which the Lord swore to give your fathers, to them and their descendants, &lsquo;a land flowing with milk and honey.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11010, 'For the land which you go to possess is not like the land of Egypt from which you have come, where you sowed your seed and watered it by foot, as a vegetable garden; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11011, 'but the land which you cross over to possess is a land of hills and valleys, which drinks water from the rain of heaven, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11012, 'a land for which the Lord your God cares; the eyes of the Lord your God are always on it, from the beginning of the year to the very end of the year. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11013, '&rsquo;And it shall be that if you earnestly obey My commandments which I command you today, to love the Lord your God and serve Him with all your heart and with all your soul, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11014, 'then I will give you the rain for your land in its season, the early rain and the latter rain, that you may gather in your grain, your new wine, and your oil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11015, 'And I will send grass in your fields for your livestock, that you may eat and be filled.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11016, 'Take heed to yourselves, lest your heart be deceived, and you turn aside and serve other gods and worship them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11017, 'lest the Lord&rsquo;s anger be aroused against you, and He shut up the heavens so that there be no rain, and the land yield no produce, and you perish quickly from the good land which the Lord is giving you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11018, 'Therefore you shall lay up these words of mine in your heart and in your soul, and bind them as a sign on your hand, and they shall be as frontlets between your eyes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11019, 'You shall teach them to your children, speaking of them when you sit in your house, when you walk by the way, when you lie down, and when you rise up.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11020, 'And you shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11021, 'that your days and the days of your children may be multiplied in the land of which the Lord swore to your fathers to give them, like the days of the heavens above the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11022, 'For if you carefully keep all these commandments which I command you to do &ndash; to love the Lord your God, to walk in all His ways, and to hold fast to Him &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11023, 'then the Lord will drive out all these nations from before you, and you will dispossess greater and mightier nations than yourselves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11024, 'Every place on which the sole of your foot treads shall be yours: from the wilderness and Lebanon, from the river, the River Euphrates, even to the Western Sea, shall be your territory. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11025, 'No man shall be able to stand against you; the Lord your God will put the dread of you and the fear of you upon all the land where you tread, just as He has said to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11026, 'Behold, I set before you today a blessing and a curse: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11027, 'the blessing, if you obey the commandments of the Lord your God which I command you today; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11028, 'and the curse, if you do not obey the commandments of the Lord your God, but turn aside from the way which I command you today, to go after other gods which you have not known. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11029, 'Now it shall be, when the Lord your God has brought you into the land which you go to possess, that you shall put the blessing on Mount Gerizim and the curse on Mount Ebal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11030, 'Are they not on the other side of the Jordan, toward the setting sun, in the land of the Canaanites who dwell in the plain opposite Gilgal, beside the terebinth trees of Moreh? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11031, 'For you will cross over the Jordan and go in to possess the land which the Lord your God is giving you, and you will possess it and dwell in it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 11032, 'And you shall be careful to observe all the statutes and judgments which I set before you today. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12001, 'These are the statutes and judgments which you shall be careful to observe in the land which the Lord God of your fathers is giving you to possess, all the days that you live on the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12002, 'You shall utterly destroy all the places where the nations which you shall dispossess served their gods, on the high mountains and on the hills and under every green tree. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12003, 'And you shall destroy their altars, break their sacred pillars, and burn their wooden images with fire; you shall cut down the carved images of their gods and destroy their names from that place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12004, 'You shall not worship the Lord your God with such things. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12005, 'But you shall seek the place where the Lord your God chooses, out of all your tribes, to put His name for His dwelling place; and there you shall go. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12006, 'There you shall take your burnt offerings, your sacrifices, your tithes, the heave offerings of your hand, your vowed offerings, your freewill offerings, and the firstborn of your herds and flocks. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12007, 'And there you shall eat before the Lord your God, and you shall rejoice in all to which you have put your hand, you and your households, in which the Lord your God has blessed you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12008, 'You shall not at all do as we are doing here today &ndash; every man doing whatever is right in his own eyes &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12009, 'for as yet you have not come to the rest and the inheritance which the Lord your God is giving you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12010, 'But when you cross over the Jordan and dwell in the land which the Lord your God is giving you to inherit, and He gives you rest from all your enemies round about, so that you dwell in safety, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12011, 'then there will be the place where the Lord your God chooses to make His name abide. There you shall bring all that I command you: your burnt offerings, your sacrifices, your tithes, the heave offerings of your hand, and all your choice offerings which you vow to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12012, 'And you shall rejoice before the Lord your God, you and your sons and your daughters, your male and female servants, and the Levite who is within your gates, since he has no portion nor inheritance with you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12013, 'Take heed to yourself that you do not offer your burnt offerings in every place that you see; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12014, 'but in the place which the Lord chooses, in one of your tribes, there you shall offer your burnt offerings, and there you shall do all that I command you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12015, 'However, you may slaughter and eat meat within all your gates, whatever your heart desires, according to the blessing of the Lord your God which He has given you; the unclean and the clean may eat of it, of the gazelle and the deer alike. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12016, 'Only you shall not eat the blood; you shall pour it on the earth like water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12017, 'You may not eat within your gates the tithe of your grain or your new wine or your oil, of the firstborn of your herd or your flock, of any of your offerings which you vow, of your freewill offerings, or of the heave offering of your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12018, 'But you must eat them before the Lord your God in the place which the Lord your God chooses, you and your son and your daughter, your male servant and your female servant, and the Levite who is within your gates; and you shall rejoice before the Lord your God in all to which you put your hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12019, 'Take heed to yourself that you do not forsake the Levite as long as you live in your land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12020, 'When the Lord your God enlarges your border as He has promised you, and you say, &lsquo;Let me eat meat,&rsquo; because you long to eat meat, you may eat as much meat as your heart desires. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12021, 'If the place where the Lord your God chooses to put His name is too far from you, then you may slaughter from your herd and from your flock which the Lord has given you, just as I have commanded you, and you may eat within your gates as much as your heart desires. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12022, 'Just as the gazelle and the deer are eaten, so you may eat them; the unclean and the clean alike may eat them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12023, 'Only be sure that you do not eat the blood, for the blood is the life; you may not eat the life with the meat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12024, 'You shall not eat it; you shall pour it on the earth like water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12025, 'You shall not eat it, that it may go well with you and your children after you, when you do what is right in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12026, 'Only the holy things which you have, and your vowed offerings, you shall take and go to the place which the Lord chooses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12027, 'And you shall offer your burnt offerings, the meat and the blood, on the altar of the Lord your God; and the blood of your sacrifices shall be poured out on the altar of the Lord your God, and you shall eat the meat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12028, 'Observe and obey all these words which I command you, that it may go well with you and your children after you forever, when you do what is good and right in the sight of the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12029, 'When the Lord your God cuts off from before you the nations which you go to dispossess, and you displace them and dwell in their land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12030, 'take heed to yourself that you are not ensnared to follow them, after they are destroyed from before you, and that you do not inquire after their gods, saying, &lsquo;How did these nations serve their gods? I also will do likewise.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12031, 'You shall not worship the Lord your God in that way; for every abomination to the Lord which He hates they have done to their gods; for they burn even their sons and daughters in the fire to their gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 12032, 'Whatever I command you, be careful to observe it; you shall not add to it nor take away from it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13001, 'If there arises among you a prophet or a dreamer of dreams, and he gives you a sign or a wonder, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13002, 'and the sign or the wonder comes to pass, of which he spoke to you, saying, &lsquo;Let us go after other gods&rsquo; &ndash; which you have not known &ndash; &rsquo;and let us serve them,&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13003, 'you shall not listen to the words of that prophet or that dreamer of dreams, for the Lord your God is testing you to know whether you love the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13004, 'You shall walk after the Lord your God and fear Him, and keep His commandments and obey His voice, and you shall serve Him and hold fast to Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13005, 'But that prophet or that dreamer of dreams shall be put to death, because he has spoken in order to turn you away from the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt and redeemed you from the house of bondage, to entice you from the way in which the Lord your God commanded you to walk. So you shall put away the evil from your midst. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13006, 'If your brother, the son of your mother, your son or your daughter, the wife of your bosom, or your friend who is as your own soul, secretly entices you, saying, &lsquo;Let us go and serve other gods,&rsquo; which you have not known, neither you nor your fathers, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13007, 'of the gods of the people which are all around you, near to you or far off from you, from one end of the earth to the other end of the earth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13008, 'you shall not consent to him or listen to him, nor shall your eye pity him, nor shall you spare him or conceal him; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13009, 'but you shall surely kill him; your hand shall be first against him to put him to death, and afterward the hand of all the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13010, 'And you shall stone him with stones until he dies, because he sought to entice you away from the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13011, 'So all Israel shall hear and fear, and not again do such wickedness as this among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13012, 'If you hear someone in one of your cities, which the Lord your God gives you to dwell in, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13013, '&rsquo;Corrupt men have gone out from among you and enticed the inhabitants of their city, saying, &ldquo;Let us go and serve other gods&rdquo; &lsquo; &ndash; which you have not known &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13014, 'then you shall inquire, search out, and ask diligently. And if it is indeed true and certain that such an abomination was committed among you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13015, 'you shall surely strike the inhabitants of that city with the edge of the sword &ndash; utterly destroying it, all that is in it and its livestock, with the edge of the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13016, 'And you shall gather all its plunder into the middle of the street, and completely burn with fire the city and all its plunder, for the Lord your God. It shall be a heap forever; it shall not be built again. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13017, 'So none of the accursed things shall remain in your hand, that the Lord may turn from the fierceness of His anger and show you mercy, have compassion on you and multiply you, just as He swore to your fathers, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 13018, 'because you have listened to the voice of the Lord your God, to keep all His commandments which I command you today, to do what is right in the eyes of the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14001, 'You are the children of the Lord your God; you shall not cut yourselves nor shave the front of your head for the dead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14002, 'For you are a holy people to the Lord your God, and the Lord has chosen you to be a people for Himself, a special treasure above all the peoples who are on the face of the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14003, 'You shall not eat any detestable thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14004, 'These are the animals which you may eat: the ox, the sheep, the goat, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14005, 'the deer, the gazelle, the roe deer, the wild goat, the mountain goat, the antelope, and the mountain sheep. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14006, 'And you may eat every animal with cloven hooves, having the hoof split into two parts, and that chews the cud, among the animals. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14007, 'Nevertheless, of those that chew the cud or have cloven hooves, you shall not eat, such as these: the camel, the hare, and the rock hyrax; for they chew the cud but do not have cloven hooves; they are unclean for you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14008, 'Also the swine is unclean for you, because it has cloven hooves, yet does not chew the cud; you shall not eat their flesh or touch their dead carcasses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14009, 'These you may eat of all that are in the waters: you may eat all that have fins and scales. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14010, 'And whatever does not have fins and scales you shall not eat; it is unclean for you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14011, 'All clean birds you may eat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14012, 'But these you shall not eat: the eagle, the vulture, the buzzard, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14013, 'the red kite, the falcon, and the kite after their kinds; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14014, 'every raven after its kind; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14015, 'the ostrich, the short-eared owl, the seagull, and the hawk after their kinds; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14016, 'the little owl, the screech owl, the white owl, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14017, 'the jackdaw, the carrion vulture, the fisher owl, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14018, 'the stork, the heron after its kind, and the hoopoe and the bat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14019, 'Also every creeping thing that flies is unclean for you; they shall not be eaten. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14020, 'You may eat all clean birds. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14021, 'You shall not eat anything that dies of itself; you may give it to the alien who is within your gates, that he may eat it, or you may sell it to a foreigner; for you are a holy people to the Lord your God. You shall not boil a young goat in its mother&rsquo;s milk. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14022, 'You shall truly tithe all the increase of your grain that the field produces year by year. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14023, 'And you shall eat before the Lord your God, in the place where He chooses to make His name abide, the tithe of your grain and your new wine and your oil, of the firstborn of your herds and your flocks, that you may learn to fear the Lord your God always. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14024, 'But if the journey is too long for you, so that you are not able to carry the tithe, or if the place where the Lord your God chooses to put His name is too far from you, when the Lord your God has blessed you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14025, 'then you shall exchange it for money, take the money in your hand, and go to the place which the Lord your God chooses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14026, 'And you shall spend that money for whatever your heart desires: for oxen or sheep, for wine or similar drink, for whatever your heart desires; you shall eat there before the Lord your God, and you shall rejoice, you and your household. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14027, 'You shall not forsake the Levite who is within your gates, for he has no part nor inheritance with you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14028, 'At the end of every third year you shall bring out the tithe of your produce of that year and store it up within your gates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 14029, 'And the Levite, because he has no portion nor inheritance with you, and the stranger and the fatherless and the widow who are within your gates, may come and eat and be satisfied, that the Lord your God may bless you in all the work of your hand which you do. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15001, 'At the end of every seven years you shall grant a release of debts. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15002, 'And this is the form of the release: Every creditor who has lent anything to his neighbor shall release it; he shall not require it of his neighbor or his brother, because it is called the Lord&rsquo;s release. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15003, 'Of a foreigner you may require it; but you shall give up your claim to what is owed by your brother, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15004, 'except when there may be no poor among you; for the Lord will greatly bless you in the land which the Lord your God is giving you to possess as an inheritance &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15005, 'only if you carefully obey the voice of the Lord your God, to observe with care all these commandments which I command you today. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15006, 'For the Lord your God will bless you just as He promised you; you shall lend to many nations, but you shall not borrow; you shall reign over many nations, but they shall not reign over you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15007, 'If there is among you a poor man of your brethren, within any of the gates in your land which the Lord your God is giving you, you shall not harden your heart nor shut your hand from your poor brother, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15008, 'but you shall open your hand wide to him and willingly lend him sufficient for his need, whatever he needs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15009, 'Beware lest there be a wicked thought in your heart, saying, &lsquo;The seventh year, the year of release, is at hand,&rsquo; and your eye be evil against your poor brother and you give him nothing, and he cry out to the Lord against you, and it become sin among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15010, 'You shall surely give to him, and your heart should not be grieved when you give to him, because for this thing the Lord your God will bless you in all your works and in all to which you put your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15011, 'For the poor will never cease from the land; therefore I command you, saying, &lsquo;You shall open your hand wide to your brother, to your poor and your needy, in your land.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15012, 'If your brother, a Hebrew man, or a Hebrew woman, is sold to you and serves you six years, then in the seventh year you shall let him go free from you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15013, 'And when you send him away free from you, you shall not let him go away empty-handed; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15014, 'you shall supply him liberally from your flock, from your threshing floor, and from your winepress. From what the Lord has blessed you with, you shall give to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15015, 'You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and the Lord your God redeemed you; therefore I command you this thing today. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15016, 'And if it happens that he says to you, &lsquo;I will not go away from you,&rsquo; because he loves you and your house, since he prospers with you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15017, 'then you shall take an awl and thrust it through his ear to the door, and he shall be your servant forever. Also to your female servant you shall do likewise. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15018, 'It shall not seem hard to you when you send him away free from you; for he has been worth a double hired servant in serving you six years. Then the Lord your God will bless you in all that you do. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15019, 'All the firstborn males that come from your herd and your flock you shall sanctify to the Lord your God; you shall do no work with the firstborn of your herd, nor shear the firstborn of your flock. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15020, 'You and your household shall eat it before the Lord your God year by year in the place which the Lord chooses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15021, 'But if there is a defect in it, if it is lame or blind or has any serious defect, you shall not sacrifice it to the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15022, 'You may eat it within your gates; the unclean and the clean person alike may eat it, as if it were a gazelle or a deer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 15023, 'Only you shall not eat its blood; you shall pour it on the ground like water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16001, 'Observe the month of Abib, and keep the Passover to the Lord your God, for in the month of Abib the Lord your God brought you out of Egypt by night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16002, 'Therefore you shall sacrifice the Passover to the Lord your God, from the flock and the herd, in the place where the Lord chooses to put His name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16003, 'You shall eat no leavened bread with it; seven days you shall eat unleavened bread with it, that is, the bread of affliction (for you came out of the land of Egypt in haste), that you may remember the day in which you came out of the land of Egypt all the days of your life. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16004, 'And no leaven shall be seen among you in all your territory for seven days, nor shall any of the meat which you sacrifice the first day at twilight remain overnight until morning. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16005, 'You may not sacrifice the Passover within any of your gates which the Lord your God gives you; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16006, 'but at the place where the Lord your God chooses to make His name abide, there you shall sacrifice the Passover at twilight, at the going down of the sun, at the time you came out of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16007, 'And you shall roast and eat it in the place which the Lord your God chooses, and in the morning you shall turn and go to your tents. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16008, 'Six days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day there shall be a sacred assembly to the Lord your God. You shall do no work on it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16009, 'You shall count seven weeks for yourself; begin to count the seven weeks from the time you begin to put the sickle to the grain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16010, 'Then you shall keep the Feast of Weeks to the Lord your God with the tribute of a freewill offering from your hand, which you shall give as the Lord your God blesses you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16011, 'You shall rejoice before the Lord your God, you and your son and your daughter, your male servant and your female servant, the Levite who is within your gates, the stranger and the fatherless and the widow who are among you, at the place where the Lord your God chooses to make His name abide. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16012, 'And you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and you shall be careful to observe these statutes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16013, 'You shall observe the Feast of Tabernacles seven days, when you have gathered from your threshing floor and from your winepress. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16014, 'And you shall rejoice in your feast, you and your son and your daughter, your male servant and your female servant and the Levite, the stranger and the fatherless and the widow, who are within your gates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16015, 'Seven days you shall keep a sacred feast to the Lord your God in the place which the Lord chooses, because the Lord your God will bless you in all your produce and in all the work of your hands, so that you surely rejoice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16016, 'Three times a year all your males shall appear before the Lord your God in the place which He chooses: at the Feast of Unleavened Bread, at the Feast of Weeks, and at the Feast of Tabernacles; and they shall not appear before the Lord empty-handed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16017, 'Every man shall give as he is able, according to the blessing of the Lord your God which He has given you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16018, 'You shall appoint judges and officers in all your gates, which the Lord your God gives you, according to your tribes, and they shall judge the people with just judgment. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16019, 'You shall not pervert justice; you shall not show partiality, nor take a bribe, for a bribe blinds the eyes of the wise and twists the words of the righteous. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16020, 'You shall follow what is altogether just, that you may live and inherit the land which the Lord your God is giving you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16021, 'You shall not plant for yourself any tree, as a wooden image, near the altar which you build for yourself to the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 16022, 'You shall not set up a sacred pillar, which the Lord your God hates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17001, 'You shall not sacrifice to the Lord your God a bull or sheep which has any blemish or defect, for that is an abomination to the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17002, 'If there is found among you, within any of your gates which the Lord your God gives you, a man or a woman who has been wicked in the sight of the Lord your God, in transgressing His covenant, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17003, 'who has gone and served other gods and worshiped them, either the sun or moon or any of the host of heaven, which I have not commanded, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17004, 'and it is told you, and you hear of it, then you shall inquire diligently. And if it is indeed true and certain that such an abomination has been committed in Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17005, 'then you shall bring out to your gates that man or woman who has committed that wicked thing, and shall stone to death that man or woman with stones. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17006, 'Whoever is deserving of death shall be put to death on the testimony of two or three witnesses; he shall not be put to death on the testimony of one witness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17007, 'The hands of the witnesses shall be the first against him to put him to death, and afterward the hands of all the people. So you shall put away the evil from among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17008, 'If a matter arises which is too hard for you to judge, between degrees of guilt for bloodshed, between one judgment or another, or between one punishment or another, matters of controversy within your gates, then you shall arise and go up to the place which the Lord your God chooses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17009, 'And you shall come to the priests, the Levites, and to the judge there in those days, and inquire of them; they shall pronounce upon you the sentence of judgment. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17010, 'You shall do according to the sentence which they pronounce upon you in that place which the Lord chooses. And you shall be careful to do according to all that they order you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17011, 'According to the sentence of the law in which they instruct you, according to the judgment which they tell you, you shall do; you shall not turn aside to the right hand or to the left from the sentence which they pronounce upon you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17012, 'Now the man who acts presumptuously and will not heed the priest who stands to minister there before the Lord your God, or the judge, that man shall die. So you shall put away the evil from Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17013, 'And all the people shall hear and fear, and no longer act presumptuously. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17014, 'When you come to the land which the Lord your God is giving you, and possess it and dwell in it, and say, &lsquo;I will set a king over me like all the nations that are around me,&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17015, 'you shall surely set a king over you whom the Lord your God chooses; one from among your brethren you shall set as king over you; you may not set a foreigner over you, who is not your brother. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17016, 'But he shall not multiply horses for himself, nor cause the people to return to Egypt to multiply horses, for the Lord has said to you, &lsquo;You shall not return that way again.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17017, 'Neither shall he multiply wives for himself, lest his heart turn away; nor shall he greatly multiply silver and gold for himself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17018, 'Also it shall be, when he sits on the throne of his kingdom, that he shall write for himself a copy of this law in a book, from the one before the priests, the Levites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17019, 'And it shall be with him, and he shall read it all the days of his life, that he may learn to fear the Lord his God and be careful to observe all the words of this law and these statutes, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 17020, 'that his heart may not be lifted above his brethren, that he may not turn aside from the commandment to the right hand or to the left, and that he may prolong his days in his kingdom, he and his children in the midst of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18001, 'The priests, the Levites &ndash; all the tribe of Levi &ndash; shall have no part nor inheritance with Israel; they shall eat the offerings of the Lord made by fire, and His portion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18002, 'Therefore they shall have no inheritance among their brethren; the Lord is their inheritance, as He said to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18003, 'And this shall be the priest&rsquo;s due from the people, from those who offer a sacrifice, whether it is bull or sheep: they shall give to the priest the shoulder, the cheeks, and the stomach. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18004, 'The firstfruits of your grain and your new wine and your oil, and the first of the fleece of your sheep, you shall give him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18005, 'For the Lord your God has chosen him out of all your tribes to stand to minister in the name of the Lord, him and his sons forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18006, 'So if a Levite comes from any of your gates, from where he dwells among all Israel, and comes with all the desire of his mind to the place which the Lord chooses, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18007, 'then he may serve in the name of the Lord his God as all his brethren the Levites do, who stand there before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18008, 'They shall have equal portions to eat, besides what comes from the sale of his inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18009, 'When you come into the land which the Lord your God is giving you, you shall not learn to follow the abominations of those nations. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18010, 'There shall not be found among you anyone who makes his son or his daughter pass through the fire, or one who practices witchcraft, or a soothsayer, or one who interprets omens, or a sorcerer, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18011, 'or one who conjures spells, or a medium, or a spiritist, or one who calls up the dead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18012, 'For all who do these things are an abomination to the Lord, and because of these abominations the Lord your God drives them out from before you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18013, 'You shall be blameless before the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18014, 'For these nations which you will dispossess listened to soothsayers and diviners; but as for you, the Lord your God has not appointed such for you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18015, 'The Lord your God will raise up for you a Prophet like me from your midst, from your brethren. Him you shall hear, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18016, 'according to all you desired of the Lord your God in Horeb in the day of the assembly, saying, &lsquo;Let me not hear again the voice of the Lord my God, nor let me see this great fire anymore, lest I die.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18017, 'And the Lord said to me: &lsquo;What they have spoken is good. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18018, 'I will raise up for them a Prophet like you from among their brethren, and will put My words in His mouth, and He shall speak to them all that I command Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18019, 'And it shall be that whoever will not hear My words, which He speaks in My name, I will require it of him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18020, 'But the prophet who presumes to speak a word in My name, which I have not commanded him to speak, or who speaks in the name of other gods, that prophet shall die.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18021, 'And if you say in your heart, &lsquo;How shall we know the word which the Lord has not spoken?&rsquo; &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 18022, 'when a prophet speaks in the name of the Lord, if the thing does not happen or come to pass, that is the thing which the Lord has not spoken; the prophet has spoken it presumptuously; you shall not be afraid of him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19001, 'When the Lord your God has cut off the nations whose land the Lord your God is giving you, and you dispossess them and dwell in their cities and in their houses, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19002, 'you shall separate three cities for yourself in the midst of your land which the Lord your God is giving you to possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19003, 'You shall prepare roads for yourself, and divide into three parts the territory of your land which the Lord your God is giving you to inherit, that any manslayer may flee there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19004, 'And this is the case of the manslayer who flees there, that he may live: Whoever kills his neighbor unintentionally, not having hated him in time past &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19005, 'as when a man goes to the woods with his neighbor to cut timber, and his hand swings a stroke with the ax to cut down the tree, and the head slips from the handle and strikes his neighbor so that he dies &ndash; he shall flee to one of these cities and live; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19006, 'lest the avenger of blood, while his anger is hot, pursue the manslayer and overtake him, because the way is long, and kill him, though he was not deserving of death, since he had not hated the victim in time past. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19007, 'Therefore I command you, saying, &lsquo;You shall separate three cities for yourself.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19008, 'Now if the Lord your God enlarges your territory, as He swore to your fathers, and gives you the land which He promised to give to your fathers, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19009, 'and if you keep all these commandments and do them, which I command you today, to love the Lord your God and to walk always in His ways, then you shall add three more cities for yourself besides these three, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19010, 'lest innocent blood be shed in the midst of your land which the Lord your God is giving you as an inheritance, and thus guilt of bloodshed be upon you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19011, 'But if anyone hates his neighbor, lies in wait for him, rises against him and strikes him mortally, so that he dies, and he flees to one of these cities, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19012, 'then the elders of his city shall send and bring him from there, and deliver him over to the hand of the avenger of blood, that he may die. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19013, 'Your eye shall not pity him, but you shall put away the guilt of innocent blood from Israel, that it may go well with you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19014, 'You shall not remove your neighbor&rsquo;s landmark, which the men of old have set, in your inheritance which you will inherit in the land that the Lord your God is giving you to possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19015, 'One witness shall not rise against a man concerning any iniquity or any sin that he commits; by the mouth of two or three witnesses the matter shall be established. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19016, 'If a false witness rises against any man to testify against him of wrongdoing, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19017, 'then both men in the controversy shall stand before the Lord, before the priests and the judges who serve in those days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19018, 'And the judges shall make careful inquiry, and indeed, if the witness is a false witness, who has testified falsely against his brother, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19019, 'then you shall do to him as he thought to have done to his brother; so you shall put away the evil from among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19020, 'And those who remain shall hear and fear, and hereafter they shall not again commit such evil among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 19021, 'Your eye shall not pity: life shall be for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20001, 'When you go out to battle against your enemies, and see horses and chariots and people more numerous than you, do not be afraid of them; for the Lord your God is with you, who brought you up from the land of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20002, 'So it shall be, when you are on the verge of battle, that the priest shall approach and speak to the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20003, 'And he shall say to them, &lsquo;Hear, O Israel: Today you are on the verge of battle with your enemies. Do not let your heart faint, do not be afraid, and do not tremble or be terrified because of them; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20004, 'for the Lord your God is He who goes with you, to fight for you against your enemies, to save you.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20005, 'Then the officers shall speak to the people, saying: &lsquo;What man is there who has built a new house and has not dedicated it? Let him go and return to his house, lest he die in the battle and another man dedicate it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20006, 'Also what man is there who has planted a vineyard and has not eaten of it? Let him go and return to his house, lest he die in the battle and another man eat of it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20007, 'And what man is there who is betrothed to a woman and has not married her? Let him go and return to his house, lest he die in the battle and another man marry her.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20008, 'The officers shall speak further to the people, and say, &lsquo;What man is there who is fearful and fainthearted? Let him go and return to his house, lest the heart of his brethren faint like his heart.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20009, 'And so it shall be, when the officers have finished speaking to the people, that they shall make captains of the armies to lead the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20010, 'When you go near a city to fight against it, then proclaim an offer of peace to it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20011, 'And it shall be that if they accept your offer of peace, and open to you, then all the people who are found in it shall be placed under tribute to you, and serve you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20012, 'Now if the city will not make peace with you, but makes war against you, then you shall besiege it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20013, 'And when the Lord your God delivers it into your hands, you shall strike every male in it with the edge of the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20014, 'But the women, the little ones, the livestock, and all that is in the city, all its spoil, you shall plunder for yourself; and you shall eat the enemies&rsquo; plunder which the Lord your God gives you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20015, 'Thus you shall do to all the cities which are very far from you, which are not of the cities of these nations. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20016, 'But of the cities of these peoples which the Lord your God gives you as an inheritance, you shall let nothing that breathes remain alive, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20017, 'but you shall utterly destroy them: the Hittite and the Amorite and the Canaanite and the Perizzite and the Hivite and the Jebusite, just as the Lord your God has commanded you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20018, 'lest they teach you to do according to all their abominations which they have done for their gods, and you sin against the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20019, 'When you besiege a city for a long time, while making war against it to take it, you shall not destroy its trees by wielding an ax against them; if you can eat of them, do not cut them down to use in the siege, for the tree of the field is man&rsquo;s food. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 20020, 'Only the trees which you know are not trees for food you may destroy and cut down, to build siegeworks against the city that makes war with you, until it is subdued. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21001, 'If anyone is found slain, lying in the field in the land which the Lord your God is giving you to possess, and it is not known who killed him, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21002, 'then your elders and your judges shall go out and measure the distance from the slain man to the surrounding cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21003, 'And it shall be that the elders of the city nearest to the slain man will take a heifer which has not been worked and which has not pulled with a yoke. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21004, 'The elders of that city shall bring the heifer down to a valley with flowing water, which is neither plowed nor sown, and they shall break the heifer&rsquo;s neck there in the valley. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21005, 'Then the priests, the sons of Levi, shall come near, for the Lord your God has chosen them to minister to Him and to bless in the name of the Lord; by their word every controversy and every assault shall be settled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21006, 'And all the elders of that city nearest to the slain man shall wash their hands over the heifer whose neck was broken in the valley. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21007, 'Then they shall answer and say, &lsquo;Our hands have not shed this blood, nor have our eyes seen it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21008, 'Provide atonement, O Lord, for Your people Israel, whom You have redeemed, and do not lay innocent blood to the charge of Your people Israel.&rsquo; And atonement shall be provided on their behalf for the blood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21009, 'So you shall put away the guilt of innocent blood from among you when you do what is right in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21010, 'When you go out to war against your enemies, and the Lord your God delivers them into your hand, and you take them captive, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21011, 'and you see among the captives a beautiful woman, and desire her and would take her for your wife, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21012, 'then you shall bring her home to your house, and she shall shave her head and trim her nails. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21013, 'She shall put off the clothes of her captivity, remain in your house, and mourn her father and her mother a full month; after that you may go in to her and be her husband, and she shall be your wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21014, 'And it shall be, if you have no delight in her, then you shall set her free, but you certainly shall not sell her for money; you shall not treat her brutally, because you have humbled her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21015, 'If a man has two wives, one loved and the other unloved, and they have borne him children, both the loved and the unloved, and if the firstborn son is of her who is unloved, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21016, 'then it shall be, on the day he bequeaths his possessions to his sons, that he must not bestow firstborn status on the son of the loved wife in preference to the son of the unloved, the true firstborn. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21017, 'But he shall acknowledge the son of the unloved wife as the firstborn by giving him a double portion of all that he has, for he is the beginning of his strength; the right of the firstborn is his. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21018, 'If a man has a stubborn and rebellious son who will not obey the voice of his father or the voice of his mother, and who, when they have chastened him, will not heed them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21019, 'then his father and his mother shall take hold of him and bring him out to the elders of his city, to the gate of his city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21020, 'And they shall say to the elders of his city, &lsquo;This son of ours is stubborn and rebellious; he will not obey our voice; he is a glutton and a drunkard.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21021, 'Then all the men of his city shall stone him to death with stones; so you shall put away the evil from among you, and all Israel shall hear and fear. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21022, 'If a man has committed a sin deserving of death, and he is put to death, and you hang him on a tree, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 21023, 'his body shall not remain overnight on the tree, but you shall surely bury him that day, so that you do not defile the land which the Lord your God is giving you as an inheritance; for he who is hanged is accursed of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22001, 'You shall not see your brother&rsquo;s ox or his sheep going astray, and hide yourself from them; you shall certainly bring them back to your brother. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22002, 'And if your brother is not near you, or if you do not know him, then you shall bring it to your own house, and it shall remain with you until your brother seeks it; then you shall restore it to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22003, 'You shall do the same with his donkey, and so shall you do with his garment; with any lost thing of your brother&rsquo;s, which he has lost and you have found, you shall do likewise; you must not hide yourself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22004, 'You shall not see your brother&rsquo;s donkey or his ox fall down along the road, and hide yourself from them; you shall surely help him lift them up again. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22005, 'A woman shall not wear anything that pertains to a man, nor shall a man put on a woman&rsquo;s garment, for all who do so are an abomination to the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22006, 'If a bird&rsquo;s nest happens to be before you along the way, in any tree or on the ground, with young ones or eggs, with the mother sitting on the young or on the eggs, you shall not take the mother with the young; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22007, 'you shall surely let the mother go, and take the young for yourself, that it may be well with you and that you may prolong your days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22008, 'When you build a new house, then you shall make a parapet for your roof, that you may not bring guilt of bloodshed on your household if anyone falls from it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22009, 'You shall not sow your vineyard with different kinds of seed, lest the yield of the seed which you have sown and the fruit of your vineyard be defiled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22010, 'You shall not plow with an ox and a donkey together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22011, 'You shall not wear a garment of different sorts, such as wool and linen mixed together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22012, 'You shall make tassels on the four corners of the clothing with which you cover yourself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22013, 'If any man takes a wife, and goes in to her, and detests her, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22014, 'and charges her with shameful conduct, and brings a bad name on her, and says, &lsquo;I took this woman, and when I came to her I found she was not a virgin,&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22015, 'then the father and mother of the young woman shall take and bring out the evidence of the young woman&rsquo;s virginity to the elders of the city at the gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22016, 'And the young woman&rsquo;s father shall say to the elders, &lsquo;I gave my daughter to this man as wife, and he detests her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22017, 'Now he has charged her with shameful conduct, saying, &ldquo;I found your daughter was not a virgin,&rdquo; and yet these are the evidences of my daughter&rsquo;s virginity.&rsquo; And they shall spread the cloth before the elders of the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22018, 'Then the elders of that city shall take that man and punish him; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22019, 'and they shall fine him one hundred shekels of silver and give them to the father of the young woman, because he has brought a bad name on a virgin of Israel. And she shall be his wife; he cannot divorce her all his days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22020, 'But if the thing is true, and evidences of virginity are not found for the young woman, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22021, 'then they shall bring out the young woman to the door of her father&rsquo;s house, and the men of her city shall stone her to death with stones, because she has done a disgraceful thing in Israel, to play the harlot in her father&rsquo;s house. So you shall put away the evil from among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22022, 'If a man is found lying with a woman married to a husband, then both of them shall die &ndash; the man that lay with the woman, and the woman; so you shall put away the evil from Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22023, 'If a young woman who is a virgin is betrothed to a husband, and a man finds her in the city and lies with her, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22024, 'then you shall bring them both out to the gate of that city, and you shall stone them to death with stones, the young woman because she did not cry out in the city, and the man because he humbled his neighbor&rsquo;s wife; so you shall put away the evil from among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22025, 'But if a man finds a betrothed young woman in the countryside, and the man forces her and lies with her, then only the man who lay with her shall die. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22026, 'But you shall do nothing to the young woman; there is in the young woman no sin deserving of death, for just as when a man rises against his neighbor and kills him, even so is this matter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22027, 'For he found her in the countryside, and the betrothed young woman cried out, but there was no one to save her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22028, 'If a man finds a young woman who is a virgin, who is not betrothed, and he seizes her and lies with her, and they are found out, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22029, 'then the man who lay with her shall give to the young woman&rsquo;s father fifty shekels of silver, and she shall be his wife because he has humbled her; he shall not be permitted to divorce her all his days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 22030, 'A man shall not take his father&rsquo;s wife, nor uncover his father&rsquo;s bed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23001, 'He who is emasculated by crushing or mutilation shall not enter the assembly of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23002, 'One of illegitimate birth shall not enter the assembly of the Lord; even to the tenth generation none of his descendants shall enter the assembly of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23003, 'An Ammonite or Moabite shall not enter the assembly of the Lord; even to the tenth generation none of his descendants shall enter the assembly of the Lord forever, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23004, 'because they did not meet you with bread and water on the road when you came out of Egypt, and because they hired against you Balaam the son of Beor from Pethor of Mesopotamia, to curse you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23005, 'Nevertheless the Lord your God would not listen to Balaam, but the Lord your God turned the curse into a blessing for you, because the Lord your God loves you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23006, 'You shall not seek their peace nor their prosperity all your days forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23007, 'You shall not abhor an Edomite, for he is your brother. You shall not abhor an Egyptian, because you were an alien in his land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23008, 'The children of the third generation born to them may enter the assembly of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23009, 'When the army goes out against your enemies, then keep yourself from every wicked thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23010, 'If there is any man among you who becomes unclean by some occurrence in the night, then he shall go outside the camp; he shall not come inside the camp. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23011, 'But it shall be, when evening comes, that he shall wash with water; and when the sun sets, he may come into the camp. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23012, 'Also you shall have a place outside the camp, where you may go out; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23013, 'and you shall have an implement among your equipment, and when you sit down outside, you shall dig with it and turn and cover your refuse. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23014, 'For the Lord your God walks in the midst of your camp, to deliver you and give your enemies over to you; therefore your camp shall be holy, that He may see no unclean thing among you, and turn away from you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23015, 'You shall not give back to his master the slave who has escaped from his master to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23016, 'He may dwell with you in your midst, in the place which he chooses within one of your gates, where it seems best to him; you shall not oppress him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23017, 'There shall be no ritual harlot of the daughters of Israel, or a perverted one of the sons of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23018, 'You shall not bring the wages of a harlot or the price of a dog to the house of the Lord your God for any vowed offering, for both of these are an abomination to the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23019, 'You shall not charge interest to your brother &ndash; interest on money or food or anything that is lent out at interest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23020, 'To a foreigner you may charge interest, but to your brother you shall not charge interest, that the Lord your God may bless you in all to which you set your hand in the land which you are entering to possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23021, 'When you make a vow to the Lord your God, you shall not delay to pay it; for the Lord your God will surely require it of you, and it would be sin to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23022, 'But if you abstain from vowing, it shall not be sin to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23023, 'That which has gone from your lips you shall keep and perform, for you voluntarily vowed to the Lord your God what you have promised with your mouth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23024, 'When you come into your neighbor&rsquo;s vineyard, you may eat your fill of grapes at your pleasure, but you shall not put any in your container. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 23025, 'When you come into your neighbor&rsquo;s standing grain, you may pluck the heads with your hand, but you shall not use a sickle on your neighbor&rsquo;s standing grain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24001, 'When a man takes a wife and marries her, and it happens that she finds no favor in his eyes because he has found some uncleanness in her, and he writes her a certificate of divorce, puts it in her hand, and sends her out of his house, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24002, 'when she has departed from his house, and goes and becomes another man&rsquo;s wife, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24003, 'if the latter husband detests her and writes her a certificate of divorce, puts it in her hand, and sends her out of his house, or if the latter husband dies who took her as his wife, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24004, 'then her former husband who divorced her must not take her back to be his wife after she has been defiled; for that is an abomination before the Lord, and you shall not bring sin on the land which the Lord your God is giving you as an inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24005, 'When a man has taken a new wife, he shall not go out to war or be charged with any business; he shall be free at home one year, and bring happiness to his wife whom he has taken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24006, 'No man shall take the lower or the upper millstone in pledge, for he takes one&rsquo;s living in pledge. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24007, 'If a man is found kidnapping any of his brethren of the children of Israel, and mistreats him or sells him, then that kidnapper shall die; and you shall put away the evil from among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24008, 'Take heed in an outbreak of leprosy, that you carefully observe and do according to all that the priests, the Levites, shall teach you; just as I commanded them, so you shall be careful to do. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24009, 'Remember what the Lord your God did to Miriam on the way when you came out of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24010, 'When you lend your brother anything, you shall not go into his house to get his pledge. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24011, 'You shall stand outside, and the man to whom you lend shall bring the pledge out to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24012, 'And if the man is poor, you shall not keep his pledge overnight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24013, 'You shall in any case return the pledge to him again when the sun goes down, that he may sleep in his own garment and bless you; and it shall be righteousness to you before the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24014, 'You shall not oppress a hired servant who is poor and needy, whether one of your brethren or one of the aliens who is in your land within your gates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24015, 'Each day you shall give him his wages, and not let the sun go down on it, for he is poor and has set his heart on it; lest he cry out against you to the Lord, and it be sin to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24016, 'Fathers shall not be put to death for their children, nor shall the children be put to death for their fathers; a person shall be put to death for his own sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24017, 'You shall not pervert justice due the stranger or the fatherless, nor take a widow&rsquo;s garment as a pledge. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24018, 'But you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and the Lord your God redeemed you from there; therefore I command you to do this thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24019, 'When you reap your harvest in your field, and forget a sheaf in the field, you shall not go back to get it; it shall be for the stranger, the fatherless, and the widow, that the Lord your God may bless you in all the work of your hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24020, 'When you beat your olive trees, you shall not go over the boughs again; it shall be for the stranger, the fatherless, and the widow. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24021, 'When you gather the grapes of your vineyard, you shall not glean it afterward; it shall be for the stranger, the fatherless, and the widow. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 24022, 'And you shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt; therefore I command you to do this thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25001, 'If there is a dispute between men, and they come to court, that the judges may judge them, and they justify the righteous and condemn the wicked, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25002, 'then it shall be, if the wicked man deserves to be beaten, that the judge will cause him to lie down and be beaten in his presence, according to his guilt, with a certain number of blows. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25003, 'Forty blows he may give him and no more, lest he should exceed this and beat him with many blows above these, and your brother be humiliated in your sight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25004, 'You shall not muzzle an ox while it treads out the grain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25005, 'If brothers dwell together, and one of them dies and has no son, the widow of the dead man shall not be married to a stranger outside the family; her husband&rsquo;s brother shall go in to her, take her as his wife, and perform the duty of a husband&rsquo;s brother to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25006, 'And it shall be that the firstborn son which she bears will succeed to the name of his dead brother, that his name may not be blotted out of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25007, 'But if the man does not want to take his brother&rsquo;s wife, then let his brother&rsquo;s wife go up to the gate to the elders, and say, &lsquo;My husband&rsquo;s brother refuses to raise up a name to his brother in Israel; he will not perform the duty of my husband&rsquo;s brother.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25008, 'Then the elders of his city shall call him and speak to him. But if he stands firm and says, &lsquo;I do not want to take her,&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25009, 'then his brother&rsquo;s wife shall come to him in the presence of the elders, remove his sandal from his foot, spit in his face, and answer and say, &lsquo;So shall it be done to the man who will not build up his brother&rsquo;s house.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25010, 'And his name shall be called in Israel, &lsquo;The house of him who had his sandal removed.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25011, 'If two men fight together, and the wife of one draws near to rescue her husband from the hand of the one attacking him, and puts out her hand and seizes him by the genitals, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25012, 'then you shall cut off her hand; your eye shall not pity her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25013, 'You shall not have in your bag differing weights, a heavy and a light. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25014, 'You shall not have in your house differing measures, a large and a small. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25015, 'You shall have a perfect and just weight, a perfect and just measure, that your days may be lengthened in the land which the Lord your God is giving you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25016, 'For all who do such things, all who behave unrighteously, are an abomination to the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25017, 'Remember what Amalek did to you on the way as you were coming out of Egypt, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25018, 'how he met you on the way and attacked your rear ranks, all the stragglers at your rear, when you were tired and weary; and he did not fear God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 25019, 'Therefore it shall be, when the Lord your God has given you rest from your enemies all around, in the land which the Lord your God is giving you to possess as an inheritance, that you will blot out the remembrance of Amalek from under heaven. You shall not forget. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26001, 'And it shall be, when you come into the land which the Lord your God is giving you as an inheritance, and you possess it and dwell in it, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26002, 'that you shall take some of the first of all the produce of the ground, which you shall bring from your land that the Lord your God is giving you, and put it in a basket and go to the place where the Lord your God chooses to make His name abide. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26003, 'And you shall go to the one who is priest in those days, and say to him, &lsquo;I declare today to the Lord your God that I have come to the country which the Lord swore to our fathers to give us.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26004, 'Then the priest shall take the basket out of your hand and set it down before the altar of the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26005, 'And you shall answer and say before the Lord your God: &lsquo;My father was a Syrian, about to perish, and he went down to Egypt and dwelt there, few in number; and there he became a nation, great, mighty, and populous.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26006, 'But the Egyptians mistreated us, afflicted us, and laid hard bondage on us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26007, 'Then we cried out to the Lord God of our fathers, and the Lord heard our voice and looked on our affliction and our labor and our oppression. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26008, 'So the Lord brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand and with an outstretched arm, with great terror and with signs and wonders. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26009, 'He has brought us to this place and has given us this land, a land flowing with milk and honey;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26010, 'and now, behold, I have brought the firstfruits of the land which you, O Lord, have given me.&rsquo; Then you shall set it before the Lord your God, and worship before the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26011, 'So you shall rejoice in every good thing which the Lord your God has given to you and your house, you and the Levite and the stranger who is among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26012, 'When you have finished laying aside all the tithe of your increase in the third year &ndash; the year of tithing &ndash; and have given it to the Levite, the stranger, the fatherless, and the widow, so that they may eat within your gates and be filled, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26013, 'then you shall say before the Lord your God: &lsquo;I have removed the holy tithe from my house, and also have given them to the Levite, the stranger, the fatherless, and the widow, according to all Your commandments which You have commanded me; I have not transgressed Your commandments, nor have I forgotten them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26014, 'I have not eaten any of it when in mourning, nor have I removed any of it for an unclean use, nor given any of it for the dead. I have obeyed the voice of the Lord my God, and have done according to all that You have commanded me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26015, 'Look down from Your holy habitation, from heaven, and bless Your people Israel and the land which You have given us, just as You swore to our fathers, &ldquo;a land flowing with milk and honey.&rdquo; &lsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26016, 'This day the Lord your God commands you to observe these statutes and judgments; therefore you shall be careful to observe them with all your heart and with all your soul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26017, 'Today you have proclaimed the Lord to be your God, and that you will walk in His ways and keep His statutes, His commandments, and His judgments, and that you will obey His voice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26018, 'Also today the Lord has proclaimed you to be His special people, just as He promised you, that you should keep all His commandments, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 26019, 'and that He will set you high above all nations which He has made, in praise, in name, and in honor, and that you may be a holy people to the Lord your God, just as He has spoken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27001, 'Now Moses, with the elders of Israel, commanded the people, saying: &ldquo;Keep all the commandments which I command you today. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27002, 'And it shall be, on the day when you cross over the Jordan to the land which the Lord your God is giving you, that you shall set up for yourselves large stones, and whitewash them with lime. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27003, 'You shall write on them all the words of this law, when you have crossed over, that you may enter the land which the Lord your God is giving you, &lsquo;a land flowing with milk and honey,&rsquo; just as the Lord God of your fathers promised you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27004, 'Therefore it shall be, when you have crossed over the Jordan, that on Mount Ebal you shall set up these stones, which I command you today, and you shall whitewash them with lime. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27005, 'And there you shall build an altar to the Lord your God, an altar of stones; you shall not use an iron tool on them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27006, 'You shall build with whole stones the altar of the Lord your God, and offer burnt offerings on it to the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27007, 'You shall offer peace offerings, and shall eat there, and rejoice before the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27008, 'And you shall write very plainly on the stones all the words of this law.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27009, 'Then Moses and the priests, the Levites, spoke to all Israel, saying, &ldquo;Take heed and listen, O Israel: This day you have become the people of the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27010, 'Therefore you shall obey the voice of the Lord your God, and observe His commandments and His statutes which I command you today.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27011, 'And Moses commanded the people on the same day, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27012, 'These shall stand on Mount Gerizim to bless the people, when you have crossed over the Jordan: Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph, and Benjamin; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27013, 'and these shall stand on Mount Ebal to curse: Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27014, 'And the Levites shall speak with a loud voice and say to all the men of Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27015, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who makes a carved or molded image, an abomination to the Lord, the work of the hands of the craftsman, and sets it up in secret.&rsquo;And all the people shall answer and say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27016, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who treats his father or his mother with contempt.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27017, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who moves his neighbor&rsquo;s landmark.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27018, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who makes the blind to wander off the road.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27019, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who perverts the justice due the stranger, the fatherless, and widow.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27020, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who lies with his father&rsquo;s wife, because he has uncovered his father&rsquo;s bed.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27021, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who lies with any kind of animal.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27022, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who lies with his sister, the daughter of his father or the daughter of his mother.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27023, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who lies with his mother-in-law.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27024, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who attacks his neighbor secretly.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27025, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who takes a bribe to slay an innocent person.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 27026, '&rsquo;Cursed is the one who does not confirm all the words of this law.&rsquo;And all the people shall say, &lsquo;Amen!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28001, 'Now it shall come to pass, if you diligently obey the voice of the Lord your God, to observe carefully all His commandments which I command you today, that the Lord your God will set you high above all nations of the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28002, 'And all these blessings shall come upon you and overtake you, because you obey the voice of the Lord your God: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28003, 'Blessed shall you be in the city, and blessed shall you be in the country. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28004, 'Blessed shall be the fruit of your body, the produce of your ground and the increase of your herds, the increase of your cattle and the offspring of your flocks. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28005, 'Blessed shall be your basket and your kneading bowl. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28006, 'Blessed shall you be when you come in, and blessed shall you be when you go out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28007, 'The Lord will cause your enemies who rise against you to be defeated before your face; they shall come out against you one way and flee before you seven ways. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28008, 'The Lord will command the blessing on you in your storehouses and in all to which you set your hand, and He will bless you in the land which the Lord your God is giving you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28009, 'The Lord will establish you as a holy people to Himself, just as He has sworn to you, if you keep the commandments of the Lord your God and walk in His ways. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28010, 'Then all peoples of the earth shall see that you are called by the name of the Lord, and they shall be afraid of you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28011, 'And the Lord will grant you plenty of goods, in the fruit of your body, in the increase of your livestock, and in the produce of your ground, in the land of which the Lord swore to your fathers to give you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28012, 'The Lord will open to you His good treasure, the heavens, to give the rain to your land in its season, and to bless all the work of your hand. You shall lend to many nations, but you shall not borrow. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28013, 'And the Lord will make you the head and not the tail; you shall be above only, and not be beneath, if you heed the commandments of the Lord your God, which I command you today, and are careful to observe them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28014, 'So you shall not turn aside from any of the words which I command you this day, to the right or the left, to go after other gods to serve them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28015, 'But it shall come to pass, if you do not obey the voice of the Lord your God, to observe carefully all His commandments and His statutes which I command you today, that all these curses will come upon you and overtake you: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28016, 'Cursed shall you be in the city, and cursed shall you be in the country. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28017, 'Cursed shall be your basket and your kneading bowl. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28018, 'Cursed shall be the fruit of your body and the produce of your land, the increase of your cattle and the offspring of your flocks. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28019, 'Cursed shall you be when you come in, and cursed shall you be when you go out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28020, 'The Lord will send on you cursing, confusion, and rebuke in all that you set your hand to do, until you are destroyed and until you perish quickly, because of the wickedness of your doings in which you have forsaken Me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28021, 'The Lord will make the plague cling to you until He has consumed you from the land which you are going to possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28022, 'The Lord will strike you with consumption, with fever, with inflammation, with severe burning fever, with the sword, with scorching, and with mildew; they shall pursue you until you perish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28023, 'And your heavens which are over your head shall be bronze, and the earth which is under you shall be iron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28024, 'The Lord will change the rain of your land to powder and dust; from the heaven it shall come down on you until you are destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28025, 'The Lord will cause you to be defeated before your enemies; you shall go out one way against them and flee seven ways before them; and you shall become troublesome to all the kingdoms of the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28026, 'Your carcasses shall be food for all the birds of the air and the beasts of the earth, and no one shall frighten them away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28027, 'The Lord will strike you with the boils of Egypt, with tumors, with the scab, and with the itch, from which you cannot be healed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28028, 'The Lord will strike you with madness and blindness and confusion of heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28029, 'And you shall grope at noonday, as a blind man gropes in darkness; you shall not prosper in your ways; you shall be only oppressed and plundered continually, and no one shall save you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28030, 'You shall betroth a wife, but another man shall lie with her; you shall build a house, but you shall not dwell in it; you shall plant a vineyard, but shall not gather its grapes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28031, 'Your ox shall be slaughtered before your eyes, but you shall not eat of it; your donkey shall be violently taken away from before you, and shall not be restored to you; your sheep shall be given to your enemies, and you shall have no one to rescue them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28032, 'Your sons and your daughters shall be given to another people, and your eyes shall look and fail with longing for them all day long; and there shall be no strength in your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28033, 'A nation whom you have not known shall eat the fruit of your land and the produce of your labor, and you shall be only oppressed and crushed continually. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28034, 'So you shall be driven mad because of the sight which your eyes see. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28035, 'The Lord will strike you in the knees and on the legs with severe boils which cannot be healed, and from the sole of your foot to the top of your head. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28036, 'The Lord will bring you and the king whom you set over you to a nation which neither you nor your fathers have known, and there you shall serve other gods &ndash; wood and stone. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28037, 'And you shall become an astonishment, a proverb, and a byword among all nations where the Lord will drive you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28038, 'You shall carry much seed out to the field but gather little in, for the locust shall consume it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28039, 'You shall plant vineyards and tend them, but you shall neither drink of the wine nor gather the grapes; for the worms shall eat them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28040, 'You shall have olive trees throughout all your territory, but you shall not anoint yourself with the oil; for your olives shall drop off. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28041, 'You shall beget sons and daughters, but they shall not be yours; for they shall go into captivity. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28042, 'Locusts shall consume all your trees and the produce of your land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28043, 'The alien who is among you shall rise higher and higher above you, and you shall come down lower and lower. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28044, 'He shall lend to you, but you shall not lend to him; he shall be the head, and you shall be the tail. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 28045, 'Moreover all these curses shall come upon you and pursue and overtake you, until you are destroyed, because you did not obey the voice of the Lord your God, to keep His commandments and His statutes which He commanded you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29001, 'These are the words of the covenant which the Lord commanded Moses to make with the children of Israel in the land of Moab, besides the covenant which He made with them in Horeb. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29002, 'Now Moses called all Israel and said to them: &ldquo;You have seen all that the Lord did before your eyes in the land of Egypt, to Pharaoh and to all his servants and to all his land &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29003, 'the great trials which your eyes have seen, the signs, and those great wonders. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29004, 'Yet the Lord has not given you a heart to perceive and eyes to see and ears to hear, to this very day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29005, 'And I have led you forty years in the wilderness. Your clothes have not worn out on you, and your sandals have not worn out on your feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29006, 'You have not eaten bread, nor have you drunk wine or similar drink, that you may know that I am the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29007, 'And when you came to this place, Sihon king of Heshbon and Og king of Bashan came out against us to battle, and we conquered them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29008, 'We took their land and gave it as an inheritance to the Reubenites, to the Gadites, and to half the tribe of Manasseh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29009, 'Therefore keep the words of this covenant, and do them, that you may prosper in all that you do. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29010, 'All of you stand today before the Lord your God: your leaders and your tribes and your elders and your officers, all the men of Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29011, 'your little ones and your wives &ndash; also the stranger who is in your camp, from the one who cuts your wood to the one who draws your water &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29012, 'that you may enter into covenant with the Lord your God, and into His oath, which the Lord your God makes with you today, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29013, 'that He may establish you today as a people for Himself, and that He may be God to you, just as He has spoken to you, and just as He has sworn to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29014, 'I make this covenant and this oath, not with you alone, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29015, 'but with him who stands here with us today before the Lord our God, as well as with him who is not here with us today ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29016, '(for you know that we dwelt in the land of Egypt and that we came through the nations which you passed by, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29017, 'and you saw their abominations and their idols which were among them &ndash; wood and stone and silver and gold); ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29018, 'so that there may not be among you man or woman or family or tribe, whose heart turns away today from the Lord our God, to go and serve the gods of these nations, and that there may not be among you a root bearing bitterness or wormwood; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29019, 'and so it may not happen, when he hears the words of this curse, that he blesses himself in his heart, saying, &lsquo;I shall have peace, even though I follow the dictates of my heart&rsquo; &ndash; as though the drunkard could be included with the sober. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29020, 'The Lord would not spare him; for then the anger of the Lord and His jealousy would burn against that man, and every curse that is written in this book would settle on him, and the Lord would blot out his name from under heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29021, 'And the Lord would separate him from all the tribes of Israel for adversity, according to all the curses of the covenant that are written in this Book of the Law, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29022, 'so that the coming generation of your children who rise up after you, and the foreigner who comes from a far land, would say, when they see the plagues of that land and the sicknesses which the Lord has laid on it: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29023, '&rsquo;The whole land is brimstone, salt, and burning; it is not sown, nor does it bear, nor does any grass grow there, like the overthrow of Sodom and Gomorrah, Admah, and Zeboim, which the Lord overthrew in His anger and His wrath.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29024, 'All nations would say, &lsquo;Why has the Lord done so to this land? What does the heat of this great anger mean?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29025, 'Then people would say: &lsquo;Because they have forsaken the covenant of the Lord God of their fathers, which He made with them when He brought them out of the land of Egypt; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29026, 'for they went and served other gods and worshiped them, gods that they did not know and that He had not given to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29027, 'Then the anger of the Lord was aroused against this land, to bring on it every curse that is written in this book. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29028, 'And the Lord uprooted them from their land in anger, in wrath, and in great indignation, and cast them into another land, as it is this day.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 29029, 'The secret things belong to the Lord our God, but those things which are revealed belong to us and to our children forever, that we may do all the words of this law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30001, 'Now it shall come to pass, when all these things come upon you, the blessing and the curse which I have set before you, and you call them to mind among all the nations where the Lord your God drives you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30002, 'and you return to the Lord your God and obey His voice, according to all that I command you today, you and your children, with all your heart and with all your soul, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30003, 'that the Lord your God will bring you back from captivity, and have compassion on you, and gather you again from all the nations where the Lord your God has scattered you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30004, 'If any of you are driven out to the farthest parts under heaven, from there the Lord your God will gather you, and from there He will bring you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30005, 'Then the Lord your God will bring you to the land which your fathers possessed, and you shall possess it. He will prosper you and multiply you more than your fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30006, 'And the Lord your God will circumcise your heart and the heart of your descendants, to love the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul, that you may live. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30007, 'Also the Lord your God will put all these curses on your enemies and on those who hate you, who persecuted you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30008, 'And you will again obey the voice of the Lord and do all His commandments which I command you today. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30009, 'The Lord your God will make you abound in all the work of your hand, in the fruit of your body, in the increase of your livestock, and in the produce of your land for good. For the Lord will again rejoice over you for good as He rejoiced over your fathers, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30010, 'if you obey the voice of the Lord your God, to keep His commandments and His statutes which are written in this Book of the Law, and if you turn to the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30011, 'For this commandment which I command you today is not too mysterious for you, nor is it far off. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30012, 'It is not in heaven, that you should say, &lsquo;Who will ascend into heaven for us and bring it to us, that we may hear it and do it?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30013, 'Nor is it beyond the sea, that you should say, &lsquo;Who will go over the sea for us and bring it to us, that we may hear it and do it?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30014, 'But the word is very near you, in your mouth and in your heart, that you may do it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30015, 'See, I have set before you today life and good, death and evil, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30016, 'in that I command you today to love the Lord your God, to walk in His ways, and to keep His commandments, His statutes, and His judgments, that you may live and multiply; and the Lord your God will bless you in the land which you go to possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30017, 'But if your heart turns away so that you do not hear, and are drawn away, and worship other gods and serve them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30018, 'I announce to you today that you shall surely perish; you shall not prolong your days in the land which you cross over the Jordan to go in and possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30019, 'I call heaven and earth as witnesses today against you, that I have set before you life and death, blessing and cursing; therefore choose life, that both you and your descendants may live; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 30020, 'that you may love the Lord your God, that you may obey His voice, and that you may cling to Him, for He is your life and the length of your days; and that you may dwell in the land which the Lord swore to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, to give them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31001, 'Then Moses went and spoke these words to all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31002, 'And he said to them: &ldquo;I am one hundred and twenty years old today. I can no longer go out and come in. Also the Lord has said to me, &lsquo;You shall not cross over this Jordan.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31003, 'The Lord your God Himself crosses over before you; He will destroy these nations from before you, and you shall dispossess them. Joshua himself crosses over before you, just as the Lord has said. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31004, 'And the Lord will do to them as He did to Sihon and Og, the kings of the Amorites and their land, when He destroyed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31005, 'The Lord will give them over to you, that you may do to them according to every commandment which I have commanded you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31006, 'Be strong and of good courage, do not fear nor be afraid of them; for the Lord your God, He is the One who goes with you. He will not leave you nor forsake you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31007, 'Then Moses called Joshua and said to him in the sight of all Israel, &ldquo;Be strong and of good courage, for you must go with this people to the land which the Lord has sworn to their fathers to give them, and you shall cause them to inherit it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31008, 'And the Lord, He is the one who goes before you. He will be with you, He will not leave you nor forsake you; do not fear nor be dismayed.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31009, 'So Moses wrote this law and delivered it to the priests, the sons of Levi, who bore the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and to all the elders of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31010, 'And Moses commanded them, saying: &ldquo;At the end of every seven years, at the appointed time in the year of release, at the Feast of Tabernacles, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31011, 'when all Israel comes to appear before the Lord your God in the place which He chooses, you shall read this law before all Israel in their hearing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31012, 'Gather the people together, men and women and little ones, and the stranger who is within your gates, that they may hear and that they may learn to fear the Lord your God and carefully observe all the words of this law, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31013, 'and that their children, who have not known it, may hear and learn to fear the Lord your God as long as you live in the land which you cross the Jordan to possess.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31014, 'Then the Lord said to Moses, &ldquo;Behold, the days approach when you must die; call Joshua, and present yourselves in the tabernacle of meeting, that I may inaugurate him.&rdquo; So Moses and Joshua went and presented themselves in the tabernacle of meeting. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31015, 'Now the Lord appeared at the tabernacle in a pillar of cloud, and the pillar of cloud stood above the door of the tabernacle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31016, 'And the Lord said to Moses: &ldquo;Behold, you will rest with your fathers; and this people will rise and play the harlot with the gods of the foreigners of the land, where they go to be among them, and they will forsake Me and break My covenant which I have made with them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31017, 'Then My anger shall be aroused against them in that day, and I will forsake them, and I will hide My face from them, and they shall be devoured. And many evils and troubles shall befall them, so that they will say in that day, &lsquo;Have not these evils come upon us because our God is not among us?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31018, 'And I will surely hide My face in that day because of all the evil which they have done, in that they have turned to other gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31019, 'Now therefore, write down this song for yourselves, and teach it to the children of Israel; put it in their mouths, that this song may be a witness for Me against the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31020, 'When I have brought them to the land flowing with milk and honey, of which I swore to their fathers, and they have eaten and filled themselves and grown fat, then they will turn to other gods and serve them; and they will provoke Me and break My covenant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31021, 'Then it shall be, when many evils and troubles have come upon them, that this song will testify against them as a witness; for it will not be forgotten in the mouths of their descendants, for I know the inclination of their behavior today, even before I have brought them to the land of which I swore to give them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31022, 'Therefore Moses wrote this song the same day, and taught it to the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31023, 'Then He inaugurated Joshua the son of Nun, and said, &ldquo;Be strong and of good courage; for you shall bring the children of Israel into the land of which I swore to them, and I will be with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31024, 'So it was, when Moses had completed writing the words of this law in a book, when they were finished, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31025, 'that Moses commanded the Levites, who bore the ark of the covenant of the Lord, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31026, 'Take this Book of the Law, and put it beside the ark of the covenant of the Lord your God, that it may be there as a witness against you; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31027, 'for I know your rebellion and your stiff neck. If today, while I am yet alive with you, you have been rebellious against the Lord, then how much more after my death? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31028, 'Gather to me all the elders of your tribes, and your officers, that I may speak these words in their hearing and call heaven and earth to witness against them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31029, 'For I know that after my death you will become utterly corrupt, and turn aside from the way which I have commanded you; and evil will befall you in the latter days, because you will do evil in the sight of the Lord, to provoke Him to anger through the work of your hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 31030, 'Then Moses spoke in the hearing of all the assembly of Israel the words of this song until they were ended: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32001, 'Give ear, O heavens, and I will speak; And hear, O earth, the words of my mouth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32002, 'Let my teaching drop as the rain, My speech distill as the dew, As raindrops on the tender herb, And as showers on the grass. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32003, 'For I proclaim the name of the Lord: Ascribe greatness to our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32004, 'He is the Rock, His work is perfect; For all His ways are justice, A God of truth and without injustice; Righteous and upright is He. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32005, 'They have corrupted themselves; They are not His children, Because of their blemish: A perverse and crooked generation. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32006, 'Do you thus deal with the Lord, O foolish and unwise people? Is He not your Father, who bought you? Has He not made you and established you? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32007, 'Remember the days of old, Consider the years of many generations. Ask your father, and he will show you; Your elders, and they will tell you: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32008, 'When the Most High divided their inheritance to the nations, When He separated the sons of Adam, He set the boundaries of the peoples According to the number of the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32009, 'For the Lord&rsquo;s portion is His people; Jacob is the place of His inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32010, 'He found him in a desert land And in the wasteland, a howling wilderness; He encircled him, He instructed him, He kept him as the apple of His eye. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32011, 'As an eagle stirs up its nest, Hovers over its young, Spreading out its wings, taking them up, Carrying them on its wings, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32012, 'So the Lord alone led him, And there was no foreign god with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32013, 'He made him ride in the heights of the earth, That he might eat the produce of the fields; He made him draw honey from the rock, And oil from the flinty rock; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32014, 'Curds from the cattle, and milk of the flock, With fat of lambs; And rams of the breed of Bashan, and goats, With the choicest wheat; And you drank wine, the blood of the grapes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32015, 'But Jeshurun grew fat and kicked; You grew fat, you grew thick, You are obese! Then he forsook God who made him, And scornfully esteemed the Rock of his salvation. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32016, 'They provoked Him to jealousy with foreign gods; With abominations they provoked Him to anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32017, 'They sacrificed to demons, not to God, To gods they did not know, To new gods, new arrivals That your fathers did not fear. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32018, 'Of the Rock who begot you, you are unmindful, And have forgotten the God who fathered you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32019, 'And when the Lord saw it, He spurned them, Because of the provocation of His sons and His daughters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32020, 'And He said: &lsquo;I will hide My face from them, I will see what their end will be, For they are a perverse generation, Children in whom is no faith. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32021, 'They have provoked Me to jealousy by what is not God; They have moved Me to anger by their foolish idols. But I will provoke them to jealousy by those who are not a nation; I will move them to anger by a foolish nation. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32022, 'For a fire is kindled by my anger, And shall burn to the lowest hell; It shall consume the earth with her increase, And set on fire the foundations of the mountains. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32023, '&rsquo;I will heap disasters on them; I will spend My arrows on them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32024, 'They shall be wasted with hunger, Devoured by pestilence and bitter destruction; I will also send against them the teeth of beasts, With the poison of serpents of the dust. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32025, 'The sword shall destroy outside; There shall be terror within For the young man and virgin, The nursing child with the man of gray hairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32026, 'I would have said, I will dash them in pieces, I will make the memory of them to cease from among men, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32027, 'Had I not feared the wrath of the enemy, Lest their adversaries should misunderstand, Lest they should say, Our hand is high; And it is not the Lord who has done all this. &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32028, 'For they are a nation void of counsel, Nor is there any understanding in them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32029, 'Oh, that they were wise, that they understood this, That they would consider their latter end! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32030, 'How could one chase a thousand, And two put ten thousand to flight, Unless their Rock had sold them, And the Lord had surrendered them? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32031, 'For their rock is not like our Rock, Even our enemies themselves being judges. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32032, 'For their vine is of the vine of Sodom And of the fields of Gomorrah; Their grapes are grapes of gall, Their clusters are bitter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32033, 'Their wine is the poison of serpents, And the cruel venom of cobras. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32034, '&rsquo;Is this not laid up in store with Me, Sealed up among My treasures? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32035, 'Vengeance is Mine, and recompense; Their foot shall slip in due time; For the day of their calamity is at hand, And the things to come hasten upon them.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32036, 'For the Lord will judge His people And have compassion on His servants, When He sees that their power is gone, And there is no one remaining, bond or free. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32037, 'He will say: &lsquo;Where are their gods, The rock in which they sought refuge? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32038, 'Who ate the fat of their sacrifices, And drank the wine of their drink offering? Let them rise and help you, And be your refuge. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32039, '&rsquo;Now see that I, even I, am He, And there is no God besides Me; I kill and I make alive; I wound and I heal; Nor is there any who can deliver from My hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32040, 'For I raise My hand to heaven, And say, As I live forever, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32041, 'If I whet My glittering sword, And My hand takes hold on judgment, I will render vengeance to My enemies, And repay those who hate Me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32042, 'I will make My arrows drunk with blood, And My sword shall devour flesh, With the blood of the slain and the captives, From the heads of the leaders of the enemy.&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32043, 'Rejoice, O Gentiles, with His people; For He will avenge the blood of His servants, And render vengeance to His adversaries; He will provide atonement for His land and His people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32044, 'So Moses came with Joshua the son of Nun and spoke all the words of this song in the hearing of the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32045, 'Moses finished speaking all these words to all Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32046, 'and He said to them: &ldquo;Set your hearts on all the words which I testify among you today, which you shall command your children to be careful to observe &ndash; all the words of this law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32047, 'For it is not a futile thing for you, because it is your life, and by this word you shall prolong your days in the land which you cross over the Jordan to possess.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32048, 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses that very same day, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32049, 'Go up this mountain of the Abarim, Mount Nebo, which is in the land of Moab, across from Jericho; view the land of Canaan, which I give to the children of Israel as a possession; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32050, 'and die on the mountain which you ascend, and be gathered to your people, just as Aaron your brother died on Mount Hor and was gathered to his people; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32051, 'because you trespassed against Me among the children of Israel at the waters of Meribah Kadesh, in the Wilderness of Zin, because you did not hallow Me in the midst of the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 32052, 'Yet you shall see the land before you, though you shall not go there, into the land which I am giving to the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33001, 'Now this is the blessing with which Moses the man of God blessed the children of Israel before his death. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33002, 'And he said: &ldquo;The Lord came from Sinai, And dawned on them from Seir; He shone forth from Mount Paran, And He came with ten thousands of saints; From His right hand Came a fiery law for them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33003, 'Yes, He loves the people; All His saints are in Your hand; They sit down at Your feet; Everyone receives Your words. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33004, 'Moses commanded a law for us, A heritage of the congregation of Jacob. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33005, 'And He was King in Jeshurun, When the leaders of the people were gathered, All the tribes of Israel together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33006, 'Let Reuben live, and not die, Nor let his men be few. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33007, 'And this he said of Judah: &ldquo;Hear, Lord, the voice of Judah, And bring him to his people; Let his hands be sufficient for him, And may You be a help against his enemies.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33008, 'And of Levi he said: &ldquo;Let Your Thummim and Your Urim be with Your holy one, Whom You tested at Massah, And with whom You contended at the waters of Meribah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33009, 'Who says of his father and mother, &lsquo;I have not seen them&rsquo;; Nor did he acknowledge his brothers, Or know his own children; For they have observed Your word And kept Your covenant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33010, 'They shall teach Jacob Your judgments, And Israel Your law. They shall put incense before You, And a whole burnt sacrifice on Your altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33011, 'Bless his substance, Lord, And accept the work of his hands; Strike the loins of those who rise against him, And of those who hate him, that they rise not again.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33012, 'Of Benjamin he said: &ldquo;The beloved of the Lord shall dwell in safety by Him, Who shelters him all the day long; And he shall dwell between His shoulders.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33013, 'And of Joseph he said: &ldquo;Blessed of the Lord is his land, With the precious things of heaven, with the dew, And the deep lying beneath, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33014, 'With the precious fruits of the sun, With the precious produce of the months, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33015, 'With the best things of the ancient mountains, With the precious things of the everlasting hills, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33016, 'With the precious things of the earth and its fullness, And the favor of Him who dwelt in the bush. Let the blessing come &lsquo;on the head of Joseph, And on the crown of the head of him who was separate from his brothers.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33017, 'His glory is like a firstborn bull, And his horns like the horns of the wild ox; Together with them He shall push the peoples To the ends of the earth; They are the ten thousands of Ephraim, And they are the thousands of Manasseh.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33018, 'And of Zebulun he said: &ldquo;Rejoice, Zebulun, in your going out, And Issachar in your tents! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33019, 'They shall call the peoples to the mountain; There they shall offer sacrifices of righteousness; For they shall partake of the abundance of the seas And of treasures hidden in the sand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33020, 'And of Gad he said: &ldquo;Blessed is he who enlarges Gad; He dwells as a lion, And tears the arm and the crown of his head. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33021, 'He provided the first part for himself, Because a lawgiver&rsquo;s portion was reserved there. He came with the heads of the people; He administered the justice of the Lord, And His judgments with Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33022, 'And of Dan he said: &ldquo;Dan is a lion&rsquo;s whelp; He shall leap from Bashan.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33023, 'And of Naphtali he said: &ldquo;O Naphtali, satisfied with favor, And full of the blessing of the Lord, Possess the west and the south.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33024, 'And of Asher he said: &ldquo;Asher is most blessed of sons; Let him be favored by his brothers, And let him dip his foot in oil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33025, 'Your sandals shall be iron and bronze; As your days, so shall your strength be. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33026, 'There is no one like the God of Jeshurun, Who rides the heavens to help you, And in His excellency on the clouds. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33027, 'The eternal God is your refuge, And underneath are the everlasting arms; He will thrust out the enemy from before you, And will say, &lsquo;Destroy!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33028, 'Then Israel shall dwell in safety, The fountain of Jacob alone, In a land of grain and new wine; His heavens shall also drop dew. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 33029, 'Happy are you, O Israel! Who is like you, a people saved by the Lord, The shield of your help And the sword of your majesty! Your enemies shall submit to you, And you shall tread down their high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34001, 'Then Moses went up from the plains of Moab to Mount Nebo, to the top of Pisgah, which is across from Jericho. And the Lord showed him all the land of Gilead as far as Dan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34002, 'all Naphtali and the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, all the land of Judah as far as the Western Sea,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34003, 'the South, and the plain of the Valley of Jericho, the city of palm trees, as far as Zoar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34004, 'Then the Lord said to him, &ldquo;This is the land of which I swore to give Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, saying, &lsquo;I will give it to your descendants.&rsquo; I have caused you to see it with your eyes, but you shall not cross over there.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34005, 'So Moses the servant of the Lord died there in the land of Moab, according to the word of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34006, 'And He buried him in a valley in the land of Moab, opposite Beth Peor; but no one knows his grave to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34007, 'Moses was one hundred and twenty years old when he died. His eyes were not dim nor his natural vigor diminished. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34008, 'And the children of Israel wept for Moses in the plains of Moab thirty days. So the days of weeping and mourning for Moses ended. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34009, 'Now Joshua the son of Nun was full of the spirit of wisdom, for Moses had laid his hands on him; so the children of Israel heeded him, and did as the Lord had commanded Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34010, 'But since then there has not arisen in Israel a prophet like Moses, whom the Lord knew face to face, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34011, 'in all the signs and wonders which the Lord sent him to do in the land of Egypt, before Pharaoh, before all his servants, and in all his land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Deut', 34012, 'and by all that mighty power and all the great terror which Moses performed in the sight of all Israel. ');
